Name: Bulbasaur

FlavorText: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

Name: Ivysaur

Name: Venusaur

Name: Venusaur

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander’s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

Name: Charmeleon

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the air temperature to  unbearably high levels.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

FlavorText: It spreads its beautiful wings wide to frighten its enemies. It can fly at Mach 2 speed.

Name: Pidgeot
FlavorText: Its well-developed chest muscles make it strong enough to whip up a gusty windstorm with just a few flaps.

Name: Pidgeot
FlavorText: This POKéMON has gorgeous, glossy feathers. Many TRAINERS are so captivated by the beautiful feathers on its head that they choose PIDGEOT as their POKéMON.

Name: Pidgeot
FlavorText: Its outstanding vision allows it to spot splashing MAGIKARP, even while flying at 3300 feet.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Its whiskers provide it with a keen sense of smell, enabling it to pick up the scent of hidden food and locate it instantly.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Night after night, they sneak into people’s homes seeking food. A massive outbreak of them has become an issue of public concern.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: It shows no interest in anything that isn’t fresh. If you take it shopping with you, it will help you pick out ingredients.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: When the sun goes down, it becomes active. It runs around town on a chase for good food for the boss of its nest—Raticate.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: With its incisors, it gnaws through doors and infiltrates people’s homes. Then, with a twitch of its whiskers, it steals whatever food it finds.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: It’s cautious in the extreme, and its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: This Pokémon is common but hazardous. Its sharp incisors can easily cut right through hard wood.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life. If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: With their strong capacity for survival, they can live in dirty places without concern. Left unchecked, their numbers multiply rapidly.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Its incisors continue growing until its death. If its Trainer doesn’t offer it a file to gnaw on, it will gnaw on door frames, table legs, and so on.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Rattata is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives—it will make its nest anywhere.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Its fangs are long and very sharp. They grow continuously, so it gnaws on hard things to whittle them down.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Living wherever there is food available, it ceaselessly scavenges for edibles the entire day.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: It eats anything. Wherever food is available, it will settle down and produce offspring continuously.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: A RATTATA is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly moves its ears and listens for danger. It will make its nest anywhere.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: RATTATA is cautious in the extreme. Even while it is asleep, it constantly listens by moving its ears around. It is not picky about where it lives - it will make its nest anywhere.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: This POKéMON’s impressive vitality allows it to live anywhere. It also multiplies very quickly.

Name: Rattata
FlavorText: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, it is certain that 40 more live in the area.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: It makes its Rattata underlings gather food for it, dining solely on the most nutritious and delicious fare.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: It commands a nest of Rattata. Different nests don’t get along, whipping up severe fights over feeding grounds.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: It has an incredibly greedy personality. Its nest is filled with so much food gathered by Rattata at its direction, it can’t possibly eat it all.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: This gourmet Pokémon is particular about the taste and freshness of its food. Restaurants where Raticate live have a good reputation.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: It forms a group of Rattata, which it assumes command of. Each group has its own territory, and disputes over food happen often.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: It whittles down its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder block walls.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Its disposition is far more violent than its looks would suggest. Don’t let your hand get too close to its face, as it could bite your hand clean off.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Its hind feet are webbed, so it’s a strong swimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimes even oceans.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Raticate’s sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: The webs on its hind legs enable it to cross rivers. It searches wide areas for food.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Its whiskers help it to maintain balance. Its fangs never stop growing, so it gnaws to pare them down.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Gnaws on anything with its tough fangs. It can even topple concrete buildings by gnawing on them.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: A RATICATE’s sturdy fangs grow steadily. To keep them ground down, it gnaws on rocks and logs. It may even chew on the walls of houses.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

Name: Raticate
FlavorText: Its rear feet have three toes each. They are webbed, enabling it to swim across rivers.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Due to its short wings, it can’t fly long distances. It wanders about restlessly and pecks at bug Pokémon.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Its reckless nature leads it to stand up to others—even large Pokémon—if it has to protect its territory.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Farmers whose fields are troubled by bug Pokémon appreciate Spearow for its vigorous appetite and look after it.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Its short wings make it inept at flying. It moves about hurriedly and pecks at Bug-type Pokémon in the tall grass.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Spearow has a very loud cry that can be heard over half a mile away. If its high, keening cry is heard echoing all around, it is a sign that they are warning each other of danger.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Very protective of its territory, it flaps its short wings busily to dart around at high speed.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: It flaps its short wings to flush out insects from tall grass. It then plucks them with its stubby beak.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: Its loud cry can be heard over half a mile away. If its high, keening cry is heard echoing all around, it is a sign that they are warning each other of danger.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: It busily flits around here and there. Even if it is frail, it can be a tough foe that uses MIRROR MOVE.

Name: Spearow
FlavorText: To protect its territory, it flies around ceaselessly, making high-pitched cries.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: In Alola, fish Pokémon are its prey. It can be seen circling above the ocean searching for food.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: Carrying food through Fearow’s territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: Drawings of a Pokémon resembling Fearow can be seen in murals from deep in ancient history.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: It’s tough and has excellent stamina. It has no problem flying continuously for a whole day carrying a heavy load.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: Fearow is recognized by its long neck and elongated beak. They are conveniently shaped for catching prey in soil or water. It deftly moves its long and skinny beak to pluck prey.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: It cleverly uses its thin, long beak to pluck and eat small insects that hide under the ground.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: It shoots itself suddenly high into the sky, then plummets down in one fell swoop to strike its prey.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: It has the stamina to keep flying all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: Its long neck and elongated beak are ideal for catching prey in soil or water. It deftly moves this extended and skinny beak to pluck prey.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: Its huge and magnificent wings can keep it aloft in the sky. It can remain flying a whole day without landing.

Name: Fearow
FlavorText: It uses its long beak to attack. It has a surprisingly long reach, so it must be treated with caution.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: The eggs of bird Pokémon are its favorite food. It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg gets stuck, and Ekans faints.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: Ekans curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any direction with a glare from its upraised head.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: Moving silently and stealthily, it eats the eggs of birds, such as Pidgey and Spearow, whole.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: It always hides in grass. When first born, it has no poison, so its bite is painful, but harmless.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move, however.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: An EKANS curls itself up in a spiral while it rests. This position allows it to quickly respond to an enemy from any direction with a threat from its upraised head.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: A very common sight in grassland, etc. It flicks its tongue in and out to sense danger in its surroundings.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: It flutters the tip of its tongue to seek out the scent of prey, then swallows the prey whole.

Name: Ekans
FlavorText: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: After stunning its opponents with the pattern on its stomach, it quickly wraps them up in its body and waits for them to stop moving.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: The latest research has determined that there are over 20 possible arrangements of the patterns on its stomach.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: This Pokémon is terrifically strong in order to constrict things with its body. It can even flatten steel oil drums. Once Arbok wraps its body around its foe, escaping its crunching embrace is impossible.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: To intimidate foes, it spreads its chest wide and makes eerie sounds by expelling air from its mouth.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: With a very vengeful nature, it won’t give up the chase, no matter how far, once it targets its prey.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: Transfixing prey with the face-like pattern on its belly, it binds and poisons the frightened victim.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: This POKéMON has a terrifically strong constricting power. It can even flatten steel oil drums. Once it wraps its body around its foe, escaping is impossible.

Name: Arbok
FlavorText: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: When it smashes its opponents with its bolt- shaped tail, it delivers a surge of electricity equivalent to a lightning strike.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: Its Gigantamax power expanded, forming its supersized body and towering tail.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed during adventures across the Alola region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon and its partner traveling across the Alola region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is proof that the two traveled throughout the Alola region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of traveling through the Alola region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed during adventures across the Hoenn region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon and its partner traveling across the Hoenn region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is proof that the two traveled throughout the Hoenn region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of traveling through the Hoenn region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed during adventures across the Kalos region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon and its partner traveling across the Kalos region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is proof that the two traveled throughout the Kalos region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of traveling through the Kalos region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed during adventures across many different regions.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon and its partner traveling across lots of different regions together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is proof that the two traveled across many regions together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of traveling through many different regions.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed as the two overcame many hardships together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon traveling together with its partner, whom it met in a fateful encounter.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is a precious symbol of a fateful encounter.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of when they first met.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed during adventures across the Sinnoh region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon and its partner traveling across the Sinnoh region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is proof that the two traveled throughout the Sinnoh region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of traveling through the Sinnoh region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed during adventures across the Unova region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon and its partner traveling across the Unova region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is proof that the two traveled throughout the Unova region together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of traveling through the Unova region.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap—proof of the strong bond Pikachu and its partner formed during adventures across the world.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: The cap this Pikachu wears is filled with memories of this Pokémon and its partner traveling across the world together.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. The cap is a precious symbol that travels across different regions with Pikachu.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu wears its partner’s cap, which is brimming with memories of traveling through different regions.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer’s cap. Since the cap’s not the right size, the fit is a bit loose.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This form of Pikachu is somewhat rare. It wears the hat of its Trainer, who is also its partner.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: Possesses cheek sacs in which it stores electricity. This clever forest-dweller roasts tough berries with an electric shock before consuming them.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: If it looses crackling power from the electric sacs on its cheeks, it is being wary.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: When Pikachu meet, they’ll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This forest-dwelling Pokémon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you’ll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: While sleeping, it generates electricity in the sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It’s in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it’s unable to fully discharge the electricity.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This Pokémon has electricity-storing pouches on its cheeks. These appear to become electrically charged during the night while Pikachu sleeps. It occasionally discharges electricity when it is dozy after waking up.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it’s evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: This intelligent Pokémon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It stores electricity in the electric sacs on its cheeks. When it releases pent-up energy in a burst, the electric power is equal to a lightning bolt.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: It keeps its tail raised to monitor its surroundings. If you yank its tail, it will try to bite you.

Name: Pikachu
FlavorText: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: This Pokémon rides on its tail while it uses its psychic powers to levitate. It attacks with star-shaped thunderbolts.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It’s believed that the weather, climate, and food of the Alola region all play a part in causing Pikachu to evolve into this form of Raichu.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It loves pancakes prepared with a secret Alolan recipe. Some wonder whether that recipe holds the key to this Pokémon’s evolution.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: When you rub its cheeks, a sweet fragrance comes wafting out. However, you’ll also get a light shock!

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It focuses psychic energy into its tail and rides it like it’s surfing. Another name for this Pokémon is “hodad.”

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It uses psychokinesis to control electricity. It hops aboard its own tail, using psychic power to lift the tail and move about while riding it.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It only evolves to this form in the Alola region. According to researchers, its diet is one of the causes of this change.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It can discharge bursts of electricity exceeding 100,000 volts— a single strike with that amount of power would incapacitate one of the Copperajah of my homeland.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It turns aggressive if it has too much electricity in its body. It discharges power through its tail.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: If its electric pouches run empty, it raises its tail to gather electricity from the atmosphere.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: When electricity builds up inside its body, it becomes feisty. It also glows in the dark.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: Because so many Trainers like the way Pikachu looks, you don’t see this Pokémon very often.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: As electricity builds up inside its body, it becomes more aggressive. One theory is that the electricity buildup is actually causing stress.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It becomes aggressive when it has electricity stored up. At such times, even its Trainer has to take care to avoid being attacked.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: It unleashes electric shocks that can reach 100,000 volts. When agitated, it can knock out even an Indian elephant.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: This Pokémon exudes a weak electrical charge from all over its body that makes it take on a slight glow in darkness. Raichu plants its tail in the ground to discharge electricity.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: If the electrical sacs become excessively charged, Raichu plants its tail in the ground and discharges. Scorched patches of ground will be found near this Pokémon’s nest.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: When its electricity builds, its muscles are stimulated, and it becomes more aggressive than usual.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: If it stores too much electricity, its behavior turns aggressive. To avoid this, it occasionally discharges excess energy and calms itself down.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: Its electric charges can reach even 100,000 volts. Careless contact can cause even an Indian elephant to faint.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: This POKéMON exudes a weak electrical charge from all over its body that makes it take on a slight glow in darkness. RAICHU searches for electricity by planting its tail in the ground.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: If the electrical sacks become excessively charged, RAICHU plants its tail in the ground and discharges. Scorched patches of ground will be found near this POKéMON’s nest.

Name: Raichu
FlavorText: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It lives in snowy mountains on southern islands. When a blizzard rolls in, this Pokémon hunkers down in the snow to avoid getting blown away.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Life on mountains covered with deep snow has granted this Pokémon a body of ice that’s as hard as steel.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Its ice-covered body lets it slide across the ground with bullet-like speed, sending its enemies flying when it hits them.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: The skin on its back is as hard as steel. Predators go after its soft belly, so it clings to the ground desperately.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: After fleeing a volcanic eruption, it ended up moving to an area of snowy mountains. Its ice shell is as hard as steel.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: An ancient tradition of Alolan festivals, still carried on to this day, is a competition to slide Sandshrew across ice as far as one can.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It lives on snowy mountains. Its steel shell is very hard—so much so, it can’t roll its body up into a ball.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: To protect itself from attackers, it curls up into a ball. It lives in arid regions with minimal rainfall.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling, it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Its body is dry. When it gets cold at night, its hide is said to become coated with a fine dew.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: When its skin gets wrinkled from moisture, it heads for a volcano. It lies flat on a spot with a lot of geothermal heat and dries itself out.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It lives in areas of limited rainfall. When danger approaches, it curls up into a ball to protect its soft stomach.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It usually makes its home in deserts and arid zones, where rain does not fall. It digs holes to catch Bug-type Pokémon.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It can roll its body into a ball. It moves through the desert by rolling at high speeds.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Sandshrew has a very dry hide that is extremely tough. The Pokémon can roll into a ball that repels any attack. At night, it burrows into the desert sand to sleep.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Sandshrew’s body is configured to absorb water without waste, enabling it to survive in an arid desert. This Pokémon curls up to protect itself from its enemies.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It burrows and lives underground. If threatened, it curls itself up into a ball for protection.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: If it fell from a great height, this Pokémon could save itself by rolling into a ball and bouncing.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: When it curls up in a ball, it can make any attack bounce off harmlessly. Its hide has turned tough and solid as a result of living in the desert.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for prey.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: It prefers dry, sandy places because it uses the sand to protect itself when threatened.

Name: Sandshrew
FlavorText: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Many people climb snowy mountains, hoping to see the icy spikes of these Pokémon glistening in the light of dawn.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It uses large, hooked claws to cut a path through deep snow as it runs. On snowy mountains, this Sandslash is faster than any other Pokémon.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: This is Sandslash’s form after adaptation to a frigid environment. The cold air emitted by its body sharpens its icy spikes.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: A long, long time ago, it lived in the desert. With its sharp claws fully extended, it can climb right up an iceberg without slipping.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It runs across snow-covered plains at high speeds. It developed thick, sharp claws to plow through the snow.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s steel spikes are sheathed in ice. Stabs from these spikes cause deep wounds and severe frostbite as well.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Fleeing a volcanic eruption, it settled on a snowy mountain. As it races through the snowfields, it sends up a spray of snow.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It curls up, then rolls into foes with its back. Its sharp spines inflict severe damage.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It climbs trees by hooking on with its sharp claws. Sandslash shares the berries it gathers, dropping them down to Sandshrew waiting below the tree.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon’s spikes will feel when touched.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It is skilled at slashing enemies with its claws. If broken, they start to grow back in a day.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Thanks to its thick claws, it’s good at climbing trees. There are plenty of Sandslash that park themselves in trees and go right to sleep.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Its claws and horns often break off. The broken claws and horns can be used to carve plows for tilling farm fields.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It uses its claws to climb trees and then curls its body into a spiny ball, ready to drop onto any prey that appears.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Although they are sharp, its claws and spikes often break off. They grow back the next day, so it is not bothered by the temporary loss.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Sandslash can roll up its body as if it were a ball covered with large spikes. In battle, this Pokémon will try to make the foe flinch by jabbing it with its spines. It then leaps at the stunned foe to tear wildly with its sharp claws.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Sandslash’s body is covered by tough spikes, which are hardened sections of its hide. Once a year, the old spikes fall out, to be replaced with new spikes that grow out from beneath the old ones.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: If it digs at an incredible pace, it may snap off its spikes and claws. They grow back in a day.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: In an attempt to hide itself, it will run around at top speed to kick up a blinding dust storm.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It curls up in a ball to protect itself from enemy attacks. It also curls up to prevent heatstroke during the daytime when temperatures rise sharply.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: It is adept at attacking with the spines on its back and its sharp claws while quickly scurrying about.

Name: Sandslash
FlavorText: Adept at climbing trees, it rolls into a spiny ball, then attacks its enemies from above.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: While this Pokémon does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the venom it secretes from its barbs can be fatal.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran’s horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male’s horn.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they’ll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: A mild-mannered Pokémon that does not like to fight. Beware—its small horn secretes venom.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: Nidoran♀ has barbs that secrete a powerful poison. They are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied Pokémon. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: Small and very docile, it protects itself with its small, poisonous horn when attacked.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: Although small, its venomous barbs render this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: While it does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the poison it secretes from barbs can be fatal.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: Although not very combative, it will torment its foes with poison spikes if it is threatened in any way.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: The poison hidden in its small horn is extremely potent. Even a tiny scratch can have fatal results.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: Its highly toxic barbs are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied POKéMON. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: Though small, it must be treated with caution because of its powerfully toxic barbs. The female has smaller horns.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: NIDORAN has barbs that secrete a powerful poison. They are thought to have developed as protection for this small-bodied POKéMON. When enraged, it releases a horrible toxin from its horn.

Name: Nidoran♀ (female)
FlavorText: A mild-mannered POKéMON that does not like to fight. Beware, its small horns secrete venom.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow more slowly than Nidorino’s.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get poked while their mother is feeding them.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When Nidorina are with their friends or family, they keep their barbs tucked away to prevent hurting each other. This Pokémon appears to become nervous if separated from the others.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When feeding its young, it first chews the food into a paste, then spits it out for the offspring.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: The female has a gentle temperament. It emits ultrasonic cries that have the power to befuddle foes.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow slower than Nidorino’s.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: It has a calm and caring nature. Because its horn grows slowly, it prefers not to fight.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When it is with its friends or family, its barbs are tucked away to prevent injury. It appears to become nervous if separated from the others.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: The female’s horns develop slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: It has a docile nature. If it is threatened with attack, it raises the barbs that are all over its body.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When feeding its young, it first chews and tenderizes the food, then spits it out for the offspring.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: When resting deep in its burrow, its thorns always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

Name: Nidorina
FlavorText: The female’s horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: Tough scales cover the sturdy body of this Pokémon. It appears that the scales grow in cycles.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: Nidoqueen’s body is encased in extremely hard scales. It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles. This Pokémon is at its strongest when it is defending its young.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: The body is covered by stiff, needlelike scales. If it becomes excited, the needles bristle outwards.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: It uses its scaly, rugged body to seal the entrance of its nest and protect its young from predators.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: Its body is covered with needle-like scales. It never shows signs of shrinking from any attack.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles using its tough, scaly body. This POKéMON is at its strongest when it is defending its young.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: The body is covered by stiff, needle-like scales. If it becomes excited, the needles bristle outwards.

Name: Nidoqueen
FlavorText: The hard scales that cover its strong body serve as excellent protection from any attack.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: Small but brave, this Pokémon will hold its ground and even risk its life in battle to protect the female it’s friendly with.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses danger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: Nidoran♂ has developed muscles for moving its ears. Thanks to them, the ears can be freely moved in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this Pokémon’s notice.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. It will strike first if it senses any danger.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: It is small, but its horn is filled with poison. It charges then stabs with the horn to inject poison.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: The male NIDORAN has developed muscles that freely move its ears in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this POKéMON’s notice.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: It stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more  powerful its secreted venom.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: The male NIDORAN has developed muscles for moving its ears. Thanks to them, the ears can be freely moved in any direction. Even the slightest sound does not escape this POKéMON’s notice.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: It constantly moves its large ears in many directions in order to detect danger right away.

Name: Nidoran♂ (male)
FlavorText: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes venom upon impact.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: It’s nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: With a horn that’s harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: Its horn contains venom. If it stabs an enemy with the horn, the impact makes the poison leak out.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: Nidorino has a horn that is harder than a diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: An aggressive Pokémon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. If it senses anything, it attacks immediately.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: Quick to anger, it stabs enemies with its horn to inject a powerful poison when it becomes agitated.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: Its horn is harder than a diamond. If it senses a hostile presence, all the barbs on its back bristle up at once, and it challenges the foe with all its might.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: It is easily angered. By swinging its well-developed horn wildly, it can even punch through diamond.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: It is easily agitated and uses its horn for offense as soon as it notices an attacker.

Name: Nidorino
FlavorText: Its horns contain venom. If they are stabbed into an enemy, the impact makes the poison leak out.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It’s forceful and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail and diamond-crushing horn.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: When it goes on a rampage, it’s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle. Its horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: Nidoking’s thick tail packs enormously destructive power. With one swing, it can topple a metal transmission tower. Once this Pokémon goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn, as it contains venom.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: Its tail is thick and powerful. If it binds an enemy, it can render the victim helpless quite easily.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: It swings its big tail around during battle. If its foe flinches, it will charge with its sturdy body.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: A NIDOKING’s thick tail packs enormously destructive power capable of toppling a metal transmission tower. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey’s bones.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn as it contains venom.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: It uses its thick arms, legs and tail to attack forcefully. Melee combat is its specialty.

Name: Nidoking
FlavorText: Its tail is thick and powerful. If it binds an enemy, it can snap the victim’s spine quite easily.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: It can be found in quiet mountain areas on a full moon’s night. Its dancing and its tiny, faintly glowing wings confer upon it a lovely fairylike quality.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Moonlight gathers on the wings on Clefairy’s back, allowing Clefairy to fly. This Pokémon is difficult to find.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Thought to live with others on quiet mountains, it is popular for its adorable nature.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this cute Pokémon is rarely found.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Adored for their cute looks and playfulness. They are thought to be rare, as they do not appear often.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Bathed in moonlight, its wings glow faintly. Without even flapping, Clefairy rises into the air, where it dances around.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: They’re popular, but they’re rare. Trainers who show them off recklessly may be targeted by thieves.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: On nights with a full moon, they gather together and dance. The surrounding area is enveloped in an abnormal magnetic field.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Its adorable behavior and appearance make it popular with men and women, young and old. Its numbers are few, however.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: On every night of a full moon, groups of this Pokémon come out to play. When dawn arrives, the tired Clefairy return to their quiet mountain retreats and go to sleep nestled up against each other.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: On nights with a full moon, Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: It flies using the wings on its back to collect moonlight. This Pokémon is difficult to find.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: On every night of a full moon, they come out to play. When dawn arrives, the tired CLEFAIRY go to sleep nestled up against each other in deep and quiet mountains.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: With its magical and cute appeal, it has  many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Its adorable appearance makes it popular as a pet. However, it is rare and difficult to find.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Though rarely seen, it becomes easier to spot, for some reason, on the night of a  full moon.

Name: Clefairy
FlavorText: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Legend says that on clear, quiet nights, it listens for the voices of its kin living on the moon. I, too, often think of my homeland, so far away.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Its hearing is so acute it can hear a pin drop over half a mile away. It lives on quiet mountains.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Rarely seen by people, it is said to be drawn by the full moon to play at deserted lakes.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they’re usually found in quiet places.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: They appear to be very protective of their own world. It is a kind of fairy, rarely seen by people.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Some scientists believe that it gazes intently at the sky on nights with a full moon because it’s homesick.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: It can’t help but hear a pin drop from over half a mile away, so it lives deep in the mountains where there aren’t many people or Pokémon.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: According to tradition, people who see a pair of Clefable skipping by can look forward to a happy marriage.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: They don’t like to reveal themselves in front of people. They live quietly in packs deep in the mountains.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Clefable moves by skipping lightly as if it were flying using its wings. Its bouncy step lets it even walk on water. It is known to take strolls on lakes on quiet, moonlit nights.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: It is very wary and rarely shows itself to people. Its ears can hear a pin drop over half a mile away.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Its very sensitive ears let it distinguish distant sounds. As a result, it prefers quiet places.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: With its acute hearing, it can pick up sounds from far away. It usually hides in quiet places.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: A CLEFABLE uses its wings to skip lightly  as if it were flying. Its bouncy step lets it even walk on water. On quiet, moonlit nights, it strolls on lakes.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: It has an acute sense of hearing. It can easily hear a pin being dropped nearly 1,100 yards away.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Said to live in quiet, remote mountains, this type of fairy has a strong aversion to being seen.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: Its very sensitive ears lets it distinguish distant sounds. As a result, it prefers quiet places.

Name: Clefable
FlavorText: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in packs in the snowy mountains and defend themselves with icy breath. I suspect this species changed its form to adapt to the frigid climate.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: If you observe its curly hairs through a microscope, you’ll see small ice particles springing up.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: After long years in the ever-snowcapped mountains of Alola, this Vulpix has gained power over ice.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It looks like snow come to life, and the breath it exhales is –58 degrees Fahrenheit. Another name for it is Keokeo.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: They live together in a skulk, helping one another. Before eating their prey, they freeze it solid with their –58 degree Fahrenheit breath.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: If you carelessly approach it because it’s cute, the boss of the pack, Ninetales, will appear and freeze you.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: In hot weather, this Pokémon makes ice shards with its six tails and sprays them around to cool itself off.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It exhales air colder than -58 degrees Fahrenheit. Elderly people in Alola call this Pokémon by an older name—Keokeo.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: In its belly burns a fire, which Vulpix spits out in the form of fireballs. When young, this Pokémon has but one white tail. As the Pokémon matures, this single tail splits into six.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Both its fur and its tails are beautiful. As it grows, the tails split and form more tails.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It manipulates balls of fire to catch its prey. If you raise one from when it’s young, it will grow close to you like a puppy Pokémon.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Its beautiful tails have made it very popular. However, if it’s not brushed diligently, it will be a mass of tangles before you know it.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: From its mouth spew flames that seem to resemble the spirits of the deceased. Some people mistakenly think this fire is a ghost.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Its beautiful fur and tails have made it very popular. As it grows, its tails split to form more tails.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Inside Vulpix’s body burns a flame that never goes out. During the daytime, when the temperatures rise, this Pokémon releases flames from its mouth to prevent its body from growing too hot.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: At the time of its birth, Vulpix has one white tail. The tail separates into six if this Pokémon receives plenty of love from its Trainer. The six tails become magnificently curled.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: When it is born, it has just one snow-white tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: If it is attacked by an enemy that is stronger than itself, it feigns injury to fool the enemy and escapes.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As it develops, its single white tail gains color and splits into six. It is quite warm and cuddly.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It can freely control fire, making fiery orbs fly like will-o’-the-wisps. Just before evolution, its six tails grow hot  as if on fire.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As its body grows larger, its six warm tails become more beautiful, with a more luxurious coat of fur.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As it develops,  its single white tail gains color and splits into six. It is quite warm and cuddly.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Dwells on sacred peaks perpetually covered in snow. Said to appear to virtuous people who have lost their way on mountain paths—it then guides them back down to the mountain’s base.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: While it will guide travelers who get lost on a snowy mountain down to the mountain’s base, it won’t forgive anyone who harms nature.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: A deity resides in the snowy mountains where this Pokémon lives. In ancient times, it was worshiped as that deity’s incarnation.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It lives on mountains perpetually covered in snow and is revered as a deity incarnate. It appears draped in a blizzard.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Some said that deities visited mountains where Ninetales live, so in times long past, no one was allowed to go into those mountains.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: The reason it guides people all the way down to the mountain’s base is that it wants them to hurry up and leave.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Possessing a calm demeanor, this Pokémon was revered as a deity incarnate before it was identified as a regional variant of Ninetales.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It creates drops of ice in its coat and showers them over its enemies. Anyone who angers it will be frozen stiff in an instant.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: The coat of gleaming golden fur is quite magnificent. This species is said to store sacred power in its nine long tails and to live for a millennium.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. The Pokémon is said to live for 1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: According to an enduring legend, nine noble saints were united and reincarnated as this Pokémon.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: The flickering flames it spews from its mouth leave its opponents hypnotized. Then, this extremely intelligent Pokémon attacks.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It is vindictive and relentless by nature. Those who cross it even once will be cursed for a thousand years, along with their descendants.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Said to live for a thousand years, this Pokémon uses its supernatural abilities to manipulate fire. It can burn its prey to a crisp as it pleases.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Legend has it that this mystical Pokémon was formed when nine saints coalesced into one.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Legend has it that Ninetales came into being when nine wizards possessing sacred powers merged into one. This Pokémon is highly intelligent—it can understand human speech.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Ninetales casts a sinister light from its bright red eyes to gain total control over its foe’s mind. This Pokémon is said to live for a thousand years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It has nine long tails and fur that gleams gold. It is said to live for 1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Each of its nine tails is imbued with supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. It can live for a thousand years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Its nine beautiful tails are filled with a wondrous energy that could keep it alive for 1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Some legends claim that each of its nine tails has its own unique type of special mystical power.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It has long been said that each of the nine tails embody an enchanted power. A long-lived NINETALES will have fur that shines like gold.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It has nine long tails and fur that  gleams gold. It is said to live for  1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Legend has it that NINETALES came into being when nine wizards possessing sacred powers merged into one. This POKéMON is highly intelligent - it can understand human speech.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It is said to live a thousand years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: According to an enduring legend, 9 noble saints were united and reincarnated as this POKéMON.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: When it wavers its big, round eyes, it begins singing a lullaby that makes everyone drowsy.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: By freely changing the wavelength of its voice, Jigglypuff sings a mysterious melody sure to make any listener sleepy.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Jigglypuff has top-notch lung capacity, even by comparison to other Pokémon. It won’t stop singing its lullabies until its foes fall asleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Uses its cute round eyes to enrapture its foe. It then sings a pleasing melody that lulls the foe to sleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: The songs they sing are totally different depending on the region they live in. Some even sound like they’re shouting!

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Recordings of Jigglypuff’s strange lullabies can be purchased from department stores. These CDs can be found near the bedding area.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Jigglypuff possess a vocal range that exceeds 12 octaves, but each individual’s singing skill depends on its own effort.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: It hugely inflates its stomach and sings a mysterious melody. If you hear this melody, you’ll become sleepy right away.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: When this Pokémon sings, it never pauses to breathe. If it is in a battle against an opponent that does not easily fall asleep, Jigglypuff cannot breathe, endangering its life.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Jigglypuff’s vocal cords can freely adjust the wavelength of its voice. This Pokémon uses this ability to sing at precisely the right wavelength to make its foes most drowsy.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: It captivates foes with its huge, round eyes, then lulls them to sleep by singing a soothing melody.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Looking into its cute, round eyes makes it start singing a song so pleasant listeners can’t help but fall asleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Looking into its cute, round eyes causes it to sing a relaxing melody, inducing its enemies to sleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Nothing can avoid falling asleep hearing a JIGGLYPUFF’s song. The sound waves of its singing voice match the brain waves of someone in a deep sleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: JIGGLYPUFF’s vocal chords can freely adjust the wavelength of its voice. This POKéMON uses this ability to sing at precisely the right wavelength to make its foes most drowsy.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: It rolls its cute eyes as it sings a soothing lullaby. Its gentle song puts anyone who hears it to sleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: Uses its alluring eyes to enrapture its foe. It then sings a pleasing melody that lulls the foe to sleep.

Name: Jigglypuff
FlavorText: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: The rich, fluffy fur that covers its body feels so good that anyone who feels it can’t stop touching it.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Its fine fur feels sublime to the touch. It can expand its body by inhaling air.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: It’s proud of its fur, which is fine and delicate. In particular, the curl on its forehead has a texture that’s perfectly heavenly.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: The more air it takes in, the more it inflates. If opponents catch it in a bad mood, it will inflate itself to an enormous size to intimidate them.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Its body is very elastic. By inhaling deeply, it can continue to inflate itself without limit.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: When it gets angry, it inhales with all its might, and its body gradually inflates. Sometimes they can grow 20 times larger!

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Thanks to its bouncy body and fine fur, this Pokémon is sought after. Holding one in your arms while you sleep feels great.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: As it inhales, it expands...and expands...and expands. Wigglytuff compete to see which one can inflate itself the most.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: It sheds its fine fur when the seasons change. The fur is gathered and spun into a luxurious yarn.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Wigglytuff’s body is very flexible. By inhaling deeply, this Pokémon can inflate itself seemingly without end. Once inflated, Wigglytuff bounces along lightly like a balloon.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Wigglytuff has large, saucerlike eyes. The surfaces of its eyes are always covered with a thin layer of tears. If any dust gets in this Pokémon’s eyes, it is quickly washed away.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Their fur feels so good that if two of them snuggle together, they won’t want to be separated.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Its fine fur feels so pleasant, those who accidentally touch it cannot take their hands away.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Its fur is the ultimate in luxuriousness. Sleeping alongside a WIGGLYTUFF is simply divine. Its body expands seemingly without end when it inhales.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Its fur is extremely fine, dense, and supple. The exquisitely pleasant fur conveys an image of luxury.

Name: Wigglytuff
FlavorText: Its body is full of elasticity. By inhaling deeply, it can continue to inflate itself without limit.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Makes its home in gloomy caves. Atrophied eyes have left this Pokémon blind, so it scans its surroundings via sound waves that it emits from its mouth as it flies.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Disliking sunlight, it sleeps deep in forests and caves until sundown.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Even though it has no eyes, it can sense obstacles using ultrasonic waves it emits from its mouth.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun’s light won’t reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as a sonar used to check for objects in its way.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Their skin is so thin that they’ll be burned if sunlight hits them. When it gets cold out, they gather together to warm one another’s bodies.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It has no eyeballs, so it can’t see. It checks its surroundings via the ultrasonic waves it emits from its mouth.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: When exposed to sunlight, they suffer burns. The frequency of their ultrasonic waves can differ slightly from colony to colony.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It sleeps in caves during the day. It has no eyes, so to check its surroundings while flying, it emits ultrasonic waves.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Zubat avoids sunlight because exposure causes it to become unhealthy. During the daytime, it stays in caves or under the eaves of old houses, sleeping while hanging upside down.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Zubat remains quietly unmoving in a dark spot during the bright daylight hours. It does so because prolonged exposure to the sun causes its body to become slightly burned.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It has no eyes. Instead, it relies on its ultrasonic cries for echolocation to flit about in darkness.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It does not need eyes, because it emits ultrasonic waves to check its surroundings while it flies.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It checks its surroundings and location using reflections of the ultrasonic waves from its mouth.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Capable of flying safely in dark places, it emits ultrasonic cries to check for any obstacles.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: While flying, it constantly emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: While living in pitch-black caverns, their eyes gradually grew shut and deprived them of vision. They use ultrasonic waves to detect obstacles.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It forms colonies in perpetually dark  places and uses ultrasonic waves to   identify and approach targets.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: It has no eyes. Instead, it relies on its ultrasonic cries for echo location to flit about in darkness.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: During the day, it gathers with others and hangs from the ceilings of old buildings and caves.

Name: Zubat
FlavorText: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: It sinks its sharp fangs into other creatures and slurps up their blood. A closer look at the fangs reveals that they are hollow and akin to straws.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Once it starts sucking blood, it does not stop until it is full. It flies at night in search of prey.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: It loves the blood of humans and Pokémon. It flies around at night in search of neck veins.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and to suck blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: They can suck down over 10 ounces of blood in one go. They have been known to drink so much blood that they can no longer fly.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Every once in a while, you’ll see a Golbat that’s missing some fangs. This happens when hunger drives it to try biting a Steel-type Pokémon.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Sometimes they drink so much blood, they can’t fly anymore. Then they fall to the ground and become food for other Pokémon.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Its thick fangs are hollow like straws, making them unexpectedly fragile. These fangs are specialized for sucking blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Golbat bites down on prey with its four fangs and drinks the victim’s blood. It becomes active on inky dark moonless nights, flying around to attack people and Pokémon.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Golbat loves to drink the blood of living things. It is particularly active in the pitch black of night. This Pokémon flits around in the night skies, seeking fresh blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Once it bites, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Flitting around in the dead of night, it sinks its fangs into its prey and drains a nearly fatal amount of blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Its sharp fangs puncture the toughest of hides and have small holes for greedily sucking blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: It can drink more than 10 ounces of blood at once. If it has too much, it gets heavy and flies clumsily.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: However hard its victim’s hide may be, it punctures with sharp fangs and gorges itself with blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Its fangs easily puncture even thick animal hide. It loves to feast on the blood of people and POKéMON. It flits about in darkness and strikes from behind.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: It clamps down on its prey with needle-sharp fangs and drains over 10 ounces of blood in one gulp.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: When it plunges its fangs into its prey, it instantly draws and gulps down more than ten ounces of blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and suck blood.

Name: Golbat
FlavorText: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: It may be mistaken for a clump of weeds. If you try to yank it out of the ground, it shrieks horribly.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Oddish searches for fertile, nutrient-rich soil, then plants itself. During the daytime, while it is planted, this Pokémon’s feet are thought to change shape and become similar to the roots of trees.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the daytime, Oddish buries itself in soil to absorb nutrients from the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Its scientific name is “Oddium Wanderus.” At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Awakened by moonlight, it roams actively at night. In the day, it stays quietly underground.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: This POKéMON grows by absorbing moonlight. During the daytime, it buries itself in the ground, leaving only its leaves exposed to avoid detection by its enemies.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the daytime, ODDISH buries itself in soil to absorb nutrients from  the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Awakened by moonlight, it roams  actively at night. In the day, it stays quietly underground.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The nectar it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious that it can make noses curl from more than a mile away.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: From its mouth Gloom drips honey that smells absolutely horrible. Apparently, it loves the horrid stench. It sniffs the noxious fumes and then drools even more of its honey.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Gloom releases a foul fragrance from the pistil of its flower. When faced with danger, the stench worsens. If this Pokémon is feeling calm and secure, it does not release its usual stinky aroma.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: It secretes a sticky, drool-like honey. Although sweet, it smells too repulsive to get very close.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: A horribly noxious honey drools from its mouth. One whiff of the honey can result in memory loss. Some fans are said to enjoy this overwhelming stink, however.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn’t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: From its mouth GLOOM drips honey that smells absolutely horrible. Apparently, it loves the horrid stench. It sniffs the noxious fumes and then  drools even more of its honey.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The smell from its drool-like syrup and the pollen on its petals is so bad, it may make opponents faint.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around 1 out of 1,000 people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Flaps its broad flower petals to scatter its poisonous pollen. The flapping sound is very loud.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Vileplume has the world’s largest petals. They are used to attract prey that are then doused with toxic spores. Once the prey are immobilized, this Pokémon catches and devours them.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Vileplume’s toxic pollen triggers atrocious allergy attacks. That’s why it is advisable never to approach any attractive flowers in a jungle, however pretty they may be.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic, poisonous pollen.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: In seasons when it produces more pollen, the air around a VILEPLUME turns yellow with the powder as it walks. The pollen is highly toxic and causes paralysis.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. It fiendishly scatters allergy-causing pollen from its petals.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: By shaking its big petals, it scatters toxic pollen into the air, turning the air yellow.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Sometimes seen at the foot of trees in humid forests. The mushrooms on its back—called tochukaso—are not present on infant specimens and instead emerge as Paras matures.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Whether it’s due to a lack of moisture or a lack of nutrients, in Alola the mushrooms on Paras don’t grow up quite right.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Mushrooms called tochukaso sprout from its back. They can be dried and powdered to make a medicine used to extend life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Paras has parasitic mushrooms growing on its back called tochukaso. They grow large by drawing nutrients from this Bug Pokémon host. They are highly valued as a medicine for extending life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Growing out of the bug’s back are mushrooms called tochukaso. The mushrooms grow with the bug host.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: As its body grows, large mushrooms named tochukaso start sprouting out of its back.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: It is doused with mushroom spores when it is born. As its body grows, mushrooms sprout from its back.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: A PARAS has parasitic tochukaso mushrooms growing on its back. They grow by drawing nutrients from the host. They are valued as a medicine for long life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: PARAS has parasitic mushrooms growing on its back called tochukaso. They grow large by drawing nutrients from the BUG POKéMON host. They are highly valued as a medicine for extending life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: The tochukaso growing on this POKéMON’s back orders it to extract juice from tree trunks.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: As its body grows large, oriental mushrooms named tochukaso start sprouting out of its back.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect’s actions.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It is controlled by the mushroom, which has grown larger than the bug body. It is said to prefer damp places.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Parasect is controlled by a mushroom that has grown larger than its host’s body. The Pokémon scatters poisonous spores.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushrooms on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Its poisonous spores are also used in traditional medicine. Apparently, spores produced in Alola are not of very good quality.

Name: Parasect
