FlavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It scatters toxic spores from its mushroom cap. Once harvested, these spores can be steeped and boiled down to prepare herbal medicines.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Parasect is known to infest large trees en masse and drain nutrients from the lower trunk and roots. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: A mushroom grown larger than the host’s body controls Parasect. It scatters poisonous spores.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It stays mostly in dark, damp places, the preference not of the bug, but of the big mushroom on its back.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It is controlled by a mushroom grown larger than the bug body. It is said to prefer damp places.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: PARASECT are known to infest the roots of large trees en masse and drain nutrients. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It scatters toxic spores from the mushroom cap. In China, the spores are used as herbal medicine.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: When nothing’s left to extract from the bug, the mushrooms on its back leave spores on the bug’s egg.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It stays mostly in dark, damp places, the preference not of the bug, but of the big mushrooms on its back.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushrooms on its back. They appear to do all the thinking.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Its eyes act as radar, enabling it to be active in darkness. The eyes can also shoot powerful beams.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Its large eyes act as a radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Venonat is said to have evolved with a coat of thin, stiff hair that covers its entire body for protection. It possesses large eyes that never fail to spot even minuscule prey.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats bugs. It is attracted by light at night.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches and eats small bugs at night that are attracted by light.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Its eyes also function as radar units. It catches and eats small bugs that hide in darkness.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Its coat of thin, stiff hair that covers its entire body is said to have evolved for protection. Its large eyes never fail to spot even miniscule prey.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: VENONAT is said to have evolved with a coat of thin, stiff hair that covers its entire body for protection. It possesses large eyes that never fail to spot even miniscule prey.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: The small bugs it eats appear only at night, so it sleeps in a hole in a tree until night falls.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Its large eyes act as radars. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

Name: Venonat
FlavorText: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: When it attacks, it flaps its large wings violently to scatter its poisonous powder all around.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: Venomoth is nocturnal—it is a Pokémon that only becomes active at night. Its favorite prey are small insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The scales it scatters will paralyze anyone who touches them, making that person unable to stand.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The powder on its wings is poisonous if it is dark in hue. If it is light in hue, it causes paralysis.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: VENOMOTH are nocturnal--they only are active at night. Their favorite prey are insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The dustlike scales covering its wings are color-coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: VENOMOTH is nocturnal - it is a POKéMON that only becomes active at night. Its favorite prey are small insects that gather around streetlights, attracted by the light in the darkness.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The powder on its wings is poisonous if it is dark in color. If it is light, it causes paralysis.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

Name: Venomoth
FlavorText: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Its three hairs change shape depending on Diglett’s mood. They’re a useful communication tool among these Pokémon.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: The metal-rich geology of this Pokémon’s habitat caused it to develop steel whiskers on its head.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: After living in soil with high iron content for some time, three steel whiskers sprouted from the top of its head.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: The need to dig through volcanic rock in the ground has made them more powerful than the Diglett of other regions.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Although it’s powerful enough to dig right through volcanic rock, it doesn’t allow itself to be seen very often.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Its golden hairs function as sensors. It pokes them out of its burrow to monitor its surroundings.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Its head sports an altered form of whiskers made of metal. When in communication with its comrades, its whiskers wobble to and fro.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: It prefers dark places. It spends most of its time underground, though it may pop up in caves.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Around their crops, farmers plant the kind of tree that Diglett like to eat as a way of getting Diglett to plow the fields for them.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: It travels through tunnels that it digs underground. It hates sunlight, so it comes out only after the sun goes down.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Many farmers cherish and nurture Diglett because its droppings enrich the soil it lives in.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: It chews on plant roots underground. Farmers whose vegetables are vulnerable find it can be quite a pest.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Diglett are raised in most farms. The reason is simple— wherever this Pokémon burrows, the soil is left perfectly tilled for planting crops. This soil is made ideal for growing delicious vegetables.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: DIGLETT are raised in most farms. The reason is simple--wherever they burrow, the soil is left perfectly tilled for growing delicious crops.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: DIGLETT are raised in most farms. The reason is simple - wherever this POKéMON burrows, the soil is left perfectly tilled for planting crops. This soil is made ideal for growing delicious vegetables.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: It digs underground and chews on tree roots, sticking its head out only when the sun isn’t bright.

Name: Diglett
FlavorText: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: The three of them get along very well. Through their formidable teamwork, they defeat powerful opponents.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Their beautiful, metallic whiskers create a sort of protective helmet on their heads, and they also function as highly precise sensors.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: They’re referred to as triplets, but they’re not identical—the metallic elements in their bodies differ slightly. The proof shows in their whiskers!

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Its shining gold whiskers are advanced sensors that can detect vibrations from sounds several miles away.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Its metallic whiskers are heavy, so it’s not very fast, but it has the power to dig through bedrock.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: These Pokémon are cherished in the Alola region, where they are thought to be feminine deities of the land incarnate.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Its shining gold hair provides it with protection. It’s reputed that keeping any of its fallen hairs will bring bad luck.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: These Diglett triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it’s like underground.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: A team of triplets that can burrow to a depth of 60 miles. It’s reported that this triggers an earthquake.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Dugtrio’s heads are sleek and smooth and incredibly hard. It can dig through any soil with its headbutts.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: While the three of them normally get along splendidly, on rare occasions a huge fight will break out over which head gets to eat first.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Despite the closeness between this Pokémon and farmers and other people, no one has ever seen the parts of it concealed underground.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: This set of triplets moves cooperatively. It’s the power of teamwork that enables this Pokémon to dig to a depth of 60 miles.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Extremely powerful, they can dig through even the hardest ground to a depth of over 60 miles.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: Because the triplets originally split from one body, they think exactly alike. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly through the ground.

Name: Dugtrio
FlavorText: A team of triplets that can burrow over 60 MPH. Due to this, some people think it’s an earthquake.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect among Meowth.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokémon’s body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Deeply proud and keenly smart, this Pokémon moves with cunning during battle and relentlessly attacks enemies’ weak points.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It’s accustomed to luxury because it used to live with Alolan royalty. As a result, it’s very picky about food.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Highly intelligent and prideful, it’s famously difficult to handle—but that’s also a reason for its popularity.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: A royal house that flourished in the distant past brought it here from another region. Meowth is both selfish and prideful.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It’s impulsive, selfish, and fickle. It’s very popular with some Trainers who like giving it the attention it needs.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: When its delicate pride is wounded, or when the gold coin on its forehead is dirtied, it flies into a hysterical rage.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: This Pokémon was not originally found in Alola. Human actions caused a surge in their numbers, and they went feral. They’re prideful and crafty.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Its body has grown incredibly long and the coin on its forehead has grown incredibly large—all thanks to Gigantamax power.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: The pattern that has appeared on its giant coin is thought to be the key to unlocking the secrets of the Dynamax phenomenon.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines, too.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It is nocturnal by nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter as brightly as the shiny object.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It doesn’t get along with Galarian Meowth.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can’t stop itself from picking them up.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It loves coins, so if you give it one, you can make friends with Meowth easily. But it’s fickle, so you can’t count on that friendship lasting.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: When visiting a junkyard, you may catch sight of it having an intense fight with Murkrow over shiny objects.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It loves shiny things. It often fights with Murkrow over prey they’re both trying to catch.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It lies around all day, becoming active near dusk. At night, it wanders the city in search of loose change.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Meowth withdraws its sharp claws into its paws to slinkily sneak about without making any incriminating footsteps. For some reason, this Pokémon loves shiny coins that glitter with light.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It loves anything that shines. It especially adores coins that it picks up and secretly hoards.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It is fascinated by round objects. It can’t stop playing with them until it tires and falls asleep.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: MEOWTH withdraw their sharp claws into their paws to silently sneak about. For some reason, this POKéMON loves shiny coins that glitter with light.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: It loves things that sparkle. When it sees a shiny object, the gold coin on its head shines too.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can’t stop from picking them up.

Name: Meowth
FlavorText: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: This Pokémon is one tough opponent. Not only does it have formidable physical abilities, but it’s also not above fighting dirty.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: The round face of Alolan Persian is considered to be a symbol of prosperity in the Alola region, so these Pokémon are very well cared for.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: It has the classiest coat. The rippling of its fur in the heat of battle has a beauty all its own.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Its round face is a symbol of wealth. Persian that have bigger, plumper faces are considered more beautiful.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: In contrast to its lovely face, it’s so brutal that it tortures its weakened prey rather than finishing them off.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: It looks down on everyone other than itself. Its preferred tactics are sucker punches and blindside attacks.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Its round face and smooth coat—softer than the most high-class velvet—have made this a very popular Pokémon in Alola.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: It has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. This is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: It is a very haughty Pokémon. Among fans of Persian, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Getting this prideful Pokémon to warm up to you takes a lot of effort, and it will claw at you the moment it gets annoyed.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: The gem in its forehead glows on its own! It walks with all the grace and elegance of a proud queen.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: This Pokémon is popular with rich people. It’s also targeted by hunters who are after the jewel in its forehead.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Although the jewel on its forehead appears to be a different color than those of Alolan Persian, it’s mostly made of the same material.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: It has a high opinion of itself, although not to the same extent as the Alolan Persian. It’s quite difficult to make friends with this Pokémon.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: It has a violent temperament. It will attack anything that looks it in the eye. Its sharp claws inflict deep wounds.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Persian has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in the Pokémon’s surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: A very haughty Pokémon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Many adore it for its sophisticated air. However, it will lash out and scratch for little reason.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: A PERSIAN’s six bold whiskers sense air movements to determine what is in its vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Has a vicious temperament. Beware if it raises its tail straight up. It is a signal that it is about to pounce and bite.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: PERSIAN has six bold whiskers that give it a look of toughness. The whiskers   sense air movements to determine what is in the POKéMON’s surrounding vicinity. It becomes docile if grabbed by the whiskers.

Name: Persian
FlavorText: Behind its lithe, elegant appearance lies a barbaric side. It will tear apart its prey on a mere whim.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Suffers perpetual headaches. If the agony grows too great, Psyduck’s latent power erupts, contrary to Psyduck’s intent. Ergo, I am exploring ways to ease the pain.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It never remembers using its odd powers, so it always tilts its head in puzzlement.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: If its usual headache worsens, it starts exhibiting odd powers. It can’t remember doing so, however.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: As Psyduck gets stressed out, its headache gets progressively worse. It uses intense psychic energy to overwhelm those around it.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Psyduck is constantly beset by headaches. If the Pokémon lets its strange power erupt, apparently the pain subsides for a while.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but whether it intends to do so is not known.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It has been found that its brain cells are 10 times more active when Psyduck is experiencing a headache.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Using psychokinesis gives it a headache, so it normally passes the time spacing out and doing as little as possible.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: This Pokémon is troubled by constant headaches. The more pain it’s in, the more powerful its psychokinesis becomes.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: If it uses its mysterious power, Psyduck can’t remember having done so. It apparently can’t form a memory of such an event because it goes into an altered state that is much like deep sleep.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Psyduck uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this Pokémon generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It has mystical powers but doesn’t recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: When its headache intensifies, it starts using strange powers. However, it has no recollection of its powers, so it always looks befuddled and bewildered.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: PSYDUCK uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this POKéMON  generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: The only time it can use its psychic power is when its sleeping brain cells happen to wake.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but it is not known if it intends to do so.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It swims gracefully along on the quiet, slow-moving rivers and lakes of which it is so fond.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Its body is strong, and it has webbing on its hands and feet. Golduck can swim easily through rough seas, clawing its way through the high waves.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: The flippers of its well-developed limbs give it shocking speed. It is the best swimmer among Pokémon.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in lakes. It swims faster than any world-class swimmer.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Old tales tell of Golduck punishing those that defiled its river. The guilty were dragged into the water and taken away.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: A professional swimmer, it can continue swimming for two days straight by waving its long tail skillfully.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Even fast-swimming fish Pokémon can be disabled by Golduck. It brings them to a standstill and seizes them.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It swims along the banks of lakes and catches fish Pokémon. It takes them to the shore and quietly eats them up.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It is said that the red part of its forehead grants supernatural powers to those who possess one, so it was over-hunted in the past.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Golduck is the fastest swimmer among all Pokémon. It swims effortlessly, even in a rough, stormy sea. It sometimes rescues people from wrecked ships floundering in high seas.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: The webbed flippers on its forelegs and hind legs and the streamlined body of Golduck give it frightening speed. This Pokémon is definitely much faster than even the most athletic swimmer.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It appears by waterways at dusk. It may use telekinetic powers if its forehead glows mysteriously.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: When its forehead shines mysteriously, Golduck can use the full extent of its power.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It is seen swimming dynamically and elegantly using its well-developed limbs and flippers.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lives in lakes. It swims faster than any human swimming champion.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: A GOLDUCK is an adept swimmer. It sometimes joins competitive swimmers in training. It uses psychic powers when its forehead shimmers with light.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Often seen swimming elegantly by lakeshores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster Kappa.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Its slim and long limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Often seen swimming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: It is extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away the next instant.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: It lives in treetop colonies. If one member of the group becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: If one gets angry, all the others around it will get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop of Mankey.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: The smallest of things could cause it to lose its temper. Because it doesn’t hold in its stress, this Pokémon can live a long time.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: Its raging tires it out and causes it to fall asleep, but the anger resonating in its dreams causes it to wake up—which infuriates it all over again.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: It can spontaneously become enraged. Everyone near it clears out as it rampages, and the resulting loneliness makes it angrier still.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: When Mankey starts shaking and its nasal breathing turns rough, it’s a sure sign that it is becoming angry. However, because it goes into a towering rage almost instantly, it is impossible for anyone to flee its wrath.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: It’s unsafe to approach if it gets violently enraged for no reason and can’t distinguish friends from foes.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: It is extremely ill-tempered. Groups of them will attack any handy target for no reason.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: When it starts shaking and its nasal breathing turns rough, it’s a sure sign of anger. However, since this happens instantly, there is no time to flee.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment, then thrashing away  the next instant.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: Light and agile on its feet, and ferocious in temperament. When angered, it flies into an uncontrollable frenzy.

Name: Mankey
FlavorText: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: Some researchers theorize that Primeape remains angry even when inside a Poké Ball.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It becomes angry if it sees an opponent’s eyes and gets angrier if the opponent runs. Even after it beats the opponent, it is still angry.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: The blood vessels in its brain are sturdier than those of other Pokémon, so it can stay healthy despite its constant raging.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It will never forgive opponents who have angered it. Even after it has beaten them down until they can’t move, it never ever forgives.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It has been known to become so angry that it dies as a result. Its face looks peaceful in death, however.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: When Primeape becomes furious, its blood circulation is boosted. In turn, its muscles are made even stronger. However, it also becomes much less intelligent at the same time.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: If approached while asleep, it may awaken and angrily give chase in a groggy state of semi-sleep.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: When it becomes furious, its blood circulation becomes more robust, and its muscles are made stronger. But it also becomes much less intelligent.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it catches up.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: It will beat up anyone who makes it mad, even if it has to chase them until the end of the world.

Name: Primeape
FlavorText: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It’s very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It is a Pokémon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: A Pokémon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It has lived alongside humans since ages ago. Its bones have been found in excavations of ruins from the Stone Age.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: While it’s quite friendly toward humans once it’s grown used to them, in the wild it must be quite fierce to defend its territory from Rockruff.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It looks cute, but when you approach another Trainer’s Growlithe, it will bark at you and bite.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It’s both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Growlithe has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything, this Pokémon won’t forget the scent, no matter what. It uses its advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions of other living things.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: A Pokémon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Its superb sense of smell ensures that this POKéMON won’t forget any scent, no matter what. It uses its sense of smell to detect the emotions of others.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It is very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It controls a big territory. If it detects an unknown smell, it roars loudly to force out the intruder.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can’t help but grovel before it.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A Pokémon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A legendary Pokémon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: There are so many old tales about them that they’re called legendary Pokémon, but there are way more of them around than you’d expect.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Legends tell of its fighting alongside a general and conquering a whole country.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: The fire burning inside its body serves as the energy to fuel it as it runs great distances. It appears in many legends.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Overflowing with beauty and majesty, this strong Pokémon appears in ancient Eastern folklore.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Arcanine is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this Pokémon’s body is its source of power.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: This legendary Chinese Pokémon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: This fleet-footed POKéMON is said to run over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within its body is its source of power.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A POKéMON that is described in Chinese legends. It is said to race at an unbelievable speed.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were attracted to its movement as it ran through prairies.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: This legendary Chinese POKEMON is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A legendary POKéMON in China. Many people are charmed by its grace and beauty while running.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokémon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon’s innards showing through the skin.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The direction of the swirl on their stomachs differs depending on where they live. Poliwag aficionados can tell them apart at a glance.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Despite the danger, it wants to come up on land. So it does its best to waddle along, but when an enemy finds it, it rushes back to the water.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: It’s still not very good at walking. Its Trainers should train this Pokémon to walk every day.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The swirl on its belly is its internal organs showing through. If the swirl is tinged white, that means it’s affected by some disease.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Poliwag has a very thin skin. It is possible to see the Pokémon’s spiral innards right through the skin. Despite its thinness, however, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its slick black skin is thin and damp. A part of its internal organs can be seen through the skin as a spiral pattern.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The direction of its belly spiral differs by area. The equator is thought to have an effect on this.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Because it is inept at walking on its newly grown legs, it always  swims around in water.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: It is possible to see this POKéMON’s spiral innards right through its thin skin. However, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its newly grown legs prevent it from walking well. It appears to prefer swimming over walking.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The swirl on its belly is its insides showing through the skin. It looks clearer after it eats.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies’ grasp and escape.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl’s has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Its health suffers when its skin dries out, so be sure to moisturize it diligently.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Although it has become capable of living on land, it spends its time in the water, where its prey, fish Pokémon, are plentiful.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: It marches over the land in search of bug Pokémon to eat. Then it takes them underwater so it can dine on them where it’s safe.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Although it can live on land, it prefers to stay in the water, where it has fewer natural enemies.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The surface of Poliwhirl’s body is always wet and slick with a slimy fluid. Because of this slippery covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: It can live in or out of water. When out of water, it constantly sweats to keep its body slimy.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The skin on most of its body is moist. However, the skin on its belly spiral feels smooth.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The swirl on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it may gradually cause drowsiness.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Its body surface is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The surface of POLIWHIRL’s body is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Though it is skilled at walking, it prefers to live underwater where there is less danger.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Under attack, it uses its belly  spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: With its extremely tough muscles, it could keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: The muscles it has developed through swimming are thick and powerful. When it lands a square punch, it can turn huge boulders to dust.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: It’s quite a gifted swimmer, even among Water-type Pokémon, but it normally spends its time on land.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Poliwrath in the Alola region are strong swimmers that use the breaststroke. Many children learn to swim by imitating Poliwrath.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Poliwrath’s highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokémon can swim back and forth across the ocean without effort.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: A swimmer adept at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: This strong and skilled swimmer is even capable of crossing the Pacific Ocean just by kicking.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Its highly developed muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. This POKéMON can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: An adept swimmer, it knows the front crawl, butterfly, and more. It is faster than the best human swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: POLIWRATH’s highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this POKéMON can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: It can use its well-developed arms and legs to run on the surface of the water for a split second.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake champion swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Spends 18 hours of the day sleeping. Even while asleep, Abra can control its psychic powers—should danger approach, the Pokémon will simply teleport away.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Even while asleep, it maintains a telepathic radar. It teleports when it is threatened.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It sleeps for 18 hours a day. Even when awake, it teleports itself while remaining seated.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger, it will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It can read others’ minds and will teleport away when danger approaches. You must clear your mind if you want to catch it.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It uses various psychic powers even while it’s sleeping, so you can’t tell whether or not it’s awake.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It can teleport itself to safety while it’s asleep, but when it wakes, it doesn’t know where it is, so it panics.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It sleeps 18 hours a day. Even while sleeping, it will teleport itself to treetops and pick and eat berries there.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Abra needs to sleep for eighteen hours a day. If it doesn’t, this Pokémon loses its ability to use telekinetic powers. If it is attacked, Abra escapes using Teleport while it is still sleeping.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Abra sleeps for eighteen hours a day. However, it can sense the presence of foes even while it is sleeping. In such a situation, this Pokémon immediately teleports to safety.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It senses impending attacks and teleports away to safety before the actual attacks can strike.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It sleeps for 18 hours a day. It uses a variety of extrasensory powers even while asleep.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Using its psychic power is such a strain on its brain that it needs to sleep for 18 hours a day.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: If it decides to teleport randomly, it evokes the illusion that it has created copies of itself.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: A POKéMON that sleeps 18 hours a day. Observation revealed that it uses TELEPORT to change its location once every hour.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Using its ability to read minds, it will sense impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: It hypnotizes itself so that it can teleport away when it senses danger, even if it is asleep.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: If it decides to TELEPORT randomly, it creates the illusion that it has created copies of itself.

Name: Abra
FlavorText: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: There are rumors that a child with mystical powers became a Kadabra; however, this remains unverified. I suspect that the spoon Kadabra holds enhances its brain waves.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: When it uses its psychic power, it emits strong alpha waves that can ruin precision instruments.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: If one is nearby, an eerie shadow appears on TV screens. Seeing the shadow is said to bring bad luck.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: Many odd things happen if this Pokémon is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backward.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It possesses strong mental capabilities, but its psychic powers are halved when it’s not holding a silver spoon.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It stares at a silver spoon to amplify its psychic powers before it lets loose. Apparently, gold spoons are no good.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: Kadabra’s presence infests televisions and monitors with creepy shadows that bring bad luck.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: A theory exists that this Pokémon was a young boy who couldn’t control his psychic powers and ended up transformed into this Pokémon.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: Kadabra holds a silver spoon in its hand. The spoon is used to amplify the alpha waves in its brain. Without the spoon, the Pokémon is said to be limited to half the usual amount of its telekinetic powers.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: Kadabra emits a peculiar alpha wave if it develops a headache. Only those people with a particularly strong psyche can hope to become a Trainer of this Pokémon.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: If it uses its abilities, it emits special alpha waves that cause machines to malfunction.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: When it uses its psychic power, it emits strong alpha waves that can ruin precision devices.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It stares at its silver spoon to focus its mind. It emits more alpha waves while doing so.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It possesses strong spiritual power. The more danger it faces, the stronger its psychic power.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: When it uses its psychic power, it emits strong ha waves that can ruin precision devices.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It is rumored that a boy with psychic abilities suddenly transformed into KADABRA while he was assisting research into extrasensory powers.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It happened one morning - a boy with extrasensory powers awoke in bed transformed into KADABRA.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: When it closes its eyes, twice as many alpha particles come out of the surface of its body.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: Many odd things happen if this POKéMON is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backwards.

Name: Kadabra
FlavorText: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: It’s adept at precognition. When attacks completely miss Alakazam, that’s because it’s seeing the future.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Having traded away its muscles, Alakazam’s true power has been unleashed. With its psychic powers, it can foresee all things.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: It sends out psychic power from the red organ on its forehead to foresee its opponents’ every move.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Its hidden psychic power has been unleashed. A glance at someone gives it knowledge of the course of that person’s life, from birth to death.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: As a result of Mega Evolution, its power has been entirely converted into psychic energy, and it has lost all strength in its muscles.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: The longer Alakazam lives, the larger and heavier its head becomes. Our tests have shown that the strength of its psychic powers correlates positively to the weight of its head.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Its highly developed brain is on par with a supercomputer. It can use all forms of psychic abilities.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Its superb memory lets it recall everything it has experienced from birth. Its IQ exceeds 5,000.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Alakazam wields potent psychic powers. It’s said that this Pokémon used these powers to create the spoons it holds.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: A Pokémon that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns—that’s why this Pokémon is smart.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: If it trusts someone deeply, it will let them have one of its spoons. Anything you eat with that spoon is apparently delicious.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Alakazam uses its psychic powers to make the spoons it carries. Each spoon is an original that there’s only one of in the whole world.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Its brain cells continue to increase in number until its death. The older the Alakazam, the larger its head.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: It is said to have an IQ of approximately 5,000. Its overflowing psychokinetic powers cause headaches to anyone nearby.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Alakazam’s brain continually grows, infinitely multiplying brain cells. This amazing brain gives this Pokémon an astoundingly high IQ of 5,000. It has a thorough memory of everything that has occurred in the world.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Alakazam’s brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its IQ (intelligence quotient) is said to be around 5,000.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Its brain cells multiply continually until it dies. As a result, it remembers everything.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Closing both its eyes heightens all its other senses. This enables it to use its abilities to their extremes.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: While it has strong psychic abilities and high intelligence, an ALAKAZAM’s muscles are very weak. It uses psychic power to move its body.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: It does not like physical attacks very  much. Instead, it freely uses extrasensory powers to defeat foes.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: It has an IQ of 5000. It calculates many things in order to gain the edge in every battle.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: A POKéMON that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns--that’s why this POKéMON is smart.

Name: Alakazam
FlavorText: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Though as small as a child, it has strength enough to easily throw a well-built adult. Striving to become ever stronger, Machop trains by carrying a Graveler on its shoulders.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Its muscles never cramp however much it trains. It lives in the mountains away from humans.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: It hefts a Graveler repeatedly to strengthen its entire body. It uses every type of martial arts.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Very powerful in spite of its small size. Its mastery of many types of martial arts makes it very tough.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: It likes food that’s highly nutritious because its instincts drive it to build muscle efficiently.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Once this Pokémon has gained enough confidence and muscle from training with its friends, it challenges Makuhita to a battle.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: With its superhuman strength, it’s able to throw a hundred people all at the same time. Its strength comes from lifting Graveler every day.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: It loves working out. As it gazes at its muscles, which continue to swell day by day, it becomes more and more dedicated to its training.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Machop exercises by hefting around a Graveler as if it were a barbell. There are some Machop that travel the world in a quest to master all kinds of martial arts.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Machop’s muscles are special—they never get sore no matter how much they are used in exercise. This Pokémon has sufficient power to hurl a hundred adult humans.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: It loves to work out and build its muscles. It is never satisfied, even if it trains hard all day long.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: It continually undertakes strenuous training to master all forms of martial arts. Its strength lets it easily hoist a sumo wrestler onto its shoulders.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: MACHOP’s muscles are special - they never get sore no matter how much they are used in exercise. This POKéMON has sufficient power to hurl a hundred adult humans.

Name: Machop
FlavorText: It trains by lifting rocks in the mountains. It can even pick up a GRAVELER with ease.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: A sturdy creature boasting a robust physique and boundless stamina. Loves training above all else and voluntarily assists with tasks such as construction and clearing land.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: It can lift a dump truck with one hand. Using that kind of strength, it helps people do heavy jobs.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: Machoke’s boundless power is very dangerous, so it wears a belt that suppresses its energy.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: The belt around its waist holds back its energy. Without it, this Pokémon would be unstoppable.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: A popular motif for sculptures, its incredibly well-developed muscles have captured the imagination of many an artist.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: When it encounters an enemy that’s truly mighty, this Pokémon removes the power-save belt from its waist and unleashes its full power.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: It willingly assists with hard labor because it knows the work is good training for its muscles.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: As a result of its continual workouts, it has developed tremendous power. It uses that power to help people with their work.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: Machoke undertakes bodybuilding every day even as it helps people with tough, physically demanding labor. On its days off, this Pokémon heads to the fields and mountains to exercise and train.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: Machoke’s thoroughly toned muscles possess the hardness of steel. This Pokémon has so much strength, it can easily hold aloft a sumo wrestler on just one finger.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: It can lift a dump truck with one hand. Using that power, it helps people with heavy jobs.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: The muscles covering its body teem with power. Even when still, it exudes an amazing sense of strength.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: It always goes at its full power, but this very tough and durable Pokémon never gets tired.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: A belt is worn by a MACHOKE to keep its overwhelming power under control. Because it is so dangerous, no one has ever removed the belt.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: This tough POKéMON always stays in the zone. Its muscles become thicker after every battle.

Name: Machoke
FlavorText: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: One of these Pokémon once used its immeasurable strength to lift a large ship that was in trouble. It then carried the ship to port.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: The Gigantamax energy coursing through its arms makes its punches hit as hard as bomb blasts.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: In close combat, its four arms afford it offensive and defensive supremacy. In but a blink, this valiant Pokémon can overwhelm its foes with more than 1,000 blows from its fists.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It can knock a train flying with a punch. However, it is terrible at delicate work using its fingers.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It punches with its four arms at blinding speed. It can launch 1,000 punches in two seconds.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: With four arms that react more quickly than it can think, it can execute many punches at once.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: One arm alone can move mountains. Using all four arms, this Pokémon fires off awesome punches.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: With four arms, it can attack and defend simultaneously. It’s said to have mastered every martial art in the world.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It grasps its opponents with its four arms and twists them up in an intricate hold. People call it “the Machamp special.”

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It can lift heavy loads with the greatest of ease. It can even heft dump trucks. But its clumsy fingers prevent it from doing any precision work.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It unleashes megaton-level punches that send opponents flying clear over the horizon.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: Machamp is known as the Pokémon that has mastered every kind of martial arts. If it grabs hold of the foe with its four arms, the battle is all but over. The hapless foe is thrown far over the horizon.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: Machamp has the power to hurl anything aside. However, trying to do any work requiring care and dexterity causes its arms to get tangled. This Pokémon tends to leap into action before it thinks.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It uses its four powerful arms to pin the limbs of its foe, then throws the victim over the horizon.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: Its four ruggedly developed arms can launch a flurry of 1,000 punches in just two seconds.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: It is impossible to defend against punches and chops doled out by its four arms. Its fighting spirit flares up when it faces a tough opponent.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: Its superpowerful punches are said to knock the victim flying clear over the horizon.

Name: Machamp
FlavorText: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Bellsprout’s thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, this Pokémon spits a corrosive fluid that melts even iron.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: It plants its feet deep underground to replenish water. It can’t escape its enemy while it’s rooted.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: A BELLSPROUT’s thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, it leaks a fluid that melts even iron.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It appears to use its root feet to replenish moisture.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: If it notices anything that moves, it immediately flings its vine at the object.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny insects with its vines and devours them.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: This Pokémon has the appearance of a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: Weepinbell has a large hook on its rear end. At night, the Pokémon hooks on to a tree branch and goes to sleep. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: A Pokémon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: If its prey is bigger than its mouth, it slices up the victim with sharp leaves, then eats every morsel.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: Even though it is filled with acid, it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: At night, a WEEPINBELL hangs on to a tree branch with its hooked rear and sleeps. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: When it’s hungry, it swings its razor-sharp leaves, slicing up any unlucky object nearby for food.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: Even though it is filled with ACID, it does not melt because it also oozes a neutralizing fluid.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is melted inside by strong acids.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: In its mouth, it pools a fragrant nectar-like fluid. The fluid is really an acid that dissolves anything.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Victreebel has a long vine that extends from its head. This vine is waved and flicked about as if it were an animal to attract prey. When an unsuspecting prey draws near, this Pokémon swallows it whole.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Once ingested into this Pokémon’s body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honey-like scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honeylike scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: This horrifying plant Pokémon attracts prey with aromatic honey, then melts them in its mouth.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Acid that has dissolved many prey becomes sweeter, making it even more effective at attracting prey.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: The long vine extending from its head is waved about as if it were a living thing to attract prey. When an unsuspecting victim approaches, it is swallowed whole.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Lures prey into its mouth with a honeylike aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is melted in a day, bones and all.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: They fire beams from the glassy, magenta orbs that resemble eyes atop their heads, and they drift in shallow seas. During low tide, they can sometimes be found on beaches, desiccated.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts in sea currents. Countless fishers are hurt by its poison stingers.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is mostly composed of water. It shoots strange beams from its crystal-like eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: This Pokémon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot, because its body blends in with the sea.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It can sometimes be found all dry and shriveled up on a beach. Toss it back into the sea to revive it.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is 99% water. The remaining 1% contains the organ that makes its poison.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts through the sea searching for prey. Its poisonous tentacles break off sometimes, but after a while, they grow back.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts in shallow seas, such as the areas near beaches. If you get bitten or stabbed by its toxic tentacles, rush to the hospital.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: They can be found lying dehydrated on beaches, but they are often still alive. When soaked in water, they will revive.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Tentacool absorbs sunlight and refracts it using water inside its body to convert it into beam energy. This Pokémon shoots beams from the small round organ above its eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Tentacool’s body is largely composed of water. If it is removed from the sea, it dries up like parchment. If this Pokémon happens to become dehydrated, put it back into the sea.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by their stingers.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is virtually composed of water. It shoots strange beams from its crystal-like eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Because its body is almost entirely composed of water, it shrivels up if it is washed ashore.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts aimlessly in waves. Very difficult to see in water, it may not be noticed until it stings.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: When the tide goes out, dehydrated TENTACOOL remains can be found washed up on the shore.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts in sea currents. Countless fishermen are hurt by its poison stingers.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is almost entirely composed of water. It ensnares its foe with its two long tentacles, then stabs with the poison stingers at their tips.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its eyes are as transparent as crystals. From them, it shoots mysterious beams of light.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: TENTACOOL absorbs sunlight and refracts it using water inside its body to convert it into beam energy. This POKéMON shoots beams from its crystal-like eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: As it floats along on the waves, it uses its toxic feelers to stab anything it touches.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It has 80 tentacles, each with a venomous tip. These tentacles are also extendible, lengthening when Tentacruel attempts to catch prey. Use caution.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It alerts others to danger by stridently flashing the red orbs on its head.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: With 80 tentacles for ensnaring victims, it prevents escape until the prey is weakened by poison.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely. Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out tentacles, delivering venomous stings to its catch.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely. They wrap around prey and weaken it with poison.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It communicates with others of its kind by lighting up the red orbs on its head. When the orbs are blinking, it’s a warning sign.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It fires off ultrasonic waves from its red orbs to weaken its prey, and then it wraps them up in its 80 tentacles.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Although these Pokémon are rare, when a large outbreak of them occurs, all fish Pokémon disappear from the surrounding sea.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Normally, it has 80 poisonous tentacles. The longer one has been alive, the fewer tentacles it will have.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Tentacruel has tentacles that can be freely elongated and shortened at will. It ensnares prey with its tentacles and weakens the prey by dosing it with a harsh toxin. It can catch up to 80 prey at the same time.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon’s outburst creates rough waves around it.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: In battle, it extends all 80 of its tentacles to entrap its opponent inside a poisonous net.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Its 80 tentacles absorb water and stretch almost endlessly to constrict its prey and enemies.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It lives in complex rock formations on the ocean floor and traps prey using its 80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it grows excited or agitated.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: When its 80 feelers absorb water, it stretches to become like a net to entangle its prey.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Its stone head is imbued with electricity and magnetism. If you carelessly step on one, you’ll be in for a painful shock.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Geodude compete against each other with headbutts. The iron sand on their heads will stick to whichever one has stronger magnetism.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: If you mistake it for a rock and step on it, it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: If you accidentally step on a Geodude sleeping on the ground, you’ll hear a crunching sound and feel a shock ripple through your entire body.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Its body is a magnetic stone. Iron sand attaches firmly to the portions of its body that are particularly magnetic.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Makes its home in mountainous regions, using its arms to climb along harsh mountain roads. Can be troublesome—carelessly kicking one will cause it to fly into a rage and chase after you.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: It is impossible to distinguish from rocks. It slams against others in contests of toughness.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Many live on mountain trails and remain half-buried while keeping an eye on climbers.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs. People who see it in action have been known to take up bouldering.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Geodude that have lived a long life have had all their edges smoothed out until they’re totally round. They also have a calm, quiet disposition.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: There are plenty of them to be found along any road. A scholar with too much free time once counted a hundred of them along a single route.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Its round body makes it easy to pick up, but it is hard and heavy. It’s dangerous to play with them as if they were snowballs.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: When Geodude sleeps deeply, it buries itself halfway into the ground. It will not awaken even if hikers step on it unwittingly. In the morning, this Pokémon rolls downhill in search of food.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: The longer a Geodude lives, the more its edges are chipped and worn away, making it more rounded in appearance. However, this Pokémon’s heart will remain hard, craggy, and rough always.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: It is impossible to distinguish from rocks. It slams against others in contests of hardness.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: It uses its arms to steadily climb steep mountain paths. It swings its fists around if angered.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Most people may not notice, but a closer look should reveal that there are many GEODUDE around.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Many live on mountain trails and remain half buried while keeping an eye on climbers.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: It climbs mountain paths using only the power of its arms. Because they look just like boulders lining paths, hikers may step on them without noticing.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Its round form makes it easy to pick up. Some people have used them to hurl at each other in a snowball fight.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Proud of their sturdy bodies, they bash against each other in a contest to prove whose is harder.

Name: Geodude
FlavorText: Commonly found near mountain trails, etc. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: When it comes rolling down a mountain path, anything in its way gets zapped by electricity and sent flying.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Graveler’s entire body is tinged with electricity due to the stones it likes to eat. It’s very quick-tempered.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: When two Graveler fight each other, it fills the surroundings with flashes of light and sound. People call it the “fireworks of the earth.”

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: They eat rocks and often get into a scrap over them. The shock of Graveler smashing together causes a flash of light and a booming noise.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Its preferred food is dravite. After it has eaten this mineral, crystals form inside the Pokémon, rising to the surface of part of its body.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Dwells in holes dug into sheer walls of stone. It enjoys rolling down slopes as though it were a boulder during a rockfall, so keep an eye upward while traversing mountain roads.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: It tumbles down slopes, heedless of any body parts chipping off. It eats a ton of rocks daily.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Graveler make their homes on sheer cliff faces that have numerous holes in them.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: This slow-footed Pokémon moves by curling up and rolling instead of walking. With enough momentum, its speed can exceed 60 mph.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Mossy rocks are its favorite food. It can devour a ton a day while crunching loudly.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Rocks are Graveler’s favorite food. This Pokémon will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokémon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn’t mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokémon can stop it without difficulty.

Name: Graveler
