FlavorText: A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: GRAVELER make their homes on sheer cliff faces by gouging out numerous horizontal holes.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: They descend from mountains by tumbling down steep slopes. They are so brutal, they smash aside obstructing trees and massive boulders with thunderous tackles.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: Be careful while hiking on mountain trails. GRAVELER may come rolling down the path without slowing.

Name: Graveler
FlavorText: It travels by rolling on mountain paths. If it gains too much speed, it stops by running into huge rocks.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It uses magnetism to accelerate and fire off rocks tinged with electricity. Even if it doesn’t score a direct hit, the jolt of electricity will do the job.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It shoots large rocks that are charged with electricity. Tremendous electric shocks are flung out across the whole area of impact.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It’s grumpy and stubborn. If you upset it, it discharges electricity from the surface of its body and growls with a voice like thunder.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Because it can’t fire boulders at a rapid pace, it’s been known to seize nearby Geodude and fire them from its back.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It fires rocks charged with electricity. Even if the rock isn’t fired that accurately, just grazing an opponent will cause numbness and fainting.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: The rocklike shell is shed each year. The cast-off shell then crumbles, reverting to a mass of soil, which can be spread across fields to promote crop growth.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It tumbles down mountains, leaving grooves from peak to base. Stay clear of these grooves.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It sheds its hide once a year. Its boulder-like body is so tough, even dynamite can’t harm it.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it’s exposed to air.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It detonates its own body. The power from that explosion can propel it up steep mountain paths with amazing speed.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: When Golem grow old, they stop shedding their shells. Those that have lived a long, long time have shells green with moss.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Once a year, this Pokémon molts, and its shed shell returns to the soil. This process creates enriched soil, so farmers collect the shells.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Its body can survive dynamite blasts without a single scratch, but it hates rain and humidity.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Golem is known for rolling down from mountains. To prevent them from rolling into the homes of people downhill, grooves have been dug into the sides of mountains to serve as guideways for diverting this Pokémon’s course.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Golem live up on mountains. If there is a large earthquake, these Pokémon will come rolling down off the mountains en masse to the foothills below.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Even dynamite can’t harm its hard, boulder-like body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Even dynamite can’t harm its hard, boulderlike body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It is capable of blowing itself up. It uses this explosive force to jump from mountain to mountain.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It sheds its skin once a year. The discarded shell immediately hardens and crumbles away.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It sheds its hide once a year. Its boulderlike body is so tough, even dynamite can’t harm it.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It is said to live in volcanic craters on mountain peaks. Once a year, it sheds its hide and grows larger. The shed hide crumbles and returns to the soil.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without taking damage.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Its rock-like body is so durable, even high-powered dynamite blasts fail to scratch its rugged hide.

Name: Golem
FlavorText: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its small horn hides a healing power. With a few rubs from this Pokémon’s horn, any slight wound you have will be healed.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parents. It runs all day in fields and on mountains.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: About an hour after birth, Ponyta’s fiery mane and tail grow out, giving the Pokémon an impressive appearance.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: If you’ve been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Capable of jumping incredibly high. Its hooves and sturdy legs absorb the impact of a hard landing.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. This Pokémon becomes stronger by stumbling and falling to keep up with its parent.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hind legs, which have hooves that are harder than diamond, kick back at any presence it senses behind it.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: It is a weak runner immediately after birth. It gradually becomes faster by chasing after its parents.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: About an hour after birth, its fiery mane and tail grow out, giving it an impressive appearance.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: A PONYTA is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. Its legs become stronger as it stumbles and falls while trying to keep up with its parent.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hooves are ten times harder than diamond. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its body is light, and its legs are incredibly powerful. It can clear Ayers Rock in one leap.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Training by jumping over grass that grows longer every day has made it a world-class jumper.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hind legs, which have harder-than-diamond hooves, kick back at any presence it senses behind it.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Little can stand up to its psycho cut. Unleashed from this Pokémon’s horn, the move will punch a hole right through a thick metal sheet.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Fiery mane aglow, Rapidash darts like an arrow across the land. This prodigiously swift creature can traverse the vast region of Hisui in a day and a half.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It has astounding acceleration. From a standstill, it can reach top speed within 10 steps.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd’s pace and direction of travel.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Just loves to run. If it sees something faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Rapidash usually can be seen casually cantering in the fields and plains. However, when this Pokémon turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: With incredible acceleration, it reaches its top speed of 150 mph after running just 10 steps.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: At full gallop, its four hooves barely touch the ground because it moves so incredibly fast.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It usually canters casually in the fields and plains. But once a RAPIDASH turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It can gallop at a top speed of 150 miles per hour. It can race as fast as a bullet train while ablaze.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It just loves to gallop. The faster it goes, the longer the swaying flames of its mane will become.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: With incredible acceleration, it reaches its top speed of 150 mph after running just ten steps.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Although this Pokémon is normally zoned out, its expression abruptly sharpens on occasion. The cause for this seems to lie in Slowpoke’s diet.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: When this Pokémon’s tail is soaked in water, sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pokémon.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokémon won’t feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won’t notice when its tail grows back, either.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Incredibly slow and sluggish. It is quite content to loll about without worrying about the time.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Although their tails, which fall off naturally, can easily be found lying around, they’re a precious ingredient for cooking.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: There are some places where Slowpoke is worshiped because of a long-standing belief that whenever Slowpoke yawns, it rains.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Alolan home cooking involves drying Slowpoke tails and then simmering them into a salty stew.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn’t really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn’t particularly bothered.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this Pokémon often forgets what it’s doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water’s edge.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won’t even notice for a whole day.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: A sweet sap leaks from its tail’s tip. Although not nutritious, the tail is pleasant to chew on.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It catches prey by dipping its tail in water at the side of a river. But it often forgets what it is doing and spends entire days just loafing at water’s edge.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It is always so absent-minded that it won’t react, even if its flavorful tail is bitten.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: A Shellder bite set off a chemical reaction with the spices inside Slowbro’s body, causing Slowbro to become a Poison-type Pokémon.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Under the influence of Shellder’s digestive fluids, Slowpoke has awakened, gaining a great deal of power—and a little motivation to boot.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Having been swallowed whole by Shellder, Slowbro now has an iron defense. It’s pretty comfortable in there, too.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Tremendous energy strengthened the power of the Shellder on its tail, but it doesn’t really affect Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: When bathed in the energy of Mega Evolution, Shellder converts into impregnable armor. There is virtually no change in Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: All the energy from Mega Evolution poured into the Shellder on its tail, leaving Slowpoke to be swallowed whole.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Though usually dim-witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Being bitten by a Shellder shocked this Pokémon into standing on two legs. If the Shellder lets go, it seems Slowbro will turn back into a Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more sweetness from Slowbro’s tail, has metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Spacing out is basically all it does. It turns back into Slowpoke if its tail, along with Shellder, breaks off.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Whenever Shellder bites down hard on its tail, it gives Slowbro a flash of inspiration...which it forgets a moment later.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: It spaces out while gazing at the sea. With Shellder’s poison flowing through its body, it becomes even spacier.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Slowbro’s tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can’t be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: An attached Shellder won’t let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to SHELLDER’s seeping poison.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: If the tail-biting SHELLDER is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordinary SLOWPOKE.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Its tail has a SHELLDER firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can’t be used for fishing anymore. This forces it to reluctantly swim and catch prey.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: The SHELLDER that latches onto SLOWPOKE’s tail is said to feed on the host’s leftover scraps.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE’s tail is said to feed on the host’s left over scraps.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges electromagnetic waves and so on from the units at its sides.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: A bizarre Pokémon with but a single eye embedded in an iron sphere. I suspect this creature levitates due to the magnetism it emits from its arms, which resemble horseshoe-shaped magnets.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: The units at its sides generate electromagnetic waves that keep it airborne. It feeds on electricity.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It subsists on electricity. As Magnemite flies, it emits electromagnetic waves from the units on each side of its body.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: At times, Magnemite runs out of electricity and ends up on the ground. If you give batteries to a grounded Magnemite, it’ll start moving again.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It is hatched with the ability to defy gravity. It floats while emitting powerful electromagnetic waves.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: Perhaps because electrical lines are often buried these days, the number of Magnemite attacks on power plants has increased.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It’s frequently the cause of power outages, which is why some power plants send out electrical signals that it can’t stand.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It sends out electromagnetic waves, which let it float through the air. Touching it while it’s eating electricity will give you a full-body shock.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: They gather in places where electricity is available. They can be found clinging to the steel towers used to support power lines.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: Magnemite floats in the air by emitting electromagnetic waves from the units at its sides. These waves block gravity. This Pokémon becomes incapable of flight if its internal electrical supply is depleted.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: Magnemite attaches itself to power lines to feed on electricity. If your house has a power outage, check your circuit breakers. You may find a large number of this Pokémon clinging to the breaker box.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges Thunder Wave and so on from the units at its sides.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: The units at the sides of its body generate antigravity energy to keep it aloft in the air.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: The faster the units at its sides rotate, the greater the magnetic force they generate.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It is attracted by electromagnetic waves. It may approach Trainers if they are using their Pokégear.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: The units at its sides are extremely powerful magnets. They generate enough magnetism to draw in iron objects from over 300 feet away.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: Uses antigravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: The electricity emitted by the units on each side of its body cause it to become a strong magnet.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: It is born with the ability to defy gravity. It floats in air on powerful electromagnetic waves.

Name: Magnemite
FlavorText: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: They’re formed by several Magnemite linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Three Magnemite gathered to evolve into this Pokémon. The source of much vexation on my part, as its powerful magnetism destroys my research equipment.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: A Magneton is actually three Magnemite linked by magnetism. A group of these Pokémon can set off a magnetic storm.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: This Pokémon is constantly putting out a powerful magnetic force. Most computers go haywire when a Magneton approaches.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: This Pokémon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 3.6 degrees Fahrenheit within 3,300 feet.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: When rain clouds form, many Magneton gather in high places to wait for lightning to strike.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Delicate equipment can malfunction in areas inhabited by Magneton, which send out mysterious electrical signals.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: It has about three times the electrical power of Magnemite. For some reason, outbreaks of this Pokémon happen when lots of sunspots appear.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: When three Magnemite link together, their brains also become one. They do not become three times more intelligent.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Magneton emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to electronics and precision instruments. Because of this, it is said that some towns warn people to keep this Pokémon inside a Poké Ball.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Magneton emits a powerful magnetic force that is fatal to mechanical devices. As a result, large cities sound sirens to warn citizens of large-scale outbreaks of this Pokémon.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: A linked cluster formed of several Magnemite. It discharges powerful magnetic waves at high voltage.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: The stronger electromagnetic waves from the three linked Magnemite are enough to dry out surrounding moisture.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Many mysteriously appear when more sunspots dot the sun. They stop TV sets from displaying properly.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: The MAGNEMITE are united by a magnetism so powerful, it dries all moisture in its vicinity.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: It is actually three MAGNEMITE linked by magnetism. A group can set off a magnetic storm.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: It is actually three MAGNEMITE linked by magnetism. It generates powerful radio waves that raise temperatures by 3.6 degrees F within a 3,300-foot radius.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Formed by several MAGNEMITE linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: When many MAGNETON gather together, the resulting magnetic storm disrupts radio waves.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: The MAGNEMITE are united by a magnetism so powerful, it dries all moisture in its vicinities.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 3.6F degrees within 3,300 feet.

Name: Magneton
FlavorText: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch’d that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: The Farfetch’d of the Galar region are brave warriors, and they wield thick, tough leeks in battle.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: They live where reedy plants grow. Farfetch’d are rarely seen, so it’s thought their numbers are decreasing.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: Farfetch’d is always seen with a stalk from a plant of some sort. Apparently, there are good stalks and bad stalks. This Pokémon has been known to fight with others over stalks.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: The plant stalk it holds is its weapon. The stalk is used like a sword to cut all sorts of things.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: If it eats the plant stalk it carries as emergency rations, it runs off in search of a new stalk.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: If anyone tries to disturb where the essential plant stalks grow, it uses its own stalk to thwart them.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: It is always seen with a stick from a plant. Apparently, there are good sticks and bad sticks. This POKéMON occasionally fights with others over choice sticks.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: FARFETCH’D is always seen with a stick from a plant of some sort. Apparently, there are good sticks and bad sticks. This POKéMON has been known to fight with others over sticks.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: In order to prevent their extinction, more people have made an effort to breed these POKéMON.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: If it eats the plant stick it carries as emergency rations, it runs off in search of a new stick.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: If anyone tries to disturb where the essential plant sticks grow, it uses its own stick to thwart them.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: Lives where reedy plants grow. They are rarely seen, so it’s thought their numbers are decreasing.

Name: Farfetch'd
FlavorText: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: Doduo’s two heads contain completely identical brains. A scientific study reported that on rare occasions, there will be examples of this Pokémon possessing different sets of brains.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: Doduo’s two heads never sleep at the same time. Its two heads take turns sleeping, so one head can always keep watch for enemies while the other one sleeps.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: A two-headed Pokémon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: It races through grassy plains with powerful strides, leaving footprints up to four inches deep.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: By alternately raising and lowering its two heads, it balances itself to be more stable while running.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: Even while eating or sleeping, one of the heads remains always vigilant for any sign of danger. When threatened, it flees at over 60 miles per hour.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

Name: Doduo
FlavorText: It lives on a grassy plain where it can see a long way. If it sees an enemy, it runs away at 60 mph.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. This Pokémon runs at nearly 40 mph.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: One of Doduo’s two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: Apparently, the heads aren’t the only parts of the body that Dodrio has three of. It has three sets of hearts and lungs as well, so it is capable of running long distances without rest.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: Watch out if Dodrio’s three heads are looking in three separate directions. It’s a sure sign that it is on its guard. Don’t go near this Pokémon if it’s being wary—it may decide to peck you.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: An enemy that takes its eyes off any of the three heads--even for a second--will get pecked severely.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: If one of the heads gets to eat, the others will be satisfied, too, and they will stop squabbling.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: It collects data and plans three times as wisely, but it may think too much and fall into a state of immobility.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: A peculiar POKéMON species with three heads. It vigorously races across grassy plains even in arid seasons with little rainfall.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head is said to stay awake.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: Watch out if DODRIO’s three heads are looking in three separate directions. It’s a sure sign that it is on its guard. Don’t go near this POKéMON if it’s being wary - it may decide to peck you.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: It collects data  and plans three times as wisely, but it may think too much and become immobilized.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: One of DODUO’s 2 heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 MPH in prairies.

Name: Dodrio
FlavorText: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives on icebergs. It uses the sharp point on its head to break up ice as it swims in the sea.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don’t bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: It has always been supposed that Seel live only in cold seas. Their having shown up in Alola is a mystery.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Seel hunts for prey in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of -40 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: In daytime, it is often found asleep on the seabed in shallow waters. Its nostrils close while it swims.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Although it can’t walk well on land, it is a graceful swimmer. It especially loves being in frigid seas.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: SEEL hunt for prey in frigid, ice-covered seas. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick icebergs.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of minus 40 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The light blue fur that covers it keeps it protected against the cold. It loves iceberg-filled oceans.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Loves freezing cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14F degrees.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It swims through the ocean at a speed of eight knots, searching for Pokémon that will become its prey. It’s especially fond of Wishiwashi.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature, the friskier it gets.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It loves frigid seas with ice floes. It uses its long tail to change swimming direction quickly.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this POKéMON sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It stores thermal energy in the body. It swims at a steady eight knots even in intensely cold waters.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It sleeps under shallow ocean waters during the day, then looks for food at night when it’s cold.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its entire body is a snowy-white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: It has a passion for trash above all else, speedily digesting it and creating brilliant crystals of sparkling poison.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Brought to Alola to solve the garbage problem, Grimer seems to relish any and all kinds of trash.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: There are a hundred or so of them living in Alola’s waste-disposal site. They’re all hard workers who eat a lot of trash.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: The crystals on Grimer’s body are lumps of toxins. If one falls off, lethal poisons leak out.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: A Grimer, which had been brought in to solve a problem with garbage, developed over time into this form.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: When two of these Pokémon’s bodies are combined together, new poisons are created.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon’s X-rays. It appears among filth.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: The wastewater coming from factories is clean these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat. They’re said to be on the verge of extinction.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: It was born from sludge on the ocean floor. In a sterile environment, the germs within its body can’t multiply, and it dies.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: It was born from sludge transformed by exposure to X-rays from the moon. When its internal load of germs decreases, it dies.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Its main source of food is the slimy industrial waste of factories. This Pokémon’s numbers have been decreasing in recent years.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Grimer emerged from the sludge that settled on a polluted seabed. This Pokémon loves anything filthy. It constantly leaks a horribly germ-infested fluid from all over its body.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Grimer’s sludgy and rubbery body can be forced through any opening, however small it may be. This Pokémon enters sewer pipes to drink filthy wastewater.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Appears in filthy areas. It thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Sludge exposed to X-rays from the moon transformed into Grimer. It loves feeding on filthy things.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Wherever GRIMER has passed, so many germs are left behind that no plants will ever grow again.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: As it moves, it loses bits of its body, from which new GRIMER emerge. This worsens the stench around it.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Born from polluted sludge in the sea, GRIMER’s favorite food is anything filthy. They feed on wastewater pumped out from factories.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Sludge exposed to X rays from the moon transformed into GRIMER. It loves feeding on filthy things.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: As it moves, it loses bits of its body from which new GRIMER emerge. This worsens the stench around it.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Made of hardened sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

Name: Grimer
FlavorText: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: Muk’s coloration becomes increasingly vivid the more it feasts on its favorite dish—trash.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: What look like fangs and claws are actually crystallized poison that will afflict you at a mere touch, so don’t get too close.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: There are over a hundred kinds of poison inside its body. Chemical reactions between different poisons are the source of its vitality.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: While it’s unexpectedly quiet and friendly, if it’s not fed any trash for a while, it will smash its Trainer’s furnishings and eat up the fragments.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: The garbage it eats causes continuous chemical changes in its body, which produce its exceedingly vivid coloration.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: It’s so stinky! Muk’s body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: It’s thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid kills plants and trees immediately upon contact.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: Because they scatter germs everywhere, they’ve long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: Their food sources have decreased, and their numbers have declined sharply. Sludge ponds are being built to prevent their extinction.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: After recent environmental improvements, this Pokémon is now hardly seen at all. People speculate that it may go extinct at some point.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: The stench it gives off will make your nose scrunch up. Still, there are Muk fans who think that’s a good thing.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s favorite food is anything that is repugnantly filthy. In dirty towns where people think nothing of throwing away litter on the streets, Muk are certain to gather.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: From Muk’s body seeps a foul fluid that gives off a nose-bendingly horrible stench. Just one drop of this Pokémon’s body fluid can turn a pool stagnant and rancid.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: A toxic fluid seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: They love to gather in smelly areas where sludge accumulates, making the stench around them worse.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: Its body is made of a powerful poison. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: It prefers warm and humid habitats. In the summertime, the toxic substances in its body intensify, making MUK reek like putrid kitchen garbage.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: It is usually undetectable because it blends in with the ground. Touching it can cause terrible poisoning.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: As it moves, a very strong poison leaks from it, making the ground there barren for three years.

Name: Muk
FlavorText: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration, it lost its sense of smell.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: The shell can withstand any attack. However, when it is open, the tender body is exposed.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Even when its shell is closed, its tongue still hangs out. If you give its tongue a good yank, the shock will cause Shellder to open its shell.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: The sand that accumulates inside its shell eventually becomes a pearl. But the pearl gets in the way, so it spits it out and discards it.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s tongue is always hanging out. It uses its tongue with great dexterity to dig up sand from the seabed in its search for food.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: The hardness of its shell surpasses the hardness of a diamond. In days gone by, people used the shells to make shields.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: At night, this Pokémon uses its broad tongue to burrow a hole in the seafloor sand and then sleep in it. While it is sleeping, Shellder closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Grains of sand trapped in its shells mix with its body fluids to form beautiful pearls.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: At night, it burrows a hole in the seafloor with its broad tongue to make a place to sleep. While asleep, it closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: When attacked, it launches its spikes in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Once it slams its shell shut, it is impossible to open, even by those with superior strength.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: For protection, it uses its harder-than-diamonds shell. It also shoots spikes from the shell.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Slowpoke tails are its favorite food. It has even been known to come up on land to look for Slowpoke from time to time.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: If areas of Cloyster’s very hard shell get damaged, those areas swell, gradually growing into large sharp spikes.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Excavation of the tombs of ancient hunting tribes has turned up many spears tipped with spikes that had fallen off this Pokémon’s shell.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Its hard shell cannot be shattered—not even by a bomb. The contents of the shell remain unknown.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Cloyster is capable of swimming in the sea. It does so by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. This Pokémon shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: It swims in the sea by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. The CLOYSTER shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Even a missile can’t break the spikes it uses to stab opponents. They’re even harder than its shell.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Gaseous and completely impalpable. Also highly dangerous— inhaling part of its poisonous body will cause one to faint instantly.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: It’s a Pokémon born from poison gases. It defeats even the largest foes by enveloping them in gas.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s body is 95 percent made up of gases. The Pokémon can be blown away by strong gusts of wind.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: With its gas-like body, it can sneak into any place it desires. However, it can be blown away by wind.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape, as it appears to be made of a gas.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Poisonous gas comprises 95% of its body. It’s said that the remaining 5% is made up of the souls of those who died from the gas.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: It’s said that gas emanating from a graveyard was possessed by the grievances of the deceased and thus became a Pokémon.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Although Gastly is barely visible, when it’s near, a faint sweet smell lingers.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Should a strange light be seen flickering in an abandoned building, Gastly is lurking there.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Gastly is largely composed of gaseous matter. When exposed to a strong wind, the gaseous body quickly dwindles away. Groups of this Pokémon cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: A Pokémon born from poison gases. It defeats even the largest foes by enveloping them in gas.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s body is 95% made up of gases, which are blown away by strong gusts of wind.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: When exposed to a strong wind, a GASTLY’s gaseous body quickly dwindles away. They cluster under the eaves of houses to escape the ravages of wind.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKéMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: A being that exists as a thin gas. It can topple an Indian elephant by enveloping the prey in two seconds.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Its thin body is made of gas. It can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.

Name: Gastly
FlavorText: Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape as it appears to be made of a gas.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: In total darkness, where nothing is visible, Haunter lurks, silently stalking its next victim.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: This frightful, malevolent spirit can glide through walls, appearing wherever it likes. According to rumor, victims of a Haunter’s lick will wither to death day by day.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It licks with its gaseous tongue to steal its victim’s life-force. It lurks in darkness, waiting for prey.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It can slip through any obstacle. It lurks inside walls to keep an eye on its foes.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: By licking, it saps the victim’s life. It causes shaking that won’t stop until the victim’s demise.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It’s dangerous to go outside alone on nights when you’re feeling sad. Haunter will catch you, and you won’t be able to go back home.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: On moonless nights, Haunter searches for someone to curse, so it’s best not to go out walking around.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It fears the light and revels in the dark. It may be on the verge of extinction in cities that stay brightly lit at night.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It strikes at humans from total darkness. Those licked by its cold tongue grow weaker with each passing day until they die.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: Haunter is a dangerous Pokémon. If one beckons you while floating in darkness, you must never approach it. This Pokémon will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It licks with its gaseous tongue to steal the victim’s life force. It lurks in darkness for prey.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: If a HAUNTER beckons you while it is floating in darkness, don’t approach it. This POKéMON will try to lick you with its tongue and steal your life away.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.

Name: Haunter
FlavorText: It hides in the dark, planning to take the life of the next living thing that wanders close by.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It can pass through other dimensions and can appear anywhere. It caused a stir one time when it stuck just one leg out of a wall.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Mega Evolution has made it possible for Gengar to access other dimensions. Its entire body is brimming with strange power.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It tries to take the lives of anyone and everyone. It will even try to curse the Trainer who is its master!

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: The energy of Mega Evolution awakened it. It sinks into another dimension, where it keeps a patient watch for its chance to attack.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Gengar’s relationships are warped. It has no interest in opponents unless it perceives them as prey.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It lays traps, hoping to steal the lives of those it catches. If you stand in front of its mouth, you’ll hear your loved ones’ voices calling out to you.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Rumor has it that its gigantic mouth leads not into its body, filled with cursed energy, but instead directly to the afterlife.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Hiding in people’s shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey’s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Possesses potential victims’ shadows in an effort to steal away the victims’ lives. If your shadow begins to laugh, you must take hold of a protective charm posthaste!

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Lurking in the shadowy corners of rooms, it awaits chances to steal its prey’s life-force.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It hides in shadows. It is said that in rooms where Gengar is hiding, the temperature drops by nearly 10 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar’s doing.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: A Gengar is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Even your home isn’t safe. Gengar will lurk in whatever dark corner of a room it can find and wait for its chance to catch its prey.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: You can hear tales told all over the world about how Gengar will pay a visit to children who are naughty.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It apparently wishes for a traveling companion. Since it was once human itself, it tries to create one by taking the lives of other humans.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Should you feel yourself attacked by a sudden chill, it is evidence of an approaching Gengar. There is no escaping it. Give up.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Sometimes, on a dark night, your shadow thrown by a streetlight will suddenly and startlingly overtake you. It is actually a Gengar running past you, pretending to be your shadow.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It hides in shadows. It is said that if Gengar is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It steals heat from its surroundings. If you feel a sudden chill, it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Lurking in the shadowy corners of rooms, it awaits chances to steal its prey’s life force.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: It hides in shadows. It is said that if GENGAR is hiding, it cools the area by nearly 10 degrees F.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Deep in the night, your shadow cast by a streetlight may suddenly overtake you. It is actually a GENGAR running past you, pretending to be your shadow.

Name: Gengar
FlavorText: Under a full moon, this POKéMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: This chain of immense stones resembles a giant serpent. Tremors shake the earth above as it burrows deep beneath the ground, feeding on boulders as it goes.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: It squirms through the ground using its long and rugged body. It always eats while burrowing.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: When it travels underground, it causes rumbling and tremors. It can move at 50 mph.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes increasingly rounder and smoother.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: Opening its large mouth, it ingests massive amounts of soil and creates long tunnels.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: It burrows through the ground at a speed of 50 mph while feeding on large boulders.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: It twists and squirms through the ground. The thunderous roar of its tunneling echoes a long way.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: There is a magnet in its brain that prevents an ONIX from losing direction while tunneling. As it grows older, its body becomes steadily rounder and smoother.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to black-colored diamonds.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by DIGLETTs.

Name: Onix
FlavorText: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: When it twitches its nose, it can tell where someone is sleeping and what that person is dreaming about.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children’s are much tastier.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: It puts its prey to sleep and devours their dreams. It seems that bad dreams taste sour, so Drowzee doesn’t particularly like eating them.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: It can be spotted near recreational facilities, intending to eat the pleasant dreams of children who enjoyed themselves there that day.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: It finds really fun dreams tasty. When it makes friends with people, it may show them the most delicious dreams it’s ever eaten.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: A Pokémon that nourishes itself by eating dreams, it is thought to share common ancestry with Munna and Musharna.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it’s a sure sign that one of these Pokémon is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: If you think that you had a good dream but you can’t remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: Puts enemies to sleep, then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating only bad dreams.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: If your nose becomes itchy while you are sleeping, it’s a sure sign that a DROWZEE is standing above your pillow and trying to eat your dream through your nostrils.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: A descendent of the legendary animal baku, which is said to eat dreams. It is skilled at hypnotism.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: If you think that you had a good dream, but you can’t remember it, a DROWZEE has probably eaten it.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it has eaten in the past.

Name: Drowzee
FlavorText: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: There are some Hypno that assist doctors with patients who can’t sleep at night in hospitals.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: In Alola, Komala is Hypno’s main target. It rarely harms people.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: As a matter of course, it makes anyone it meets fall asleep and has a taste of their dreams. Anyone having a good dream, it carries off.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: While it is an extremely dangerous Pokémon, people who are in need of a good, sound sleep call it their savior.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: Hypno holds a pendulum in its hand. The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum lull the foe into a deep state of hypnosis. While this Pokémon searches for prey, it polishes the pendulum.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: It carries a pendulum-like device. There once was an incident in which it took away a child it hypnotized.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: When it is very hungry, it puts humans it meets to sleep, then it feasts on their dreams.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: The arcing movement and glitter of the pendulum in a HYPNO’s hand lull the foe into deep hypnosis. While searching for prey, it polishes the pendulum.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: It carries a pendulum-like device. There once was an incident in which it took  away a child it hypnotized.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: The longer it swings its pendulum, the longer the effects of its hypnosis last.

Name: Hypno
FlavorText: Always holding a pendulum that it rocks at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are lost in battle.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: Its pincers are superb weapons. They sometimes break off during battle, but they grow back fast.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: Krabby live on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. On sandy beaches with little in the way of food, these Pokémon can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: The pincers break off easily. If it loses a pincer, it somehow becomes incapable of walking sideways.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: KRABBY live in holes dug into beaches. On sandy shores with little in the way of food, they can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: If it is unable to find food, it will absorb nutrients by swallowing a mouthful of sand.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The bubbles it spews out are strongly alkaline. Any opponents hit by them will have their bodies quickly melted away.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The flow of Gigantamax energy has spurred this Pokémon’s left pincer to grow to an enormous size. That claw can pulverize anything.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it’s not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the Pokémon quickly tires.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its balance and staggers.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: It can hardly lift its massive, overgrown pincer. The pincer’s size makes it difficult to aim properly.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: It waves its huge, oversized claw in the air to communicate with others. But since the claw is so heavy, this POKéMON quickly tires.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The large pincer has 10,000-horsepower crushing force. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: One claw grew massively and as hard as steel. It has 10,000-HP strength. However, it is too heavy.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: It’s usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: Voltorb is extremely sensitive—it explodes at the slightest of shocks. It is rumored that it was first created when a Poké Ball was exposed to a powerful pulse of energy.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: Voltorb was first sighted at a company that manufactures Poké Balls. The link between that sighting and the fact that this Pokémon looks very similar to a Poké Ball remains a mystery.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on contact.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: It bears an uncanny and unexplained resemblance to a POKé BALL. Because it explodes at the slightest shock, even veteran TRAINERS treat it with caution.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: A life-form whose identity is unknown. It is said to SCREECH or suddenly SELFDESTRUCT.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: VOLTORB is extremely sensitive - it explodes at the slightest of shocks. It is rumored that it was first created when a POKé BALL was exposed to a powerful pulse of energy.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: During the study of this POKéMON, it was discovered that its components are not found in nature.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL, they have zapped many people.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokémon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of the Bomb Ball.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: One of Electrode’s characteristics is its attraction to electricity. It is a problematical Pokémon that congregates mostly at electrical power plants to feed on electricity that has just been generated.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: Electrode eats electricity in the atmosphere. On days when lightning strikes, you can see this Pokémon exploding all over the place from eating too much electricity.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of “The Bomb Ball.”

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: It is dangerous. If it has too much electricity and has nothing to do, it amuses itself by exploding.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: They appear in great numbers at electric power plants. Because they feed on electricity, they cause massive and chaotic blackouts in nearby cities.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: These Pokémon get nervous when they’re not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be six heads for it to maintain balance.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Although they are the same size as other Exeggcute, the ones produced in Alola are quite heavy. Their shells are packed full.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Six of them together form a full-fledged Pokémon. It’s often hunted by Crabrawler, but uses psychokinesis to drive it off.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: This Pokémon consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, Exeggcute is close to evolution.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life-form more like plant seeds.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Using telepathy only they can employ, they always form a cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Their shells are very durable. Even if they crack, they can survive without spilling their contents.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: It consists of six eggs that care for each other. The eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear, it is close to evolution.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: It is often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: If even one is separated from the group, the energy bond between the six will make them rejoin instantly.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Using telepathy only they can receive, they always form a cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: The shell is very durable. Even if it cracks, it can survive without spilling the contents.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be 6 heads for it to maintain balance.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s psychic powers aren’t as strong as they once were. The head on this Exeggutor’s tail scans surrounding areas with weak telepathy.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Blazing sunlight has brought out the true form and powers of this Pokémon.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: The strong sunlight of the Alola region has awakened the power hidden within Exeggcute. This is the result.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It swings its long neck like a whip and smacks its opponents. This makes Exeggutor itself dizzy, too.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Exeggutor is the pride of the Alolan people. Its image is carved into historical buildings and murals.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Alola is the best environment for this Pokémon. Local people take pride in its appearance, saying this is how Exeggutor ought to look.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is called the Walking Jungle. If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: When they work together, Exeggutor’s three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the three heads thinks about whatever it likes.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It engages its enemies using psychic powers. Each of its three heads fires off psychokinetic energy, tripling its power.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: When the time comes, one of its three heads falls off. Before long, the fallen head grows into an Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Each of its heads has its own will. They use telepathy to discuss their plans before coming to a joint decision.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is called “The Walking Jungle.” If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Its three heads think independently. However, they are friendly and never appear to squabble.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: If a head drops off, it emits a telepathic call in search of others to form an EXEGGCUTE cluster.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Originally from the tropics, EXEGGUTOR’s heads grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall, they group to form an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is said that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is called “The Walking Tropical Rainforest.” Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Living in a good environment makes it grow lots of heads. A head that drops off becomes an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the 3 heads thinks about whatever it likes.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: This Pokémon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone’s dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: Wears the skull of its deceased mother. Its cries echo inside the skull and come out as a sad melody.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: It wears its mother’s skull on its head, so no one knows what its bare face looks like. However, it’s clear that it’s always crying.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: At night, it weeps loudly for its dead mother, but those cries only attract its natural enemy—Mandibuzz.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: The skull it wears on its head is that of its dead mother. According to some, it will evolve when it comes to terms with the pain of her death.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: When it thinks of its deceased mother, it weeps loudly. Mandibuzz that hear its cries will attack it from the air.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: Cubone pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull the Pokémon wears are made by the tears it sheds.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: It always wears the skull of its dead mother, so no one has any idea what its hidden face looks like.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: It wears the skull of its dead mother on its head. When it becomes lonesome, it is said to cry loudly.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: If it is sad or lonely, the skull it wears shakes and emits a plaintive and mournful sound.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: It pines for the mother it will never see again. Seeing a likeness of its mother in the full moon, it cries. The stains on the skull it wears are from its tears.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKéMON’s real face.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: It lost its mother after its birth. It wears its mother’s skull, never revealing its true face.

Name: Cubone
FlavorText: If it is sad or lonely, the skull it wears shakes, and emits a plaintive and mournful sound.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The cursed flames that light up the bone carried by this Pokémon are said to cause both mental and physical pain that will never fade.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: This Pokémon sets the bone it holds on fire and dances through the night as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: It has transformed the spirit of its dear departed mother into flames, and tonight it will once again dance in mourning of others of its kind.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: When it beats opponents with its bone, the cursed flames spread to them. No amount of water will stop those flames from burning.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The rich greenery of the Alola region is hard on Marowak. It controls fire to stay alive.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: Its custom is to mourn its lost companions. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The bones it possesses were once its mother’s. Its mother’s regrets have become like a vengeful spirit protecting this Pokémon.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The bones it uses have been in its possession since it was born. It has a ferocious nature.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: When this Pokémon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak’s temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: Small and weak, this Pokémon is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: It throws bones at Mandibuzz to knock it down. It’s thought that Marowak is trying to avenge its parent.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: This Pokémon is out for vengeance on its natural enemy, Mandibuzz. It throws bones like boomerangs to try to take it down.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: Originally, it was weak and timid. After evolution, its temperament becomes violent, and it begins to wield bones as weapons.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: Marowak is the evolved form of a Cubone that has overcome its sadness at the loss of its mother and grown tough. This Pokémon’s tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: It is small and was originally very weak. Its temperament turned ferocious when it began using bones.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: From its birth, this savage Pokémon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: It collects bones from an unknown place. Some whisper that a MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out messages to others.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: A MAROWAK is the evolved form of a CUBONE that has grown tough by overcoming the grief of losing its mother. Its tempered and hardened spirit is not easily broken.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: Somewhere in the world is a cemetery just for MAROWAK. It gets its bones from those graves.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: It collects bones from an unknown place. A MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world, rumors say.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: Its legs can stretch to double their length. First-time foes are startled by Hitmonlee’s extensible reach.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: When kicking, the sole of its foot turns as hard as a diamond on impact and destroys its enemy.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: Hitmonlee’s legs freely contract and stretch. Using these springlike legs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its legs and loosens the muscles to overcome fatigue.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: If it starts kicking repeatedly, both legs will stretch even longer to strike a fleeing foe.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: Its legs freely stretch and contract. Using these springlike limbs, it bowls over foes with devastating kicks. After battle, it rubs down its tired legs.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra-long, loping strides.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: It is also called the Kick Master. It uses its elastic legs to execute every known kick.

Name: Hitmonlee
FlavorText: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: When Hitmonchan twists its arm while throwing a punch, the blow will pulverize even concrete. The Pokémon rests after three minutes of fighting.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.

Name: Hitmonchan
