FlavorText: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: Punches in corkscrew fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall like a drill.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: Hitmonchan is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working toward a world championship. This Pokémon has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this Pokémon. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: A HITMONCHAN is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who aimed to become the world champion. Having an indomitable spirit means that it will never give up.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning-fast volleys that are impossible to see.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: HITMONCHAN is said to possess the spirit of a boxer who had been working towards a world championship. This POKéMON has an indomitable spirit and will never give up in the face of adversity.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: To increase the strength of all its punch moves, it spins its arms just before making contact.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: Punches in corkscrew fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall in the same way as a drill.

Name: Hitmonchan
FlavorText: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Wields its long tongue deftly, as though it were an arm. The Pokémon’s viscous saliva, once it has been collected and boiled down, yields a strong and highly useful adhesive.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Instead of its hands, it uses its tongue, which can stretch to twice this Pokémon’s height. Lickitung’s sticky saliva grips anything.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Bug Pokémon are Lickitung’s main food source. This Pokémon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Its tongue spans almost seven feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: It licks filth clean with its tongue. Whatever it licks always stinks afterward, so whether it’s really clean is...questionable.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: It checks out whatever’s around it by licking everything. If you don’t clean off a spot where it’s licked you, you’ll break out in a rash!

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Whenever Lickitung comes across something new, it will unfailingly give it a lick. It does so because it memorizes things by texture and by taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Being licked by its long, saliva-covered tongue leaves a tingling sensation. Extending its tongue retracts its tail.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: When it extends its over-six-foot-long tongue, its tail quivers. There is a possibility they are connected.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Its tongue has well-developed nerves that run to the very tip, so it can be deftly manipulated.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Whenever it sees something unfamiliar, it always licks the object because it memorizes things by texture and taste. It is somewhat put off by sour things.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon’s. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: It has a tongue that is over 6’6’’ long. It uses this long tongue to lick its body clean.

Name: Lickitung
FlavorText: Its tongue spans almost 7 feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell; they are also explosive.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing used to be more plentiful in the Galar region than they are now.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: In hot places, its internal gases could expand and explode without any warning. Be very careful!

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Koffing embodies toxic substances. It mixes the toxins with raw garbage to set off a chemical reaction that results in a terribly powerful poison gas. The higher the temperature, the more gas is concocted by this Pokémon.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: If Koffing becomes agitated, it raises the toxicity of its internal gases and jets them out from all over its body. This Pokémon may also overinflate its round body, then explode.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horribly toxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: The poisonous gases it contains are a little bit lighter than air, keeping it slightly airborne.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Its thin, filmy body is filled with gases that cause constant sniffles, coughs and teary eyes.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Getting up close to a KOFFING will give you a chance to observe, through its thin skin, the toxic gases swirling inside. It blows up at the slightest stimulation.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

Name: Koffing
FlavorText: If one gets close enough to it when it expels poisonous gas, the gas swirling inside it can be seen.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: This Pokémon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: It can’t suck in air quite as well as a Galarian Weezing, but the toxins it creates are more potent than those of its counterpart.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: It mixes gases between its two bodies. It’s said that these Pokémon were seen all over the Galar region back in the day.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives and grows by absorbing poison gas, dust, and germs that exist inside garbage.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Weezing alternately shrinks and inflates its twin bodies to mix together toxic gases inside. The more the gases are mixed, the more powerful the toxins become. The Pokémon also becomes more putrid.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Weezing loves the gases given off by rotted kitchen garbage. This Pokémon will find a dirty, unkempt house and make it its home. At night, when the people in the house are asleep, it will go through the trash.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Inhaling toxic fumes from trash and mixing them inside its body lets it spread an even fouler stench.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: By diluting its toxic gases with a special process, the highest grade of perfume can be extracted. To WEEZING, gases emanating from garbage are the ultimate feast.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, two KOFFING can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: When it inhales poisonous gases from garbage, its body expands, and its insides smell much worse.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: It lives and grows by absorbing dust, germs and poison gases that are contained in toxic waste and garbage.

Name: Weezing
FlavorText: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Ludicrously strong—when it butts heads with a mountain, it is the mountain that shatters. But its short legs struggle with turns, and it is incapable of stopping unless it collides with something.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Its body is clad in a thick hide, and its tackles topple buildings. Unfortunately, it is not smart.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it starts rushing, it forgets why it started.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: A Pokémon with a one-track mind. Once it charges, it won’t stop running until it falls asleep.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Rhyhorn’s brain is very small. It is so dense, while on a run it forgets why it started running in the first place. It apparently remembers sometimes if it demolishes something.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Rhyhorn runs in a straight line, smashing everything in its path. It is not bothered even if it rushes headlong into a block of steel. This Pokémon may feel some pain from the collision the next day, however.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Its powerful tackles can destroy anything. However, it is too slow witted to help people work.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: It doesn’t care if there is anything in its way. It just charges and destroys all obstacles.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Once it starts running, it doesn’t stop. Its tiny brain makes it so stupid that it can’t remember why it started running in the first place.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Its massive bones are 1,000 times harder than human bones. Its TACKLE can knock a semitrailer flying.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: A POKéMON with a one-track mind. Once it charges,  it won’t stop running until it falls asleep.

Name: Rhyhorn
FlavorText: Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Rapidly rotates its horn to bore through bedrock. It swaggers around volcanic regions, protected from the lava’s heat by its tough, armorlike hide.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Its brain developed after it stood up on its hind legs. Its drill horn bores tunnels through solid rock.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Its brain developed when it began walking on its hind legs. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Rhydon has a horn that serves as a drill. It is used for destroying rocks and boulders. This Pokémon occasionally rams into streams of magma, but the armor-like hide prevents it from feeling the heat.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Rhydon’s horn can crush even uncut diamonds. One sweeping blow of its tail can topple a building. This Pokémon’s hide is extremely tough. Even direct cannon hits don’t leave a scratch.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Its brain developed when it began walking on hind legs. Its thick hide protects it even in magma.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Its rugged hide protects it from even the heat of lava. However, the hide also makes it insensitive.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Its horn, which rotates like a drill, destroys tall buildings with one strike. It stands on its hind legs, and its brain is well developed.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: By lightly spinning its drill-like horn, it can easily shatter even a diamond in the rough.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Walks on its hind legs. Shows signs of intelligence. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.

Name: Rhydon
FlavorText: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: This purehearted Pokémon shares its eggs with the injured. These eggs are so nutritious that they’ve been nicknamed “doctors’ doubles.”

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: It lays several eggs a day and won’t share them with those who have evil in their hearts.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: It is said to deliver happiness. Being compassionate, it shares its eggs with injured people.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: This species was once very slow. To protect their eggs from other creatures, these Pokémon became able to flee quickly.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: The egg Chansey carries is not only delicious but also packed with nutrition. It’s used as a high-class cooking ingredient.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: A gentle and kindhearted Pokémon that shares its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured Pokémon.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: Because the eggs on their bellies have been overharvested by people in the past, the Chansey population remains very small.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: It seems that other Pokémon’s efforts to take its delicious, nutritious egg away from it caused Chansey to get faster at fleeing.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: Not only are these Pokémon fast runners, they’re also few in number, so anyone who finds one must be lucky indeed.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: The eggs laid by Chansey are rich in nutrients and a favorite food of many Pokémon.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: Chansey lays nutritionally excellent eggs on an everyday basis. The eggs are so delicious, they are easily and eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: It lays several eggs a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: Being few in number and difficult to capture, it is said to bring happiness to the Trainer who catches it.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: CHANSEY lay nutritionally excellent eggs every day. The eggs are so delicious, they are eagerly devoured by even those people who have lost their appetite.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to catch one.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: People try to catch it for its extremely nutritious eggs, but it rarely can be found.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: Few in number and difficult to capture, it is said to bring happiness to the trainer who catches it.

Name: Chansey
FlavorText: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: It is cloaked entirely in blue vines, preventing any glimpse of its true identity. The vines impart a refreshing sensation when chewed—they’re useful as a spice.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: It is shrouded by blue vines. No one has seen the face hidden behind this growth of vines.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The vines of a Tangela have a distinct scent. In some parts of Galar, Tangela vines are used as herbs.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Its identity is obscured by masses of thick blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Tangela’s vines snap off easily if they are grabbed. This happens without pain, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by newly grown vines the very next day.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The blue vines shrouding its body are covered in a growth of fine hair. It is known to be ticklish.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The vines that cloak its entire body are always jiggling. They effectively unnerve its foes.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Its vines snap off easily and painlessly if they are grabbed, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by new growth the very next day.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. The vines sway as it walks.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Blue plant vines cloak the POKéMON’s identity in a tangled mass. It entangles anything that gets close.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: During battle, it constantly moves the vines that cover its body in order to annoy its opponent.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Its identity is obscured by masses of thick, blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. Its vines shake as it walks.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: Its child has grown rapidly, thanks to the energy of Mega Evolution. Mother and child show their harmonious teamwork in battle.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: When the mother sees the back of her Mega-Evolved child, it makes her think of the day when her child will inevitably leave her.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: The explosive energy the child is bathed in causes temporary growth. The mother is beside herself with worry about it.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: Thanks to Mega Evolution, its child grows. But as the child is good only at fighting and nothing else, its mother feels uneasy about its future.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: Mega Kangaskhan’s strength derives from the mother’s happiness about her child’s growth. Watching it grow up keeps her spirits high.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets its baby out to play only when it feels safe to do so.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: Raises its young in its belly pouch. Won’t run from any fight to keep its young protected.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: You shouldn’t get close to the child when it’s playing outside its mother’s pouch. Its mother is always nearby watching over it.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: Kangaskhan protects its child by keeping it in its pouch. It has zero forgiveness for those who harm its child and will beat them down.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: The child in its pouch leaves home after roughly three years. That is the only time the mother is heard to cry wildly.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: Kangaskhan’s maternal love is so deep that it will brave death to protect its offspring.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: If you come across a young Kangaskhan playing by itself, you must never disturb it or attempt to catch it. The baby Pokémon’s parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged at you.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: To protect its young, it will never give up during battle, no matter how badly wounded it is.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: If you come across a young KANGASKHAN playing by itself, never try to catch it. The baby’s parent is sure to be in the area, and it will become violently enraged.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother’s protective pouch until it is three years old.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: The female raises its offspring in a pouch on its belly. It is skilled at attacking using COMET PUNCH.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: To avoid crushing the baby it carries in its pouch, it always sleeps standing up.

Name: Kangaskhan
FlavorText: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother’s protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits black ink and flees.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If it senses any danger, it will vigorously spray water or a special type of ink from its mouth.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If Horsea senses danger, it will reflexively spray a dense black ink from its mouth and try to escape. This Pokémon swims by cleverly flapping the fin on its back.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Horsea eats small insects and moss off of rocks. If the ocean current turns fast, this Pokémon anchors itself by wrapping its tail around rocks or coral to prevent being washed away.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Its big, developed fins move rapidly, allowing it to swim backward while still facing forward.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If attacked by a larger enemy, it quickly swims to safety by adeptly controlling its well-developed dorsal fin.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: By cleverly flicking the fins on its back side to side, it moves in any direction while facing forward. It spits ink to escape if it senses danger.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: It maintains balance using its tail, which is wound up like a coil. It may spray ink from its mouth.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If HORSEA senses danger, it will reflexively spray a dense black ink from its mouth and try to escape. This POKéMON swims by cleverly flapping the fins on its back.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: When they’re in a safe location, they can be seen playfully tangling their tails together.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If attacked by a larger enemy, it quickly swims to safety by adeptly controlling its dorsal fin.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Seadra’s mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that’s larger than the opening of its mouth.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: It’s the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Touching the back fin causes numbness. It hooks its tail to coral to stay in place while sleeping.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Seadra generates whirlpools by spinning its body. The whirlpools are strong enough to swallow even fishing boats. This Pokémon weakens prey with these currents, then swallows it whole.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Seadra sleeps after wriggling itself between the branches of coral. Those trying to harvest coral are occasionally stung by this Pokémon’s poison barbs if they fail to notice it.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional-medicine ingredients.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its fin-tips leak poison. Its fins and bones are highly valued as ingredients in herbal medicine.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: An examination of its cells revealed the presence of a gene not found in HORSEA. It became a hot topic.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: The poisonous barbs all over its body are highly valued as ingredients for making traditional herbal medicine. It shows no mercy to anything approaching its nest.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: The male raises the young. If it is approached, it uses its toxic spikes to fend off the intruder.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: It swims at a steady five knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: It swims elegantly by flittering its tail fin as if it were a dress. It has the look of a queen.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: When it is time for them to lay eggs, they can be seen swimming up rivers and falls in large groups.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: The way it swims along fluttering its dress-like fins has earned it the name “princess of the water.”

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Although known for their splendid tail fins, Goldeen apparently compete among themselves to see whose horn is thickest and sharpest.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Spellbound by the length of its horn and the beauty of its fins, many strange Trainers raise Goldeen and nothing but Goldeen.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: When the weather grows warm, they form groups and swim upriver. This sight serves as a poetic reminder that spring has arrived.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Goldeen loves swimming wild and free in rivers and ponds. If one of these Pokémon is placed in an aquarium, it will shatter even the thickest glass with one ram of its horn and make its escape.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Goldeen is a very beautiful Pokémon with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don’t let your guard down around this Pokémon—it could ram you powerfully with its horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: It swims at a steady 5 knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Though it appears very elegant when swimming with fins unfurled, it can jab powerfully with its horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: A strong swimmer, it is capable of swimming nonstop up fast streams at a steady speed of five knots per hour.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its dorsal, pectoral and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the water dancer.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: In the springtime, schools of GOLDEEN can be seen swimming up falls and rivers. It metes out staggering damage with its single horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of “The Water Queen.”

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: GOLDEEN is a very beautiful POKéMON with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don’t let your guard down around this POKéMON - it could ram you powerfully with its horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: During spawning season, they swim gracefully in the water, searching for their perfect mate.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: A strong swimmer, it is capable of swimming nonstop up fast streams at a steady speed of five knots.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: To protect its family, it will fight with its drill-sharp horn. It lives in hollowed rocks in streams.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in streams with its horn. The Pokémon defends its eggs with its life.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It is the male’s job to make a nest by carving out boulders in a stream using the horn on its head.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: To attract females, males dance on the river’s floor. The females gather around the male that dances most gracefully.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Its horn spins like a drill to steadily hollow out rocks—even harder ones. The coloration of the male is more vivid.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Trainers who are crazy for Seaking are divided into horn enthusiasts and fin enthusiasts. The two groups do not get along well.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: When the weather grows cold, its whole body flushes a deep red. This sight serves as a poetic reminder that autumn has arrived.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Seaking is very protective of its eggs. The male and female will take turns patrolling around their nest and eggs. The guarding of eggs by these Pokémon goes on for over a month.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: In the autumn, Seaking males can be seen performing courtship dances in riverbeds to woo females. During this season, this Pokémon’s body coloration is at its most beautiful.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in streams with its horn. It defends its eggs with its life.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: During spawning season, SEAKING gather from all over, causing rivers to appear a brilliant red.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It punches holes in boulders on streambeds. This is a clever innovation that prevents its eggs from being attacked or washed away by the current.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: The horn on its head is sharp like a drill. It bores a hole in a boulder to make its nest.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: When autumn comes, the males patrol the area around their nests in order to protect their offspring.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: During spawning season, SEAKING gather from all over, coloring the rivers a brilliant red.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: If Staryu’s body is damaged, it will regenerate as long as the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn’t bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: As long as the center section is unharmed, this Pokémon can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: No number of injuries can bother Staryu. Its amazing regenerative powers return it to its previous state in half a day!

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: In many places, there are folktales of stardust falling into the ocean and becoming Staryu.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: This Pokémon gets nibbled on by Lumineon and others. Thanks to its red core, it regenerates fast, so it’s unconcerned by their snack attacks.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Large numbers of these Pokémon make their home at the seaside. At night, a strange red glow radiates from the center of their bodies.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Staryu apparently communicates with the stars in the night sky by flashing the red core at the center of its body. If parts of its body are torn, this Pokémon simply regenerates the missing pieces and limbs.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Staryu’s center section has an organ called the core that shines bright red. If you go to a beach toward the end of summer, the glowing cores of these Pokémon look like the stars in the sky.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Even if its body is torn, it can regenerate as long as the glowing central core remains intact.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: As long as its red core remains, it can regenerate its body instantly, even if it’s torn apart.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: At night, the middle of its body slowly flickers with the same rhythm as a human heartbeat.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: It gathers with others in the night and makes its red core glow on and off with the twinkling stars. It can regenerate limbs if they are severed from its body.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: An enigmatic POKéMON that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: When the stars twinkle at night, it floats up from the sea floor, and its body’s center core flickers.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: At night, the center of its body slowly flickers with the same rhythm as a human heartbeat.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: As long as the center section is unharmed, it can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: At the center of its body is a red core that sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The center section is named the core. People think it is communicating when it glows in seven colors.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: It rotates its geometrically shaped body to swim through the water. It always seems to be sending out mysterious radio waves.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its sparkling core is called “the gem of the sea.” This core can be made into high-priced accessories that are traded in secret.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its unusual body shape, reminiscent of abstract art, led local people to spread rumors that this Pokémon may be an invader from outer space.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its shining core is thought to receive and transmit enigmatic signals. It has been known to cause headaches in those who approach it.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Starmie swims through water by spinning its star-shaped body as if it were a propeller on a ship. The core at the center of this Pokémon’s body glows in seven colors.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Starmie’s center section—the core—glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this Pokémon has been given the nickname “the gem of the sea.”

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its core shines in many colors and sends radio signals into space to communicate with something.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Regardless of the environment it lives in, its body grows to form a symmetrical geometric shape.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The middle section of its body is called the core. It glows in a different color each time it is seen.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: People in ancient times imagined that STARMIE were transformed from the reflections of stars that twinkled on gentle waves at night.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: This POKéMON has a geometric body. Because of its body, the locals suspect that it is an alien creature.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: STARMIE’s center section - the core - glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this POKéMON has been given the nickname “the gem of the sea.”

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: It is said that it uses the seven-colored core of its body to send electric waves into outer space.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The center section of its body is called the core. It glows in a different color each time it is seen.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The center section is named the core. People think it is communicating when it glows in 7 colors.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It’ll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: Its talent is tap-dancing. It can also manipulate temperatures to create a floor of ice, which this Pokémon can kick up to use as a barrier.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: The behavior of this clown-like Pokémon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emitted from its fingertips.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: Emanations from its fingertips solidify the air into invisible walls that repel even harsh attacks.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: It is a pantomime expert that can create invisible but solid walls using miming gestures.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: It’s known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: Always practices its pantomime act. It makes enemies believe something exists that really doesn’t.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: It creates invisible walls with its pantomiming. If you don’t act impressed, it will attack you with a double slap!

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: Its pantomime skills are wonderful. You may become enraptured while watching it, but next thing you know, Mr. Mime has made a real wall.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: Mr. Mime is a master of pantomime. Its gestures and motions convince watchers that something unseeable actually exists. Once the watchers are convinced, the unseeable thing exists as if it were real.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: It shapes an invisible wall in midair by minutely vibrating its fingertips to stop molecules in the air.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: Its fingertips emit a peculiar force field that hardens air to create an actual wall.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: A skilled mime from birth, it gains the ability to create invisible objects as it matures.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: A MR. MIME is a master of pantomime. It can convince others that something unseeable actually exists. Once believed, the imaginary object does become real.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: If interrupted while it is miming, it will suddenly DOUBLESLAP the offender with its broad hands.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: MR. MIME is a master of pantomime. Its gestures and motions convince watchers that something unseeable actually exists. Once it is believed, it will exist as if it were a real thing.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: It uses the mysterious power it has in its fingers to solidify air into an invisible wall.

Name: Mr. Mime
FlavorText: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: The large, wickedly sharp scythes on its forearms are truly fearsome weapons. Prey’s attempts to flee are unfailingly thwarted by this Pokémon’s nimble motions.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: It is nearly impossible to parry its attacking scythes. Its movements are like a ninja’s.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: If you come across an area in a forest where a lot of the trees have been cut down, what you’ve found is a Scyther’s territory.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: As Scyther fights more and more battles, its scythes become sharper and sharper. With a single slice, Scyther can fell a massive tree.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: Leaps out of tall grass and slices prey with its scythes. The movement looks like that of a ninja.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: Some call it a ninja. Its movements— imperceptibly quick—are sufficient to cleave the air in two. It’s very popular in Alola.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: Its two sharp scythes are more than just weapons. It uses them with dexterity to dress its prey before eating.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: While young, they live together deep in the mountains, training themselves in how to fight with their scythes and move at high speeds.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: It confuses its prey with its quick, ninja-like movements. Then, in an instant, it cleaves them with its scythes.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: Scyther is blindingly fast. Its blazing speed enhances the effectiveness of the twin scythes on its forearms. This Pokémon’s scythes are so effective, they can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: It tears and shreds prey with its wickedly sharp scythes. It very rarely spreads its wings to fly.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: When it moves, it leaves only a blur. If it hides in grass, its protective coloration makes it invisible.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: Its blindingly fast speed adds to the sharpness of its twin forearm scythes. The scythes can slice through thick logs in one wicked stroke.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one of itself.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: It’s very proud of its speed. It moves so fast that its opponent does not even know what knocked it down.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: When it moves, it leaves only a blur. If it hides in grass, its protective colors make it invisible.

Name: Scyther
FlavorText: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: The Jynx of Galar often have beautiful and delicate voices. Some of these Pokémon have even gathered a fan base.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: Its strange cries sound like human language. There are some musicians who compose songs for Jynx to sing.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: It sways its hips to a rhythm all its own. The precise movements of Jynx living in Alola are truly wonderful.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: Jynx walks rhythmically, swaying and shaking its hips as if it were dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly alluring, people seeing it are compelled to shake their hips without giving any thought to what they are doing.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: It speaks using a language that sounds human. Research is under way to determine what is being said.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: It wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: It speaks a language similar to that of humans. However, it seems to use dancing to communicate.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: It rocks its body rhythmically. It appears to alter the rhythm depending on how it is feeling.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: A JYNX sashays rhythmically as if it were dancing. Its motions are so bouncingly alluring, people seeing it are compelled to shake their hips without noticing.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

Name: Jynx
FlavorText: It has several different cry patterns, each of which seems to have its own meaning.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Feeds on electrical energy. During sudden showers beneath looming thunderclouds, one can observe Electabuzz scaling tall trees, where the Pokémon will then wait for lightning to strike.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Half of all blackouts occur when this Pokémon appears at power plants and eats electricity.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: With the coming of a storm, many of these Pokémon will gather under tall trees and sit there waiting for lightning to strike.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: If a major power outage occurs, it is certain that this Pokémon has eaten electricity at a power plant.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: While it’s often blamed for power outages, the truth is the cause of outages is more often an error on the part of the electric company.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Electricity permeates its body. It swings its arms round and round to charge up electricity before unleashing a punch.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Electricity leaks from it in amounts far greater than the amount of electricity it eats.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Half of all sudden blackouts are caused by Electabuzz gathering at electric power plants and gobbling up electricity.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: When a storm arrives, gangs of this Pokémon compete with each other to scale heights that are likely to be stricken by lightning bolts. Some towns use Electabuzz in place of lightning rods.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Electricity runs across the surface of its body. In darkness, its entire body glows a whitish blue.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: It windmills its arms to slightly boost its punches. Foes have been known to escape in the meantime.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Electricity runs across the surface of its body. In darkness, its entire body glows a whitish-blue.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: When a storm approaches, it competes with others to scale heights that are likely to be stricken by lightning. Some towns use ELECTABUZZ in place of lightning rods.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

Name: Electabuzz
FlavorText: When two ELECTABUZZ touch, they control the electric currents to communicate their feelings.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Legend has it that this Pokémon was born from the crater of a volcano. When wounded, it bathes in lava to heal its body, much as one would soak in a hot spring.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: It was born in the crater of a volcano. Its body is covered with flames that shimmer like the sun.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: These Pokémon’s bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: The hotter the place, the better they feel. Magmar in Alola are said to be hardier than those in other areas.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Its entire body is burning. When it breathes, the temperature rises. When it sneezes, flames shoot out!

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: When angered, it spouts brilliant fire from all over its body. It doesn’t calm down until its opponent has burned to ash.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: When it’s tired, it leaps into the mouth of a volcano and soaks its body in magma to ease its weariness. Its body burns at 2,192 degrees F.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: In battle, Magmar blows out intensely hot flames from all over its body to intimidate its opponent. This Pokémon’s fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in its surroundings.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: The scorching fire exhaled by Magmar forms heat waves around its body, making it hard to see the Pokémon clearly.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: When it breathes deeply, heat waves form around its body, making it hard to see clearly.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: The fiery surface of its body gives off a wavering, rippling glare that is similar to the sun.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: It dislikes cold places, so it blows scorching flames to make the environment suitable for itself.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: In battle, it blows out intense flames from all over its body to intimidate its foe. These fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in the area.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly amidst flames.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: It moves more frequently in hot areas. It can heal itself by dipping its wound into lava.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: With its vaunted horns, it can lift an opponent 10 times heavier than itself and fly about with ease.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: It zips around at blistering speeds, looking for an opening to skewer its opponent on its giant pincers.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: After Mega Evolution, it becomes able to fly. Perhaps because it’s so happy, it rarely touches the ground.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Bathed in the energy of Mega Evolution, its wings become unusually developed. It flies at speeds of approximately 30 mph.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: The influence of Mega Evolution leaves it in a state of constant excitement. It pierces enemies with its two large horns before shredding them.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn apart. What it can’t tear, it tosses far away.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Grips its prey in its pincers and squeezes hard! It can’t move if it’s cold, so it lives in warm places.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Although it’s tough, it can’t handle cold well. When night falls, it buries itself in leafage and sleeps.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: It gets into territorial disputes with Vikavolt. For some reason, it apparently gets along well with Heracross in Alola.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: It grips its prey in its pincers and splits them apart. Although it is a powerful Pokémon, it can’t deal with the cold.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Pinsir has a pair of massive horns. Protruding from the surface of these horns are thorns. These thorns are driven deeply into the foe’s body when the pincer closes, making it tough for the foe to escape.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Pinsir is astoundingly strong. It can grip a foe weighing twice its weight in its horns and easily lift it. This Pokémon’s movements turn sluggish in cold places.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: It swings its long pincer horns wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can’t tear, it tosses far.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: It grips prey with its powerful pincers and will not let go until the prey is torn in half.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: With its pincer horns, it digs burrows to sleep in at night. In the morning, damp soil clings to its body.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Their pincers are strong enough to shatter thick logs. Because they dislike cold, PINSIR burrow and sleep under the ground on chilly nights.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: If it fails to crush the foe in its pincers, it will swing around and toss the opponent.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Its two long pincer horns are powerful. Once they grip an enemy, they won’t release until the foe is torn.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: PINSIR has a pair of massive horns  Protruding from the surface of these horns are thorns. These thorns are driven deeply into the foe’s body when the pincer closes, making it tough for the foe to escape.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: When the temperature drops at night, it sleeps on treetops or among roots where it is well hidden.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: Swings its long antlers wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: With its horns, it digs burrows to sleep in at night. In the morning, damp soil clings to its body.

Name: Pinsir
FlavorText: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: It swims by jetting water from its horns. The most notable characteristic of the Aqua Breed is its high body fat, which allows it to float easily.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: This Pokémon blasts water from holes on the tips of its horns—the high-pressure jets pierce right through Tauros’s enemies.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: People call this kind of Tauros the Blaze Breed due to the hot air it snorts from its nostrils. Its three tails are intertwined.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: When heated by fire energy, its horns can get hotter than 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Those gored by them will suffer both wounds and burns.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: This kind of Tauros, known as the Combat Breed, is distinguished by its thick, powerful muscles and its fierce disposition.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a muscular body and excels at close-quarters combat. It uses its short horns to strike the opponent’s weak spots.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd’s protector takes pride in its battle-scarred horns.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: Once it takes aim at its prey, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: The Tauros of the Galar region are volatile in nature, and they won’t allow people to ride on their backs.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: A rowdy Pokémon with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won’t stop until it hits something.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: The climate seems to be related to the reason Tauros in Alola are a little calmer than those in other regions.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: Although it’s known to be a fierce Pokémon, Tauros in the Alola region are said to possess a measure of calmness.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: Historically, people in areas all over the world have ridden Tauros, but the practice is said to have started in Alola.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: This Pokémon is not satisfied unless it is rampaging at all times. If there is no opponent for Tauros to battle, it will charge at thick trees and knock them down to calm itself.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: When it is about to tackle, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: After heightening its will to fight by whipping itself with its three tails, it charges at full speed.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

Name: Tauros

FlavorText: Despite having strong fangs and tentacles, it went extinct when its heavy shell made it unable to catch prey.

Name: Omastar
FlavorText: Its heavy shell allowed it to reach only nearby food. This could be the reason it is extinct.

Name: Omastar
FlavorText: Sharp beaks ring its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

Name: Omastar
FlavorText: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a sturdy shell.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: While some say this species has gone extinct, Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common in some places.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: A Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It used the eyes on its back while hiding on the seafloor.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: This Pokémon became extinct everywhere, except in a few areas. It protects itself with its hard shell.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: This Pokémon thrived 300 million years ago. It’s said that living specimens can still be seen in a certain region—a rare sight.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: Kabuto is a Pokémon that has been regenerated from a fossil. However, in extremely rare cases, living examples have been discovered. The Pokémon has not changed at all for 300 million years.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: This Pokémon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: This Pokémon lived in ancient times. On rare occasions, it has been discovered as a living fossil.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: On rare occasions, some have been found as fossils which they became while hiding on the ocean floor.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: It is a POKéMON that has been regenerated from a fossil. However, in rare cases, living examples have been discovered. KABUTO have not changed for 300 million years.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: A POKéMON that was regenerated from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor long ago.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: Three hundred million years ago, it hid on the sea floor. It also has eyes on its back that glow.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: A POKéMON that was recovered from a fossil. It uses the eyes on its back while hiding on the sea floor.

Name: Kabuto
FlavorText: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokémon that inhabited warm seas.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: A slim and fast swimmer. It sliced its prey with its sharp sickles and drank the body fluids.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: It swims at speeds of roughly 29 knots, quickly closing in on its prey and slashing into them with its scythes to finish them off.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: Its body had begun to change so it could function on land. But it didn’t adapt in time and went extinct.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: A slim and fast swimmer. It slices its prey with its sharp sickles and drinks the body fluids.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: In the water, it tucks in its limbs to become more compact, then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: With sharp claws, this ferocious, ancient Pokémon rips apart prey and sucks their body fluids.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: KABUTOPS once swam underwater to hunt  for prey. It was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from changes in its gills and legs.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains their fluids.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: It swims freely through water. It catches prey with its scythe-like arms and drains the victim’s fluids.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: KABUTOPS swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The POKéMON was apparently evolving from being a water-dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: It was able to swim quickly through the water by compactly folding up its razor-sharp sickles.

Name: Kabutops
FlavorText: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: The power of Mega Evolution has completely restored its genes. The rocks on its body are harder than diamond.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: Mega Evolution awakened some dormant genes, bringing back the sharp rocks that once covered Aerodactyl’s entire body.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: It will attack anything that moves. Mega Evolution is a burden on its body, so it’s incredibly irritated.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: When it Mega Evolves, it becomes more vicious than ever before. Some say that’s because its excess of power is causing it pain.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: Part of its body has become stone. Some scholars claim that this is Aerodactyl’s true appearance.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: It’s a Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: Aerodactyl’s sawlike fangs can shred skin to tatters—even the skin of Steel-type Pokémon.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: A savage Pokémon that died out in ancient times. It was resurrected using DNA taken from amber.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: It flew through the open skies over the ancient continent as if they were its own. When it touched ground, its walk was weak and slow.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: Restored from DNA found in amber, this Pokémon exhibited ferocity that was greater than expected. Some casualties resulted.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: In ancient times, it ruled the skies. A widely accepted theory is that it went extinct due to a large meteor impact.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: A Pokémon from the age of the dinosaurs. It used its sawlike fangs to shred its prey before eating them.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: Aerodactyl is a Pokémon from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from genetic material extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies in ancient times.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: This vicious Pokémon is said to have flown in ancient skies while shrieking high-pitched cries.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: It was regenerated from a dinosaur’s genetic matter that was found in amber. It flies with high-pitched cries.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: A vicious Pokémon from the distant past, it appears to have flown by spreading its wings and gliding.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: AERODACTYL is a POKéMON from the age of dinosaurs. It was regenerated from DNA extracted from amber. It is imagined to have been the king of the skies.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: A ferocious, prehistoric POKéMON that goes for the enemy’s throat with its serrated, sawlike fangs.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: In prehistoric times, this POKéMON flew freely and fearlessly through the skies.

Name: Aerodactyl
FlavorText: A ferocious, prehistoric POKéMON that goes for the enemy’s throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Terrifyingly strong, this Pokémon is the size of a mountain—and moves about as much as one as well.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy has affected stray seeds and even pebbles that got stuck to Snorlax, making them grow to a huge size.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: This glutton appears in villages without warning and devours the entirety of their rice granaries—such occurrences have long been counted among the gravest of disasters.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: It stops eating only to sleep. It doesn’t feel full unless it eats nearly 900 pounds a day.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Its stomach can digest any kind of food, even if it happens to be moldy or rotten.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Will eat anything, even if the food happens to be a little moldy. It never gets an upset stomach.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: It has no interest in anything other than eating. Even if you climb up on its stomach while it’s napping, it doesn’t seem to mind at all!

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: It doesn’t do anything other than eat and sleep. When prompted to make a serious effort, though, it apparently displays awesome power.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: It eats nearly 900 pounds of food every day. It starts nodding off while eating—and continues to eat even while it’s asleep.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Its stomach is said to be incomparably strong. Even Muk’s poison is nothing more than a hint of spice on Snorlax’s tongue.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Snorlax’s typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile Pokémon that there are children who use its expansive belly as a place to play.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Its stomach’s digestive juices can dissolve any kind of poison. It can even eat things off the ground.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: What sounds like its cry may actually be its snores or the rumblings of its hungry belly.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: SNORLAX’s typical day consists of nothing more than eating and sleeping. It is such a docile POKéMON that there are children who use its big belly as a place to play.

Name: Snorlax
FlavorText: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: Its feather-like blades are composed of psychic energy and can shear through thick iron sheets as if they were paper.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: It’s said that this Pokémon’s beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: Articuno is a legendary bird Pokémon that can control ice. The flapping of its wings chills the air. As a result, it is said that when this Pokémon flies, snow will fall.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon, it chills moisture in the atmosphere to create snow while flying.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: The magnificent, seemingly translucent wings of this legendary bird Pokémon are said to be made of ice.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: One of the legendary bird POKéMON. With its long tail trailing behind, its flying form is magnificent.

Name: Articuno
FlavorText: Legendary bird POKéMON. As it flies through the sky, it cools the air, causing snow to fall.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: When its feathers rub together, they produce a crackling sound like the zapping of electricity. That’s why this Pokémon is called Zapdos.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It’s said that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together, lightning will fall immediately after.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. The Pokémon gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear only when a thundercloud parts into two halves.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: This legendary bird Pokémon causes savage thunderstorms by flapping its glittering wings.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: ZAPDOS is a legendary bird POKéMON that has the ability to control electricity. It usually lives in thunderclouds. It gains power if it is stricken by lightning bolts.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: One of the legendary bird POKéMON. While it is flying, it makes crackling and snapping sounds.

Name: Zapdos
FlavorText: Legendary bird POKéMON. They say lightning caused by the flapping of its wings causes summer storms.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s sinister, flame-like aura will consume the spirit of any creature it hits. Victims become burned-out shadows of themselves.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: There are stories of this Pokémon using its radiant, flame-cloaked wings to light up paths for those lost in the mountains.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: It’s one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: Moltres is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control fire. If this Pokémon is injured, it is said to dip its body in the molten magma of a volcano to burn and heal itself.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: It is said to be the legendary bird Pokémon of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flare of flames.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to bring early spring to the wintry lands it visits.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: This legendary Pokémon scatters embers with every flap of its wings. It is a thrilling sight to behold.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: MOLTRES is a legendary bird POKéMON that can control fire. If injured, it is said to dip its body in the molten magma of a volcano to burn and heal itself.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: One of the legendary bird POKéMON. Those seeing it are overwhelmed by its orange wings that seem to be on fire.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: Legendary bird POKéMON. It is said to migrate from the south along with the spring.

Name: Moltres
FlavorText: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: It is born large to start with. It repeatedly sheds its skin as it steadily grows longer.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: It is called the Mirage Pokémon because so few have seen it, but its shed skin has been found.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: This Pokémon was long considered to be no more than a myth. The small lump on a Dratini’s forehead is actually a horn that’s still coming in.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: Dratini dwells near bodies of rapidly flowing water, such as the plunge pools of waterfalls. As it grows, Dratini will shed its skin many times.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: Long thought to be a myth, this Pokémon’s existence was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: It sheds its skin—almost on a daily basis—and grows larger. Its skin is soft just after it’s been shed.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: It’s still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: It grows by molting repeatedly. Boots made from the tanned cast-off skin are a super luxury item.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: Dratini continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: This Pokémon is full of life energy. It continually sheds its skin and grows steadily larger.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: It is called the “Mirage Pokémon” because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: A DRATINI continually molts and sloughs off its old skin. It does so because the life energy within its body steadily builds to reach uncontrollable levels.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently, when a small colony was found living underwater.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: Even the young can exceed 6.5 feet in length. It grows larger by repeatedly shedding skin.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: The existence of this mythical POKéMON was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

Name: Dratini
FlavorText: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: It is called the divine Pokémon. When its entire body brightens slightly, the weather changes.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: This Pokémon gathers power in the orbs on its tail and controls the weather. When enshrouded by an aura, Dragonair has a mystical appearance.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in pristine oceans and lakes. It can control the weather, and it uses this power to fly into the sky, riding on the wind.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: According to a witness, its body was surrounded by a strange aura that gave it a mystical look.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: Some say that if you see it at the start of the year, flying through the sky and twisting its body, you’ll be healthy all year long.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: Lakes where Dragonair live are filled with offerings from people, because they believe this Pokémon is able to control the weather.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: From time immemorial, it has been venerated by agricultural peoples as an entity able to control the weather.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: It has long been thought that its crystalline orbs are imbued with the power to control the weather.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: Dragonair stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter weather conditions in its vicinity by discharging energy from the crystals on its neck and tail.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: A mystical Pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. It is said to have the ability to change the weather.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: Its crystalline orbs appear to give this Pokémon the power to freely control the weather.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: A DRAGONAIR stores an enormous amount of energy inside its body. It is said to alter the weather around it by loosing energy from the crystals on its neck and tail.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: It is said to live in seas and lakes. Even though it has no wings, it has been seen flying occasionally.

Name: Dragonair
FlavorText: A mystical POKéMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides wrecked ships to shore.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Sea Incarnate. Figureheads that resemble Dragonite decorate the bows of many ships.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It’s a kindhearted Pokémon. If it spots a drowning person or Pokémon, Dragonite simply must help them.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It is said that this Pokémon lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, these are only rumors.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: You’ll often hear tales of this kindhearted Pokémon rescuing people or Pokémon that are drowning.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It flies over raging seas as if they were nothing. Observing this, a ship’s captain dubbed this Pokémon “the sea incarnate.”

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: Incur the wrath of this normally calm Pokémon at your peril, because it will smash everything to smithereens before it’s satisfied.

Name: Dragonite
