FlavorText: This Pokémon saved a shipwrecked man, taking him to a remote island—a paradise occupied solely by Dragonite.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: This marine Pokémon has an impressive build that lets it freely fly over raging seas without trouble.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It is said that this Pokémon constantly flies over the immense seas and rescues drowning people.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It can circle the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted POKéMON that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: Only a very few people ever see this POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: DRAGONITE is capable of circling the globe in just sixteen hours. It is a kindhearted POKéMON that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: It is said that this POKéMON lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, it is only a rumor.

Name: Dragonite
FlavorText: An extremely rarely seen marine POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Despite its diminished size, its mental power has grown phenomenally. With a mere thought, it can smash a skyscraper to smithereens.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Psychic power has augmented its muscles. It has a grip strength of one ton and can sprint a hundred meters in two seconds flat!

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Mewtwo was created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: The research efforts of a certain scientist ultimately resulted in this Pokémon. Its powers are dedicated to battling.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Created from the DNA of Mew, this Pokémon is a dangerous combination of overwhelming power and a savage heart.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Mewtwo is a Pokémon that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans created this Pokémon’s body, they failed to endow Mewtwo with a compassionate heart.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: It usually remains motionless to conserve energy, so that it may unleash its full power in battle.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Because its battle abilities were raised to the ultimate level, it thinks only of defeating its foes.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: A POKéMON that was created by genetic manipulation. However, even though the scientific power of humans made its body, they failed to give it a warm heart.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: A POKéMON whose genetic code was repeatedly recombined for research. It turned vicious as a result.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: Said to rest quietly in an undiscovered cave, this POKéMON was created solely for battling.

Name: Mewtwo
FlavorText: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: This mythical Pokémon is said to be extinct, but sightings of it are still being reported to this day.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: It’s very intelligent and can use an incredible variety of moves. Many believe that all other Pokémon are descendants of this one.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: Mew is said to possess the genetic composition of all Pokémon. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: Apparently, it appears only to those people who are pure of heart and have a strong desire to see it.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: A MEW is said to possess the genes of all POKéMON. It is capable of making itself invisible at will, so it entirely avoids notice even if it approaches people.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: A POKéMON of South America that was thought to have been extinct. It is very intelligent and learns any move.

Name: Mew
FlavorText: Because it can learn any move, some people began research to see if it is the ancestor of all POKéMON.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the air’s temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up sun rays.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: Its pleasantly aromatic leaf has the ability to check humidity and temperature.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up sunrays.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: It waves its leaf around to keep foes at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, creating a friendly atmosphere that becalms the battlers.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun’s rays.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: Its pleasantly aromatic leaves have the ability to check the humidity and temperature.

Name: Chikorita
FlavorText: It loves to bask in the sunlight. It uses the leaf on its head to seek out warm places.

Name: Bayleef
FlavorText: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

Name: Bayleef
FlavorText: Bayleef’s neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

Name: Bayleef
FlavorText: A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.

Name: Bayleef
FlavorText: The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.

Name: Bayleef
FlavorText: A BAYLEEF’s neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each leaf is a small tree shoot. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

Name: Bayleef
FlavorText: The scent that wafts from the leaves on its neck causes anyone who smells it to become energetic.

Name: Meganium
FlavorText: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.

Name: Meganium
FlavorText: The fragrance of Meganium’s flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe’s fighting spirit.

Name: Meganium
FlavorText: Meganium’s breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

Name: Meganium
FlavorText: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.

Name: Meganium
FlavorText: The fragrance of a MEGANIUM’s flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, it gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe’s fighting spirit.

Name: Meganium
FlavorText: Anyone who stands beside it becomes refreshed, just as if they were relaxing in a sunny forest.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: Hails from the Johto region. Though usually curled into a ball due to its timid disposition, it harbors tremendous firepower.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: It is timid and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: It is timid, and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: It flares flames from its back to protect itself. The fire burns vigorously if the POKéMON is angry. When it is tired, it sputters with incomplete combustion.

Name: Cyndaquil
FlavorText: The fire that spouts from its back burns hottest when it is angry. The flaring flames intimidate foes.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: This creature’s fur is most mysterious—it is wholly impervious to the burning touch of flame. Should Quilava turn its back to you, take heed! Such a posture indicates a forthcoming attack.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns stronger as it prepares to fight.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns more strongly when it readies to fight.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: This Pokémon is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.

Name: Quilava
FlavorText: It intimidates foes with intense gusts of flames and superheated air. Its quick nimbleness lets it dodge attacks even while scorching an enemy.

Name: Typhlosion
FlavorText: Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. I believe its form has been influenced by the energy of the sacred mountain towering at Hisui’s center.

Name: Typhlosion
FlavorText: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.

Name: Typhlosion
FlavorText: Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

Name: Typhlosion
FlavorText: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

Name: Typhlosion
FlavorText: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

Name: Typhlosion
FlavorText: It can hide behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intense flames. TYPHLOSION create blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

Name: Typhlosion
FlavorText: When heat from its body causes the air around it to shimmer, this is a sign that it is ready to battle.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: It has a habit of biting everything with its well-developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile’s jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: It has the habit of biting anything with its developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: Despite its small body, TOTODILE’s jaws are very powerful. While it may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough strength to cause serious injury.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its TRAINER must be careful.

Name: Totodile
FlavorText: This rough critter chomps at any moving object it sees. Turning your back on it is not recommended.

Name: Croconaw
FlavorText: Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

Name: Croconaw
FlavorText: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

Name: Croconaw
FlavorText: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.

Name: Croconaw
FlavorText: It opens its huge jaws wide when attacking. If it loses any fangs while biting, they grow back in.

Name: Croconaw
FlavorText: Once its jaws clamp down on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like fishhooks, they become irremovably embedded.

Name: Croconaw
FlavorText: Once CROCONAW has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when  they have sunk in.

Name: Croconaw
FlavorText: The tips of its fangs are slanted backward. Once those fangs clamp down, the prey has no hope of escape.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: It is hard for it to support its weight out of water, so it sometimes gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: It opens its huge mouth to intimidate enemies. In battle, it runs using its thick and powerful hind legs to charge the foe with incredible speed.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears up its victim.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: Although it has a massive body, its powerful hind legs enable it to move quickly, even on the ground.

Name: Sentret
FlavorText: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.

Name: Sentret
FlavorText: When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

Name: Sentret
FlavorText: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

Name: Sentret
FlavorText: When acting as a lookout, it warns others of danger by screeching and hitting the ground with its tail.

Name: Sentret
FlavorText: A very cautious Pokémon, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.

Name: Sentret
FlavorText: They take turns standing guard when it is time to sleep. The sentry awakens the others if it senses danger. If one becomes separated, it turns sleepless with fear.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: There is no telling where the tail begins. Despite its short legs, it is quick and likes to chase RATTATA.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: A FURRET has a very slim build. When under attack, it can squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, it is very nimble and fleet.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: There is no telling where its tail begins. Despite its short legs, it is quick at hunting RATTATA.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: It lives in narrow burrows that fit its slim body. The deeper the nests go, the more mazelike they become.

Name: Furret
FlavorText: There is no telling where the tail begins. Despite its short legs, it is quick at hunting RATTATA.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It switches its standing foot so quickly that the switch can’t be seen. It cries at the same time every day.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It always stands on one foot. Even when attacked, it does not brace itself using both feet.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It begins to hoot at the same time every day. Some Trainers use them in place of clocks.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It cries out at the same time every day. A long time ago, people cherished it and considered it a divine messenger sent to tell the time.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: Every day, it tilts its head in the same rhythm. A long time ago, people raised these Pokémon to serve as clocks.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: Hoothoot has an internal organ that senses and tracks the earth’s rotation. Using this special organ, this Pokémon begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It marks time precisely. Some countries consider it to be a wise friend, versed in the world’s ways.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It switches its standing foot so quickly, it can’t be seen. It cries at the same time every day.

Name: Hoothoot
FlavorText: It has an internal organ that senses the earth’s rotation. Using this special organ, a HOOTHOOT begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: If it flips its head upside down, it’s a sign that it is engaged in very complex thinking.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: Its eyes are special. They can pick out objects as long as there is the tiniest amount of light.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: When it turns its head entirely upside down, you know it’s troubled by something. If you don’t leave it be, it will peck you.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: With eyes that can see in pitch-darkness, it never lets its prey escape. Some even call it “the emperor of dark nights.”

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: Noctowl never fails at catching prey in darkness. This Pokémon owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft, supple wings that make no sound in flight.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: It unfailingly catches prey in darkness. NOCTOWL owe their success to superior vision that allows them to see in minimal light, and to their supple and silent wings.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: NOCTOWL never fails at catching prey in darkness. This POKéMON owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft,  supple wings that make no sound in flight.

Name: Noctowl
FlavorText: Its extremely soft feathers make no sound in flight. It silently sneaks up on prey without being detected.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: It’s so timid that it can’t move unless it’s with a swarm. It conveys its feelings through scent.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: These very cowardly Pokémon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: This Pokémon is very sensitive to cold. In the warmth of Alola, it appears quite lively.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: They communicate with one another using bodily fluids that give off odors. When they’re angry, their odor smells sour.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: Ledyba secretes an aromatic fluid from where its legs join its body. This fluid is used for communicating with others. This Pokémon conveys its feelings to others by altering the fluid’s scent.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: When the weather turns cold, lots of Ledyba gather from everywhere to cluster and keep each other warm.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: It is so timid, it can’t move if it isn’t with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: It is very timid. It will be afraid to move if it is alone. But it will be active if it is in a group.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: LEDYBA communicate using a fluid that they secrete from where the legs join the body. They are said to convey feelings to others by altering the fluid’s scent.

Name: Ledyba
FlavorText: When the weather turns cold, numerous LEDYBA gather from everywhere to cluster and keep each other warm.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: It’s said that the patterns on its back are related to the stars in the night sky, but the details of that relationship remain unclear.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: In battle, it throws punches with all four arms. The power of each individual blow is piddly, so it aims to win by quantity rather than quality.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: While it’s believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokémon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this—the Pokémon uses the light of the stars as its energy.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live many LEDIAN. For good reason, they use the light of the stars as energy.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: The star patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live LEDIAN in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this - the POKéMON uses the light of the stars as its energy.

Name: Ledian
FlavorText: In the daytime when it gets warm, it curls up inside a big leaf and drifts off into a deep slumber.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong thread. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: Although the poison from its fangs isn’t that strong, it’s potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: With threads from its mouth, it fashions sturdy webs that won’t break even if you set a rock on them.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: Some fishermen weave its sturdy thread into nets to catch fish Pokémon.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: It waits intently until its preferred prey, Cutiefly, gets caught in its web. In fact, it’s quite a patient Pokémon.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: The web spun by Spinarak can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that this Pokémon can determine what kind of prey is touching its web just by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web’s strands.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: It spins a web using fine--but durable--thread. It then waits patiently for prey to be trapped.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong silk. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: The web it spins can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that a SPINARAK determines its prey by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web.

Name: Spinarak
FlavorText: If prey becomes ensnared in its nest of spun string, it waits motionlessly until it becomes dark.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: Every night, it wanders around in search of prey, whose movements it restrains by spewing threads before it bites into them with its fangs.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: It spins thread from both its rear and its mouth. Then it wraps its prey up in thread and sips their bodily fluids at its leisure.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: There are some areas where people use the string Ariados spins for their own weaving. The resulting cloth is popular for its strength.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: Ariados’s feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. This Pokémon constricts the foe with thin and strong silk webbing.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It’s hard to tell which end is which.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: A single strand of a special string is endlessly spun out of its rear. The string leads back to its nest.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: Its feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. It constricts its foe with thin and strong silk webbing.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It is hard to tell which end is which.

Name: Ariados
FlavorText: Rather than making a nest in one specific spot, it wanders in search of food after darkness falls.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Its hind limbs have become another set of wings. Crobat expertly maneuvers its four wings to dart in exquisite fashion through even the most confined caves without losing any speed.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: This Pokémon gained vastly enhanced flying capabilities after its legs became wings.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Having four wings enables it to fly faster and more quietly. It turns active when the night comes.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: This Pokémon flaps its four wings skillfully. Crobat can fly through cramped caves without needing to slow down.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target’s neck.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: It feeds on the blood of living people and Pokémon. If it can’t drink any blood for even a short while, it becomes weak and unable to fly.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Its fangs are so sharp, if it bites you in the dark and sucks your blood, you won’t notice any pain or realize you’ve been bitten.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Silent and swift in its four-winged flight, it bites down on its prey before they realize what’s happening. In a heartbeat, it drains their blood.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Both its legs became wings, and as a result, it can’t move well on the ground. All it can do is crawl around.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Crobat sneaks up on its intended prey using wings that barely make a sound. This Pokémon rests by hanging on a tree branch with its rear legs that serve as wings.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: If this Pokémon is flying by fluttering only a pair of wings on either the forelegs or hind legs, it’s proof that Crobat has been flying a long distance. It switches the wings it uses if it is tired.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Having four wings allows it to fly more quickly and quietly so it can sneak up on prey without its noticing.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: It flies so silently through the dark on its four wings that it may not be noticed even when nearby.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: The transformation of its legs into wings made it better at flying, but more clumsy at walking.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: The development of wings on its legs enables it to fly fast but also makes it tough to stop and rest.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: A Pokémon that gained vastly enhanced flying performance by having its legs turn into wings.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: Over the course of evolution, its hind legs turned into wings. By alternately resting its front and rear wings, it can fly all day without having to stop.

Name: Crobat
FlavorText: As a result of its pursuit of faster, yet more silent flight, a new set of wings grew on its hind legs.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It discharges positive and negative electricity from the tips of its antennae to shock its foes.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Chinchou blink their shining antennae at one another to claim their respective turf.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Its two antennae glow softly to lure in prey, making it a useful Pokémon for night fishing.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It lives in the depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Its two antennae were originally fins. It discharges electricity to stun its prey before attacking.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Chinchou’s two antennas are filled with cells that generate strong electricity. This Pokémon’s cells create so much electrical power, it even makes itself tingle slightly.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Chinchou lets loose positive and negative electrical charges from its two antennas to make its prey faint. This Pokémon flashes its electric lights to exchange signals with others.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: When it senses danger, it discharges positive and negative electricity from its two antennae. It lives in depths beyond sunlight’s reach.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed the Deep-Sea Star.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea’s surface from a depth of over three miles.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: It lives far down in the depths of the ocean. It blinds its prey with light, using the moment they’re dazzled to swallow them whole.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: When the bacteria living inside its antennae absorb Lanturn’s bodily fluids, a strong luminescent effect is produced.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Should you peer into the ocean at night and see a light shining like the stars, that is Lanturn.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn is known to emit light. If you peer down into the dark sea from a ship at night, you can sometimes see this Pokémon’s light rising from the depths where it swims. It gives the sea an appearance of a starlit night.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn is nicknamed “the deep-sea star” for its illuminated antenna. This Pokémon produces light by causing a chemical reaction between bacteria and its bodily fluids inside the antenna.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed “The Deep-Sea Star.”

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: The light-emitting orbs on its back are very bright. They are formed from a part of its dorsal fin. This POKéMON illuminates the inky darkness of deep seas.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light, then swallows the immobilized prey in a single gulp.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: This POKéMON uses the bright part of its body, which changed from a dorsal fin, to lure prey.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: Despite this Pokémon’s cute appearance, those who want to live with one should prepare to be on the receiving end of its electric jolts.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: It is unskilled at storing electric power. Any kind of shock causes it to discharge energy spontaneously.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: Pichu stores electricity in the sacs on its cheeks but discharges it inadvertently when agitated or excited. Being yet immature, the Pokémon’s handling of electricity is rather inept.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: It plays with others by touching tails and setting off sparks. This appears to be a test of courage.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: The electric sacs on its cheeks are still small. They cannot store much electricity yet.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: The electric sacs in its cheeks are small. If even a little electricity leaks, it becomes shocked.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: It has electric sacs in its cheeks. When they’re fully charged, Pichu plays very energetically.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: It still can’t use electricity well. When it’s surprised or excited, it discharges electricity unintentionally.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: It is not yet skilled at controlling electricity. If you take your eyes off it, it may shock itself.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: When Pichu plays with others, it may short out electricity with another Pichu, creating a shower of sparks. In that event, this Pokémon will begin crying, startled by the flash of sparks.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: Pichu charges itself with electricity more easily on days with thunderclouds or when the air is very dry. You can hear the crackling of static electricity coming off this Pokémon.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: The electric pouches on its cheeks are still small. They cannot store much electricity yet.

Name: Pichu
FlavorText: It is still inept at retaining electricity. When it is startled, it discharges power accidentally. It gets better at holding power as it grows older.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: In silhouette, they resemble twinkling starlight. When shooting stars rain from the night sky, Cleffa gather in numbers and dance as though they are indeed incarnations of the stars.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: Many appear when the night skies are filled with shooting stars. They disappear with sunrise.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: Its silhouette is like a star. It is believed to arrive riding on shooting stars.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: Said to have ridden here on a shooting star, Cleffa seem to appear in places where meteorites have struck in the past.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: On nights with many shooting stars, they gather in packs and dance in circles. If you should see them, something good will happen!

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: Because of its silhouette, it’s believed to be a star reborn. For some reason, it loves Minior.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: On late nights illuminated by shooting stars, it gazes intently skyward, as if thinking of its home.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: On nights with many shooting stars, Cleffa can be seen dancing in a ring. They dance through the night and stop only at the break of day, when these Pokémon quench their thirst with the morning dew.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: It is often seen when shooting stars fill the night skies. It’s said to arrive riding on a shooting star.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: When numerous meteors illuminate the night sky, sightings of CLEFFA strangely increase.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: On nights with many shooting stars, CLEFFA can be seen dancing in a ring. They dance until daybreak, when they quench their thirst with the morning dew.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: If the impact site of a meteorite is found, this POKéMON is certain to be within the immediate area.

Name: Cleffa
FlavorText: Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: It likes to sing but is not yet good at it. With praise and encouragement, it will get better little by little.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Its body has a faintly sweet scent and is bouncy and soft. If it bounces even once, it cannot stop.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: It has a soft and bouncy body. Once it starts bouncing, it becomes impossible to stop.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Taking advantage of the softness of its body, Igglybuff moves as if bouncing. Its body turns a deep pink when its temperature rises.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Igglybuff loves to sing. Its marshmallow-like body gives off a faint sweet smell.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Left to its own devices, it will constantly practice singing. You should make it take a break so it doesn’t hurt its throat.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: It’s always practicing its singing because it wants to improve. Even when it’s asleep, it keeps singing in its dreams!

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: It moves by bouncing along. As it moves a lot, it sweats, and its body gives off a sweet aroma.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Igglybuff has a soft and plushy body that feels very much like a marshmallow. From this body wafts a gently sweet fragrance that soothes and calms the emotions of its foes.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Igglybuff’s vocal cords are not sufficiently developed. It would hurt its throat if it were to sing too much. This Pokémon gargles with freshwater from a clean stream.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Instead of walking with its short legs, it moves around by bouncing on its soft, tender body.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Its extremely flexible and elastic body makes it bounce continuously--anytime, anywhere.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: Its soft and pliable body is very bouncy. When it sings continuously with all its might, its body steadily turns a deepening pink color.

Name: Igglybuff
FlavorText: IGGLYBUFF’s vocal chords are not sufficiently developed. It would hurt its throat if it were to sing too much. This POKéMON gargles with freshwater from a clean stream.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: This ovate creature is frequently mistaken for a moving egg when encountered out in the fields or in the mountains. Its guileless smile soothes the soul.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: Its shell is said to be stuffed with happiness that it shares with kindhearted people.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: It is considered to be a symbol of good luck. Its shell is said to be filled with happiness.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: It transforms the kindness and joy of others into happiness, which it stores in its shell.

Name: Togepi
FlavorText: As its energy, it uses the feelings of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and POKéMON. It stores up happy feelings in its shell, then shares them out.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: No records exist of Togetic being seen in the wilds. Rumors abound that it evolves under the loving care of a trusted human companion, upon whom the Pokémon then bestows great joy.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: It is said to appear in front of kindly people to scatter a glowing down called joy dust.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: To share its happiness, it flies around the world seeking kind-hearted people.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: To share its happiness, it flies around the world seeking kindhearted people.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: It is said to appear in front of kindly people to scatter a glowing down called “joy dust.”

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: It is said to be a POKéMON that brings good fortune. When it spots someone who is pure of heart, a TOGETIC appears and shares its happiness with that person.

Name: Togetic
FlavorText: Although it does not flap its wings very much, it can stay up in the air as it tags along after its trainer.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: Because its wings aren’t yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: The look in its eyes gives the impression that it’s carefully observing you. If you approach it, Natu will hop away.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: Although it still can’t fly, its jumping power is outstanding. It jumps way up into trees and plucks the buds from the branches.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: Natu has a highly developed jumping ability. The Pokémon flaps and leaps onto tree branches that are taller than grown-up people to pick at the tree’s new shoots.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: Natu cannot fly because its wings are not yet fully grown. If your eyes meet with this Pokémon’s eyes, it will stare back intently at you. But if you move even slightly, it will hop away to safety.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

Name: Natu
FlavorText: It runs up short trees that grow on the savanna to peck at new shoots. A NATU’s eyes look as if they are always observing something.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: While it can see the future, it has no desire to change it, which is probably why it remains motionless at all times.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: It’s said that while this Pokémon has the power to predict the future, it’s not powerful enough to change the future it sees.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: Xatu is known to stand motionless while staring at the sun all day long. Some people revere it as a mystical Pokémon out of their belief that Xatu is in possession of the power to see into the future.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: Xatu stands rooted and still in one spot all day long. People believe that this Pokémon does so out of fear of the terrible things it has foreseen in the future.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: Once it begins to meditate at sunrise, the entire day will pass before it will move again.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: In South America, it is said that its right eye sees the future and its left eye views the past.

Name: Xatu
FlavorText: It has the enigmatic power of foreseeing the future. Some people in different lands have long believed that XATU are emissaries from another world.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: Its fluffy coat doubles in size when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You’ll want to pet it because it’s cute, but if you use your bare hand, you’ll get a painful shock.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: Clothing made from Mareep’s fleece is easily charged with static electricity, so a special process is used on it.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: Mareep’s fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: When cold weather increases static electricity, its wool doubles in size and the tip of its tail glows slightly.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: Its fluffy wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more energy is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.

Name: Mareep
FlavorText: MAREEP’s fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail grows.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: Because of its rubbery, electricity-resistant skin, it can store lots of electricity in its fur.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won’t grow.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. Flaaffy can fire hair that zaps on impact.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: In the places on its body where fleece doesn’t grow, its skin is rubbery and doesn’t conduct electricity. Those spots are safe to touch.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: Flaaffy’s wool quality changes so that it can generate a high amount of static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare and slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: Its fluffy fleece easily stores electricity. Its rubbery hide keeps it from being electrocuted.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: Not even downy wool will grow on its rubbery, nonconductive patches of skin that prevent electrical shock.

Name: Flaaffy
FlavorText: Its fleece quality changes to generate strong static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare, slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: Massive amounts of energy intensely stimulated Ampharos’s cells, apparently awakening its long-sleeping dragon’s blood.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: Excess energy from Mega Evolution stimulates its genes, and the wool it had lost grows in again.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean’s surface.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the light from this Pokémon’s tail.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: The light from its tail can be seen from space. This is why you can always tell exactly where it is, which is why it usually keeps the light off.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: The tail’s tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: The tip of its tail shines so brightly it can be used to send sea-navigation beacons to distant foreign shores.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail’s light.

Name: Ampharos
FlavorText: It gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used its light to send signals back and forth with others far away.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Bellossom gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: A Bellossom grows flowers more beautifully if it has evolved from a smelly Gloom—the more stinky the better. At night, this Pokémon closes its petals and goes to sleep.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: When Bellossom gets exposed to plenty of sunlight, the leaves ringing its body begin to spin around. This Pokémon’s dancing is renowned in the southern lands.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Bellossom gather at times and seem to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Its flower petals deepen in color through exposure to sunlight. When cloudy weather persists, it does a dance that is thought to be a ritual for summoning the sun.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: A BELLOSSOM grows flowers more beautifully if it has evolved from a smelly GLOOM - the stinkier the better. At night, this POKéMON closes its petals and goes to sleep.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: When these dance together, their petals rub against each other, making pretty, relaxing sounds.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it’s fine even in rivers with strong currents.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Using its tail as a float, it dives underwater. It likes eating plants that grow in riverbeds.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Even after Marill swims in a cold sea, its water- repellent fur dries almost as soon as Marill leaves the water. That’s why this Pokémon is never cold.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses its round tail as a float. The ball of Marill’s tail is filled with nutrients that have been turned into an oil.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: When fishing for food at the edge of a fast-running stream, Marill wraps its tail around the trunk of a tree. This Pokémon’s tail is flexible and configured to stretch.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Marill’s oil-filled tail acts much like a life preserver. If you see just its tail bobbing on the water’s surface, it’s a sure indication that this Pokémon is diving beneath the water to feed on aquatic plants.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry, even when it plays in the water.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The oil-filled end of its tail floats on water. It keeps Marill from drowning even in a strong current.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The tip of its tail, which contains oil that is lighter than water, lets it swim without drowning.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Using its tail as a float, it dives underwater. It likes eating plants that grow on river bottoms.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Its body is covered with water-repellent fur. Because of the fur, it can swim through water at high speed without being slowed by the water’s resistance.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It lives in rivers and lakes. In water, its coloring and patterns trick the vision of foes.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: These Pokémon create air-filled bubbles. When Azurill play in rivers, Azumarill will cover them with these bubbles.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It spends most of its time in the water. On sunny days, Azumarill floats on the surface of the water and sunbathes.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Azumarill can make balloons out of air. It makes these air balloons if it spots a drowning Pokémon. The air balloons enable the Pokémon in trouble to breathe.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Azumarill’s long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it’s in the water.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It lives in water virtually all day long. Its body color and pattern act as camouflage that makes it tough for enemies to spot in water.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: By keeping still and listening intently, it can even tell what is in wild, fast-moving rivers.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo’s extreme aversion to water merits special note.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: It stands along paths pretending to be a tree. If it starts raining, it seems to disappear.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: Though it looks like a tree, its body is actually more like rock or stone. The Pokémon is very weak to water.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it’s a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: The result of its holding the same pose all the time is arms that have become supple yet strong.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: It’s so popular with the elderly that there’s a magazine devoted to this Pokémon. Fans obsess over the particular length and angle of its arms.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: Apparently, the larger the green parts of this Pokémon, the more collectors value it. It’s a particular favorite among elderly people.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: To avoid attack, it mimics a tree. It will run off if splashed with water, which it hates.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pokémon is easily identified as a fake during the winter.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: Despite appearing to be a tree, its body is closer to rocks and stones. It is very weak to water.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: It mimics a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. But since its forelegs remain green throughout the year, it is easily identified as a fake in the winter.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears to be closer to a rock than a plant.

Name: Sudowoodo
FlavorText: SUDOWOODO camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because the forelegs remain green throughout the year, the POKéMON is easily identified as a fake during the winter.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: A group of Poliwag and Poliwhirl will form with a Politoed as the leader. Politoed’s cries make the Pokémon of the group obey.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The cry of a male is louder than that of a female. Male Politoed with deep, menacing voices find more popularity with the opposite gender.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The longer and more luxurious the curled hair on its head, the greater the number of Poliwag and Poliwhirl that will obey it.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: Although its cries sound like screams, a composer created a beautiful ballad that was influenced by the sounds.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: It’s the leader of Poliwag and Poliwhirl. When Politoed roars, they all cower in fear.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: They gather on moonlit nights to form a large chorus. Their cries sound angry and not at all pleasant, but they are certainly distinctive.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The curled hair on Politoed’s head is proof of its status as a king. It is said that the longer and more curled the hair, the more respect this Pokémon earns from its peers.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make Poliwag obey.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The curled hair on its head proves its status as a king. It is said that the longer and curlier the hair, the more respect it earns from its peers.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: When it expands its throat to croak out a tune, nearby POLIWAG and POLIWHIRL gather immediately.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found practically everywhere. This is because the wind carries this species all over the world.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: They are blown adrift by winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. But they do enjoy gentle breezes.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: This POKéMON drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, a HOPPIP links leaves with others to prepare against being blown away.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: It can be carried away on even the gentlest breeze. It may even float all the way to the next town.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: When the weather grows cold, Skiploom’s flower closes and the Pokémon cannot photosynthesize, so it flies away to warmer regions.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon’s head.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: Skiploom’s flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: It blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees F. Because its flower’s blooming changes with the temperature, it is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: SKIPLOOM’s flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees F. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this POKéMON is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: As soon as it rains, it closes its flower and hides in the shade of a tree to avoid getting wet.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Beware its cotton spores. If you accidentally breathe them in, you’ll be racked with coughs and itchiness.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Drifts on seasonal winds and spreads its cotton-like spores all over the world to make more offspring.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores--it can even float around the world.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: JUMPLUFF ride warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. This POKéMON lands when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: It drifts on seasonal winds and spreads its cotton-like spores all over the world  to make more offspring.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: It lives atop giant trees. It wraps its tail around a branch so it won’t fall off while asleep.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: It uses its tail to pluck fruits that are out of reach. Its tail is more adept than its real hands.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: It searches for prey from the tops of trees. When it spots its favorite food, Bounsweet, Aipom gets excited and pounces.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: As it did more and more with its tail, its hands became clumsy. It makes its nest high in the treetops.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: Aipom’s tail ends in a hand-like appendage that can be cleverly manipulated. However, because the Pokémon uses its tail so much, its real hands have become rather clumsy.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: It lives high among the treetops. It can use its tail as freely and cleverly as its hands.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: Its tail ends with a dexterous, handlike appendage. However, because it uses the tail so much, AIPOM’s real hands have become rather clumsy.

Name: Aipom
FlavorText: It uses its tail to hang on to tree branches. It uses its momentum to swing from one branch to another.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it’s weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: They may suddenly fall out of the sky in the morning. In the year following a cold summer, their population explodes.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It may plummet from the sky. If attacked by a Spearow, it will violently shake its leaves.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: SUNKERN try to minimize movement to conserve the nutrients they have stored in their bodies for evolution. They will not eat, subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will violently shake its leaves.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: SUNKERN tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing,  subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: As the hot season approaches, the petals on this Pokémon’s face become more vivid and lively.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: It converts sunlight into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: SUNFLORA convert solar energy into nutrition. They are highly active in the warm daytime but suddenly stop moving as soon as the sun sets.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: Its frail wings are so thin that one can see clear through them. However, during flight these wings exhibit the power to churn air with force enough to launch a house skyward.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without the Pokémon moving its head. It won’t miss prey— even those behind it.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won’t miss prey--even those behind it.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: By flapping its wings at high speed, it can fly freely through the air. Even sudden stops are no problem.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: It can hover in one spot by flapping its wings at high speed. It flits about to guard its territory.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: Its large eyes can scan 360 degrees. It looks in all directions to seek out insects as its prey.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: It can see 360 degrees without moving its eyes. It is a great flier capable of making sudden stops and turning midair to quickly chase down targeted prey.

Name: Yanma
FlavorText: It can see in all directions without moving its big eyes, helping it spot attackers and food right away.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: It’s dangerous for Wooper to travel alone. They line up in groups of three or four and help each other as they walk around the wetlands.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: After losing a territorial struggle, Wooper began living on land. The Pokémon changed over time, developing a poisonous film to protect its body.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: It lives in cold water, half burying itself in mud at the bottom to sleep.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: WOOPER usually live in water but come out onto land seeking food occasionally. On land, they coat their bodies with a gooey, toxic film.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: A mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it barehanded will cause a shooting pain.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: A dim-witted Pokémon. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head into boats or rocks while swimming.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: It has a sluggish nature. It lies at the river’s bottom, waiting for prey to stray into its mouth.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: Its body is always slimy. It often bangs its head on the river bottom as it swims but seems not to care.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: This carefree Pokémon has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: A QUAGSIRE hunts by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in. Because it doesn’t move, it does not get very hungry.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy’s actions.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent’s next move.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Wields an arcane power with which it can predict the weather and even people’s thoughts. When bathed in sunshine, the scarlet orb on its brow glows and builds energy.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Its fur has the look and feel of velvet. The orb on its forehead glows when it uses psychic power.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: By reading air currents, it can predict things such as the weather or its foe’s next move.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Psychic power builds up in the orb on its forehead as it bathes in the sunshine. Espeon is not good at battling at night.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Although it originally had no powers at all, people say its precognitive faculties were awakened by its need to protect itself.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: It can instantaneously sense its opponent’s movements by feeling air currents with its fine fur.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Espeon is extremely loyal to any Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is said that this Pokémon developed its precognitive powers to protect its Trainer from harm.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Its fur is so sensitive, it can feel minute shifts in the air and predict the weather...and its foes’ thoughts.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Its fur is so sensitive, it can sense minute shifts in the air and predict the weather.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: Its fur has the look and feel of velvet. The orb on its forehead glows when it uses psycho-power.

Name: Espeon
FlavorText: An ESPEON is extremely loyal to any TRAINER it considers to be worthy. It is said to have developed precognitive powers to protect its TRAINER from harm.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: It is most active in the wee hours of the night, when moonlight bathes the land. Its large eyes can pierce the darkness and perceive prey with absolute clarity.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: The light of the moon changed Eevee’s genetic structure. It lurks in the darkness, waiting for prey.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: On the night of a full moon, or when it gets excited, the ring patterns on its body glow yellow.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: When this Pokémon becomes angry, its pores secrete a poisonous sweat, which it sprays at its opponent’s eyes.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: It lurks in the dark of night looking for prey. At the moment it pounces, the rings on its body glow dimly but ominously.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: This Pokémon is nocturnal. Even in total darkness, its large eyes can spot its prey clearly!

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: With its black fur, it blends into the darkness. It bides its time, and when prey appears, this Pokémon goes for its throat, and then eats it.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: Umbreon evolved as a result of exposure to the moon’s waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it’s filled with a mysterious power.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: The light of the moon changed Eevee’s genetic structure. It lurks in darkness for prey.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: When agitated, this Pokémon protects itself by spraying poisonous sweat from its pores.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: UMBREON evolved from exposure to the moon’s energy pulses. It lurks in darkness and waits for its foes to move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.

Name: Umbreon
FlavorText: When darkness falls, the rings on its body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it, then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: Widely shunned as a bearer of ill fortune. Upon crossing paths with this creature, I’ve been told one must chant “Workrum, Workrum—bad luck, don’t come” as a protective incantation.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: It appears near travelers to lure them into deep forests. It is said to bring misfortune.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: It is believed that seeing this Pokémon at night will bring about ominous occurrences.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow’s presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: It has a weakness for shiny things. It’s been known to sneak into the nests of Gabite—noted collectors of jewels—in search of treasure.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: Seen as a symbol of bad luck, it’s generally disliked. Yet it gives presents—objects that sparkle or shine—to Trainers it’s close to.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: They awaken at dusk and take wing in the twilight, leading to the expression, “Get home before the Murkrow fly.”

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: Murkrow was feared and loathed as the alleged bearer of ill fortune. This Pokémon shows strong interest in anything that sparkles or glitters. It will even try to steal rings from women.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: It hides any shiny object it finds in a secret location. Murkrow and Meowth loot one another’s stashes.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: It is said that when chased, it lures its attacker onto dark mountain trails where the foe will get lost.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: It appears near travelers to lure them into deep forests. It is said to carry misfortune.

Name: Murkrow
FlavorText: MURKROW were feared as the alleged bearers of ill fortune. It shows strong interest in anything that sparkles. It will even try to steal rings from women.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: While chanting strange spells, this Pokémon combines its internal toxins with what it’s eaten, creating strange potions.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: A combination of toxins and the shock of evolving has increased Shellder’s intelligence to the point that Shellder now controls Slowking.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke’s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of internationally recognized scientists.

Name: Slowking
