FlavorText: Slowking can solve any problem presented to it, but no one can understand a thing Slowking says.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Miraculously, this former Slowpoke’s latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It’s called “the sage of the sea.” It engages in battles of wits with Oranguru, but the result is usually a draw.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It’s constantly coming up with new ideas that would change the world, but as soon as it hits upon a new idea, it forgets it.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: This Pokémon is so famed for its intellect that a proverb still persists in some regions: “When in doubt, ask Slowking.”

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It undertakes research every day to solve the mysteries of the world. However, it apparently forgets everything if the SHELLDER on its head comes off.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Every time it yawns, SHELLDER injects more poison into it. The poison makes it more intelligent.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It loves to bite and yank people’s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: This Pokémon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It conceals itself in darkness, sending chills up travelers’ spines with its childlike weeping. As it observes the frightened travelers with glee, the red orbs upon its chest let off an eerie light.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It gets nourishment from fear that it absorbs into its red orbs. During the daytime, it sleeps in the shadows.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It loves to sneak up on people late at night and startle them with its shrieking cry.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: What makes it happy is imitating the voices of weeping people and scaring everyone. It doesn’t deal well with folks who aren’t easily frightened.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: What gives meaning to its life is surprising others. If you set your ear against the red orbs around its neck, you can hear shrieking.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: If you hear a sobbing sound emanating from a vacant room, it’s undoubtedly a bit of mischief from Misdreavus.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It will use any means necessary to frighten people and absorb their life energy. It practices constantly to hone its skill in causing fear.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. The Pokémon apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fearful feelings of foes and turn them into nutrition.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It likes playing mischievous tricks, such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It gets nourishment from fear that it absorbs into its red orbs. In daytime, it sleeps in darkness.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: A Pokémon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It loves to sneak up on people late at night, then startle them with its shrieklike cry.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: A MISDREAVUS frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. It apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fear of foes as its nutrition.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It likes playing mischievous tricks such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

Name: Misdreavus
FlavorText: It loves to watch people it’s scared. It frightens them by screaming loudly or appearing suddenly.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: It is hard to believe these strangely shaped Pokémon are truly living creatures. I’ve pointed out that the species’ many forms resemble writing from other lands; no one will take me seriously.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: They seem to communicate among each other telepathically. They are always found stuck on walls.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: Because the Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether written language or Unown came first.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: When alone, nothing happens. However, if there are two or more, an odd power is said to emerge.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tablets. It is said that the two are somehow related.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: This POKéMON is shaped like ancient text characters. Although research is ongoing, it is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various UNOWN.

Name: Unown
FlavorText: Because different types of UNOWN exist, it is said that they must have a variety of abilities.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. This behavior is said to be proof that its tail hides a secret.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: Wobbuffet does nothing but endure attacks—it won’t attack on its own. However, it won’t endure an attack on its tail. When that happens, the Pokémon will try to take the foe with it using Destiny Bond.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: If two or more Wobbuffet meet, they will turn competitive and try to outdo each other’s endurance. However, they may try to see which one can endure the longest without food. Trainers need to beware of this habit.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to build up its counterstrike.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: Usually docile, a WOBBUFFET strikes back ferociously if its black tail is attacked. It makes its lair in caves where it waits for nightfall.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: WOBBUFFET does nothing but endure attacks - it won’t attack on its own. However, it won’t endure an attack on its tail. When that happens, the POKéMON will try to take the foe with it using DESTINY BOND.

Name: Wobbuffet
FlavorText: In order to conceal its black tail, it lives in a dark cave and only moves about at night.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Girafarig’s tail has a small head. It instinctively bites at any foe that approaches the Pokémon from behind.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Though very small, the brain in its tail is still considered an important organ because it emits powerful psychic energy.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: While it sleeps, the head on its tail keeps watch. The tail doesn’t need to sleep.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Its tail has a separate small brain. The tail bites to repel any foe trying to sneak up on the Pokémon from behind.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Girafarig’s rear head contains a tiny brain that is too small for thinking. However, the rear head doesn’t need to sleep, so it can keep watch over its surroundings 24 hours a day.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Girafarig’s rear head also has a brain, but it is small. The rear head attacks in response to smells and sounds. Approaching this Pokémon from behind can cause the rear head to suddenly lash out and bite.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: The head on its tail contains a small brain. It can instinctively fight even while facing backward.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Its tail, which also contains a small brain, may bite on its own if it notices an alluring smell.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Its tail also has a small brain. It bites to repel any foe trying to sneak up on it from behind.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: A GIRAFARIG is an herbivore--it eats grass and tree shoots. While it is eating, its tail makes chewing and swallowing motions as if it were also eating.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent and bite.

Name: Girafarig
FlavorText: When it is in danger, its tail uses some sort of mysterious powers to drive away the enemy.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn’t bother it.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: It sticks tree bark to itself with its saliva, making itself thicker and larger. Elderly Pineco are ridiculously huge.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: Motionless, it hangs from trees, waiting for its bug Pokémon prey to come to it. Its favorite in Alola is Cutiefly.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: It hangs and waits for flying insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: A PINECO hangs from a tree branch and waits for prey. While eating, if it is disturbed by someone shaking its tree, it falls on the ground and suddenly explodes.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The extra weight doesn’t bother it.

Name: Pineco
FlavorText: It hangs and waits for flying-insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: It’s usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: It is encased in a steel shell. Forretress’s eyes peer out, but what lies within this Pokémon’s shell is unknown.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: In the moment that it gulps down its prey, the inside of its shell is exposed, but to this day, no one has ever seen that sight.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: When something approaches it, it fires off fragments of its steel shell in attack. This is not a conscious action but a conditioned reflex.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell’s inside cannot be seen.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: It keeps itself inside its steel shell. The shell is opened when it is catching prey, but it is so quick that the shell’s inside cannot be seen.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.

Name: Forretress
FlavorText: Usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: The nests Dunsparce live in are mazes of tunnels. They never get lost in their own nests—they can tell where they are by the scent of the dirt.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s tiny wings have some scientists saying that Dunsparce used to fly through the sky in ancient times.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: When it sees a person, it digs a hole with its tail to make its escape. If you happen to find one, consider yourself lucky.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: It travels by digging through the ground. Diglett and Dunsparce share one another’s tunnels happily.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: When spotted, this Pokémon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: Its drill-tipped tail is used to burrow into the ground backwards. This POKéMON is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can hover just slightly using its wings.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: DUNSPARCE has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backwards. This POKéMON is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

Name: Dunsparce
FlavorText: It hides deep inside caves where no light ever reaches it and remains virtually motionless there.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: Its tail is tipped by a thick, horrible stinger. To bring down prey, it will first obscure their vision by covering their faces with its body, and then it will use the stinger to inject them with venom.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It sails on the winds with its limbs extended to strike from the sky. It aims for the prey’s face.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It flies straight at its target’s face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It clamps on to its chosen prey then jabs the stinger on its tail into the prey while it’s stunned with surprise.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It glides as if sliding. It startles foes by clamping on to their faces, then jabs with its poison stinger.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It glides without making a single sound. It grasps the face of its foe using its hind and large front claws, then stabs with its poison barb.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding, it hops along the ground back to its nest.

Name: Gligar
FlavorText: It flies straight at its target’s face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: This Pokémon evolved through use of a strange item. Its body is coated with steel powder and notably hard—not even diamond can leave so much as a scratch.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: It chews its way through boulders with its sturdy jaws. Its eyes can see in the darkness underground.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth’s core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: The iron it ingested with the soil it swallowed transformed its body and made it harder than diamonds.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: It’s said that if an ONIX lives for 100 years, its composition becomes diamondlike as it evolves into a STEELIX.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than a diamond.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: STEELIX live even further underground than ONIX. This POKéMON is known to dig toward the earth’s core, reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result, it is even harder than diamond.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: STEELIX lives even further underground than ONIX. This POKéMON is known to dig towards the earth’s core. There are records of this POKéMON reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

Name: Steelix
FlavorText: The many small metal particles that cover this POKéMON’s body reflect bright light well.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by many people to be cute.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: In contrast to its appearance, it’s quite timid. When playing with other puppy Pokémon, it sometimes gets bullied.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: It grows close to others easily and is also easily spoiled. The disparity between its face and its actions makes many young people wild about it.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokémon tends to sleep half the day.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: Despite its intimidating face, it’s quite cowardly. Its desperate attempts to appear threatening make it popular with people.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: By baring its fangs and making a scary face, Snubbull sends smaller Pokémon scurrying away in terror. However, this Pokémon seems a little sad at making its foes flee.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: It has an active, playful nature. Many women like to frolic with it because of its affectionate ways.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: Although it looks frightening, it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: By baring its fangs and making a scary face, it sends smaller POKéMON scurrying in terror. The SNUBBULL does seem a little sad at making its foes flee.

Name: Snubbull
FlavorText: In truth, it is a cowardly POKéMON. It growls eagerly in order to hide its fear from its opponent.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: Although it’s popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it’s totally incompetent as a watchdog.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: While it has powerful jaws, it doesn’t care for disputes, so it rarely has a chance to display their might.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: More timid than Snubbull, this Pokémon is doted on by young people amused at the contrast between its looks and its attitude.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: Its well-developed lower jaw and heavy fangs are its weapons. As long as it’s not provoked, it rarely bites.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: Granbull has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: Because its fangs are too heavy, it always keeps its head tilted down. However, its bite is powerful.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.

Name: Granbull
FlavorText: It has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The huge fangs are heavy, causing it to tilt its head. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere. A different form of Qwilfish lives in other regions.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: Experienced fishers say they try to catch Qwilfish in the brief moment that these Pokémon become defenseless just after launching poisonous spikes.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: Be cautious if this Pokémon starts sucking in water—it will soon attack by scattering the toxic spikes that grow all over its body.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: It shoots the poison spikes on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent’s size.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: A QWILFISH uses the pressure of water it swallows to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming to be somewhat challenging.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of  water all at once.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: It’s better at beating things than grasping them. When it battles for a long time, the weight of its pincers becomes too much to bear.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: It stores the excess energy from Mega Evolution, so after a long time passes, its body starts to melt.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Due to the effects of Mega Evolution, its pincers have taken on a more diabolical form, ripping anything they pinch to shreds.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: The excess energy that bathes this Pokémon keeps it in constant danger of overflow. It can’t sustain a battle over long periods of time.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Evolved by way of a curious item. The shell covering its body has been shown to be stronger than forged steel.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Though its body is slim, Scizor has tremendous attacking power. Even Scizor’s muscles are made of metal.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor’s body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Once it has identified something as an enemy, it will continue beating them with its steel-hard pincers until there’s nothing left but scraps.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Its body is like steel. Its tough, heavy pincers are more suited to smashing enemies than grabbing them.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Once it has identified an enemy, this Pokémon smashes it mercilessly with pincers hard as steel.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: It uses its wings to adjust its body temperature. Otherwise, its metal body would become too hot and melt in the heat of battle.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object it gets ahold of into bits.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: A SCIZOR has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. It flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

Name: Scizor
FlavorText: This POKéMON’s pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object it gets a hold of into bits.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: It stores berries in its shell. The berries mix with its body fluids to become delicious juices.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: The berries stored in its jar-like shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: The berries it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: A SHUCKLE hides under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its shell while eating stored berries. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: The BERRIES it stores in its vaselike shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.

Name: Shuckle
FlavorText: The fluid secreted by its toes carves holes in rocks for nesting and can be mixed with BERRIES to make a drink.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: A tremendous influx of energy builds it up, but when Mega Evolution ends, Heracross is bothered by terrible soreness in its muscles.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: It can grip things with its two horns and lift 500 times its own body weight.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: With its herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: This Pokémon has an unparalleled horn. Heracross itself demonstrates tremendous power—it’s capable of throwing several people trained in the traditional arts of war at once.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: Its powerful legs and claws give it enough power to hurl foes over great distances.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: It gathers in forests to search for tree sap, its favorite food. It’s strong enough to hurl foes.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: This Pokémon takes pride in its strength, which allows it to lift things 100 times heavier than itself with no trouble at all.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: Heracross loves sweet sap and will go looking through forests for it. The Pokémon uses its two antennae to pick up scents as it searches.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: It roams through forests searching for sweet nectar. Although it boasts fantastic physical strength, it’s not that good at flying.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: It’s proud of its thick horn. In Alola, its biggest rival is Vikavolt, which it’s always fighting with.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: Heracross has sharp claws on its feet. These are planted firmly into the ground or the bark of a tree, giving the Pokémon a secure and solid footing to forcefully fling away foes with its proud horn.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe’s grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokémon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: This powerful Pokémon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies’ bellies, then lifts and throws them.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: No matter how heavy its opponents, it flings them far away with its prized horn.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: It loves sweet honey. To keep all the honey to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: It is usually docile, but if it is disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: With powerful legs and claws, it generates enough power to hurl foes over great distances.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: They gather in forests seeking the sweet sap of trees. It is completely clad in a steel-hard shell. It is proud of its horn, which it uses to fling foes.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: Usually docile, but if disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

Name: Heracross
FlavorText: This powerful POKéMON thrusts its prized horn under its enemies’ bellies then lifts and throws them.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a venom that infiltrates the nerves of any prey caught in Sneasel’s grasp.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: This is a smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: This Pokémon shares roots with the Sneasel of Hisui, but unlike that species, this one is spiteful in personality. I hypothesize that water and earth can affect Sneasel’s mind and body.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: It is extremely vicious and will not stop attacking until its foe is incapable of moving.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: It feeds on eggs stolen from nests. Its sharply hooked claws rip vulnerable spots on prey.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: It blends into the dark of night to ambush its prey. Sneasel will attack Sandshrew, but its hard skin can cause Sneasel’s claws to snap off.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: They will cooperate to steal eggs from the nests of bird Pokémon, but fights break out to determine which one gets to eat the eggs.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: It uses its claws to poke holes in eggs so it can slurp out the insides. Breeders consider it a scourge and will drive it away or eradicate it.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This Pokémon seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: A smart and sneaky Pokémon, it makes its opponents flinch by suddenly showing the claws hidden in its paws.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: A smart and sneaky Pokémon. A pair may work together to steal eggs by having one lure the parents away.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: Vicious in nature, it drives PIDGEY from their nests and scavenges any leftovers it can find.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: A SNEASEL scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. It seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.

Name: Sneasel
FlavorText: Vicious in nature, it drives PIDGEY from their nests and feasts on the eggs that are left behind.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: Its paws are soaked in oodles of honey. When nervous, Teddiursa will lick its paws and soon have a smile back on its face.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: This Pokémon discreetly follows Combee to find their hive. It scoops up big dollops of honey in its palms to eat.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: It licks its paws because of the sweet honey that has soaked into them. It is cunning, stealing into the nests of Combee and taking for itself the honey that the Combee have amassed.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they’re soaked with honey.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: It licks its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. A TEDDIURSA makes its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by BEEDRILL.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.

Name: Teddiursa
FlavorText: It always licks honey. Its palm tastes sweet because of all the honey it has absorbed.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: It is quite skilled at climbing trees. If it comes across a Primeape while searching for berries in the treetops, trouble will surely ensue.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: It usually wears a hardened expression, but when it’s licking up honey—which it loves—the joy it feels will cause it to break into a wide grin.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: When the cold season arrives in Hisui, this Pokémon will wander fields and mountains alike in search of its favorite berries. Ursaring’s hunger during this time makes it a ferocious danger.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: With its ability to distinguish any aroma, it unfailingly finds all food buried deep underground.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen berries.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: In forests, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where an URSARING gathers food. It walks through its forest collecting food every day.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap stout trees with its forelegs and eat fallen BERRIES.

Name: Ursaring
FlavorText: With its ability to distinguish any smell, it unfailingly finds all food buried deep underground.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: Slugma does not have any blood in its body. Instead, intensely hot magma circulates throughout this Pokémon’s body, carrying essential nutrients and oxygen to its organs.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: Molten magma courses throughout Slugma’s circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped, its magma body would cool and harden.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: It is a species of POKéMON that lives in volcanic areas. If its body cools, its skin hardens and immobilizes it. To avoid that, it sleeps near magma.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: These group together in areas that are hotter than normal. If it cools off, its skin hardens.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Flames burst from gaps in its shell made of hardened magma.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Magcargo’s body temperature is approximately 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Water is vaporized on contact. If this Pokémon is caught in the rain, the raindrops instantly turn into steam, cloaking the area in a thick fog.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Magcargo’s shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile—just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This Pokémon returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that  circulate throughout its body.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: The shell on its back is made of hardened magma. Tens of thousands of years spent living in volcanic craters have turned MAGCARGO’s bodies into magma.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: MAGCARGO’s body temperature is approximately 18,000 degrees F. Water is vaporized on contact. If this POKéMON is caught in the rain, the raindrops instantly turn into steam, cloaking the area in a thick fog.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: MAGCARGO’s shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile - just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This POKéMON returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: Swinub excels at sniffing out mushrooms buried beneath grass or snow. Since ancient times, the people of Hisui have often relied upon this skill.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: It loves eating mushrooms that grow under dead grass. It also finds hot springs while foraging.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: Swinub roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under the cover of dead grass. This Pokémon occasionally roots out hot springs.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: Rooting the tip of its snout into the ground, it searches for food. Sometimes it even digs up a hot spring.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: It has a very sensitive nose. It can locate mushrooms, berries, and even hot springs buried under ice.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: It roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under dried grass. It occasionally roots out hot springs.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: It uses the tip of its nose to dig for food. Its nose is so tough that even frozen ground poses no problem.

Name: Swinub
FlavorText: If it smells something enticing, it dashes headlong off to find the source of the aroma.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: The long fur of this Pokémon covers its eyes, ears, and even limbs, allowing Piloswine to resist harshly frigid conditions. The Pokémon’s white tusks can be used to defeat its enemies.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: Its shaggy coat makes it unable to see. It checks surroundings with its sensitive nose instead.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: Although its legs are short, its rugged hooves prevent it from slipping, even on icy ground.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair that enables it to endure the freezing cold. This Pokémon uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight, it just keeps charging repeatedly.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: With its excellent sense of smell, it’s even able to find mushrooms that are buried under frozen ground.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: Covered by a shaggy coat, it is strong against the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.

Name: Piloswine
FlavorText: A PILOSWINE is covered by a thick coat of long hair for enduring freezing cold. It uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Sudden climate change wiped out this ancient kind of Corsola. This Pokémon absorbs others’ life-force through its branches.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Watch your step when wandering areas oceans once covered. What looks like a stone could be this Pokémon, and it will curse you if you kick it.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in warm seas. In prehistoric times, many lived in the oceans around the Galar region as well.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: In Alola, where their natural enemies Mareanie are plentiful, many Corsola have stubby branches on their heads.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: The pink of Corsola that live in Alola is deep and vibrant, thanks to seas filled with nutrition.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokémon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Coral branches grow from its head. They break off quite easily, but they grow back in about three days.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Clusters of Corsola congregate in warm seas where they serve as ideal hiding places for smaller Pokémon. When the water temperature falls, this Pokémon migrates to the southern seas.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Corsola’s branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: In a south-sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: CORSOLA live in warm southern seas. If the sea becomes polluted, the beautiful coral stalks become discolored and crumble away in tatters.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: In a south sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these POKéMON.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: The points on its head absorb nutrients from clean water. They cannot survive in polluted water.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Spits water from its mouth with incredible accuracy. It captures Burmy by shooting them down off the branches from which they dangle.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It clings to Mantine to feed on the big Pokémon’s scraps. This is an adaptation to avoid foes.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It squirts water forcefully from its mouth to shoot down flying prey.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Also known as the “sniper of the seas,” its water gun can hit prey without fail from over 300 feet away.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: This Pokémon clings to Mantine and shares in its prosperity. When its Mantine is attacked, Remoraid will fight alongside it!

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Remoraid sucks in water, then expels it at high velocity using its abdominal muscles to shoot down flying prey. When evolution draws near, this Pokémon travels downstream from rivers.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It forcefully squirts water. The water jet never misses prey even if the Remoraid is deep in the sea.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: A REMORAID uses its abdominal muscles to forcefully expel swallowed water, then shoot down flying prey. When evolution approaches, it travels down rivers.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 100 yards.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: To escape from an attacker, it may shoot water out of its mouth, then use that force to swim backward.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 300 feet.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: While Octillery still shoots water from its mouth, the drastic anatomical difference between it and Remoraid meant that for a long time, no one believed the former evolved from the latter.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It obscures its foe’s vision by spitting a cloud of black ink. It makes its nest among boulders.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It lives in the gaps of boulders and in holes on the seafloor. Its suction cups grip prey tightly.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It usually sleeps in caves. The pitch-black ink that Octillery spits is also used for cooking.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: The ink it spits when escaping is special. It contains a substance that dulls the sense of smell, so Pokémon with keen noses get lost.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery spews ink to escape.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It loves to lurk inside holes in rocks. It sometimes sprays ink on prey by sticking out only its mouth.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It instinctively sneaks into rocky holes. If it gets sleepy, it steals the nest of a fellow OCTILLERY.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It obscures its foe’s vision by spitting a cloud of murky ink. It makes its nest among boulders.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It ensnares its foe with its suction-cupped tentacles before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, it spews ink to escape.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: Its instinct is to bury itself in holes. It often steals the nesting holes of others to sleep in them.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has a habit of sharing food with people lost in the mountains.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokémon, so it’s always scrounging around for more food.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It wraps food in its tail to carry it around. The Delibird with the biggest tail is the boss of the flock!

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It shares its food with people who are stranded. Because Delibird is omnivorous, sometimes it gives those people bug Pokémon.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: Although it naturally prefers colder locales, Delibird in Alola seem able to withstand the heat to a certain extent.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: Delibird carries its food bundled up in its tail. There once was a famous explorer who managed to reach the peak of the world’s highest mountain, thanks to one of these Pokémon sharing its food.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It carries food all day long. When someone is lost in the mountains, it shares that food.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It nests at the edge of sharp cliffs. It spends all day carrying food to its awaiting chicks.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by its stored food.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: It carries food bundled up in its tail. There was a famous explorer who managed to scale Mt. Everest thanks to a DELIBIRD sharing its food.

Name: Delibird
FlavorText: DELIBIRD carries its food bundled up in its tail. There once was a famous explorer who managed to reach the peak of Mt. Everest thanks to one of these POKéMON sharing its food.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: This calm and gentle Pokémon swims gracefully through the sea. After building speed, it can leap out of the water. It is often misidentified as a bird Pokémon due to this behavior.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: It swims elegantly, mindless of Remoraid hitching onto its broad fins. It is naturally docile.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: When the waves are calm, one may encounter a swarm of Mantine swimming as if they are in flight.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if Remoraid attach to it to scavenge for its leftovers.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: Many people have taken up surfing because they admire how magnificently Mantine swims.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: Postcards and posters featuring Mantine leaping elegantly above the waves are popular souvenirs of Alola.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be seen elegantly leaping over the sea’s waves. This Pokémon is not bothered by the Remoraid that hitches rides.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can fly over 300 feet out of the water from the surface of the ocean.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: Swimming freely in open seas, it may fly out of the water and over the waves if it builds up enough speed.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if REMORAID attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: It swims elegantly, mindless of REMORAID hitching on to its broad fins. It has a docile nature.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: On sunny days, schools of MANTINE can be seen elegantly leaping over the waves. It is not bothered by the REMORAID that hitches rides.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: It swims along freely, eating things that swim into its mouth. Its whole body is very coarse.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Skarmory is clad entirely in ironhard armor. It flies at speeds over 180 mph.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: The pointed feathers of these Pokémon are sharper than swords. Skarmory and Corviknight fight viciously over territory.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Its body is draped in steel armor. It looks heavy, but it can fly at speeds of up to 185 miles an hour!

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: The wing feathers it sheds can be processed and made into knives whose sharpness is recognized by the finest chefs.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Its metal body is sturdy, but it does rust rather easily. So on rainy days, this Pokémon prefers to stay put in its nest.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Its feathers, which fall off as it grows, are thin and sharp. In times long past, warriors used them as swords.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Skarmory’s steel wings become tattered and bashed in from repeated battles. Once a year, the battered wings grow back completely, restoring the cutting edges to their pristine state.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Skarmory is entirely encased in hard, protective armor. This Pokémon flies at close to 190 mph. It slashes foes with its wings that possess swordlike cutting edges.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Its heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Its sturdy wings look heavy, but they are actually hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: A POKéMON that has a body and wings of steel. People in the past used feathers fallen from SKARMORY to make swords and knives.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: Its sturdy wings look heavy, but its bones are hollow and light, allowing it to fly freely in the sky.

Name: Skarmory
FlavorText: The feathers that it sheds are very sharp. It is said that people once used the feathers as swords.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: They make repeated eerie howls before dawn to call attention to their pack.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It cooperates with others skillfully. When it becomes your partner, it’s very loyal to you as its Trainer and will obey your orders.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: Houndour hunt as a coordinated pack. They communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This Pokémon’s remarkable teamwork is unparalleled.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: To corner prey, they check each other’s location using barks that only they can understand.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: Around dawn, its ominous howl echoes through the area to announce that this is its territory.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: HOUNDOUR communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This POKéMON’s remarkable teamwork is simply unparalleled.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing prey.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Houndoom’s entire body generates heat when it Mega Evolves. Its fearsome fiery breath turns its opponents to ash.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Its red claws and the tips of its tail are melting from high internal temperatures that are painful to Houndoom itself.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: They spew flames mixed with poison to finish off their opponents. They divvy up their prey evenly among the members of their pack.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: In a HOUNDOOM pack, the one with its horns raked sharply back serves a leadership role. They choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: In a HOUNDOOM pack, the one with its horns raked sharply towards the back serves a leadership role. These POKéMON choose their leader by fighting amongst themselves.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: The pungent-smelling flame that shoots from its mouth results from toxins burning in its body.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: Scales shed by this Pokémon have such a splendorous gleam to them that they’ve been given to royalty as gifts.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: Kingdra sleeps on the seafloor where it is otherwise devoid of life. When a storm arrives, the Pokémon is said to awaken and wander about in search of prey.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: Kingdra lives at extreme ocean depths that are otherwise uninhabited. It has long been believed that the yawning of this Pokémon creates spiraling ocean currents.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life-forms can survive.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It sleeps quietly, deep on the seafloor. When it comes up to the surface, it creates a huge whirlpool that can swallow even ships.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: It is far stronger than it appears. If a Phanpy is swinging its trunk around and your arm gets hit by it, your arm bone will shatter.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won’t be able to settle down unless it washes its body.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: Phanpy uses its long nose to shower itself. When others gather around, they thoroughly douse each other with water. These Pokémon can be seen drying their soaking-wet bodies at the edge of water.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: For its nest, Phanpy digs a vertical pit in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: It swings its long snout around playfully, but because it is so strong, that can be dangerous.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: PHANPY’s big ears serve as broad fans. When it becomes hot, it flaps the ears busily to cool down. Even the young are very strong.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: It swings its long snout around playfully, but because it is so strong, this can be dangerous.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: For its nest, PHANPY digs a vertical pit  in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.

Name: Phanpy
FlavorText: During the deserted morning hours, it comes ashore where it deftly uses its trunk to take a shower.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: Donphan is normally a calm Pokémon, but once it is enraged, it will curl its body into a ball and charge at you while rolling.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: Donphan is covered in tough hide, so even being hit by a car won’t faze this Pokémon. However, it is extremely susceptible to rain.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: It attacks by curling up and rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: If Donphan were to tackle with its hard body, even a house could be destroyed. Using its massive strength, the Pokémon helps clear rock and mud slides that block mountain trails.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: Donphan’s favorite attack is curling its body into a ball, then charging at its foe while rolling at high speed. Once it starts rolling, this Pokémon can’t stop very easily.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its Tackle is strong enough to knock down a house.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: It attacks by curling up then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: A DONPHAN is so strong it can easily haul a dump truck. Its hide has toughened to a rock-hard state. An ordinary sort of attack won’t even leave a scratch.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take a long time to grow.

Name: Donphan
FlavorText: Because this POKéMON’s skin is so tough, a normal attack won’t even leave a scratch on it.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: A bizarre item caused this Pokémon to evolve. While it now exhibits many new gestures and expressions, its biology remains inscrutable.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: After artificial intelligence was implemented in Porygon2, the Pokémon began using a strange language that only other Porygon2 understand.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: Even though it doesn’t die in the vacuum of space, it can’t move around very well in zero gravity.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: AI has been installed in it. It learns various things all on its own, but it even remembers things it doesn’t need to know.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: Porygon was updated to a new version in readiness for planetary development. But that dream remains unrealized as yet.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: For the purposes of planetary development, Porygon was updated with the most cutting-edge technology available.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: Porygon2 was created by humans using the power of science. The man-made Pokémon has been endowed with artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: Further research enhanced its abilities. Sometimes, it may exhibit motions that were not programmed.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: Further research enhanced its  abilities. Sometimes, it may exhibit motions that were not programmed.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. It can’t fly, however.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: It was created by humans using the power of science. It has been given artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. However, it can’t even fly.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: This manmade POKéMON evolved from the latest technology. It may have unprogrammed reactions.

Name: Porygon2
FlavorText: This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. It can’t fly, though.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: It’s said that this Pokémon used to be stronger long ago when it had many enemies, and that it was even able to evolve under its own power.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: This Pokémon apparently used to live in much harsher environments, and thus it once had stronger psychic powers than it does now.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: Its strangely shaped antlers have the power to bewitch those who see them. Medicine made by grinding up the black orbs from fallen antlers is an effective treatment for insomnia.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: Stantler’s magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: Those who stare at its antlers will gradually lose control of their senses and be unable to stand.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: STANTLER’s magnificent antlers were once traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this POKéMON was hunted close to extinction.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: Its curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.

Name: Stantler
FlavorText: The round balls found on the fallen antlers can be ground into a powder that aids in sleeping.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: It draws symbols with the fluid that oozes from the tip of its tail. Depending on the symbol, Smeargle fanatics will pay big money for them.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: The fluid of Smeargle’s tail secretions changes in the intensity of its hue as the Pokémon’s emotions change.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: It draws symbols all over the place to mark its territory. In towns with many Smeargle, the walls are covered in graffiti.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: The unique creations produced by each Smeargle are painted using the fluid that oozes from its tail. This is how it marks its territory.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: Smeargle marks the boundaries of its territory using a body fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. Over 5,000 different marks left by this Pokémon have been found.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: A SMEARGLE marks its territory using a fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. About 5,000 different marks left by this POKéMON have been found.

Name: Smeargle
FlavorText: The color of the mysterious fluid secreted from its tail is predetermined for each SMEARGLE.

Name: Tyrogue
FlavorText: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.

Name: Tyrogue
FlavorText: Even though it is small, it can’t be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

Name: Tyrogue
FlavorText: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

Name: Tyrogue
FlavorText: Tyrogue becomes stressed out if it does not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish and uphold various training methods.

Name: Tyrogue
FlavorText: To brush up on its fighting skills, it will challenge anyone. It has a very strong competitive spirit.

Name: Tyrogue
FlavorText: TYROGUE become stressed out if they do not get to train every day. When raising this POKéMON, the TRAINER must establish a regular training schedule.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by a factor of 10.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: After doing a handstand to throw off the opponent’s timing, it presents its fancy kick moves.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: Hitmontop spins on its head at high speed, all the while delivering kicks. This technique is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense at the same time. The Pokémon travels faster spinning than it does walking.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: If you are enchanted by its smooth, dance-like kicks, you may get a closer experience with one than you’d like.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by 10.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by ten.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: Its technique of kicking while spinning is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense. HITMONTOP travel faster spinning than they do walking.

Name: Hitmontop
FlavorText: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dance-like kicks, you may get drilled hard.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: This is a very curious Pokémon. Smoochum decides what it likes and dislikes by touching things with its lips.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: If its face gets even slightly dirty, Smoochum will bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty, Smoochum doesn’t really seem to care.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: Highly perceptive sensors, Smoochum’s lips are kept moist by its daily application of tree sap.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: When it examines things, before touching them with its hands, it makes lip contact and then diligently licks all the dirt off its lips.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: Smoochum actively runs about, but also falls quite often. Whenever the chance arrives, it will look for its reflection to make sure its face hasn’t become dirty.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: Its lips are the most sensitive part of its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: It always rocks its head slowly backwards and forwards as if it is trying to kiss someone.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: It actively runs about, but also falls often. Whenever it falls, it will check its reflection on a lake’s surface to make sure its face hasn’t become dirty.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: Its lips are the most sensitive parts on its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

Name: Smoochum
FlavorText: The sensitivity of its lips develops most quickly. It uses them to try to identify unknown objects.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: They generate electricity by spinning their arms. During a thunderstorm, if one hears the lively voices of children out in the wilderness, what one is actually hearing are the voices of Elekid.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: It generates electricity by whirling its arms. However, it can’t store the energy it makes.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: It’s not good at storing electricity yet. This Pokémon sneaks into people’s homes, looking for electrical outlets to eat electricity from.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: When a storm approaches, this Pokémon gets restless. Once Elekid hears the sound of thunder, it gets full-on rowdy.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: When its horns shine a bluish white, that’s the sign it’s fully charged. You’ll get a shocking jolt if you touch it!

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: When it hears the crash of thunder, Elekid’s mood improves. It can be useful to record that sound and play it when Elekid’s feeling down.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: This Pokémon is constantly fighting with Togedemaru that try to steal its electricity. It’s a pretty even match.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: When it’s in a house, electrical outlets serve as its baby bottles. It sucks down electricity.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: Elekid stores electricity in its body. If it touches metal and accidentally discharges all its built-up electricity, this Pokémon begins swinging its arms in circles to recharge itself.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: Spinning its arms around to generate electricity makes the area between its horns shine light blue.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: A weak electric current flows between its horns. Sticking a hand there shocks the unwary.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: Even in the most vicious storm, this Pokémon plays happily if thunder rumbles in the sky.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it only charges up a little bit.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: If it touches metal and discharges the electricity it has stored in its body, an ELEKID begins swinging its arms in circles to recharge itself.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: It rotates its arms to generate electricity, but it tires easily, so it charges up only a little bit.

Name: Elekid
FlavorText: It loves violent thunder. The space between its horns flickers bluish-white when it is charging energy.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in volcanic areas. With each breath, sparks spurt from its mouth and nose. When Magby is in good health, its flames gain a yellow tint.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its body temperature is around 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. It is healthy if it is exhaling yellow flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: This Pokémon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day’s fatigue.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: This Pokémon is still small and timid. Whenever Magby gets excited or surprised, flames leak from its mouth and its nose.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its body temperature is always around 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. If Magby falls into a small- enough pond, the whole thing will dry up.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: When flames drip from its nose, that means it has a cold. Have it lie down for a nice rest in some magma.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: A famous potter lives with a Magby. Apparently its soft flames produce fine works.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Many of these Pokémon can be seen in areas with volcanic activity. Feeding can get them so excited, they exhale flames of 1,100 degrees F.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Magby’s state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body’s heat can top 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It’s small, but its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. Embers escape its mouth and nose when it breathes.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It’s small, but its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees F. Embers escape its mouth and nose when it breathes.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body’s heat can top 1,100 degrees F.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit, so don’t underestimate it.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble from its mouth and nostrils.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its body temperature is around 1,100 degrees F. It is healthy if it is breathing yellow flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: If a MAGBY is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body heat exceeds 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit, so don’t underestimate it.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It naturally spits an 1100-degree flame. It is said when many appear, it heralds a volcanic eruption.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body temp. is over 1100 degrees, so don’t underestimate it.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: It is said that kids who drink Miltank’s milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: This Pokémon needs to be milked every day, or else it will fall ill. The flavor of Miltank milk changes with the seasons.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it’s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: Its milk is delicious and chock-full of nutrients. However, if you drink too much, it could make your stomach hurt, so be careful.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: It produces over five gallons of milk a day. The higher the quality of the pastures it lives in, the richer and tastier its milk becomes.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: Most people raise it for its milk, but it’s quite tough and strong, so it’s also well suited for battle.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: Its milk is high in calories and packed with nutrients. Therefore, if you drink too much of it, you may wind up with a body like Miltank’s.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: Miltank gives over five gallons of milk on a daily basis. Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and grown-ups alike. People who can’t drink milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: Its milk is packed with nutrition, making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: If it is around babies, the milk it produces contains much more nutrition than usual.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: It gives over five gallons of milk daily. Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and grown-ups alike. People who can’t drink milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: If it has just had a baby, the milk it produces contains much more nutrition than usual.

Name: Miltank
FlavorText: In order to milk a MILTANK, one must have a knack for rhythmically pulling up and down on its udders.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Anyone who takes even one taste of Blissey’s egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: A kindhearted Pokémon that will care for any sick person or Pokémon until their health improves. The eggs it lays are delicious and bring good fortune to those who eat them.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: It is a Pokémon that delivers happiness. Eating its egg is said to make one kind to everyone.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: This kindhearted Pokémon nurses sick Pokémon to health. It senses feelings of sadness.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Blissey lays mysterious eggs that are filled with happiness. It’s said that anyone who eats a Blissey egg will start acting kindly to all others.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Whenever a Blissey finds a weakened Pokémon, it will share its egg and offer its care until the other Pokémon is all better.
