Name: Blissey
FlavorText: This Pokémon is overflowing with love. Only Chansey that share a strong bond with their Trainer can evolve, so people say.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Their eggs are such a delicacy that some say eating one will bring you happiness. These eggs fetch the highest prices on the market.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Its fluffy fur coat acts as a sensor, enabling it to read the feelings of people and Pokémon.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Even the most ferocious Pokémon become calm when they eat Blissey’s egg, which is said to be filled with happiness.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Blissey senses sadness with its fluffy coat of fur. If it does so, this Pokémon will rush over to a sad person, no matter how far away, to share a Lucky Egg that brings a smile to any face.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: It has a very compassionate nature. If it sees a sick Pokémon, it will nurse the sufferer back to health.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: If it senses sadness with its fluffy fur, a BLISSEY will rush over to the sad person, however far away, to share an egg of happiness that brings a smile to any face.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Anyone who takes even one bite of BLISSEY’s egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: BLISSEY senses sadness with its fluffy coat of fur. If it does so, this POKéMON will rush over to the sad person, however far they may be, to share an egg of happiness that brings a smile to any face.

Name: Blissey
FlavorText: Biting into one of the delicious eggs that BLISSEY provides will make everyone around smile with joy.

Name: Raikou
FlavorText: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

Name: Raikou
FlavorText: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

Name: Raikou
FlavorText: This rough Pokémon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.

Name: Raikou
FlavorText: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

Name: Raikou
FlavorText: A Pokémon that races across the land while barking a cry that sounds like crashing thunder.

Name: Raikou
FlavorText: RAIKOU embodies the speed of lightning. Its roars send shock waves shuddering through the air and ground as if lightning bolts were crashing down.

Name: Raikou
FlavorText: This POKéMON races across the land while barking a cry that sounds like crashing thunder.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to contain its sheer power, it races headlong around the land.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: ENTEI embodies the passion of magma. It is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It blasts fire that consumes all that it touches.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: This brawny POKéMON courses around the earth, spouting flames hotter than a volcano’s magma.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: This Pokémon races across the land. It is said that north winds will somehow blow whenever it appears.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: SUICUNE embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gliding elegance. It has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: Said to be the reincarnation of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: This divine POKéMON blows around the world, always in search of a pure reservoir.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: This Pokémon eats soil. Once it has eaten a large mountain, it goes to sleep so it can grow.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: Raised on nutrients it finds in the dirt, it eats roughly a mountain’s worth of dirt before it becomes a pupa.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: Born underground, it eats its way through dirt to the surface, where its parents are. It doesn’t deal well with the bright light it finds there.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: Larvitar is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this Pokémon must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, Larvitar cannot see its parents.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it falls asleep so it can grow.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: A Pokémon that eats soil. Once it has eaten a large mountain, it goes to sleep so it can grow.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: A LARVITAR is born deep under the ground. It must eat its way through the soil above and reach the surface for it to see its parents’ faces.

Name: Larvitar
FlavorText: LARVITAR is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this POKéMON must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, LARVITAR cannot see its parent’s face.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: Its shell is as hard as bedrock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: Its body is as hard as bedrock. By venting pressurized gas, it can launch itself like a rocket.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: It will not stay still, even while it’s a pupa. It already has arms and legs under its solid shell.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: This dangerous pupa thrashes about. Its shell is as hard as bedrock, containing its gradually forming new body within.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: This troublesome Pokémon can’t wait to evolve, so it relieves its stress by wildly propelling itself around using compressed gas.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable—it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: A PUPITAR creates a gas inside its body that it ejects under compression to propel itself like a jet. Its body can withstand a collision with solid steel.

Name: Pupitar
FlavorText: PUPITAR creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable - it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: The effects of Mega Evolution make it more ferocious than ever. It’s unclear whether it can even hear its Trainer’s orders.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: Due to the colossal power poured into it, this Pokémon’s back split right open. Its destructive instincts are the only thing keeping it moving.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and mountains crumble.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn’t care about others.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: Its body can’t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a mobile disaster, leaving mountains crumbled and houses destroyed in its wake.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: It wanders through the mountains seeking opponents to fight. If it finds an opponent that’s not worthy, Tyranitar ignores it and wanders on.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

Name: Tyranitar
FlavorText: A TYRANITAR is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. It roams in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

Name: Lugia
FlavorText: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

Name: Lugia
FlavorText: Lugia’s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

Name: Lugia
FlavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

Name: Lugia
FlavorText: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.

Name: Lugia
FlavorText: LUGIA is so powerful even a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart houses. As a result, it chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

Name: Lugia
FlavorText: LUGIA’s wings pack devastating power - a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this POKéMON chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

Name: Lugia
FlavorText: It has an incredible ability to calm raging storms. It is said that LUGIA appears when storms start.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted Trainer by shining its bright, rainbow-colored wings.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world’s skies continuously on its magnificent, seven-colored wings.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Its feathers--which glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light--are thought to bring joy. It is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Legends claim this POKéMON flies the world’s skies continuously on its magnificent seven-colored wings.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted trainer by shining its bright rainbow-colored wings.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon traveled through time to come from the future. It bolsters grass and trees with its own strength, and it can heal wounds, too.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: When CELEBI disappears deep in a forest, it is said to leave behind an egg it brought from the future.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: Revered as a guardian of the forest, CELEBI appears wherever beautiful forests exist.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny hooks, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: Treecko is cool, calm, and collected—it never panics under any situation. If a bigger foe were to glare at this Pokémon, it would glare right back without conceding an inch of ground.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: It quickly scales even vertical walls. It senses humidity with its tail to predict the next day’s weather.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: It makes its nest in a giant tree in the forest. It ferociously guards against anything nearing its territory. It is said to be the protector of the forest’s trees.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: TREECKO is cool, calm, and collected - it never panics under any situation. If a bigger foe were to glare at this POKéMON, it would glare right back without conceding an inch of ground.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: This Pokémon adeptly flies from branch to branch in trees. In a forest, no Pokémon can ever hope to catch a fleeing Grovyle however fast they may be.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: The leaves growing out of Grovyle’s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: It lives in dense jungles. While  closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: It leaps from tree branch to tree branch quite swiftly. It shows astounding agility.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: Leaves grow out of this POKéMON’s body. They help obscure a GROVYLE from the eyes of its enemies while it is in a thickly overgrown forest.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: Sceptile has seeds growing on its back. They are said to be bursting with nutrients that revitalize trees. This Pokémon raises the trees in a forest with loving care.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves growing on Sceptile’s body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile—it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: In the jungle, its power is without equal. This POKéMON carefully grows trees and plants. It regulates its body temperature by basking in sunlight.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves on its forelegs are as sharp as swords. It agilely leaps about the branches of trees to strike.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves growing on SCEPTILE’s body are very sharp edged. This POKéMON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: A fire burns inside it, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: Torchic has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug—it will be glowing with warmth. This Pokémon is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: Torchic sticks with its Trainer, following behind with unsteady steps. This Pokémon breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if it is hugged.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: Inside its body is a place where it keeps a small flame. Hug it! It will be as warm as a hot-water bottle.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: If attacked, it strikes back by spitting balls of fire it forms in its stomach. A TORCHIC dislikes darkness because it can’t see its surroundings.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: TORCHIC has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug - it will be glowing with warmth. This POKéMON is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKéMON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: Combusken battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks. This Pokémon’s cry is very loud and distracting.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: Combusken toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This Pokémon’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out 10 kicks in one second.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: It lashes out with 10 kicks per second. Its strong fighting instinct compels it to keep up its offensive until the opponent gives up.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKéMON’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs—it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon’s wrists burn.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: It learns martial arts that use punches and kicks. Every several years, its old feathers burn off, and new, supple feathers grow back in their place.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: BLAZIKEN has incredibly strong legs - it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This POKéMON’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: Using the fin on its head, Mudkip senses the flow of water to keep track of what’s going on around it. Mudkip has the strength to heft boulders.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: In water, Mudkip breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this Pokémon will unleash its amazing power—it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: The fin on Mudkip’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: Its large tail fin propels it through water with powerful acceleration. It is strong in spite of its size.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: Its power can crush boulders. It rests by covering itself with mud at the bottom of a river.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: On land, it can powerfully lift large boulders by planting its four feet and heaving. It sleeps by burying itself in soil at the water’s edge.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: In water, MUDKIP breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this POKéMON will unleash its amazing power - it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Marshtomp is much faster at traveling through mud than it is at swimming. This Pokémon’s hindquarters exhibit obvious development, giving it the ability to walk on just its hind legs.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: The surface of Marshtomp’s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Its toughened hind legs enable it to stand upright. Because it weakens if its skin dries out, it replenishes fluids by playing in mud.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: It is at its best when on muddy ground with poor footing. It quickly overwhelms foes struggling in mud.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Swampert predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break a boulder into pieces.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: If it senses the approach of a storm and a tidal wave, it protects its seaside nest by piling up boulders. It swims as fast as a jet ski.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Its arms are rock-hard. With one swing, they can batter down its foe. It makes its nest on beautiful beaches.

Name: Poochyena
FlavorText: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

Name: Poochyena
FlavorText: Poochyena is an omnivore—it will eat anything. A distinguishing feature is how large its fangs are compared to its body. This Pokémon tries to intimidate its foes by making the hair on its tail bristle out.

Name: Poochyena
FlavorText: At first sight, Poochyena takes a bite at anything that moves. This Pokémon chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

Name: Poochyena
FlavorText: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

Name: Poochyena
FlavorText: It chases its prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it turns tail if the prey strikes back.

Name: Poochyena
FlavorText: It savagely threatens foes with bared fangs. It chases after fleeing targets tenaciously. It turns tail and runs, however, if the foe strikes back.

Name: Poochyena
FlavorText: POOCHYENA is an omnivore - it will eat anything. A distinguishing feature is how large its fangs are compared to its body. This POKéMON tries to intimidate its foes by making the hair on its tail bristle out.

Name: Mightyena
FlavorText: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.

Name: Mightyena
FlavorText: Mightyena travel and act as a pack in the wild. The memory of its life in the wild compels the Pokémon to obey only those Trainers that it recognizes to possess superior skill.

Name: Mightyena
FlavorText: Mightyena gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This Pokémon will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.

Name: Mightyena
FlavorText: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

Name: Mightyena
FlavorText: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

Name: Mightyena
FlavorText: In the wild, MIGHTYENA live in a pack. They never defy their leader’s orders. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: Its restlessness has it constantly running around. If it sees another Pokémon, it will purposely run into them in order to start a fight.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: It walks in zigzag fashion. It’s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: Zigzagoon that adapted to regions outside Galar acquired this appearance. If you’ve lost something, this Pokémon can likely find it.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: The hair on Zigzagoon’s back is bristly. It rubs the hard back hair against trees to leave its territorial markings. This Pokémon may play dead to fool foes in battle.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: Zigzagoon restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This Pokémon does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: A Pokémon with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigzags.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: It gets interested in everything, which is why it zigs and zags. It is good at finding items.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: Rubbing its nose against the ground, it always wanders about back and forth in search of something. It is distinguished by the zigzag footprints it leaves.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: A POKéMON with abundant curiosity. It shows an interest in everything, so it always zigs and zags.

Name: Zigzagoon
FlavorText: The hair on ZIGZAGOON’s back is  bristly. It rubs the hard back hair against trees to leave its territorial markings. This POKéMON may play dead to fool foes in battle.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: It uses its long tongue to taunt opponents. Once the opposition is enraged, this Pokémon hurls itself at the opponent, tackling them forcefully.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: It uses its explosive speed and razor-sharp claws to bring down prey. Running along winding paths is not its strong suit.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: Its fur is strong and supple. Shaving brushes made with shed Linoone hairs are highly prized.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: When hunting, Linoone will make a beeline straight for the prey at a full run. While this Pokémon is capable of topping 60 mph, it has to come to a screeching halt before it can turn.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: Linoone always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This Pokémon is very challenged by gently curving roads.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: When running in a straight line, it can easily top 60 miles an hour. It has a tough time with curved roads.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: It is exceedingly fast if it only has to run in a straight line. When it spots pond-dwelling prey underwater, it quickly leaps in and catches it with its sharp claws.

Name: Linoone
FlavorText: When running in a straight line, it can top 60 miles per hour. However, it has a tough time with curved roads.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: Likes sap and is abundant in the wild. Why it evolves into various different forms is unknown. One cannot tell from a Wurmple’s appearance which form it will take when it evolves.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: It spits a white silk thread that turns sticky when coming into contact with air. The silk is used to immobilize foes.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: It loves to eat leaves. If it is attacked by a Starly, it will defend itself with its spiked rear.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: Wurmple is targeted by Swellow as prey. This Pokémon will try to resist by pointing the spikes on its rear at the attacking predator. It will weaken the foe by leaking poison from the spikes.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: Often targeted by bird Pokémon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by  raising up the spikes on its rear.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: It spits a white silk that turns sticky when it contacts air. It is used to immobilize foes.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: It sticks to tree branches and eats leaves. The thread it spits from its mouth, which becomes gooey when it touches air, slows the movement of its foes.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: It lives amidst tall grass and in forests. When attacked, it resists by pointing its venomous spikes at the foe.

Name: Wurmple
FlavorText: Using the spikes on its rear end,   WURMPLE peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This POKéMON’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: Wraps itself in thin strings of silk while it stores energy for evolution. It can’t extend its limbs and its movement is slow, but its eyes keep a sharp lookout—Silcoon is always on guard.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: It drinks dew that collects on its silk while it waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: It anchors itself by wrapping twigs with the silk from its body. It motionlessly awaits evolution.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: Silcoon was thought to endure hunger and not consume anything before its evolution. However, it is now thought that this Pokémon slakes its thirst by drinking rainwater that collects on its silk.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: Having wrapped silk around the branches of a tree, it quiescently awaits evolution.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: It prepares for evolution using the energy it stored while it was a WURMPLE. It keeps watch over the surroundings with its two eyes.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: It conserves its energy by moving as little as possible. It awaits evolution while drinking only a little rainwater.

Name: Silcoon
FlavorText: SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There,  this POKéMON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: A colorful and incredibly beautiful but also greedy Pokémon. In an effort to keep its favorite food all to itself, it will chase away Combee as they try to gather nectar.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: When flower fields bloom, it flits around, collecting pollen. Despite its appearance, it is savage.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey’s fluids.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: Beautifly has a long mouth like a coiled needle, which is very convenient for collecting pollen from flowers. This Pokémon rides the spring winds as it flits around gathering pollen.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: Beautifly’s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: Vibrantly patterned wings are its prominent feature. It sucks sweet flower nectar with its long mouth.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: Despite its looks, it is aggressive. It jabs with its long, thin mouth if disturbed while collecting pollen.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: Its colorfully patterned wings are its most prominent feature. It flies through flower-covered fields collecting pollen. It attacks ferociously when angered.

Name: Beautifly
FlavorText: Despite its appearance, it has an aggressive nature. It attacks by jabbing with its long, thin mouth.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: The silk coating its body is thin but sufficiently strong. Cascoon’s silk has a luster and texture superior to that of Silcoon’s, and clothes made using Cascoon silk are regarded as top-notch.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: Encased within its tough cocoon, it endures attacks. It never forgets the appearance of its foes.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: It is hot inside its cocoon. All the cells in its body create the energy for it to evolve.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: If it is attacked, Cascoon remains motionless however badly it may be hurt. It does so because if it were to move, its body would be weak upon evolution. This Pokémon will also not forget the pain it endured.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: Its body, which is made of soft silk, hardens over time. When cracks appear, evolution is near.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: It endures attacks with patience, because the more pain before evolution, the sturdier it becomes.

Name: Cascoon
FlavorText: To avoid detection by its enemies, it hides motionlessly beneath large leaves and in the gaps of branches. It also attaches dead leaves to its body for camouflage.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: Dustox are nocturnal Pokémon. Drawn by streetlights, they messily eat the leaves of trees lining boulevards.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: When Dustox flaps its wings, a fine dust is scattered all over. This dust is actually a powerful poison that will even make a pro wrestler sick. This Pokémon searches for food using its antennae like radar.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: A nocturnal Pokémon. Drawn by streetlights, they messily eat the leaves of trees lining boulevards.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: Toxic powder is scattered with each flap. At night, it is known to strip leaves off trees lining boulevards.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: It scatters its fine dust all over when it is attacked. It is a nocturnal Pokémon.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: It is a nocturnal POKéMON that flies from fields and mountains to the attraction of streetlights at night. It looses highly toxic powder from its wings.

Name: Dustox
FlavorText: It scatters horribly toxic dust when it senses danger. They tend to gather in the glow of streetlamps at night.

Name: Lotad
FlavorText: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry for Pokémon that can’t swim.

Name: Lotad
FlavorText: Its leaf grew too large for it to live on land. That is how it began to live floating in the water.

Name: Lotad
FlavorText: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

Name: Lotad
FlavorText: Lotad is said to have dwelled on land before. However, this Pokémon is thought to have returned to water because the leaf on its head grew large and heavy. It now lives by floating atop the water.

Name: Lotad
FlavorText: Lotad live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this Pokémon travels on land in search of clean water.

Name: Lotad
FlavorText: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can’t swim.

Name: Lotad
FlavorText: This POKéMON lives in ponds with clean water. It is known to ferry small POKéMON across ponds by carrying them on the broad leaf on its head.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: It lives at the water’s edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: It is nocturnal and becomes active at nightfall. It feeds on aquatic mosses that grow in the riverbed.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: Lombre’s entire body is covered by a slippery, slimy film. It feels horribly unpleasant to be touched by this Pokémon’s hands. Lombre is often mistaken for a human child.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: Lombre is nocturnal—it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief maker. When this Pokémon spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: It lives at the water’s edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water-grass by day and becomes active at night.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: In the evening, it takes great delight in popping out of rivers and startling people. It feeds on aquatic moss that grows on rocks in the riverbed.

Name: Lombre
FlavorText: LOMBRE is nocturnal - it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief-maker. When this POKéMON spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.

Name: Ludicolo
FlavorText: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can’t help breaking out into a dance.

Name: Ludicolo
FlavorText: If it hears festive music, it begins moving in rhythm in order to amplify its power.

Name: Ludicolo
FlavorText: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo’s cells, making it more powerful.

Name: Ludicolo
FlavorText: Upon hearing an upbeat and cheerful rhythm, the cells in Ludicolo’s body become very energetic and active. Even in battle, this Pokémon will exhibit an amazing amount of power.

Name: Ludicolo
FlavorText: Ludicolo begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This Pokémon is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.

Name: Ludicolo
FlavorText: When it hears festive music, all the cells in its body become stimulated, and it begins moving in rhythm. It does not quail even when it faces a tough opponent.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon that try to peck at it.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: Seedot looks exactly like an acorn when it is dangling from a tree branch. It startles other Pokémon by suddenly moving. This Pokémon polishes its body once a day using leaves.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: Seedot attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this Pokémon’s body becomes.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: It hangs off branches and absorbs nutrients. When it finishes eating, its body becomes so heavy that it drops to the ground with a thump.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: If it remains still, it becomes impossible to distinguish from real nuts. It delights in surprising foraging PIDGEY.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in the forest.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of Nuzleaf’s grass flute fills listeners with dread.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: This Pokémon pulls out the leaf on its head and makes a flute with it. The sound of Nuzleaf’s flute strikes fear and uncertainty in the hearts of people lost in a forest.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: Nuzleaf live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This Pokémon dislikes having its long nose pinched.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: A forest-dwelling POKéMON that is skilled at climbing trees. Its long and pointed nose is its weak point. It loses power if the nose is gripped.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: By flapping its leafy fans, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe’s mind and take preemptive action.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: Shiftry’s large fans generate awesome gusts of wind at a speed close to 100 feet per second. The whipped-up wind blows anything away. This Pokémon chooses to live quietly deep in forests.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: Shiftry is a mysterious Pokémon that is said to live atop towering trees dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: It is said to arrive on chilly, wintry winds. Feared from long ago as the guardian of forests, this POKéMON lives in a deep forest where people do not venture.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: SHIFTRY is a mysterious POKéMON that is said to live atop towering trees  dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

Name: Taillow
FlavorText: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

Name: Taillow
FlavorText: Taillow is young—it has only just left its nest. As a result, it sometimes becomes lonesome and cries at night. This Pokémon feeds on Wurmple that live in forests.

Name: Taillow
FlavorText: Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

Name: Taillow
FlavorText: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.

Name: Taillow
FlavorText: When it gets cold, they migrate, flying over 180 miles a day. It hunts for tasty prey.

Name: Taillow
FlavorText: Although it is small, it is very courageous. It will take on a larger SKARMORY on an equal footing. However, its will weakens if it becomes hungry.

Name: Taillow
FlavorText: TAILLOW is young - it has only just left its nest. As a result, it sometimes becomes lonesome and cries at night. This POKéMON feeds on WURMPLE that live in forests.

Name: Swellow
FlavorText: It circles the sky in search of prey and dives sharply to catch its target.

Name: Swellow
FlavorText: Swellow is very conscientious about the upkeep of its glossy wings. Once two Swellow are gathered, they diligently take care of cleaning each other’s wings.

Name: Swellow
FlavorText: Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow’s clawed feet, preventing escape.

Name: Swellow
FlavorText: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

Name: Swellow
FlavorText: If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.

Name: Swellow
FlavorText: It circles the sky in search of prey. When it spots one, it dives steeply to catch the prey.

Name: Swellow
FlavorText: A SWELLOW dives upon prey from far above. It never misses its targets. It takes to the skies in search of lands with a warm climate.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Catching sea winds with its long wings, it soars as if it were a glider. It folds its wings to rest.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea’s edge.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It makes its nest on sheer cliffs. Riding the sea breeze, it glides up into the expansive skies.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It builds nests in cliffs by the sea. It circles the skies above the ocean looking for its favorite food—Wishiwashi.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: With its long, thin wings, it catches updrafts and flies like a glider high up into the sky.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they’re circling, the ocean is sure to be teeming with fish Pokémon.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Its hollow bones enhance its lightness. It spreads its wings to the wind and soars away into the sky.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Wingull rides updrafts rising from the sea by extending its long and narrow wings to glide. This Pokémon’s long beak is useful for catching prey.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Wingull has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This Pokémon rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It makes its nest on a sheer cliff at the edge of the sea. It has trouble keeping its wings flapping in flight. Instead, it soars on updrafts.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It acts as a delivery service by carrying small Pokémon in its bill. It bobs on the waves to rest.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It dips its large bill in the sea, then scoops up numerous prey along with water.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Skimming the water’s surface, it dips its large bill in the sea, scoops up food and water, and carries it.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It scoops up Wishiwashi in its huge beak and swallows them whole. It can devour more than 30 at one go!

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It places small Pokémon into its spacious beak and carries them around. No one knows where it’s taking them.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Its spacious beak is large enough for a small child to fit right inside.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Pelipper searches for food while in flight by skimming the wave tops. This Pokémon dips its large bill in the sea to scoop up food, then swallows everything in one big gulp.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Pelipper is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon and eggs inside its massive bill. This Pokémon builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It skims the tops of waves as it flies. When it spots prey, it uses its large beak to scoop up the victim with water. It protects its eggs in its beak.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: Tends to prefer people with a chipper disposition to those who are gloomy, but it has shown no discrimination with regard to age or gender. Needs more research.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: It uses the horns on its head to sense human emotions. It is said to appear in front of cheerful people.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: Ralts has the ability to sense the emotions of people. If its Trainer is in a cheerful mood, this Pokémon grows cheerful and joyous in the same way.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.

Name: Ralts
FlavorText: A RALTS has the power to sense the emotions of people and POKéMON with the horns on its head. It takes cover if it senses any hostility.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: The cheerful spirit of its Trainer gives it energy for its psychokinetic power. It spins and dances when happy.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: It resembles a maiden in appearance, but it wields strange powers to project visions of paradise. I suspect the crimson ornaments on its head are the key to its abilities.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: It is highly perceptive of its Trainer’s feelings. It dances when it is feeling happy.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: Kirlia uses the horns on its head to amplify its psychokinetic power. When the Pokémon uses its power, the air around it becomes distorted, creating mirages of nonexistent scenery.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: It is said that a Kirlia that is exposed to the positive emotions of its Trainer grows beautiful. This Pokémon controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.

Name: Kirlia
FlavorText: A KIRLIA has the psychic power to create  a rip in the dimensions and see into the future. It is said to dance with pleasure on sunny mornings.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: It will dedicate itself to defending a master it has come to adore. Its pure white dress, reminiscent of those worn by ladies of nobility, is the dress of one who is willing to risk their life.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: It will try to guard its trusted Trainer with its life. It has the ability to see the future.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: Gardevoir has the psychokinetic power to distort the dimensions and create a small black hole. This Pokémon will try to protect its Trainer even at the risk of its own life.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokémon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.

Name: Gardevoir
FlavorText: It apparently does not feel the pull of gravity because it supports itself with psychic power. It will give its life to protect its TRAINER.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey in with a sweet scent released from the tip of its head.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It lives in ponds and marshes that feature lots of plant life. It often fights with Dewpider, whose habitat and diet are similar.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: If it’s in a pinch, it will secrete a sweet liquid from the tip of its head. Syrup made from gathering that liquid is tasty on bread.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: When this Pokémon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its head. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokémon.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It moves as if skating on the surface of the water. It often fights with Dewpider over food.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: If Surskit senses danger, it secretes a thick, sugary syrup from the tip of its head. There are some Pokémon that love eating this syrup.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: From the tips of its feet, Surskit secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: They gather on puddles after evening downpours, gliding across the surface of water as if sliding. It secretes honey with a sweet aroma from its head.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: The antennae have distinctive patterns that look like eyes. When it rains, they grow heavy, making flight impossible.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction—to and fro and sideways.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: Its thin, winglike antennae are highly absorbent. It waits out rainy days in tree hollows.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: Masquerain intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns of its eyespots. If that doesn’t work, it deftly makes its escape on its set of four wings.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: Its wings and antennae don’t cope well with moisture. After a rain, it faces sunward to dry off.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: It intimidates enemies with the eye-like patterns on its antennae. Its four wings allow it to fly in any direction.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: Masquerain’s antennas have eyelike patterns that usually give it an angry look. If the “eyes” are droopy and appear sad, it is said to be a sign that a heavy rainfall is on its way.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: Masquerain intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This Pokémon flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction—even sideways and backwards—as if it were a helicopter.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction--to and fro and sideways.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: It intimidates foes with the large eyelike patterns on its antennae. Because it can’t fly if its wings get wet, it shelters itself from rain under large trees and eaves.

Name: Masquerain
FlavorText: MASQUERAIN intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This POKéMON flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction - even sideways and backwards - as if it were a helicopter.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over the body if inhaled.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: If Shroomish senses danger, it shakes its body and scatters spores from the top of its head. This Pokémon’s spores are so toxic, they make trees and weeds wilt.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: Shroomish live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokémon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It loves to eat damp, composted soil in forests. If you enter a forest after a long rain, you can see many SHROOMISH feasting on composted soil.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: The seeds ringing Breloom’s tail are made of hardened toxic spores. It is horrible to eat the seeds. Just taking a bite of this Pokémon’s seed will cause your stomach to rumble.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon’s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: It scatters spores from holes in the cap on its head. It loves warm and humid climates. It feeds on trees and plants in fields and forests.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: It sleeps for 20 hours every day. Making drowsy those that see it is one of its abilities.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: It spends nearly all its time in a day sprawled out. Just seeing it makes one drowsy.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: Slakoth’s heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this Pokémon in motion.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: Slakoth lolls around for over 20 hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This Pokémon’s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: It sleeps virtually all day and night long. It doesn’t change its nest its entire life, but it sometimes travels great distances by swimming in rivers.

Name: Slakoth
FlavorText: SLAKOTH lolls around for over twenty hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This POKéMON’s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: It is always hungry because it won’t stop rampaging. Even while it is eating, it can’t keep still.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: Its heart beats at 10 times its previous rate, so it cannot sit still for even a moment.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: Vigoroth is simply incapable of remaining still. Even when it tries to sleep, the blood in its veins grows agitated, compelling this Pokémon to run wild throughout the jungle before it can settle down.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: Vigoroth is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can’t tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This Pokémon’s stress level rises if it can’t be moving constantly.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: Its heartbeat is fast and its blood so agitated that it can’t sit still for one second.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: Its heart beats at a tenfold tempo, so it cannot sit still for even a moment.

Name: Vigoroth
FlavorText: It can’t keep still because its blood boils with energy. It runs through the fields and mountains all day to calm itself. If it doesn’t, it can’t sleep at night.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives lying on its side. It only rolls over and moves when there is no more grass to eat.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: It is the world’s most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: It is the world’s laziest Pokémon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: Wherever Slaking live, rings of over a yard in diameter appear in grassy fields. They are made by the Pokémon as it eats all the grass within reach while lying prone on the ground.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: The world’s laziest Pokémon. It moves to another spot when there’s no food left within its reach.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: The world’s laziest Pokémon. When it is lounging, it is actually saving energy for striking back.

Name: Slaking
FlavorText: Hordes of SLAKING gather around trees when fruits come into season. They wait around patiently for ripened fruits to fall out of the trees.

Name: Nincada
FlavorText: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

Name: Nincada
FlavorText: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

Name: Nincada
FlavorText: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.

Name: Nincada
FlavorText: Nincada lives underground. It uses its sharp claws to carve the roots of trees and absorb moisture and nutrients. This Pokémon can’t withstand bright sunlight so avoids it.

Name: Nincada
FlavorText: Nincada lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This Pokémon absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.

Name: Nincada
FlavorText: It makes its nest at the roots of a mighty tree. Using its whiskerlike antennae, it probes its surroundings in the pitch-black darkness of soil.

Name: Ninjask
FlavorText: Because they move so quickly, they sometimes become unseeable. They congregate around tree sap.

Name: Ninjask
FlavorText: This Pokémon is so quick, it is said to be able to avoid any attack. It loves to feed on tree sap.

Name: Ninjask
FlavorText: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

Name: Ninjask
FlavorText: If Ninjask is not trained properly, it will refuse to obey the Trainer and cry loudly continuously. Because of this quality, this Pokémon is said to be one that puts the Trainer’s abilities to the test.

Name: Ninjask
FlavorText: Ninjask moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this Pokémon was long believed to be invisible.

Name: Ninjask
FlavorText: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

Name: Ninjask
FlavorText: Because it darts about vigorously at high speed, it is very difficult to see. Hearing its distinctive cries for too long induces a headache.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: It is a discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: A strange Pokémon—it flies without moving its wings, has a hollow shell for a body, and does not breathe.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: Shedinja is a peculiar Pokémon. It seems to appear unsought in a Poké Ball after a Nincada evolves. This bizarre Pokémon is entirely immobile—it doesn’t even breathe.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: Shedinja’s hard body doesn’t move—not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this Pokémon will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: A strange Pokémon--it flies without moving its wings, has a hollow shell for a body, and does not breathe.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: A peculiar POKéMON that floats in air even though its wings remain completely still. The inside of its body is hollow and utterly dark.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: SHEDINJA is a peculiar POKéMON. It seems to appear unsought in a POKé BALL after a NINCADA evolves. This bizarre POKéMON is entirely immobile - it doesn’t even breathe.

Name: Shedinja
FlavorText: SHEDINJA’s hard body doesn’t move - not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this POKéMON will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: When Whismur cries, the sound of its own voice startles it, making the Pokémon cry even louder. It cries until it’s exhausted, then it falls asleep.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: The cry of a Whismur is over 100 decibels. If you’re close to a Whismur when it lets out a cry, you’ll be stuck with an all-day headache.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: Whismur is very timid. If it starts to cry loudly, it becomes startled by its own crying and cries even harder. When it finally stops crying, the Pokémon goes to sleep, all tired out.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: Normally, Whismur’s voice is very quiet—it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this Pokémon senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: It usually murmurs but starts crying loudly if it senses danger. It stops when its ear covers are shut.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: Its cries equal a jet plane in volume. It inhales through its ear canals. Because of this system, it can cry continually without having to catch its breath.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: It usually murmurs, but starts crying loudly if it senses danger. It stops when its ear covers are shut.

Name: Whismur
FlavorText: Normally, WHISMUR’s voice is very quiet - it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this POKéMON senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: The force of this Pokémon’s loud voice isn’t just the sound—it’s also the wave of air pressure that blows opponents away and damages them.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: Loudred’s ears serve as speakers, and they can put out sound waves powerful enough to blow away a house.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: Loudred shouts while stamping its feet. After it finishes shouting, this Pokémon becomes incapable of hearing anything for a while. This is considered to be a weak point.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: Loudred’s bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This Pokémon’s round ears serve as loudspeakers.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: It shouts loudly by inhaling air, and then uses its well-developed stomach muscles to exhale.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: It positions the round speakers on its head to assail foes with ultrasonic waves at massive volume. It builds power by stomping the ground.

Name: Loudred
FlavorText: When it stamps its feet and bellows, it generates ultrasonic waves that can blow apart a house.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: This Pokémon can do more than just shout. To communicate with others of its kind, it’ll emit all sorts of sounds from the holes in its body.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: In the past, people would use the loud voices of these Pokémon as a means of communication between distant cities.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: Exploud communicates its feelings to the others by emitting whistle-like sounds from the tubes on its body. This Pokémon only raises its voice when it is in battle.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: Exploud triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this Pokémon violently inhales from the ports on its body, it’s a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor--or like an earthquake has struck.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: It has sound-generating organs all over its body. It communicates with others by adjusting the tone and volume of the cries it emits.

Name: Exploud
FlavorText: It emits a variety of sounds from the  holes all over its body. Its loud cries can be heard from over six miles away.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: There’s a rumor of a traditional recipe for stew that Trainers can use to raise strong Makuhita.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: It practices its slaps by repeatedly slapping tree trunks. It has been known to slap an Exeggutor and get flung away.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: Their daily routine consists of training together first thing in the morning, eating and napping in the afternoon, and then more training afterward.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: It was originally brought in from another region, but now Makuhita from Alola are more famous.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: Makuhita has a tireless spirit—it will never give up hope. It eats a lot of food, gets plenty of sleep, and it trains very rigorously. By living that way, this Pokémon packs its body with energy.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: Makuhita is tenacious—it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this Pokémon stores more energy in its body for evolving.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: It loves to toughen up its body above all else. If you hear quaking rumbles in a cave, it is the sound of MAKUHITA undertaking strenuous training.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: MAKUHITA has a tireless spirit - it will never give up hope. It eats a lot of food, gets plenty of sleep, and it trains very rigorously. By living that way, this POKéMON packs its body with energy.

Name: Makuhita
FlavorText: MAKUHITA is tenacious - it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this POKéMON stores more energy in its body for evolving.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: It stomps on the ground to build power. It can send a 10-ton truck flying with a straight-arm punch.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can send a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: Hariyama that are big and fat aren’t necessarily strong. There are some small ones that move nimbly and use moves skillfully.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: Although they enjoy comparing their strength, they’re also kind. They value etiquette, praising opponents they battle.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: They love to compare their freakish strength— strength enough to send a truck flying with a single slap.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: It is known for its fantastic strength, but as it grows older, it focuses more on training Makuhita.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: Hariyama’s thick body may appear fat, but it is actually a hunk of solid muscle. If this Pokémon bears down and tightens all its muscles, its body becomes as hard as a rock.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: Hariyama practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this Pokémon’s powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

Name: Hariyama
FlavorText: It has the habit of challenging others without hesitation to tests of strength. It’s been known to stand on train tracks and stop trains using forearm thrusts.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: Its tail bounces like a rubber ball. It flings that tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: Its tail is filled with nutrients necessary for growth. It plays by bouncing on its tail.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: It’s a Pokémon that lives by water. It moves quickly on land by bouncing on its big tail.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: Although Azurill are normally docile, an angry one will swing around the big ball on its tail and try to smash its opponents.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: The ball on Azurill’s tail bounces like a rubber ball, and it’s full of the nutrients the Pokémon needs to grow.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: Azurill’s tail is large and bouncy. It is packed full of the nutrients this Pokémon needs to grow. Azurill can be seen bouncing and playing on its big, rubbery tail.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: Azurill spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these Pokémon managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: It swings its large, nutrient-filled tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lives by water. It moves quickly on land by bouncing on its big tail.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: Its tail, which is packed with nutrition, is very bouncy like a rubber ball. On sunny days they gather at the edge of water and splash about for fun.

Name: Azurill
FlavorText: It battles by flinging around its tail, which is bigger than its body. The tail is a flotation device in water.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: Once the people of Hisui discovered that its red nose always points north, they grew to rely on it greatly when traveling afar. The nose seems to work in a similar way to ancient compasses.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: Its nose is a magnet. As a result, this Pokémon always keeps its face pointing north.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: It hunts without twitching a muscle by pulling in its prey with powerful magnetism. But sometimes it pulls natural enemies in close.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: It moves less than an inch a year, but when it’s in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the ground in a split second.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: It uses powerful magnetism to drag its prey toward it. It’s also been known to pull in metal, which it collects and uses to protect itself.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: The magnet in Nosepass’s nose provides an unerring compass, making it an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: Nosepass had been said to be completely unmoving, with its magnetic nose pointed due north. However, close observation has revealed that the Pokémon actually moves by a little over 3/8 of an inch every year.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: Nosepass’s magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these Pokémon meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check Nosepass to get their bearings.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: Its magnetic nose always faces north and draws iron objects to its body to protect itself better.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: When endangered, it may protect itself by raising its magnetism and drawing iron objects to its body.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: If two of these meet, they cannot get too close because their noses repel each other.

Name: Nosepass
FlavorText: Its body emits a powerful magnetism. It feeds on prey that is pulled in by the force. Its magnetism is stronger in cold seasons.

Name: Skitty
FlavorText: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in circles, chasing its own tail.

Name: Skitty
FlavorText: Skitty is known to chase around playfully after its own tail. In the wild, this Pokémon lives in holes in the trees of forests. It is very popular as a pet because of its adorable looks.

Name: Skitty
FlavorText: Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

Name: Skitty
FlavorText: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.

Name: Skitty
FlavorText: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

Name: Skitty
FlavorText: It’s adorable when it chases its own tail. It’s difficult to earn its trust.

Name: Skitty
