FlavorText: A SKITTY’s adorably cute behavior makes it highly popular. In battle, it makes its tail puff out. It threatens foes with a sharp growl.

Name: Skitty
FlavorText: It is said to be difficult to earn its trust. However, it is extremely popular for its cute looks and behavior.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: It is highly popular among Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: Delcatty sleeps anywhere it wants without keeping a permanent nest. If other Pokémon approach it as it sleeps, this Pokémon will never fight—it will just move away somewhere else.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: The reason it does not have a nest is that it simply searches for a clean, comfortable place then sleeps there.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: Rather than keeping a permanent lair, it habitually seeks comfortable spots and sleeps there. It is nocturnal and becomes active at dusk.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: The favorite of trend-conscious female TRAINERS, they are used in competition for their style and fur.

Name: Delcatty
FlavorText: DELCATTY sleeps anywhere it wants without keeping a permanent nest. If other POKéMON approach it as it sleeps, this POKéMON will never fight - it will just move away somewhere else.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: It blocks any and all attacks with its giant-sized gemstone. However, the stone’s a heavy burden, and it limits Mega Sableye’s movements.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: Bathed in the energy of Mega Evolution, the gemstone on its chest expands, rips through its skin, and falls out.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: Supporting a giant heavy jewel, it can’t change direction very nimbly and is vulnerable to attack from behind.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: The jewel from its chest, which has grown gigantic due to the effects of Mega Evolution, can turn back any attack.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: Materials from gems it has eaten float to the surface of its body and can form an infinite number of patterns among individuals.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: It feeds on gemstone crystals. In darkness, its eyes sparkle with the glitter of jewels.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it’s believed that Sableye will steal people’s spirits away.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: It digs through the ground with its hard claws and crunches down gems with its thick pointy teeth. Carbink is its favorite food.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: It’s a fiend for gemstones, so it stalks Carbink. Unfortunately, Gabite almost always grabs them first.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: Sableye digs the ground with sharpened claws to find rocks that it eats. Substances in the eaten rocks crystallize and rise up to the Pokémon’s body surface.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: Sableye lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these Pokémon are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.

Name: Sableye
FlavorText: It digs branching holes in caves using its sharp claws in search of food--raw gems. A SABLEYE lurks in darkness and is seen only rarely.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: Its two sets of jaws thrash about violently as if they each had a will of their own. One gnash from them can turn a boulder to dust.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: It has an extremely vicious disposition. It grips prey in its two sets of jaws and tears them apart with raw power.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: It has two mouths. The big jaws on the back of its head can’t taste anything, so that’s the mouth it uses to eat foods it doesn’t like.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: A cunning and terrifying Pokémon, its cuteness makes opponents let down their guard—and then it swallows them whole with its huge jaws.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: Don’t be taken in by this Pokémon’s cute face—it’s very dangerous. Mawile fools the foe into letting down its guard, then chomps down with its massive jaws. The steel jaws are really horns that have been transformed.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: Mawile’s huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: Its giant jaws are actually steel horns that transformed. It fools foes into complacency with its adorable gestures, then chomps them with its huge jaws.

Name: Mawile
FlavorText: Don’t be taken in by this POKéMON’s cute face - it’s very dangerous. MAWILE fools the foe into letting down its guard, then chomps down with its massive jaws. The steel jaws are really horns that have been transformed.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: It usually lives deep in mountains. But when it’s hungry, it shows up at the foot of the mountains and eats railroad tracks and cars.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: When Aron evolves, its steel armor peels off. In ancient times, people would collect Aron’s shed armor and make good use of it in their daily lives.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks—to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: Aron has a body of steel. With one all-out charge, this Pokémon can demolish even a heavy dump truck. The destroyed dump truck then becomes a handy meal for the Pokémon.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a body of steel. To make its body, Aron feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: It usually lives deep in mountains. However, hunger may drive it to eat railroad tracks and cars.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: In order to build up its steel body, it eats iron ore. This pesky Pokémon is known to eat railroad tracks.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: A POKéMON that is clad in steel armor. A new suit of armor is made when it evolves. The old, discarded armor is salvaged as metal for making iron products.

Name: Aron
FlavorText: It eats iron to build its steel body. It is a pest that descends from mountains to eat bridges and train tracks.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: For food, it digs up iron ore. It smashes its steely body against others to fight over territory.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: During territorial disputes, Lairon fight by slamming into each other. Close inspection of their steel armor reveals scratches and dents.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: Lairon feeds on iron contained in rocks and water. It makes its nest on mountains where iron ore is buried. As a result, the Pokémon often clashes with humans mining the iron ore.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: Lairon tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This Pokémon makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: It habitually shows off its strength with the size of sparks it creates by ramming its steel body into boulders.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: Lairon fight over territory, and when their steel bodies collide, sparks fly.

Name: Lairon
FlavorText: When two LAIRON meet in the wild, they fight for territory by bashing into each other with their steel bodies. The sound of their collision carries for miles.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: While seeking iron for food, it digs tunnels by breaking through bedrock with its steel horns.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: Long ago, there was a king who wore a helmet meant to resemble the head of an Aggron. He was trying to channel the Pokémon’s strength.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: Aggron is protective of its environment. If its mountain is ravaged by a landslide or a fire, this Pokémon will haul topsoil to the area, plant trees, and beautifully restore its own territory.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: Aggron claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This Pokémon vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don’t take it lightly.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: You can tell its age by the length of its iron horns. It claims an entire mountain as its territory.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: Its iron horns grow longer a little at a time. They are used to determine the AGGRON’s age. The gouges in its armor are worn with pride as mementos from battles.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: It claims a large mountain as its sole territory. It mercilessly thrashes those that violate its space.

Name: Aggron
FlavorText: AGGRON is surprisingly protective of its environment. If its mountain is ravaged by a landslide or a fire, this POKéMON will haul topsoil to the area, plant trees, and beautifully restore its own territory.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: It never misses its daily yoga workouts, and it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: It meditates in order to build up its mental energy. It’s said to eat just one Berry a day.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: Meditite heightens its inner energy through meditation. It survives on just one berry a day. Minimal eating is another aspect of this Pokémon’s training.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this Pokémon always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.

Name: Meditite
FlavorText: It continually meditates for hours every day. As a result of rigorous and dedicated yoga training, it has tempered its spiritual power so much it can fly.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe’s next move.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: Through daily meditation, it hones its spiritual power. It can sense what others are thinking.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: Through yoga training, it has honed its sixth sense. Its movements are elegant.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: Through the power of meditation, Medicham developed its sixth sense. It gained the ability to use psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon is known to meditate for a whole month without eating.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: It gains the ability to see the aura of its opponents by honing its mind through starvation.

Name: Medicham
FlavorText: Through crushingly harsh yoga training, it gained the power to foretell its foe’s actions. It battles with elegant, dance-like movement.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: Static electricity builds up all over its body as strands of its long fur rub together. This Pokémon boasts incredible speed.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: Friction between the air and its fur produces static electricity. When Electrike runs, it makes a crackling sound.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: Electrike runs faster than the human eye can follow. The friction from running is converted into electricity, which is then stored in this Pokémon’s fur.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: Electrike stores electricity in its long body hair. This Pokémon stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.

Name: Electrike
FlavorText: It generates electricity using friction from the atmosphere. In seasons with especially arid air, its entire body blazes with violent showers of sparks.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: Too much electricity has built up in its body, irritating Manectric. Its explosive speed is equal to that of a lightning bolt.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: Mega Evolution fills its body with a tremendous amount of electricity, but it’s too much for Manectric to fully control.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. The Pokémon creates a thundercloud overhead from which to drop lightning bolts.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: Manectric can be found beneath unnatural thunderclouds. People say it can run at the same speed as lightning striking.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: Manectric discharges strong electricity from its mane. The mane is used for collecting electricity in the atmosphere. This Pokémon creates thunderclouds above its head.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: Manectric is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this Pokémon creates thunderclouds.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: Its nest can be found where a thunderbolt hits. It is discharging electricity from its mane.

Name: Manectric
FlavorText: Because lightning falls in their vicinities, MANECTRIC were thought to have been born from lightning. In battle, they create thunderclouds.

Name: Plusle
FlavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

Name: Plusle
FlavorText: When Plusle is cheering on its partner, it flashes with electric sparks from all over its body. If its partner loses, this Pokémon cries loudly.

Name: Plusle
FlavorText: Plusle always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this Pokémon shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.

Name: Plusle
FlavorText: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.

Name: Plusle
FlavorText: It has the trait of cheering on its fellow POKéMON. By shorting out the electricity it releases from its paws, it creates pom-poms for cheering.

Name: Plusle
FlavorText: It cheers on partners while scattering sparks from its body. It climbs telephone poles to absorb electricity.

Name: Minun
FlavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

Name: Minun
FlavorText: Minun loves to cheer on its partner in battle. It gives off sparks from its body while it is doing so. If its partner is in trouble, this Pokémon gives off increasing amounts of sparks.

Name: Minun
FlavorText: Minun is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.

Name: Minun
FlavorText: Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.

Name: Minun
FlavorText: At a meeting of POKéMON academics, it was announced that simultaneous exposure to electricity from a PLUSLE and MINUN will promote circulation and boost vitality.

Name: Minun
FlavorText: Its dislike of water makes it take shelter under the eaves of houses in rain. It uses pom-poms made of sparks for cheering.

Name: Volbeat
FlavorText: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise’s sweet aroma.

Name: Volbeat
FlavorText: Volbeat’s tail glows like a lightbulb. With other Volbeat, it uses its tail to draw geometric shapes in the night sky. This Pokémon loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

Name: Volbeat
FlavorText: With the arrival of night, Volbeat emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This Pokémon is attracted by the sweet aroma of Illumise.

Name: Volbeat
FlavorText: It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

Name: Volbeat
FlavorText: It emits light from its tail to communicate. It loves the sweet aroma given off by ILLUMISE.

Name: Volbeat
FlavorText: With their taillights lit, VOLBEAT fly in a swarm, drawing geometric designs in the night sky. They move their nests if their pond water becomes dirty.

Name: Illumise
FlavorText: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

Name: Illumise
FlavorText: Illumise leads a flight of illuminated Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. This Pokémon is said to earn greater respect from its peers by composing more complex designs in the sky.

Name: Illumise
FlavorText: Illumise attracts a swarm of Volbeat using a sweet fragrance. Once the Volbeat have gathered, this Pokémon leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.

Name: Illumise
FlavorText: Its fragrance attracts a swarm of Volbeat, so they draw over 200 patterns in the night sky.

Name: Illumise
FlavorText: A nocturnal POKéMON that becomes active upon nightfall. It leads a VOLBEAT swarm to draw patterns in the night sky. Over 200 different patterns have been confirmed.

Name: Illumise
FlavorText: It guides VOLBEAT to draw signs in night skies. There are scientists that study the patterns it creates.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Though beautiful, it has highly poisonous thorns. There is an old tradition in my homeland wherein one would send these thorns to an opponent to challenge them to a duel.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: The beautiful flowers on its arms have toxic thorns. Don’t even think about picking those flowers.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Roselia raised on clean drinking water are known to grow vividly colored flowers.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: On extremely rare occasions, a Roselia is said to appear with its flowers in unusual colors. The thorns on this Pokémon’s head contain a vicious poison.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this Pokémon brings serenity to living things.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: The more healthy the Roselia, the more pleasant its flowers’ aroma. Its scent deeply relaxes people.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: A ROSELIA that drinks nutritionally rich springwater blooms with lovely flowers. The fragrance of its flowers has the effect of making its foes careless.

Name: Gulpin
FlavorText: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.

Name: Gulpin
FlavorText: There is nothing its stomach can’t digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.

Name: Gulpin
FlavorText: Almost all its body is its stomach. Its harsh digestive juices quickly dissolve anything it swallows.

Name: Gulpin
FlavorText: Most of Gulpin’s body is made up of its stomach—its heart and brain are very small in comparison. This Pokémon’s stomach contains special enzymes that dissolve anything.

Name: Gulpin
FlavorText: Virtually all of Gulpin’s body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This Pokémon’s stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.

Name: Gulpin
FlavorText: This POKéMON’s stomach fluid can even digest scrap iron. In one gulp, it can swallow something that is as large as itself.

Name: Gulpin
FlavorText: Most of GULPIN’s body is made up of its stomach - its heart and brain are very small in comparison. This POKéMON’s stomach contains special enzymes that dissolve anything.

Name: Swalot
FlavorText: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.

Name: Swalot
FlavorText: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

Name: Swalot
FlavorText: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

Name: Swalot
FlavorText: Swalot has no teeth, so what it eats, it swallows whole, no matter what. Its cavernous mouth yawns widely. An automobile tire could easily fit inside this Pokémon’s mouth.

Name: Swalot
FlavorText: When Swalot spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this Pokémon gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.

Name: Swalot
FlavorText: Its powerful stomach acid is capable of digesting almost anything. The one thing in the whole world a SWALOT can’t digest is its own stomach.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: These Pokémon have sharp fangs and powerful jaws. Sailors avoid Carvanha dens at all costs.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: They’re such cowards that they won’t hunt alone. When five or so of them get together, they suddenly turn ferocious!

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: If they scent the faintest trace of blood, they rush to attack en masse. When alone, they’re rather cowardly.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: Each school has its own territory. Any intruders are mercilessly attacked with fangs bared.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: If anything invades Carvanha’s territory, it will swarm and tear at the intruder with its pointed fangs. On its own, however, this Pokémon turns suddenly timid.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: Carvanha’s strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this Pokémon.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: It lives in massive rivers that course through jungles. It swarms prey that enter its territory.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: They form packs to attack boats and rip out their hulls to sink them. They live in rivers in the jungle.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: CARVANHA attack ships in swarms, making them sink. Although it is said to be a very vicious POKéMON, it timidly flees as soon as it finds itself alone.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The moment it charges into its opponent, sharp spikes pop out of Sharpedo’s head, leaving its opponent with deep wounds.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The yellow patterns it bears are old scars. The energy from Mega Evolution runs through them, causing it sharp pain and suffering.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: As a consequence of Mega Evolution, its combative instincts exploded. The yellow marks it bears are scars from a long history of battles.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The spines sprouting from its head are transformed fangs. If they’re injured or broken off, the spines will regenerate countless times.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as the Bully of the Sea.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sea. Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls home will be attacked—no exceptions.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It’s very sensitive to the scent of blood.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: People believe that carrying one of its discarded fangs will prevent mishaps at sea, so the fangs are made into accessories.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokémon became a victim of overfishing.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron. It is known as the bully of the sea.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Sharpedo can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting seawater out of its backside. This Pokémon’s drawback is its inability to swim long distances.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,” Sharpedo is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these Pokémon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as “The Bully of the Sea.”

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The vicious and sly gangster of the sea. Its skin is specially textured to minimize drag in water. Its speed tops out at over 75 miles per hour.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The ruffian of the seas, it has fangs that crunch through iron. It swims by jetting water from its rear.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nostrils.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: Due to their memories of when they once lived on land, pods of them will, very rarely, wash up on shore.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It swims along with its mouth open and swallows down seawater along with its food. It sprays excess water out of its nostrils.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It loves to startle people. It fills itself up with seawater and plays by bouncing around like a ball.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: Wailmer can store water inside its body to transform itself into a ball for bouncing around on the ground. By filling itself up with more water, this Pokémon can elevate the height of its bounces.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: Wailmer’s nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful Pokémon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: While this POKéMON usually lives in the sea, it can survive on land, although not too long. It loses vitality if its body becomes dried out.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It’s the biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: When a small Wailmer is attacked by Sharpedo or Dhelmise, its whole pod works together to protect it.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: They eat so many fish Pokémon that when Wailord become too numerous, fishermen have to chase them off.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: Wailord pursue their prey in pods. With their large mouths, they can swallow entire schools of Wishiwashi whole.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: When chasing prey, Wailord herds them by leaping out of the water and making a humongous splash. It is breathtaking to see this Pokémon leaping out of the sea with others in its pod.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: Wailord is the largest of all identified Pokémon up to now. This giant Pokémon swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It is the largest of all identified Pokémon. They jump as a pack to herd their prey.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It breathes through nostrils that it raises above the sea. By inhaling to its maximum capacity, a WAILORD can dive close to 10,000 feet beneath the waves.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It is among the largest of all POKéMON. It herds prey in a pack then swallows the massed prey in one gulp.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing Numel down.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Numel stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit within its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens. In that event, the Pokémon’s body grows heavy and its movements become sluggish.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Numel is extremely dull witted—it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees F. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: A NUMEL stores boiling magma in the hump on its back. It is a hardy POKéMON that can transport a 220-pound load. It has served humans at work since long ago.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: NUMEL stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees F within its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens. In that event, the POKéMON’s body grows heavy and its movements become sluggish.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This POKéMON’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: The humps on Camerupt’s back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This Pokémon apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: A POKéMON that lives in the crater of a volcano. Every 10 years, the volcanoes on its back erupt violently. Research is under way on the cause of eruption.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this POKéMON’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is in a tough situation.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal to produce energy. When it has burned through all of its coal, it becomes unable to move.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: You can tell how it’s feeling by the smoke spouting from its shell. Tremendous velocity is a sign of good health.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: If the fire burning within its shell goes out, it will die. Those who wish to raise one in their home must always keep something flammable at hand.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: Torkoal generates energy by burning coal. It grows weaker as the fire dies down. When it is preparing for battle, this Pokémon burns more coal.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: Torkoal digs through mountains in search of coal. If it finds some, it fills hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it. If it is attacked, this Pokémon spouts thick black smoke to beat a retreat.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It battles using energy it gets from burning coal. When loosing smoke from its nostrils, it lets off a sound that is similar to a locomotive’s horn.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal inside its shell. If it is attacked, it belches thick, black smoke and flees.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: Using its tail like a spring, it keeps its heart beating by bouncing constantly. If it stops, it dies.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl on its head amplifies its psychic powers.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: It bounces constantly, using its tail like a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: Spoink keeps a pearl on top of its head. The pearl functions to amplify this Pokémon’s psychokinetic powers. It is therefore on a constant search for a bigger pearl.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: Spoink bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this Pokémon cannot afford to stop bouncing—if it stops, its heart will stop.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: A POKéMON that manipulates psychic power at will. It doesn’t stop bouncing even when it is asleep. It loves eating mushrooms that grow underground.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: It apparently dies if it stops bouncing about. It carries a pearl from CLAMPERL on its head.

Name: Spoink
FlavorText: SPOINK bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this POKéMON cannot afford to stop bouncing - if it stops, its heart will stop.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes’ minds.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to wield its fantastic powers. When it is doing so, it dances bizarrely. This Pokémon’s black pearls are valuable as works of art.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this Pokémon uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psycho-power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: It stores power in the black pearls on its forehead. When it uses psychic power, it performs an odd dance step. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

Name: Grumpig
FlavorText: It can gain control over foes by doing odd dance steps. The black pearls on its forehead are precious gems.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Their tottering steps hinder the aim of foes.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: Each Spinda’s spot pattern is different. With its stumbling movements, it evades opponents’ attacks brilliantly!

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: Its steps are shaky and stumbling. Walking for a long time makes it feel sick.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: Each and every Spinda has a slightly different configuration of spots. There are collectors who enjoy the tiny differences in their spot patterns.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it’s walking in a straight line.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: No two Spinda are said to have identical spot patterns on their hides. This Pokémon moves in a curious manner as if it is stumbling in dizziness. Its lurching movements can cause the opponent to become confused.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: All the Spinda that exist in the world are said to have utterly unique spot patterns. The shaky, tottering steps of this Pokémon give it the appearance of dancing.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: It is distinguished by a pattern of spots that is always different. Its unsteady, tottering walk has the effect of fouling its foe’s aim.

Name: Spinda
FlavorText: No two SPINDA are said to have identical patterns. It confuses foes with its stumbling motions.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: It builds nests that double as traps, lying in wait for its prey to get caught. When night falls, it digs itself a spot beneath the sand to sleep.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: Its jaws are strong enough to crush rocks but so heavy that it can’t get up if it flips over. Sandile seize those moments as their chance.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: As it digs through the sand, its giant jaws crush any rocks that obstruct its path. It builds a funnel-shaped nest.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: It can live for a week without eating a thing. It waits patiently at the bottom of its nest for prey to appear.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: Trapinch is a patient hunter. It digs an inescapable pit in a desert and waits for its prey to come tumbling down. This Pokémon can go a whole week without access to any water.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: Trapinch’s nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand. This Pokémon patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: It lives in arid deserts. It makes a sloping pit trap in sand where it patiently awaits prey.

Name: Trapinch
FlavorText: Its big jaws crunch through boulders. Because its head is so big, it has a hard time getting back upright if it tips over onto its back.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: To help make its wings grow, it dissolves quantities of prey in its digestive juices and guzzles them down every day.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: It vibrates its wings to send out odd sound waves. Trainers who are with it need earplugs.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: It vibrates its wings to generate ultrasonic waves, causing its prey to faint. Then it buries the prey alive in the sand to preserve it.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: Rather than using its underdeveloped wings for flight, it rubs them together, producing ultrasonic waves to attack its enemies.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: Vibrava’s wings have not yet completed the process of growing. Rather than flying long distances, they are more useful for generating ultrasonic waves by vibrating.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: To make prey faint, Vibrava generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. This Pokémon’s ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: It generates ultrasonic waves by violently flapping its wings. After making its prey faint, it melts the prey with acid.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: It vibrates its wings vigorously, creating ultrasonic waves that cause serious headaches.

Name: Vibrava
FlavorText: It looses ultrasonic waves by rubbing its wings together. Since a VIBRAVA’s wings are still in the process of growing, it can only fly short distances.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as the Desert Spirit.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: It is nicknamed the Desert Spirit because the flapping of its wings sounds like a woman singing.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: People continue to have their hearts stolen by its enchanting songs and find themselves stranded in the desert.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: By flapping their wings, Flygon cause sandstorms that conceal Krookodile. The team then splits the prey they catch.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: The flapping of its wings sounds something like singing. Those lured by the sound are enveloped in a sandstorm, becoming Flygon’s prey.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: Flygon whips up a sandstorm by flapping its wings. The wings create a series of notes that sound like singing. Because the “singing” is the only thing that can be heard in a sandstorm, this Pokémon is said to be the desert spirit.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: Flygon is nicknamed “the elemental spirit of the desert.” Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this Pokémon is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: Known as “The Desert Spirit,” this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: It hides itself by kicking up desert sand with its wings. Red covers shield its eyes from sand.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as “The Desert Spirit.”

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: It is nicknamed “The Desert Spirit” because the flapping of its wings sounds like a woman singing.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: The flapping of its wings sounds like singing. To prevent detection by enemies, it hides itself by flapping up a cloud of desert sand.

Name: Flygon
FlavorText: FLYGON is nicknamed “the elemental  spirit of the desert.” Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this POKéMON is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: It prefers harsh environments, such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive for 30 days without water.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: The more arid and harsh the environment, the more pretty and fragrant a flower Cacnea grows. This Pokémon battles by wildly swinging its thorny arms.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this Pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: CACNEA live in deserts with virtually no rainfall. It battles by swinging its thick, spiked arms. Once a year, a yellow flower blooms.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day’s desert heat.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: If a traveler is going through a desert in the thick of night, Cacturne will follow in a ragtag group. The Pokémon are biding their time, waiting for the traveler to tire and become incapable of moving.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: After spending thousands of years in harsh deserts, its blood transformed into the same substances as sand. It is nocturnal, so it hunts at night.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: It can’t relax if it or its surroundings are not clean. It wipes off dirt with its wings.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: Its wings are like cotton tufts. If it perches on someone’s head, it looks like a cotton hat.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: Since Swablu looks like a cumulus cloud, foes can have a hard time finding it. Apparently its wings turned white over many generations.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: Its cottony wings are full of air, making them light and fluffy to the touch. Swablu takes diligent care of its wings.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: Swablu loves to make things clean. If it spots something dirty, it will wipe and polish it with its cottony wings. If its wings become dirty, this Pokémon finds a stream and showers itself.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: Swablu has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This Pokémon is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: For some reason, it likes to land on people’s heads softly and act like it’s a hat.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: Its wings bring cottony clouds to mind. It grooms with springwater and loves to sit on heads.

Name: Swablu
FlavorText: A POKéMON that has wings like cottony clouds. After enduring winter, in which little food is available, SWABLU flocks move closer to towns in the spring.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: It looks like a fluffy cloud when it is in flight. It hums with its soprano voice.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a kind disposition, but if it’s provoked, it will threaten opponents with shrill cries before attacking them without mercy.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: As it flies in a calm and relaxed manner, Altaria performs a humming song that would enrapture any audience.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: Altaria sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This Pokémon catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: Altaria dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this Pokémon makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you’re in a dream.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: It hums in a beautiful soprano voice. It flies among white clouds in the blue sky. It launches intensely hot fireballs from its mouth.

Name: Altaria
FlavorText: If you hear a beautiful melody trilling deep among mountains far from people, it is ALTARIA’s humming.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: If it comes across a Seviper, its fur bristles and it assumes its battle pose. Its sharp claws are its best weapon.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: It’s Seviper’s archrival. To threaten those it encounters, it fans out the claws on its front paws.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: It has feuded with Seviper for many generations. Its sharp claws are its greatest weapons.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: Zangoose usually stays on all fours, but when angered, it gets up on its hind legs and extends its claws. This Pokémon shares a bitter rivalry with Seviper that dates back over generations.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: Memories of battling its archrival Seviper are etched into every cell of Zangoose’s body. This Pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a Seviper nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: It has feuded with Seviper for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: When it battles, it stands on its hind legs and attacks with its sharply clawed forelegs. Its fur bristles if it encounters any SEVIPER.

Name: Zangoose
FlavorText: Memories of battling its arch-rival SEVIPER are etched into every cell of ZANGOOSE’s body. This POKéMON adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It’s Zangoose’s archrival.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: It sharpens its swordlike tail on hard rocks. It hides in tall grass and strikes unwary prey with venomous fangs.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: For many generations, it has feuded with Zangoose. It whets its bladed tail on rocks for battle.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: Seviper’s swordlike tail serves two purposes—it slashes foes and douses them with secreted poison. This Pokémon will not give up its long-running blood feud with Zangoose.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: Seviper shares a generations-long feud with Zangoose. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This Pokémon attacks using its sword-edged tail.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: SEVIPER and ZANGOOSE are eternal rivals. It counters a ZANGOOSE’s dazzling agility with its swordlike tail, which also oozes a horrible poison.

Name: Seviper
FlavorText: SEVIPER’s swordlike tail serves two purposes - it slashes foes and douses them with secreted poison. This POKéMON will not give up its long-running blood feud with ZANGOOSE.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: It becomes active on nights with a full moon, so it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: Lunatone becomes active around the time of the full moon. Instead of walking, it moves by floating in midair. The Pokémon’s intimidating red eyes cause all those who see it to become transfixed with fear.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteoroid fell. As a result, some people theorize that this Pokémon came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: It becomes very active on the night of a full moon. This POKéMON was first discovered 40 years ago at the site of a meteor strike.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: Its health ebbs and flows with the lunar cycle. It brims with power when exposed to the light of the full moon.

Name: Lunatone
FlavorText: LUNATONE was discovered at a location where a meteorite fell. As a result, some people theorize that this POKéMON came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: This new Pokémon species is rumored to be an avatar of the sun. The Pokémon gives off light while spinning.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: Sunlight is the source of Solrock’s power. It is said to possess the ability to read the emotions of others. This Pokémon gives off intense heat while rotating its body.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: Solrock is a new species of Pokémon that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this Pokémon releases intensely bright light.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: It absorbs solar energy during the day. Always expressionless, it can sense what its foe is thinking.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: A new Pokémon species, rumored to be from the sun. It gives off light while spinning.

Name: Solrock
FlavorText: Solar energy is the source of this  POKéMON’s power. On sunny days, groups of SOLROCK line up facing the sun and absorb its light.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey’s location.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Makes its home in swamps with murky water. The poor visibility hides this Pokémon from predators, and the slime on its body makes grasping it difficult.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its whiskers make a superb radar. They are used to locate prey, even in the murkiest of water.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: It coats its entire body with a slimy fluid so it can squirm and slip away if grabbed.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its whiskers are filled with nerves. They can sense smells and flavors just as a person’s nose or tongue would.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its entire body is gooey. When pecked at by bird Pokémon, it slips and slides its way to freedom.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its slippery body is hard to grasp, so much so that there are festivals where people compete to see how many they can catch barehanded.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Barboach’s body is covered with a slimy film. If a foe grabs it, this Pokémon just slips out of the enemy’s grip. This Pokémon grows weak if the slimy coating dries up.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Barboach’s sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This Pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: BARBOACH uses its whiskers to taste things just as a person uses his or her tongue to taste things.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its body is covered with a slimy film. The film acts as a barrier to prevent germs in muddy water from entering the BARBOACH’s body.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Strikes its caudal fin against the swamp bed to shake the ground and startle its prey. It will then swallow the fleeing prey whole. People mistook this behavior as the cause of earthquakes.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: As a result of causing tremors by thrashing about, it developed the ability to foretell real quakes.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It is very territorial. It repels foes by setting off tremors that extend over a three-mile radius.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It claims a large swamp to itself. If a foe comes near it, it sets off tremors by thrashing around.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything—if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Its vision is not that good. It senses vibrations in the water with its whiskers to determine the location of its prey.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Whiscash shakes the ground at high intensities to intimidate its opponents. It swallows its prey whole—along with mud from the swamp floor.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: A glutton that devours anything that moves, it quietly lurks at the bottom of swamps, lying in wait for prey.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: If Whiscash goes on a wild rampage, it sets off a quake-like tremor with a radius of over three miles. This Pokémon has the ability to predict real earthquakes.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Whiscash is extremely territorial. Just one of these Pokémon will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything--if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Mysteriously, it can foretell earthquakes. In the daytime, it sleeps in mud at the bottom of a pond. When it awakens, it continually feeds throughout the night.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It makes its nest at the bottom of  swamps. It will eat anything - if it is alive, WHISCASH will eat it.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: It can adapt very well to its environment. Feebas and Corphish are about the only Pokémon to live in stagnant ditches.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Individuals that have been set free by Trainers who could no longer raise them have become common, and they can now be found in Alola.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Corphish catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food—it will eat anything. This Pokémon has no trouble living in filthy water.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Corphish were originally foreign Pokémon that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This Pokémon is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Once it grips prey with its large pincers, it will never let go, no matter what. It is a hardy POKéMON that can thrive in any environment.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: It came from overseas. It is a very hardy creature that will quickly proliferate, even in polluted streams.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: CORPHISH catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food - it will eat anything. This POKéMON has no trouble living in filthy water.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Its pincers often fall off. Unlike with Crabrawler or Clauncher, the meat in its claws is utterly nasty and stinking.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Its temperament is rough and it loves to fight, but as soon as its pincers break off, it turns cowardly. It stays timid until they grow back.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Crawdaunt molts (sheds) its shell regularly. Immediately after molting, its shell is soft and tender. Until the shell hardens, this Pokémon hides in its streambed burrow to avoid attack from its foes.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Crawdaunt has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this Pokémon, making them desolate places.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: A brutish POKéMON that loves to battle. A veteran CRAWDAUNT that has prevailed in hundreds of battles has giant pincers marked with countless scars.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: When they find others of their kind, they cry out loudly and gather together. Large numbers of them can be found in old graveyards.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: Depictions of Pokémon similar to Baltoy have been found on the walls of caves where primitive humans lived.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: As soon as it spots others of its kind, Baltoy congregates with them and then begins crying noisily in unison. This Pokémon sleeps while cleverly balancing itself on its one foot.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: Baltoy moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this Pokémon living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: Discovered in ancient ruins, it moves by spinning around and forms a group when it finds others.

Name: Baltoy
FlavorText: A BALTOY moves by spinning on its single foot. It has been depicted in murals  adorning the walls of a once-bustling city in an ancient age.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: An ancient clay figurine was exposed to a mysterious ray of light, and it came to life as a Pokémon.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: The ancient people who made it apparently modeled it after something that descended from the sky. It fires beams from both arms.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: If it gets wet, its body melts. When rain starts to fall, it wraps its whole body up with its psychic powers to protect itself.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: Claydol is an enigma that appeared from a clay statue made by an ancient civilization dating back 20,000 years. This Pokémon shoots beams from both its hands.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: Claydol are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This Pokémon moves about while levitating.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokémon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.

Name: Claydol
FlavorText: A CLAYDOL sleeps while hovering in midair. Its arms are separate from its body. They are kept floating by the POKéMON’s manipulation of psychic power.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: Lileep clings to rocks on the seabed. When prey comes close, this Pokémon entangles it with petallike tentacles.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It sticks to rocks with its powerful suckers and can’t be washed away no matter how rough the surf gets.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: In ancient times, it lived in warm seas. It disguised itself as seaweed to ambush its prey and devoured them whole when they got close.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: Lileep is an ancient Pokémon that was regenerated from a fossil. It remains permanently anchored to a rock. From its immobile perch, this Pokémon intently scans for prey with its two eyes.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: Lileep became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient Pokémon attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles shaped like flower petals.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It disguises its tentacles as flowers to attract and catch prey. It became extinct in ancient times.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It disguises itself as seaweed by making its tentacles sway. Unsuspecting prey that come too close are swallowed whole. It became extinct 100 million years ago.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It became extinct roughly 100 million years ago. It was regenerated from a fossil using advanced techniques.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: LILEEP became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient POKéMON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Once Cradily catches prey in its tentacles, it digests them whole and absorbs their nutrients.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It has short legs and can’t walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: This carnivorous Pokémon lived in primordial seas. It catches prey in its eight tentacles and dissolves them with digestive fluid as it eats.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Normally, it lived on shallow sea shoals. When the tide went out, this Pokémon came up on land to search for prey.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Cradily’s body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This Pokémon secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Cradily roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This Pokémon freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It ensnares prey with its eight tentacles. It then melts the prey with a strong acid before feeding.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It lives in warm seas. Its heavy body weighs it down so it won’t get washed away in rough weather.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It drags its heavy body along the seafloor. It makes its nest in the shallows of warm seas. CRADILY can be seen on beaches when the tide goes out.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: This Pokémon ancestor was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with its claws.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: Anorith can swim swiftly by pulling its eight wings through the water like oars on a boat. This Pokémon is an ancestor of modern bug Pokémon.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100,000,000 years ago, hunting with its pair of claws.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: This is one kind of primeval bug Pokémon. With eight wings, it could apparently swim a lot faster than you’d expect.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: When restored Anorith are released into the ocean, they don’t thrive, because the water composition has changed since their era.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: Anorith is said to be a type of Pokémon predecessor, with eight wings at the sides of its body. This Pokémon swam in the primordial sea by undulating these eight wings.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: Anorith was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive Pokémon once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: It is a kind of Pokémon progenitor. It uses its extending claws to catch prey hiding among rocks on the seafloor.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: An ancestral Pokémon that lived in the ocean. Over time, its eight feet transformed into wings.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: It was resurrected from a fossil using the power of science. It swims by undulating the eight wings at its sides. They were feet that adapted to life in the sea.

Name: Anorith
FlavorText: ANORITH is said to be a type of  POKéMON predecessor, with eight wings at the sides of its body. This POKéMON swam in the primordial sea by undulating these eight wings.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: Though it lives on land, it’s also a good swimmer. It dives into the ocean in search of prey, using its sharp claws to take down its quarry.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: After evolution, this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: Armaldo adapted from living in water to living on land. It has been determined that it is the ancestor of some bug Pokémon.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: It lived on land and went out into the sea to hunt for prey. Its sharp claws were its greatest weapon.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: Armaldo is a Pokémon species that became extinct in prehistoric times. This Pokémon is said to have walked on its hind legs, which would have been more convenient for life on land.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: Armaldo’s tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This Pokémon’s two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: Protected by a hard shell, its body is very sturdy. It skewers prey with its claws to feed.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: Its enormous, retractable claws can cut through most anything. Its entire body is clad in sturdy plates.

Name: Armaldo
FlavorText: ARMALDO usually lives on land. However, when it hunts for prey, it dives beneath the ocean. It swims around using its two large wings.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It eats anything, so it can even live in polluted streams and lakes. No one pays any attention to it.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: They are famous for their shabby appearance. Although populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon’s marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Because of its wretched appearance, most people pay it no attention, but there are some who collect Feebas—and Feebas alone!

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: They look ragged, so no one catches them. They look like they’d taste bad, so predators won’t eat them. And their numbers continue to grow.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: A tough Pokémon that is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn’t popular.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: While Feebas’s body is in tatters, it has a hardy and tenacious life force that enables it to live anywhere. However, this Pokémon is also slow and dimwitted, making it an easy catch.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Feebas’s fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this Pokémon is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It is famous for its shabby appearance. While populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: FEEBAS live in ponds that are heavily infested with weeds. Because of its hopelessly shabby appearance, it seems as if few TRAINERS raise it.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Ridiculed for its shabby appearance, it is ignored by researchers. It lives in ponds choked with weeds.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It is the world’s most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: When people bicker, it is said to arise from the depths of lakes to becalm violent hearts.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It’s said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you’re feeling.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Its dwelling place is the bottom of big lakes. Those who behold its loveliness are said to have their hearts purified.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: While Milotic is said to be the most beautiful Pokémon, Trainers who like Feebas and have raised it are seemingly disappointed by Milotic.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people’s minds and hearts.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic live at the bottom of large lakes. When this Pokémon’s body glows a vivid pink, it releases a pulsing wave of energy that brings soothing calm to troubled hearts.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic is said to be the most beautiful of all the Pokémon. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic is breathtakingly beautiful. Those that see it are said to forget their combative spirits.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It is said to live at the bottom of large lakes. Considered to be the most beautiful of all POKéMON, it has been depicted in paintings and statues.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: MILOTIC live at the bottom of large lakes. When this POKéMON’s body glows a vivid pink, it releases a pulsing wave of energy that brings soothing calm to restless spirits.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form when caught in a hailstorm. Its whole body is chilled, and its skin is partially frozen!

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes when hit by hail. In an experiment where it was placed in a freezer, it didn’t change to this form.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form when caught in a hailstorm. Its cold skin is as smooth as ice.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes when covered in snow. Its body becomes an ice-like material, with a temperature near 23 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokémon didn’t change to this form.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Castform changes to this form when rain hits it. Its body is soft and slightly swollen with water.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form during a downpour of rain. Its body retains moisture and gets slippery.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes when soaked with rain. When its body is compressed, water will seep out as if from a sponge.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes on bright days. In an experiment where Castform was placed in front of a heater, it didn’t change to this form.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form when basking in fair weather. Its body is warm and toasty.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes on the brightest of days. Its skin is unexpectedly hot to the touch, so approach with care.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform’s disposition!

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Although its form changes with the weather, that is apparently the result of a chemical reaction and not the result of its own free will.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Its form changes on its own, due to its cells’ sensitive reactions to temperature and humidity.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Castform borrows the power of nature to transform itself into the guises of the sun, rain, and snow-clouds. This Pokémon’s feelings change with the weather.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Castform’s appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud, depending on the weather.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This Pokémon can change its cells, taking different forms based on the temperature and humidity.

Name: Castform
