FlavorText: Temperature and weather affect its cellular structure, so this Pokémon changes form according to the weather.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: It alters its form depending on the weather. Changes in the climate such as the temperature and humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud,  depending on the weather.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: CASTFORM borrows the power of nature to transform itself into the guises of the sun, rain clouds, and snow clouds. This POKéMON’s feelings change with the weather.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: It can freely change its body’s color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn’t change, however.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: Its color changes for concealment and also when its mood or health changes. The darker the color, the healthier it is.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: It changes its hue to blend into its surroundings. If no one takes notice of it for too long, it will pout and never reveal itself.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: Kecleon alters its body coloration to blend in with its surroundings, allowing it to sneak up on its prey unnoticed. Then it lashes out with its long, stretchy tongue to instantly ensnare the unsuspecting target.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: Kecleon is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception—this Pokémon can’t change the zigzag pattern on its belly.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: A POKéMON that has the ability to alter its body colors to match its surroundings. A KECLEON reverts to its original colors if it is startled.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: It changes body color to blend in with its surroundings. It also changes color if it is happy or sad.

Name: Kecleon
FlavorText: KECLEON is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception - this POKéMON can’t change the zigzag pattern on its belly.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: It feeds on the dark emotions of sadness and hatred, which make it grow steadily stronger.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: They love vengeful emotions and hang in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: There’s a proverb that says, “Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk.”

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: It eats up emotions like malice, jealousy, and resentment, so some people are grateful for its presence.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: Shuppet grows by feeding on dark emotions, such as vengefulness and envy, in the hearts of people. It roams through cities in search of grudges that taint people.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: Shuppet is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this Pokémon will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that person’s home.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice--or so it’s said. It’s very active at night.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice, or so it’s said. It’s very active at night.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: This POKéMON roams about deep in the night seeking such negative emotions as grudges and envy. It retreats to its nest when the sun begins to rise.

Name: Shuppet
FlavorText: SHUPPET grows by feeding on dark emotions, such as vengefulness and  envy, in the hearts of people. It roams through cities in search of grudges that taint people.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: Mega Evolution increases its vindictiveness, and the cursing power that was held back by its zipper comes spilling out.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: Extraordinary energy amplifies its cursing power to such an extent that it can’t help but curse its own Trainer.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: A doll bore a grudge over being junked, and it became a Pokémon. It seeks the child that disowned it.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: It’s a stuffed toy that was thrown away and became possessed, ever searching for the one who threw it away so it can exact its revenge.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: A cursed energy permeated the stuffing of a discarded and forgotten plush doll, giving it new life as Banette. The Pokémon’s energy would escape if it were to ever open its mouth.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: Banette generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This Pokémon was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge of being thrown away. It seeks the child who disowned it.

Name: Banette
FlavorText: An abandoned plush doll became this POKéMON. They are said to live in garbage dumps and wander about in search of the children that threw them away.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: I’ve heard that the children of Hisui all begin to behave once they’ve been told the story of how this Pokémon roams about before the witching hour to spirit away misbehaving children.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: It doggedly pursues its prey wherever the prey goes. However, the chase is abandoned at sunrise.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: Making itself invisible, it silently sneaks up to prey. It has the ability to slip through thick walls.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it’s said.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: Duskull wanders lost among the deep darkness of midnight. There is an oft-told admonishment given to misbehaving children that this Pokémon will spirit away bad children who earn scoldings from their mothers.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokémon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away--or so it’s said.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: It doggedly pursues its prey wherever it goes. However, the chase is abandoned at sunrise.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: It loves the crying of children. It startles bad kids by passing through walls and making them cry.

Name: Duskull
FlavorText: A glare from its single scarlet eye makes even burly grown-ups freeze in utter fear. It is a nocturnal POKéMON that roams about under the cloak of darkness.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: There are rumors that peeking inside its bandage-wrapped body will cause one to get pulled in through the gaps between the bandages, never to return. I’ve been too scared to verify.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: Its body is hollow. It is said that those who look into its body are sucked into the void.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: It seeks drifting will-o’-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: Dusclops absorbs anything, however large the object may be. This Pokémon hypnotizes its foe by waving its hands in a macabre manner and by bringing its single eye to bear. The hypnotized foe is made to do Dusclops’s bidding.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: Dusclops’s body is completely hollow—there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This Pokémon will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: It is thought that its body is hollow with only a spectral ball of fire burning inside. However, no one has been able to confirm this theory as fact.

Name: Dusclops
FlavorText: DUSCLOPS’s body is completely hollow - there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKéMON will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Because it continually ate only its favorite fruit, the fruit started growing around its neck.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: The bunches of fruit growing around the necks of Tropius in Alola are especially sweet compared to those in other regions.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of Tropius. This Pokémon flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: The bunches of fruit around Tropius’s neck are very popular with children. This Pokémon loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It’s a highly favored tropical snack.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: It flies by flapping its broad leaves. The bunch of fruit that grows around its neck is deliciously sweet. In the spring, it scatters pollen from its neck.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: Can emit waves of air powerful enough to knock out prey taller than itself. I hypothesize that it amplifies the faint sound of wind within its body.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: Chimecho emits ultrasonic cries. It floats on the wind to travel great distances.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: To knock foes flying, it makes the air shudder with its cries. It converses using seven cries.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: In high winds, Chimecho cries as it hangs from a tree branch or the eaves of a building using a suction cup on its head. This Pokémon plucks berries with its long tail and eats them.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: Chimecho makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this Pokémon becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: Its cries echo inside its hollow body to emerge as beautiful notes for startling and repelling foes.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: They fly about very actively when the hot season arrives. They communicate among themselves using seven different and distinguishing cries.

Name: Chimecho
FlavorText: It travels by riding on winds. It cleverly uses its long tail to pluck nuts and berries, which it loves to eat.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: It converts the energy from Mega Evolution into an intimidating aura. Fainthearted people expire from shock at the sight of it.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Normally, it dislikes fighting, so it really hates changing to this form for battles.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: As the energy of Mega Evolution fills it, its fur bristles. What you see on its back are not true wings, and this Pokémon isn’t able to fly.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: When this Pokémon whips the winglike fur on its back as though beating its wings, it sends an intimidating aura flying at its opponents.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: It senses coming disasters and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Because of this Pokémon’s ability to detect danger, people mistook Absol as a bringer of doom.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: The elderly call it the disaster Pokémon and detest it, but interest in its power to predict disasters is on the rise.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: The only thing unlucky about Absol is its appearance. It protects fields and warns people of disaster, so one ought to be grateful for it.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Although it’s said to bring disaster, in actuality, this Pokémon possesses a calm disposition and warns people of any crises that loom.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Long ago, superstitions were spread about it, saying it brought disaster. This fed a hatred of it, and it was driven deep into the mountains.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Absol has the ability to foretell the coming of natural disasters. It lives in a harsh, rugged mountain environment. This Pokémon very rarely ventures down from the mountains.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Every time Absol appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster Pokémon.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom bringer.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: It appears from deep in the mountains to warn people about upcoming disasters it has sensed with its horn.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: Rumored to sense disasters with its horn, it became a target. It fled deep into the mountains.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: It has the ability to foretell natural disasters. Its life span is over a hundred years.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: It sharply senses even subtle changes in the sky and the land to predict natural disasters. It is a long-lived POKéMON that has a life-span of 100 years.

Name: Absol
FlavorText: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom-bringer.

Name: Wynaut
FlavorText: They grow strong by pushing up against one another en masse. They love eating sweet fruit.

Name: Wynaut
FlavorText: It tends to move in a pack with others. They cluster in a tight group to sleep in a cave.

Name: Wynaut
FlavorText: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

Name: Wynaut
FlavorText: Wynaut gather on moonlit nights to play by squeezing up against each other. By being squeezed, this Pokémon gains endurance and is trained to dole out powerful counterattacks.

Name: Wynaut
FlavorText: Wynaut can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this Pokémon will be slapping the ground with its tail.

Name: Wynaut
FlavorText: It grows strong by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.

Name: Wynaut
FlavorText: A WYNAUT loves to eat sweet fruits. It cleverly picks fruits using its earlike arms. They gather in fruit gardens, drawn by the fragrance.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: It is said that a home visited by a Snorunt will prosper. It can withstand cold of −150 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: Arrives alongside the first snow. It’s thought that homes Snorunt visit will prosper for many generations. By tradition, one might offer a lump of ice made from pure water at one’s front door.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: In some snowy lands, certain folklore says a house will prosper if a Snorunt lives there.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as −150 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: It’s said that if they are seen at midnight, they’ll cause heavy snow. They eat snow and ice to survive.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: Rich people from cold areas all share childhood memories of playing with Snorunt.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: It feeds mainly on ice and snow. It’s only able to survive in a limited number of places in the warm Alola region.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: Their numbers seem to have rapidly increased in Alola. Custom has it that houses where Snorunt live will be prosperous for generations to come.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: Snorunt survives by eating only snow and ice. Old folklore claims that a house visited by this Pokémon is sure to prosper for many generations to come.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: Snorunt live in regions with heavy snowfall. In seasons without snow, such as spring and summer, this Pokémon steals away to live quietly among stalactites and stalagmites deep in caverns.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: In the snow country, certain folklore says a house will prosper if a Snorunt lives there.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: They tend to move about in groups of around five SNORUNT. In snowy regions, it is said that when they are seen late at night, snowfall will arrive by morning.

Name: Snorunt
FlavorText: It is said that a home visited by a SNORUNT will prosper. It can withstand cold of minus 150 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: The power of Mega Evolution was so strong that it smashed Glalie’s jaw. Its inability to eat very well leaves Glalie irritated.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: When it spews stupendously cold air from its broken mouth, the entire area around it gets whited out.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: It envelops prey in its mouth, freezing them instantly. But its jaw is dislocated, so it’s unable to eat them.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: The excess energy from Mega Evolution spilled over from its mouth, breaking its jaw. It spews endless blizzards.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they’re in that frozen state, it gobbles them up.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: It covers its body with an armor of ice harder than steel. Uses its breath to freeze prey, which it then devours as if they were frozen desserts.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: To protect itself, it clad its body in an armor of ice, made by freezing moisture in the air.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: It has a body of ice that won’t melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: Its actual body is a rock that isn’t particularly hard. Glalie absorbs moisture from the air and drapes itself in an armor of ice.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: It freezes its prey and chews them whole. However, it prefers to eat Pokémon like Vanillite that are already frozen.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: Legend says a boulder on an icy mountain absorbed the distress and regrets of a stranded mountaineer, giving rise to Glalie.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: Glalie has the ability to freely control ice. For example, it can instantly freeze its prey solid. After immobilizing its prey in ice, this Pokémon enjoys eating it in leisurely fashion.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokémon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: To protect itself, it clads its body in an armor of ice, made by freezing moisture in the air.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: A GLALIE has the power to instantaneously freeze moisture in the atmosphere. A dazzling cloud of diamondlike ice crystals forms around its body.

Name: Glalie
FlavorText: GLALIE has the ability to freely control ice. For example, it can instantly freeze its foe solid. After immobilizing its foe in ice, this POKéMON enjoys eating it in leisurely fashion.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: During the season when drift ice approaches the shore, Spheal prefers living on the ice—where fewer predators lurk—rather than the land. Its fur retains heat superbly and resists harsh cold.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: As it drifts among the waves, Spheal probes the sea. As soon as it spots prey, it informs the Walrein in its herd.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It’s faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: Spheal always travels by rolling around on its ball-like body. When the season for ice floes arrives, this Pokémon can be seen rolling about on ice and crossing the sea.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: Spheal is much faster rolling than walking to get around. When groups of this Pokémon eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: They can’t swim well yet, and they move much faster by rolling. When they’re happy, they clap fins.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: It crosses the oceans by rolling itself on drifting ice. Fluffy fur keeps it warm when the temperature is below freezing.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: It is completely covered with plushy fur. As a result, it never feels the cold even when it is rolling about on ice floes or diving in the sea.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: SPHEAL is much faster rolling than  walking to get around. When groups of this POKéMON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Its white whiskers are very sensitive. Sealeo will balance Spheal on the tip of its nose, checking its scent and its feel to be sure the Spheal is healthy.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: It habitually spins things on its nose. By doing so, it learns textures and odors.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a habit of spinning round things on its nose, whether those things are Poké Balls or Spheal.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Sealeo live on top of drift ice. They go swimming when they’re on the hunt, seeking out their prey by scent.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Sealeo often balances and rolls things on the tip of its nose. While the Pokémon is rolling something, it checks the object’s aroma and texture to determine whether it likes the object or not.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Sealeo has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This Pokémon occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a Spheal on its nose.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Be it Spheal or Poké Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: It has a very sensitive nose. It touches new things with its nose to examine them.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: SEALEO live in herds on ice floes. Using its powerful flippers, it shatters ice. It dives into the sea to hunt prey five times a day.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: It touches new things with its nose to test for smell and feel. It plays by spinning SPHEAL on its nose.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Its thick tusks are strong enough to shatter drift ice. They have been known to break, but they will grow back by the next year. The Hisui region is well known for these broken tusks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold but also enemy attacks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein’s tusks keep growing throughout its life. Tusks broken in battle will grow back to their usual impressive size in a year.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein form herds of 20 to 30 individuals. When a threat appears, the herd’s leader will protect the group with its life.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein swims all over in frigid seawater while crushing icebergs with its grand, imposing tusks. Its thick layer of blubber makes enemy attacks bounce off harmlessly.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein’s two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing 10 tons with one blow. This Pokémon’s thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Not only does its thick blubber keep it warm, it also protects it from attacks. It shatters ice with its prized tusks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: To protect its herd, the leader battles anything that invades its territory, even at the cost of its life. Its tusks may snap off in battle.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It swims through icy seas while shattering ice floes with its large tusks. It is protected by its thick blubber.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: WALREIN’s two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing ten tons with one blow. This POKéMON’s thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Clamperl’s pearls are exceedingly precious. They can be more than 10 times as costly as Shellder’s pearls.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Despite its appearance, it’s carnivorous. It clamps down on its prey with both sides of its shell and doesn’t let go until they stop moving.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Clamperl grows while being protected by its rock-hard shell. When its body becomes too large to fit inside the shell, it is sure evidence that this Pokémon is getting close to evolution.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Clamperl’s sturdy shell is not only good for protection—it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown Clamperl’s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: When it evolves, it makes a mysterious pearl that amplifies psychic powers when it’s held.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: A CLAMPERL slams its shell closed on prey to prevent escape. The pearl it creates upon evolution is said to be infused with a mysterious energy.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: CLAMPERL’s sturdy shell is not only good for protection - it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERL’s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: Deep seas are their habitat. According to tradition, when Huntail wash up onshore, something unfortunate will happen.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It’s not the strongest swimmer. It wags its tail to lure in its prey and then gulps them down as soon as they get close.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: Huntail’s tail is shaped like a fish. It uses the tail to attract prey, then swallows the prey whole with its large, gaping mouth. This Pokémon swims by wiggling its slender body like a snake.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: Huntail’s presence went unnoticed by people for a long time because it lives at extreme depths in the sea. This Pokémon’s eyes can see clearly even in the murky dark depths of the ocean.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It lives deep in the sea where no light ever filters down. It lights up its small fishlike tail to attract prey.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea. It attracts prey by moving its tail in mimicry of a small animal.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: To withstand the crushing pressure of water deep under the sea, its spine is very thick and sturdy. Its tail, which is shaped like a small fish, has eyes that light up.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: It sucks bodily fluids out of its prey. The leftover meat sinks to the seafloor, where it becomes food for other Pokémon.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: The color of its body changes with the water temperature. The coloration of Gorebyss in Alola is almost blindingly vivid.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Although Gorebyss is the very picture of elegance and beauty while swimming, it is also cruel. When it spots prey, this Pokémon inserts its thin mouth into the prey’s body and drains the prey of its body fluids.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Gorebyss lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this Pokémon’s body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Its pink body becomes more vivid with the rise of water temperatures in the springtime.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: A GOREBYSS siphons the body fluids of prey through its thin, tubular mouth. Its light pink body color turns vivid when it finishes feeding.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: This rare Pokémon was discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: This Pokémon was discovered during deep-sea exploration. Its appearance hasn’t changed in 100,000,000 years, so it’s called a living fossil.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: The reason it hasn’t changed at all in a hundred million years is that it’s apparently already a perfect life-form.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Thought to have gone extinct, Relicanth was given a name that is a variation of the name of the person who discovered it.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: It was fortuitously discovered during a deep sea expedition. Its teeth have atrophied, so it now survives on microscopic organisms it sucks up.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Its form has remained the same for one hundred million years. Its body is filled with fat, so it can withstand the water pressure of the deep sea.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Relicanth is a rare species that was discovered in deep-sea explorations. This Pokémon’s body withstands the enormous water pressure of the ocean depths. Its body is covered in tough scales that are like craggy rocks.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Relicanth is a Pokémon species that existed for a hundred million years without ever changing its form. This ancient Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms with its toothless mouth.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: It has remained unchanged for 100 million years. It was discovered during a deep-sea exploration.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Discovered by chance during deep-sea explorations, it has not changed since ancient times.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: A POKéMON that was once believed to have been extinct. The species has not changed its form for 100 million years. It walks on the seafloor using its pectoral fins.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: It lives in warm seas. It is said that couples who find this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola’s branches.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: There was an era when it was overfished due to the rumor that having one of its heart-shaped scales would enable you to find a sweetheart.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Loving couples have a soft spot for this Pokémon, so honeymoon hotels often release this Pokémon into their pools.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: If a Luvdisc is left on its own, it becomes despondent, leaving itself open to attack. That is when Pelipper snatch them up.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Luvdisc’s heart-shaped body is a symbol of love and romance. It is said that any couple meeting this Pokémon is promised a loving relationship that never ends.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Luvdisc live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped Pokémon earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean’s waves.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: LUVDISC make the branches of CORSOLA their nests. There is a custom from long ago of giving a LUVDISC as a gift to express one’s feelings of love.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Its belief that it will be able to fly one day is apparently the influence of information carried in its genes.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Its steel-hard head can shatter boulders. It longingly hopes for wings to grow so it can fly.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Bagon is a solitary Pokémon that doesn’t form groups with others of its kind. It also has a head hard enough to cleave a boulder in one strike.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Bagon jumps off cliffs every day, trying to grow stronger so that someday it will be able to fly.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Some theories suggest that its behavior of forcefully bashing its head into things stimulates cells that affect its evolution.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Whenever it sees bird Pokémon flying through the sky, it becomes envious and smashes its surroundings to bits with headbutts.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: With its steel-hard stone head, it headbutts indiscriminately. This is because of the stress it feels at being unable to fly.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Bagon harbors a never-ending dream of one day soaring high among the clouds. As if trying to dispel its frustration over its inability to fly, this Pokémon slams its hard head against huge rocks and shatters them into pebbles.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Bagon has a dream of one day soaring in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly, this Pokémon hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has grown tough and as hard as tempered steel.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Its well-developed neck muscles and iron-like head can smash boulders into pieces.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Its well-developed neck muscles and ironlike head can smash boulders into pieces.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: Although it is small, this POKéMON is very powerful because its body is a bundle of muscles. It launches head-butts with its ironlike skull.

Name: Bagon
FlavorText: BAGON has a dream of one day soaring in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly, this POKéMON hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has  grown tough and as hard as tempered steel.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: Its armored body makes all attacks bounce off. The armor is too tough, however, making it heavy and somewhat sluggish.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed, preparing it for evolution.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant the Pokémon evolves.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: Shelgon ignores its hunger entirely, never eating any food. Apparently, Shelgon will evolve once all its energy stores are used up.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: This Pokémon has covered its body in a hard shell that has the same composition as bone. Shelgon stores energy for evolution.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: Shelgon lives deep within caves. It stays shut up in its hard shell, dreaming of the day it will be able to fly.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: The cells within its body are changing at a bewildering pace. Its hard shell is made from the same substance as bone.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: They lurk deep within caves—motionless, neither eating nor drinking. Why they don’t die is not known.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: Covering Shelgon’s body are outgrowths much like bones. The shell is very hard and bounces off enemy attacks. When awaiting evolution, this Pokémon hides away in a cavern.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: Inside Shelgon’s armor-like shell, cells are in the midst of transformation to create an entirely new body. This Pokémon’s shell is extremely heavy, making its movements sluggish.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: It surrounds its body in an iron-hard shell to accumulate enough power to evolve.

Name: Shelgon
FlavorText: It hardly eats while it awaits evolution. It becomes hardier by enduring hunger. Its shell peels off the instant it begins to evolve.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: It puts its forelegs inside its shell to streamline itself for flight. Salamence flies at high speeds over all kinds of topographical features.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: The stress of its two proud wings becoming misshapen and stuck together because of strong energy makes it go on a rampage.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: Mega Evolution fuels its brutality, and it may even turn on the Trainer who raised it. It’s been dubbed “the blood-soaked crescent.”

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: Anyone standing in its path gets sliced right in two, while this Pokémon continues its flight without interruption.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: It becomes uncontrollable if it is enraged. It destroys everything with shredding claws and fire.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up everything it passes over.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: While basking in the joy of flight generally keeps this Pokémon in high spirits, Salamence turns into an uncontrollable menace if something angers it.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: Salamence is an unusual Pokémon in that it was able to evolve a body with wings just by constantly wishing to be able to fly.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: Thanks to its fervent wishes, the cells in its body finally mutated, and at last it has its heart’s desire—wings.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: Overjoyed at finally being able to fly, it flies all over the place and usually doesn’t land until it’s completely exhausted and needs to sleep.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up the fields it passes over.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: When angered, it loses all sense of itself and destroys everything around it. The destruction will continue until Salamence has tired itself out.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: By evolving into Salamence, this Pokémon finally realizes its long-held dream of growing wings. To express its joy, it flies and wheels all over the sky while spouting flames from its mouth.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: Salamence came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this Pokémon’s cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: It’s uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.

Name: Salamence
FlavorText: After many long years, its cellular structure underwent a sudden mutation to grow wings. When angered, it loses all thought and rampages out of control.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: They converse with one another by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: The cells in this Pokémon’s body are composed of magnetic material. Instead of blood, magnetic forces flow through Beldum’s body.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum’s sharp claws.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: If you anger it, it will do more than rampage. It will also burst out strong magnetism, causing nearby machines to break.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: Instead of blood, magnetism flows through its body. When it’s feeling bad, try giving it a magnet.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: With magnetic traction, it pulls its opponents in close. When they’re in range, it slashes them with its rear claws.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: Its cells are all magnets. It uses magnetism to communicate with others of its kind.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: Beldum keeps itself floating by generating a magnetic force that repels earth’s natural magnetism. When it sleeps, this Pokémon anchors itself to a cliff using the hooks on its rear.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout Beldum’s body. This Pokémon communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground’s natural magnetism, letting it float.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: Its cells are all magnetic, and it communicates with others by using magnetic pulses.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: When BELDUM gather in a swarm, they move in perfect unison as if they were but one POKéMON. They communicate with each other using brain waves.

Name: Beldum
FlavorText: It uses magnetic waves to converse with its kind. All the cells in its body are magnetic.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won’t be scratched if it collides with a jet.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: Using magnetic forces to stay aloft, this Pokémon flies at high speeds, weaving through harsh mountain terrain in pursuit of prey.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: It flies at high speeds around the skies. When it finds its prey, Metang takes a firm grip with its sharp claws and never lets go.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: With its two brains, it fires powerful psychic energy to stop its prey in their tracks.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: It adores magnetic minerals, so it pursues Nosepass at speeds exceeding 60 mph.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: When two Beldum link together, their psychic power is doubled. Their intelligence, however, remains unchanged.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. This Pokémon turns its arms to the rear for traveling at high speed.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this Pokémon generates strong psychokinetic power.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: When two BELDUM fuse together, a magnetic nervous system places their brains in union.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: The claws tipping its arms pack the destructive power to tear through thick iron sheets as if they were silk. It flies at over 60 miles per hour.

Name: Metang
FlavorText: It floats midair using magnetism. Its body is so tough, even a crash with a jet plane won’t leave a scratch.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: When it knows it can’t win, it digs the claws on its legs into its opponent and starts the countdown to a big explosion.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: Its intellect surpasses its previous level, resulting in battles so cruel, they’ll make you want to cover your eyes.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: Mega Evolution stimulated its brain. It emerged as a ruthless Pokémon that will clutch at any means of ensuring its victories.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: This form results from one Metagross, one Metang, and two Beldum linking up.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This Pokémon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokémon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: It analyzes its opponents with more accuracy than a supercomputer, which enables it to calmly back them into a corner.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: It boasts not only psychic powers but also fantastic strength. It grabs its prey with its four legs and holds them in place with its claws.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: A linkage of two Metang, this Pokémon can perform any calculation in a flash by utilizing parallel processing in its four brains.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: It firmly pins its prey using its four claws and large body. Then the teeth in the mouth on its stomach chew the prey to bits.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: Metagross is the result of two Metang achieving fusion. When hunting, this Pokémon pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large mouth on its stomach.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokémon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: With four linked brains, it’s more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: METAGROSS has four brains that are joined by a complex neural network. As a result of integration, this POKéMON is smarter than a supercomputer.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: It is formed by two METANG fusing. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

Name: Metagross
FlavorText: METAGROSS is the result of two METANG achieving fusion. When hunting, this POKéMON pins the prey to the ground under its massive body. It then eats the helpless victim using the large  mouth on its stomach.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, Regirock attaches rocks to repair itself.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: Cutting-edge technology was used to study the internals of this Pokémon’s rock body, but nothing was found—not even a brain or a heart.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: Regirock’s body is composed entirely of rocks. Recently, a study made the startling discovery that the rocks were all unearthed from different locations.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: Regirock was sealed away by people long ago. If this Pokémon’s body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: A POKéMON that is made entirely of rocks and boulders. If parts of its body chip off in battle, REGIROCK repairs itself by adding new rocks.

Name: Regirock
FlavorText: It is entirely composed of rocks with no sign of a brain or heart. It is a mystery even to modern scientists.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of −328 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s body is made of solid ice. It’s said that Regice was born beneath thick ice in the ice age.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: Regice cloaks itself with frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit. Things will freeze solid just by going near this Pokémon. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: Regice’s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can’t be melted, even by fire. This Pokémon controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: It is said to have slept in a glacier for thousands of years. Its body can’t be melted, even by magma.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: Its entire body is made of Antarctic ice. After extensive studies, researchers believe the ice was formed during an ice age.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: Research revealed that its body is made of the same kind of ice that is found at the South Pole.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: REGICE cloaks itself with frigid air of negative 328 degrees F. Things will freeze solid just by going near this POKéMON. Its icy body is so cold, it will not melt even if it is immersed in magma.

Name: Regice
FlavorText: REGICE’s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can’t be melted, even by fire. This POKéMON controls frigid air of minus 328 degrees F.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: It’s rumored that this Pokémon was born deep underground in the planet’s mantle and that it emerged onto the surface 10,000 years ago.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: Registeel’s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: Registeel was imprisoned by people in ancient times. The metal composing its body is thought to be a curious substance that is not of this earth.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: Registeel has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this Pokémon eats.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: Its body is harder than any other kind of metal. The body metal is composed of a mysterious substance. Not only is it hard, it shrinks and stretches flexibly.

Name: Registeel
FlavorText: It is sturdier than any kind of metal. It hardened due to pressure underground over tens of thousands of years.

Name: Latias
FlavorText: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

Name: Latias
FlavorText: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

Name: Latias
FlavorText: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

Name: Latias
FlavorText: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.

Name: Latias
FlavorText: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

Name: Latias
FlavorText: They make a small herd of only several members. They rarely make contact with people or other POKéMON. They disappear if they sense enemies.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: It is a highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its forelegs in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: Even in hiding, it can detect the locations of others and sense their emotions since it has telepathy. Its intelligence allows it to understand human languages.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: It has a docile temperament and dislikes fighting. Tucking in its forelegs, it can fly faster than a jet plane.

Name: Latios
FlavorText: LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKéMON is intelligent and understands human speech.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: KYOGRE has appeared in mythology as the creator of the sea. After long years of feuding with GROUDON, it took to sleep at the bottom of the sea.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: This POKéMON is said to have expanded the sea by bringing heavy rains. It has the power to control water.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: KYOGRE is named in mythology as the POKéMON that expanded the sea by covering the land with torrential rains and towering tidal waves. It took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with GROUDON.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: This legendary Pokémon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling Kyogre.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: GROUDON has appeared in mythology as the creator of the land. It sleeps in magma underground and is said to make volcanoes erupt on awakening.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: GROUDON has the power to scatter rain clouds and make water evaporate with light and heat. It came as a savior to people who had been suffering from terrible floods.

Name: Groudon
FlavorText: GROUDON has long been described in  mythology as the POKéMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKéMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: A POKéMON that flies endlessly in the ozone layer. It is said it would descend to the ground if KYOGRE and GROUDON were to fight.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: It has lived for hundreds of millions of years in the ozone layer. Its flying form looks like a meteor.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: RAYQUAZA is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer, above the clouds. Its existence had been completely unknown because it lived so high in the sky.

Name: Rayquaza
FlavorText: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer,  never descending to the ground. This POKéMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: It is said to wake up for just seven days every 1,000 years and use its power to grant any wish.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: It’s believed that when this Pokémon wakes from its 1,000-year slumber, it will grant any wishes written on the notes attached to its head.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: Once every 1,000 years, the singing of a pure voice will rouse this Pokémon from its near-perpetual slumber. It wakes for only seven days.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokémon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: JIRACHI is said to make wishes come true. While it sleeps, a tough crystalline shell envelops the body to protect it from enemies.

Name: Jirachi
FlavorText: It is said to make any wish come true. It is awake for only seven days out of a thousand years.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteorite underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon’s chest appears to be its brain.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: A POKéMON that mutated from an extraterrestrial virus exposed to a laser beam. Its body is configured for superior agility and speed.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: When it changes form, an aurora appears. It absorbs attacks by altering its cellular structure.

Name: Deoxys
FlavorText: This DEOXYS has transformed into its aggressive guise. It can fool enemies by altering its appearance.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: This Pokémon becomes more energetic the more sunlight there is. The part resembling a shell is similar to silt and is slightly damp and warm to the touch.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis within its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if the Pokémon is thirsty.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell should feel moist.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: Appears where there is clean spring water. The fruit that grows on the shrubs on its shell is sweet, nutritious, and truly delicious.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: Its shell is hardened soil. Some Pokémon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe the trees on its shell.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: A GROTLE that lives in the forest is said to have its own secret springwater.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: The shell is hardened soil. Some Pokémon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: This remarkable, large-bodied Pokémon would serve beautifully as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless. Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Groups of this Pokémon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for moving forests.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra’s back and spend their entire life there.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Groups of this Pokémon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for “moving forests.”

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: Full of vigor and always in high spirits. It was once known by the name “Lantern-Tail” and feared as some kind of apparition.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: The deeper the blue on its face, the more powerful it will grow to become. It leaps about every which way and lands powerful blows against its opponents with the flame on its tail.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one of its weapons.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: To intimidate attackers, it expands the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: A bigger fire on its tail and a brighter blue pattern on its face means its rank in its pack is higher.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: A tall, hardy Pokémon with a dazzling appearance. It shrouds itself in flame and battles as if engaged in dance—truly a sight to behold.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.

Name: Piplup
FlavorText: Prefers cold climes and appears along coasts. It’s an adorable little thing—as cute as any child—but it’s also prideful, unwilling to accept handouts from people.

Name: Piplup
FlavorText: It lives along the shore in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes while hunting.

Name: Piplup
FlavorText: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

Name: Piplup
FlavorText: It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

Name: Piplup
FlavorText: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

Name: Piplup
FlavorText: It lives along shores in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes to hunt.

Name: Prinplup
FlavorText: It swims gracefully through the frigid sea and sings with a voice like the roaring tide. It has powerful, sturdy wings and dignity to match.

Name: Prinplup
FlavorText: Its wings deliver wicked blows that snap even the thickest of trees. It searches for prey in icy seas.

Name: Prinplup
FlavorText: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

Name: Prinplup
FlavorText: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

Name: Prinplup
FlavorText: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.

Name: Empoleon
FlavorText: Since ancient times, it has been revered by the people of Hisui, who call it the Master of the Waves. Its wings are a match for even master-crafted blades.

Name: Empoleon
FlavorText: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

Name: Empoleon
FlavorText: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

Name: Empoleon
FlavorText: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.

Name: Empoleon
FlavorText: It avoids unnecessary disputes, but it will decimate anything that threatens its pride.

Name: Starly
FlavorText: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.

Name: Starly
FlavorText: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

Name: Starly
FlavorText: They live in the fields and mountains, gathering in large flocks. Their cries are quite obnoxious. Though small, their wings are strong—a strike from them leaves pain that persists for a week.

Name: Starly
FlavorText: Usually with a large flock, it is barely noticeable when alone. Its cries are very strident.

Name: Starly
FlavorText: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

Name: Staravia
FlavorText: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

Name: Staravia
FlavorText: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.

Name: Staravia
FlavorText: They form remarkably large flocks and are constantly fighting amongst themselves. I suspect that those with magnificent plumes on their heads are the strong ones.

Name: Staravia
FlavorText: They live in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

Name: Staravia
FlavorText: They fly around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon, moving together in huge flocks.

Name: Staravia
FlavorText: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

Name: Staravia
FlavorText: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

Name: Staraptor
FlavorText: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.

Name: Staraptor
FlavorText: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

Name: Staraptor
FlavorText: It has left the flock, having gained strength enough to survive on its own. The astounding force with which Staraptor flies through the air allows it to carry away large, burly targets.

Name: Staraptor
FlavorText: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.

Name: Staraptor
FlavorText: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger than itself.

Name: Staraptor
FlavorText: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.

Name: Bidoof
FlavorText: Bidoof has an unsophisticated face and is rarely flustered by anything. There have been incidents involving Bidoof sauntering into villages and gnawing on the houses without a single care.

Name: Bidoof
FlavorText: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

Name: Bidoof
FlavorText: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

Name: Bidoof
FlavorText: A comparison revealed that Bidoof’s front teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata’s.

Name: Bidoof
FlavorText: It lives in groups by the water.  It chews up boulders and trees around its nest with its incisors.

Name: Bibarel
FlavorText: Bibarel fur repels water and is also a fantastic material for heat retention. These Pokémon create dams on rivers to live in.

Name: Bibarel
FlavorText: While its movements out of water are sluggish, it can swim as fast as any Feebas.

Name: Bibarel
FlavorText: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

Name: Bibarel
FlavorText: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

Name: Bibarel
FlavorText: A river dammed by Bibarel will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.

Name: Kricketot
FlavorText: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

Name: Kricketot
FlavorText: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

Name: Kricketot
FlavorText: When the trees take on new hues, more of these Pokémon appear. The tone they create by striking their antennae together resembles that of the marimba, an instrument of foreign lands.

Name: Kricketot
FlavorText: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are the hallmarks of fall evenings.

Name: Kricketot
FlavorText: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.

Name: Kricketot
FlavorText: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.

Name: Kricketune
FlavorText: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.

Name: Kricketune
FlavorText: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces a captivating sound.

Name: Kricketune
FlavorText: It uses its cutlass-like arms to produce sound, the melody of which varies from individual to individual. It is a worthwhile endeavor to seek out one’s favorite tunes.

Name: Kricketune
FlavorText: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

Name: Kricketune
FlavorText: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: Shakes its body to generate electricity. Its stature belies its aggression—one must be patient to tame this Pokémon.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: Its forelegs have a muscle-based system of generating electricity. Its body shines when it is in danger.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: Electricity makes this Pokémon’s fur glow. Shinx sends signals to others of its kind by shaking the tip of its tail while the tail tip is shining brightly.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.

Name: Shinx
FlavorText: Its forelegs have a muscle-based system of generating electricity. Its body shines if endangered.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: Proudly uses its electrified claws as weapons. It seems to be a gracious Pokémon, evenly sharing the spoils of the hunt with others of its kind.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: It rests its forelegs on others to communicate with rhythmic electric pulses from its claws.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause opponents to faint. It lives in small groups.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: Upon encountering an opponent, this Pokémon prepares for battle by extending its claws, which can put out 1,000,000 volts of electricity.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokémon can receive some of the other Luxio’s electricity and power up its own electric blasts.

Name: Luxio
FlavorText: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: Luxray’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: They form packs, each having one male as leader. Legends say that when Luxray’s two eyes shimmer with gold, the Pokémon can see through anything.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey—even those taking shelter behind a wall.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: Seeing through solid objects uses up a lot of Luxray’s electricity, so the Pokémon sleeps for long periods of time to store up energy.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.

Name: Luxray
FlavorText: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hiding prey--even those taking shelter behind a wall.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: When the sun’s light strengthens, the bud atop this Pokémon’s head opens. This is a sign to the people that the harsh winter is over, and the season of budding has begun.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: It lives alongside clear ponds. It scatters pollen that induces harsh sneezing and runny noses.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: This Pokémon is highly sensitive to temperature changes. When its bud starts to open, that means spring is right around the corner.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: The pollen it releases contains poison. If this Pokémon is raised on clean water, the poison’s toxicity is increased.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: When it feels the sun’s warm touch, it opens its bud to release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: Sensitive to changing temperatures, the bud blooms when it’s warm, releasing toxic pollen.

Name: Budew
FlavorText: Sensitive to changing temperature, the bud is said to bloom when it feels the sun’s warm touch.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: Hidden within the bouquet on each hand are thorned whips loaded with virulent poison. Roserade moves gracefully as it corners its prey and mercilessly lashes them with its whips.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: The poison in its right hand is quick acting. The poison in its left hand is slow acting. Both are life threatening.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whips on its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: Each of its hands contains different toxins, but both hands can jab with near-fatal power.

Name: Roserade
FlavorText: Its sweet aroma attracts prey. Then it spews poison. The more toxic it is, the sweeter its aroma.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: An incredibly rare sight. They duel each other by ramming their heads together, and the resulting sound echoes throughout the area like the pealing of a bell.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: It was resurrected from an iron-ball-like fossil. It downs prey with its headbutts.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: Its hard skull is its distinguishing feature. It snapped trees by headbutting them, and then it fed on their ripe berries.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: A primeval Pokémon, it possesses a hard and sturdy skull, lacking any intelligence within.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: In rock layers where Cranidos fossils are found, the fossilized trunks of trees snapped in two are also often found.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat Aerodactyl.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: It was resurrected from an iron ball-like fossil. It downs prey with its headbutts.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with head butts.

Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: CRANIDOS toughen up their already rock-hard heads by headbutting one another.
