Name: Cranidos
FlavorText: It was resurrected from an iron ball-like fossil. It downs prey with its head butts.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: Very little is known about its biology. Can knock down massive trees by smashing its beautiful, pearl-like crown against them.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: Its powerful headbutt has enough force to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: This ancient Pokémon used headbutts skillfully. Its brain was really small, so some theories suggest that its stupidity led to its extinction.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: In ancient times, people would dig up fossils of this Pokémon and use its skull, which is harder than steel, to make helmets.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: Records exist of a revived fossil that evolved into Rampardos. It proceeded to escape and then destroy a skyscraper with a headbutt.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: The result of repeated headbutts is a skull grown thick and hard. However, its brain has shrunk in size compared with Cranidos’s.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: Its skull withstands impacts of any magnitude. As a result, its brain never gets the chance to grow.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: If two were to smash their heads together, their foot-thick skulls would keep them from fainting.

Name: Rampardos
FlavorText: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: Much remains unknown about this Pokémon, as few have ever seen it. However, we know that it is calm and dislikes conflict, and it enjoys polishing its face against trees and rocks.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: It habitually polishes its face by rubbing it against tree trunks. It is weak to attacks from behind.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: Although its fossils can be found in layers of primeval rock, nothing but its face has ever been discovered.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: A mild-mannered, herbivorous Pokémon, it used its face to dig up tree roots to eat. The skin on its face was plenty tough.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: This Pokémon lived in primeval jungles. Few enemies would have been willing to square off against its heavily armored face, so it’s thought.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: Many fossils of this Pokémon have been found, but almost none have shown signs of damage to the face.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

Name: Shieldon
FlavorText: It is outstandingly armored. As a result, it can eat grass and berries without having to fight.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: Its face is sturdy—as strong as diamond—and this hardness offers a very stable defense. Much about this species is still unknown, such as its natural habitat.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: When attacked, they form a wall with their shield-like faces to protect their young.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: This Pokémon is from roughly 100 million years ago. Its terrifyingly tough face is harder than steel.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: The bones of its face are huge and hard, so they were mistaken for its spine until after this Pokémon was successfully restored.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: It lived in the same environments as Rampardos. Their fossils have been found together— seemingly from after they’d fought to the finish.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front, it is left without recourse when attacked from behind.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: When attacked, they form a wall. Their rock-hard faces serve to protect them from the attacks.

Name: Bastiodon
FlavorText: When attacked, they form a wall with their shieldlike faces to protect their young.

Name: Burmy
FlavorText: When confronted by a lack of other materials, Burmy will create its cloak using dust and refuse. The cloak seems to be more comfortable than one would think.

Name: Burmy
FlavorText: It creates a cloak by weaving together sand, mud, and silk it has spat out. This earthen cloak is ruined by wind and rain, so the Pokémon hides away in caves and other such places.

Name: Burmy
FlavorText: If its cloak is even slightly damaged, Burmy will immediately repair it with whatever is close at hand. The Pokémon within the cloak is scrawny and vulnerable to the cold.

Name: Burmy
FlavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

Name: Burmy
FlavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

Name: Burmy
FlavorText: Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.

Name: Burmy
FlavorText: It covers itself with a cloak to shelter from the cold. When it’s hot, its cloak is thinner.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: Its body, composed of refuse, blends in to the scenery so much as to be inconspicuous. This seems to be the perfect way for the Pokémon to evade the detection of predators.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: Its earthen skin is reasonably hard—it has no problem repelling a Starly’s pecking, at least.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: The cloak—fashioned from plant matter—has merged with the Pokémon and is now part of the body, like fur or skin. I suspect this fusion is an effect of the energy involved in evolution.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: When Burmy evolves, its cloak becomes a part of its body. Wormadam’s cloak is never shed.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.

Name: Wormadam
FlavorText: It is said that a WORMADAM that evolves on a cold day will have a thicker cloak.

Name: Mothim
FlavorText: Scatters steel-colored scales as it flaps its wings. Despite being observed feeding primarily on the nectar of flowers, Mothim is not often seen around flower gardens.

Name: Mothim
FlavorText: It does not keep a nest. It flies over fields and mountains in constant search of its much-beloved nectar.

Name: Mothim
FlavorText: It loves the nectar of flowers and steals nectar collected by Combee.

Name: Mothim
FlavorText: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

Name: Mothim
FlavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.

Name: Mothim
FlavorText: While it loves floral honey, it won’t gather any itself. Instead, it plots to steal some from Combee.

Name: Mothim
FlavorText: It does not keep a nest. It flies over fields and mountains in constant search of floral honey.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers nectar from flowers to please Vespiquen.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a hundred, packed closely together in a lump.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: They swear fealty to a queen Pokémon and work diligently to gather nectar. Each swarm produces a different flavor of honey.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: They collect and deliver honey to their colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: Three Pokémon joined to become one. It busily carries sweet nectar to Vespiquen.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: It ceaselessly gathers nectar from sunrise to sundown, all for the sake of Vespiquen and the swarm.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathers honey from flowers to please Vespiquen.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a set of three. When they sleep, they gather up and form a giant hive of 100 Combee.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: At night, COMBEE sleep in a group of about a thousand, packed closely together in a lump.

Name: Combee
FlavorText: A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control Combee.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: Commands its subjects to build its hive. It will dispatch any interlopers who dare sneak into its nest and use them as nourishment for itself.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: When it is in danger, grubs from its six-cell honeycomb strike back. There is only one in a colony.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on nectar collected by Combee.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: Vespiquen that give off more pheromones have larger swarms of Combee attendants.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: It releases various pheromones to make the grubs in its body do its bidding while fighting foes.

Name: Vespiquen
FlavorText: When endangered, grubs from its six-cell honeycomb strike back. There is only one in a colony.

Name: Pachirisu
FlavorText: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

Name: Pachirisu
FlavorText: It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

Name: Pachirisu
FlavorText: A species related to the Pikachu line. Though Pachirisu is a calm Pokémon, it still presents a danger should one touch its electrified tail or cheeks.

Name: Pachirisu
FlavorText: It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It lives atop trees.

Name: Pachirisu
FlavorText: It stores its own fur balls that crackle with static electricity together with its favorite berries in tree hollows.

Name: Pachirisu
FlavorText: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

Name: Pachirisu
FlavorText: It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon  with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

Name: Buizel
FlavorText: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.

Name: Buizel
FlavorText: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

Name: Buizel
FlavorText: It moves freely in the water by spinning its forked tail for propulsion. The resemblance to the screw of a steamboat is coincidental.

Name: Buizel
FlavorText: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

Name: Buizel
FlavorText: When air fills the flotation sac on its neck, the sac balloons like an inner tube. This Pokémon floats with its head out of the water.

Name: Buizel
FlavorText: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

Name: Buizel
FlavorText: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

Name: Floatzel
FlavorText: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and help fishers carry what they caught.

Name: Floatzel
FlavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

Name: Floatzel
FlavorText: Has a long, rather splendid flotation sac, which prevents Floatzel from drowning even in stormy seas. One might glimpse this species around fishing hamlets from time to time.

Name: Floatzel
FlavorText: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. Floatzel carries people as if it were a rubber raft.

Name: Floatzel
FlavorText: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

Name: Floatzel
FlavorText: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

Name: Floatzel
FlavorText: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and carry off prey.

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: Once the fruit growing alongside the main body is large and plump, Cherubi will use the nutrients within to evolve. The fruit then detaches, becoming nourishment for other creatures.

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: Sunlight colors it red. When the small ball is drained of nutrients and shriveled, evolution is near.

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: The deeper a Cherubi’s red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokémon that would love to make off with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: Sunlight colors it red. When the small ball is drained of nutrients, it shrivels to herald evolution.

Name: Cherubi
FlavorText: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: Cheerfully active on sunny days. Immediately closes its petals and becomes immobile once the sun becomes hidden, however.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: After absorbing plenty of sunlight, Cherrim takes this form. It’s full of energy while it’s like this, and its liveliness will go on until sundown.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: Its folded petals are pretty tough. Bird Pokémon can peck at them all they want, and Cherrim won’t be bothered at all.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: As a bud, it barely moves. It sits still, placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: Motionless, save for the occasional quiver. A rich array of Pokémon can be found gathered around it, drawn by the scent exuded from Cherrim’s folded petals.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: It is docile as a bud and turns cheerful when it blooms. It folds back into a bud if sunlight wanes.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. The Pokémon tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun’s rays with its whole body.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: During times of strong sunlight, its bud blooms, its petals open fully, and it becomes very active.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: It is docile as a bud, but turns cheerful when it blooms. It folds back into a bud if sunlight wanes.

Name: Cherrim
FlavorText: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: It oozes a purple fluid to deter enemies. Apparently, there are more West Sea Shellos now than there were in the past.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: It used to have a shell on its back long ago. This species is closely related to Pokémon like Shellder.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: This Pokémon can often be seen along seashores. It’s capable of spending a limited amount of time on land.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: A recently published research paper states that this form of Shellos is gradually decreasing in number.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Found in abundance on seashores bordering cold waters. When pressed upon, the Pokémon will secrete from its body’s surface a purple fluid that will stain one’s clothes.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Its appearance changes depending on the environment. One theory suggests that living in cold seas causes Shellos to take on this form.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: There’s speculation that its appearance is determined by what it eats, but the truth remains elusive.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Scientists interested in its great regenerative capabilities are currently analyzing the materials from which its cells are made.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: When it senses danger, it gushes a purple liquid. Some theories suggest this liquid is a greasy sweat induced by stress.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: The difference in color from one Shellos to another seems to be a result of their diet. No large changes can be seen in their capabilities.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Shellos lives in the sea and feasts on plankton. The lovelier the ocean where Shellos resides, the more vibrant its color becomes.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Subjecting this Pokémon to a strong force causes it to secrete a strange purple fluid. Though harmless, the fluid is awfully sticky.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s habitat shapes its physique. According to some theories, life in warm ocean waters causes this variation to develop.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: When it senses danger, a purple liquid oozes out of it. The liquid is thought to be something like greasy sweat.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: While they normally live in the sea, they can function on land, too, until their skin dries out.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Purple mucus sticks to the hands of anyone who touches it. Take care, as the substance is troublesome to wash off.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: For the most part, it makes its home along the seashore. Its color and form differ according to its habitat and the quality of its food.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Found in abundance on seashores bordering warm waters. Shellos are unexpectedly friendly and will crawl toward any person they see. Take care not to get coated in mucus!

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: It lives along bodies of water. Its body shape changed to suit its habitat.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.

Name: Shellos
FlavorText: It lives along bodies of water. Its body shape has changed to suit its habitat.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: It appears on beaches where the waters are shallow. Once it catches prey, it will slowly melt them with its mucus before slurping them up.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Its whole body is sticky with mucus. In the past, this form of Gastrodon was by far the more numerous one.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Fishers say that they didn’t see many of these Pokémon in the past, but this form of Gastrodon is now increasing in number.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: They normally inhabit rocky seashores, but in times of continuous rain, they can sometimes be found in the mountains, far from the sea.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Found more often on the land than in the sea. More active when it’s cloudy or rainy out than when the weather is fair.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Its body is covered in a sticky slime. It’s very susceptible to dehydration, so it can’t spend too much time on land.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: It secretes a purple fluid to deter enemies. This fluid isn’t poisonous—instead, it’s super sticky, and once it sticks, it’s very hard to unstick.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: A relative of Shellder and Cloyster, this ocean dweller sometimes comes onto land in search of food.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: When it’s attacked, it gushes a purple liquid that’s not poisonous but makes Gastrodon’s meat bitter and inedible.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Experiments are being conducted to discover what happens when a Gastrodon is raised in a location other than the sea where it was born.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: A team of researchers is scouring the oceans of the world in search of a Gastrodon in a color never seen before.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: The softness of its body helps disperse the force of impacts, so although its body is uncommonly squishy, it’s also surprisingly resilient.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Their shape and color change, depending on their environment and diet. There are many of them at beaches where the waves are calm.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Long ago, it had a shell on its back. There’s now a vestigial plate on its back that’s hard but thin.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Plankton, invisible to the naked eye, is its main food source. It comes onto the land periodically, but the reason for this is not known.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: It has strong regenerative capabilities. Even if parts of it are bitten off by fish Pokémon, it will return to normal within a few hours.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Eats beach sand for nourishment. Should one Gastrodon encounter another of a different color, a fierce battle will inevitably ensue.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: When its natural enemy attacks, it oozes purple fluid and escapes.

Name: Gastrodon
FlavorText: Long ago, its entire back was shielded with a sturdy shell. There are traces of it left in its cells.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: To affirm their kinship, members of this species will form a ring by linking their newly doubled tails together. On rare occasions, humans have been accepted into such rings.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: They work in large colonies and make rings by linking their tails, apparently in friendship.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that’s proof it really likes you.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: In their search for comfortable trees, they get into territorial disputes with groups of Passimian. They win about half the time.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: It is very difficult to dodge the consecutive strikes of its two tails.

Name: Ambipom
FlavorText: They live on large trees. They are said to communicate by connecting their tails to those of others.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “signpost for wandering spirits.”

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: Said to lure away young children and carry them off to the afterlife. Some whisper that Drifloon are formed of reincarnated human souls, but these rumors are as yet unconfirmed.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: It tugs on the hands of children to spirit them away. However, it gets pulled around instead.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: It is a Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: The gathering of many souls gave rise to this Pokémon. During humid seasons, they seem to appear in abundance.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: Perhaps seeking company, it approaches children. However, it often quickly runs away again when the children play too roughly with it.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: Wandering souls gathered together to form this Pokémon. When trying to make friends with children, Drifloon grabs them by the hand.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: Its round body is stuffed with souls and expands each time it leads someone away.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: If for some reason its body bursts, its soul spills out with a screaming sound.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: Stories go that it grabs the hands of small children and drags them away to the afterlife. It dislikes heavy children.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: These Pokémon are called the “Signpost for Wandering Spirits.” Children holding them sometimes vanish.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

Name: Drifloon
FlavorText: It tugs on the hands of children to steal them away. However, it gets pulled around instead.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: It can generate and release gas within its body. That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: It drifts along at dusk, perfectly silent. Its transient, melancholy aspect touches some people deeply—every so often, one will come upon a song or poem devoted to Drifblim.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: It carries people and Pokémon when it flies. But since it only drifts, it can end up anywhere.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: They’re drowsy in daytime but fly off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: It grabs people and Pokémon and carries them off somewhere. Where do they go? Nobody knows.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: Some say this Pokémon is a collection of souls burdened with regrets, silently drifting through the dusk.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: The raw material for the gas inside its body is souls. When its body starts to deflate, it’s thought to carry away people and Pokémon.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: There’s a rumor that if you catch a Drifblim floating on the wind at dusk, you’ll be carried away to the afterlife.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: Even while under careful observation, large flocks of Drifblim flying at dusk will inexplicably disappear from view.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: There was once an incident in which a man took a trip riding a Drifblim, only to go missing.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: It’s drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: At dusk, swarms of them are carried aloft on winds. When noticed, they suddenly vanish.

Name: Drifblim
FlavorText: It’s drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: My hypothesis as to why Buneary rolls up its ears is that its hearing is far too keen. I surmise that the Pokémon protects its hearing by limiting the sound that may enter its ears.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: Buneary can attack by rolling up their ears and then striking with the force created by unrolling them. This attack becomes stronger with training.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the Pokémon is in need of care.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: The reason it keeps one ear rolled up is so it can launch a swift counterattack if it’s attacked by an enemy.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: Its arms and legs are weak, but when it rolls its ears up tight and then unleashes them with its full force, it can smash boulders to dust.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefully extended to shatter even a large boulder.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: By extending its rolled-up ears and striking the ground, it can bound so high it surprises itself.

Name: Buneary
FlavorText: You can tell how it feels by the way it rolls its ears. When it’s scared, both ears are rolled up.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: Mega Evolution awakens its combative instincts. It has shed any fur that got in the way of its attacks.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: It swings its ears like whips and strikes its enemies with them. It has an intensely combative disposition.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: Its fur is warm and yet remarkably light. This Pokémon kicks as though it were a master of karate, driving back its opponents with ease.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: It likes to keep itself clean and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: An extremely cautious Pokémon that cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: Once hot seasons are over, Lopunny’s coat will be replaced with fur that holds a lot of insulating air in preparation for colder weather.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: It’s notably wary and has a dislike of fighting, but at the same time, it can deliver powerful kicks with its lithe legs.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: Lopunny regrows its coat twice a year. Mufflers and hats made from its fur are really warm.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: It sheds its fur twice a year. Its winter fur is soft and fluffy.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: It is very conscious of its looks and never fails to groom its ears. It runs with sprightly jumps.

Name: Lopunny
FlavorText: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: The incantations Mismagius chants can ward against misfortune, so a custom exists of inviting it into one’s home. Incur the Pokémon’s displeasure, however, and disaster will surely ensue.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: It chants incantations. While these incantations can torment targets, some bring happiness.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: Its cries sound like incantations. Those who hear it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: Its muttered curses can cause awful headaches or terrifying visions that torment others.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokémon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: Mismagius have been known to cast spells to make people fall in love, so some people search for this Pokémon as if their life depended on it.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: It appears as if from nowhere—muttering incantations, placing curses, and giving people terrifying visions.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: It chants incantations. While they usually torment targets, some chants bring happiness.

Name: Mismagius
FlavorText: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than 100 of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: One cry from this Pokémon, and a murder of Murkrow come flying. At such times, one would think the curtain of night had fallen, plunging the world into jet-black darkness.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: It makes its Murkrow cronies bring it food. It idles its time away, grooming itself in its nest.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: Becoming active at night, it is known to form flocks with numerous Murkrow in tow.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: It will absolutely not forgive failure from or betrayal by its goons. It has no choice in this if it wants to maintain the order of the flock.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: If its Murkrow cronies fail to catch food for it, or if it feels they have betrayed it, it will hunt them down wherever they are and punish them.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than a hundred of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

Name: Honchkrow
FlavorText: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called “Summoner of Night.”

Name: Glameow
FlavorText: Bewitches humans with its helical tail and piercing gaze. Its hidden claws are quite sharp as well, making this Pokémon an exceedingly tricky opponent if antagonized.

Name: Glameow
FlavorText: With its sharp glare, it puts foes in a mild hypnotic state. It is a very fickle Pokémon.

Name: Glameow
FlavorText: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

Name: Glameow
FlavorText: When it’s happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

Name: Glameow
FlavorText: It hides its spiteful tendency of hooking its claws into the nose of its Trainer if it isn’t fed.

Name: Purugly
FlavorText: Though impudent and difficult to tame, Purugly enjoys great popularity due to its fur, the beauty of which surpasses even velveteen.

Name: Purugly
FlavorText: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its split tail.

Name: Purugly
FlavorText: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.

Name: Purugly
FlavorText: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

Name: Purugly
FlavorText: It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

Name: Purugly
FlavorText: It binds its body with its tails to make itself look bigger. If it locks eyes, it will glare ceaselessly.

Name: Chingling
FlavorText: This Pokémon gave me an excruciating headache when it seemingly cried out without making a sound. Perhaps there are some sounds that the human ear is simply incapable of hearing.

Name: Chingling
FlavorText: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.

Name: Chingling
FlavorText: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

Name: Chingling
FlavorText: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

Name: Chingling
FlavorText: It emits high-frequency cries that  people can’t hear. Once it starts, it can cry for an awfully long time.

Name: Stunky
FlavorText: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.

Name: Stunky
FlavorText: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.

Name: Stunky
FlavorText: The poison that gushes from its aft end is accompanied by an utterly evil-smelling odor with such potency that one whiff can induce memory loss.

Name: Stunky
FlavorText: It sprays a nose-curling, stinky fluid from its rear to repel attackers.

Name: Stunky
FlavorText: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

Name: Stunky
FlavorText: If it lifts its tail and points its rear at you, beware. It’s about to spray you with a fluid stinky enough to make you faint.

Name: Stunky
FlavorText: From its rear, it sprays a foul-smelling liquid at opponents. It aims for their faces, and it can hit them from over 16 feet away.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: Sprays a poisonous fluid to take down prey. Sometimes, unable to stomach the stench of its own fluid, it leaves the bested prey uneaten.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester in its belly.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. It can fire this spray more than 160 feet.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: It digs holes in the ground to make its nest. The stench of the fluid it lets fly from the tip of its tail is extremely potent.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: In its belly, it reserves stinky fluid that it shoots from its tail during battle. As this Pokémon’s diet varies, so does the stench of its fluid.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

Name: Skuntank
FlavorText: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor’s back contained a mysterious power.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: Floats using a mysterious energy. The pattern engraved upon its back is held as sacred and can sometimes be found in imagery from ancient cemeteries and other such timeworn places.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: X-ray photos were taken to check its body structure, but nothing was seen.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: Implements shaped like Bronzor were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown whether they are related.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth, according to common lore. Be that as it may, Bronzor hates being polished.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn’t come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: There are researchers who believe this Pokémon reflected like a mirror in the distant past.

Name: Bronzor
FlavorText: X-ray photos were taken to check its body structure. Nothing appeared, however.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: It brought rains by opening portals to another world. It was revered as a bringer of plentiful harvests.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: Some believe that its bell-like cry opens holes to another world. It has been revered as a deity since ancient times.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: It can summon rain clouds. People long ago revered it as the bringer of plentiful harvests.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: One caused a media storm when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered, it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.

Name: Bronzong
FlavorText: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: From its eyes, it can expel excess moisture from its body. This liquid is similar in composition to human sweat.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: In order to adjust the level of fluids in its body, it exudes water from its eyes. This makes it appear to be crying.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: Its tears elicit sympathy from those who see them, but do not be deceived! This expulsion of body water is merely a physiological mechanism for keeping itself in good health.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: It prefers arid environments. It leaks water from its eyes to adjust its body’s fluid levels.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body’s fluid levels by eliminating excess.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in dry, rocky areas. As its green spheres dry out, their dull luster increases.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: It expels both sweat and tears from its eyes. The sweat is a little salty, while the tears have a slight bitterness.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: If its body gets too damp, it will die. So, in a process reminiscent of sweating, its eyes expel moisture.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: It discharges moisture from its eyes, making it look like it’s crying—apparently an effective way of getting enemies to let down their guard.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: It does not deal well with water, so it lives in dry locales. Since its surroundings tend to lack greenery, it stands out noticeably.

Name: Bonsly
FlavorText: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: Known to turn up in bustling marketplaces now and again. It mimics people much as a child would, then watches how they react, eyes sparkling.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: It likes places where people gather. It mimics foes to confuse them, then makes its getaway.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: It habitually mimics foes. The mimicked foe is said to be unable to look away from Mime Jr.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: It looks for a Mr. Rime that’s a good dancer and carefully copies the Mr. Rime’s steps like an apprentice.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: It mimics everyone it sees, but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: When this gifted mimic surprises an opponent, Mime Jr. feels so happy that it ends up forgetting it was imitating something.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: It does its absolute best to mimic the movements and expressions of its opponents, but it’s still not very good at it.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy’s movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!

Name: Mime Jr.
FlavorText: It mimics the expressions and motions of those it sees to understand the feelings of others.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It’s bothered by how curly its hair looks.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It carries a round, white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone, it will sometimes give that person the rock.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: In imitation of Chansey, it keeps a round stone tucked into its belly pouch and cherishes it dearly. It gets along well with children and will sometimes play house with them for fun.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It carries a round, egg-shaped rock in its belly pouch and gives the rock to its friends.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It loves round, white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of Chansey.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: Happiny’s willing to lend its precious round stone to those it’s friendly with, but if the stone isn’t returned, Happiny will cry and throw a tantrum.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: Mimicking Chansey, Happiny will place an egg- shaped stone in its belly pouch. Happiny will treasure this stone.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: When it sees something round and white, Happiny puts it into the pouch on its stomach. It sometimes becomes overloaded and can’t move.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: Usually it’s a well-behaved Pokémon, but if you take its round rock away, it will cry and fuss and throw a big old tantrum.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It’s too small to lay eggs yet. As a surrogate, it searches out round white stones.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It carries a round white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone, it will sometimes give that person the rock.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others’ feet and cause them to stumble.

Name: Happiny
FlavorText: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.

Name: Chatot
FlavorText: A versatile performer skilled in the imitation of human speech. It is said that older, more experienced Chatot can even understand the meaning of the words they mimic.

Name: Chatot
FlavorText: It keeps rhythm by flicking its tail feathers like a metronome. It also imitates human speech.

Name: Chatot
FlavorText: They can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

Name: Chatot
FlavorText: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

Name: Chatot
FlavorText: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.

Name: Chatot
FlavorText: Its tongue is just like a human’s. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.

Name: Chatot
FlavorText: It keeps rhythm by flicking its tail feathers like a metronome. It imitates human speech.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: It lays curses by thinking wicked thoughts. Writings tell that this Pokémon was born out of the assembly of five score and eight malevolent spirits.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: It is a Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: All Spiritomb’s mischief and misdeeds compelled a traveler to use a mysterious spell to bind Spiritomb to an odd keystone.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.

Name: Spiritomb
FlavorText: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It nests in caves untouched by sunlight. Its sharp teeth may fall out when worn away or after an impact, but they regrow within a few days.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It once lived in the tropics. To avoid the cold, it lives in caves warmed by geothermal heat.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: Gible attacks anything that moves, and it drags whatever it catches into the crevice that is its lair. Despite the big mouth, Gible’s stomach is small.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: Gible prefers to stay in narrow holes in the sides of caves heated by geothermal energy. This way, Gible can stay warm even during a blizzard.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: Its original home is an area much hotter than Alola. If you’re planning to live with one, your heating bill will soar.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It reacts to anything that moves—flies right at it and bites it. Sometimes it injures itself, but it doesn’t care too much.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It lives in caves warmed by geothermal heat. Even so, when the weather gets cold, it will huddle close with others of its kind.

Name: Gible
FlavorText: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: Though Gabite are usually of a violent disposition, when I gave one a glass bead it had been eyeing covetously, it suddenly became quite docile.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: It habitually digs up and hoards gems in its nest. Its loot is constantly targeted by thieves.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal incurable illnesses.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: Jewels are buried in the caves these Pokémon nest in, but you’ll be torn apart by claws and fangs the moment you enter one of these caves.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from a protrusion on either side of its head to probe pitch-dark caves.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: It sheds its skin and gradually grows larger. Its scales can be ground into a powder and used as raw materials for traditional medicine.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: It loves shiny things. When it finds a Sableye trying to catch a Carbink, Gabite becomes furiously angry and attacks the Sableye.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: Shiny objects are its passion. It can be found in its cave, scarcely moving, its gaze fixed on the jewels it’s amassed or Carbink it has caught.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.

Name: Gabite
FlavorText: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Its disposition is more vicious than before its Mega Evolution. Garchomp carves its opponents up with the scythes on both arms.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Its arms and wings melted into something like scythes. Mad with rage, it rampages on and on.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Its vaunted wings become scythes, sending it mad with rage. It swings its scythes wildly and slices the ground to pieces.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Excess energy melted its arms and wings, transforming them into giant scythes.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: The protuberances on its head serve as sensors. It can even detect distant prey.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Soars across the heavens at blinding speed—a magnificent sight! It has a feral disposition. Utmost caution is required if one meets a Garchomp out in the wilds.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Garchomp is fast both underground and above. It can bring down prey and return to its den before its body has chilled from being outside.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Its fine scales don’t just reduce wind resistance—their sharp edges also cause injury to any opponent who attacks it.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: It flies at the speed of sound while searching for prey, and it has midair battles with Salamence as the two compete for food.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: It can fly at speeds rivaling jet planes. It dives into flocks of bird Pokémon and gulps the entire flock down whole.

Name: Garchomp
FlavorText: Its body is covered in fine scales that reduce drag, enabling it to fly at high speeds.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: Its robust stomach allows it to nonchalantly devour even rotted matter. It pays frequent visits to villages, seeking out food scraps intended for compost.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: It hides food under its long body hair. However, it forgets it has hidden the food.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing it whole with almost no chewing.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: It stores food beneath its fur. It might share just one bite, but only if it really trusts you.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: Stuffing itself with vast amounts of food is its only concern. Whether the food is rotten or fresh, yummy or tasteless—it does not care.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: Anything that looks edible, Munchlax will go on and swallow whole. Its stomach is tough enough to handle it even if the food has gone rotten.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: It hides food under its long fur, but it sometimes forgets about it and causes a stinky disturbance.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: When it finds something that looks like it might be edible, it goes right ahead and swallows it whole. That’s why it gets fatter day by day.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: It needs to consume its own weight in food every day. As far as flavor is concerned, it’s indifferent.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: In its desperation to gulp down food, it forgets about the food it has hidden under its fur.

Name: Munchlax
FlavorText: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions, such as joy and rage, in the form of waves.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: Though infantile in appearance, it has the mysterious ability to read the minds of humans. The pure of heart are met with Riolu’s approval, while those of ill nature earn only its loathing.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: Its body is lithe yet powerful. It can crest three mountains and cross two canyons in one night.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It can use waves called auras to gauge how others are feeling. These same waves can also tell this Pokémon about the state of the environment.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It’s exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It uses waves called auras to communicate with others of its kind. It doesn’t make any noise during this time, so its enemies can’t detect it.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It knows how people and Pokémon feel by looking at their auras. It doesn’t approach dangerous opponents.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It’s tough enough to run right through the night, and it’s also a hard worker, but it’s still just a youngster.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It can discern the physical and emotional states of people, Pokémon, and other natural things from the shape of their aura waves.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It uses the shapes of auras, which change according to emotion, to communicate with others.

Name: Riolu
FlavorText: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: Bathed in explosive energy, its combative instincts have awakened. For its enemies, it has no mercy whatsoever.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: Its aura has expanded due to Mega Evolution. Governed only by its combative instincts, it strikes enemies without mercy.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: It readies itself to face its enemies by focusing its mental energies. Its fighting style can be summed up in a single word: heartless.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: Black streaks all over its body show where its auras and the energy of Mega Evolution intermingled and raced through it.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: A well-trained one can use its aura to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: A most gallant-looking creature. It emits energy waves and controls them with precision, using them to sense even faraway beings. I have given the name “aura” to this power.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: By sensing the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: It can tell what people are thinking. Only Trainers who have justice in their hearts can earn this Pokémon’s trust.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: Lucario reads its opponent’s feelings with its aura waves. It finds out things it would rather not know, so it gets stressed out easily.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: It concentrates its mental energy and fires off mysterious waves called auras, which can crush boulders of large size to dust.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: They can detect the species of a living being— and its emotions—from over half a mile away. They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: By catching the aura emanating from others, it can read their thoughts and movements.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.

Name: Lucario
FlavorText: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to LUCARIO, since it can detect auras. Even foes it could not otherwise see.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: It shuts its nostrils tight, then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: Though large and languid, Hippopotas is difficult to detect due to its tendency to burrow into and lurk beneath the soil. When agitated or excited, it expels sand from its nostrils.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: This Pokémon is active during the day and passes the cold desert nights burrowed snugly into the sand.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

Name: Hippopotas
FlavorText: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around ten.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: Short-tempered and easily moved to violence. It whips up whirlwinds of sand to crush its foes’ spirits, then goes in for the attack.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: Its huge mouth opens almost seven feet wide. It has enough power to completely crush a car.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: When roused to violence by its rage, it spews out the quantities of sand it has swallowed and whips up a sandstorm.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.

Name: Hippowdon
FlavorText: Its huge mouth is almost seven feet across. It has enough power to completely crush a car.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: Its claws are not only razor-sharp but poisonous, making Skorupi a highly dangerous Pokémon. It seems to be weakened by cold temperatures, however.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: It lives in arid lands. It buries itself in sand and lies in wait for unsuspecting prey.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: It attacks using the claws on its tail. Once locked in its grip, its prey is unable to move as this Pokémon’s poison seeps in.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: It lives in arid regions and can go without food for a year while waiting for prey.

Name: Skorupi
FlavorText: As soon as the tail claws close, its needle tips secrete poison. It can survive a year without food.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: Has a brutish, ferocious temperament. With immense strength and a sturdy shell off which swords will bounce, it rampages about and wreaks havoc.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: Its body is encased in a sturdy shell. Its head rotates 180 degrees, eliminating blind spots.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: It’s so vicious that it’s called the Sand Demon. Yet when confronted by Hippowdon, Drapion keeps a low profile and will never pick a fight.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: Possessing a sturdy build, it takes pride in its strength, taking down foes without using toxins.

Name: Drapion
FlavorText: It attacks people and Pokémon that cross the desert. This has only furthered its bad reputation.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: A poison wielder with a dastardly personality. Despite such qualities, this species is afforded a measure of popularity due to its peculiar cry and comical features.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: It inflates its poison sacs and makes a blubbering sound to intimidate foes.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: Once diluted, its poison becomes medicinal. This Pokémon came into popularity after a pharmaceutical company chose it as a mascot.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: It makes frightening noises with its poison-filled cheek sacs. When opponents flinch, Croagunk hits them with a poison jab.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: Fluid squeezed from its finger, albeit poisonous, is a significant ingredient in remedies for lower back pain.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: Fluid squeezed from its finger, albeit poisonous, is a significant ingredient in remedies for lower-back pain.

Name: Croagunk
FlavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks, the stored poison is churned for greater potency.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: Its crimson claws contain a virulent toxin. This toxin can be made into a tonic by diluting it, mixing it with several types of wild grass, and boiling it down over two days.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: The toxin made in its poison sac is pumped to the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: It booms out a victory croak when its prey goes down in defeat. This Pokémon and Seismitoad are related species.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: The croaking that Toxicroak produces before a battle is for churning the poison it has stored in its poison sac.

Name: Toxicroak
FlavorText: The toxin made in its poison sacs is pumped to the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: Though this is a plant Pokémon, it has a gluttonous and unruly temperament. Carnivine attacks its prey with its cavernous maw wide open.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: Using its tentacles to hang from branches, it looks like a plant when it is not moving. It awaits prey with its mouth wide open.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat its prey.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: Using its tentacles to lash itself to trees, it lies in wait for prey, luring it close with sweet-smelling drool.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: It walks around on its tentacles in search of a tree branch where it can dangle down and ambush prey.

Name: Carnivine
FlavorText: Hanging from branches using its tentacles, it looks like a plant. It awaits prey, mouth wide open.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: What a gorgeous sight this Pokémon is as it swims with its long, pink-painted caudal fins fluttering behind it. Finneon’s beautiful appearance has led to its nickname: “finery fish.”

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: The way its two tail fins flutter while it swims has earned it the nickname Beautifly of the Sea.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: When night falls, their pink patterns begin to shine. They’re popular with divers, so there are resorts that feed them to keep them close.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: Its double tail fins propel its energetic jumps. When it breaks the surface of the sea, Wingull swoop down to grab it on the fly.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: Swimming and fluttering its two tail fins, it looks like a BEAUTIFLY. At night, the patterns on its tail fins softly shine.

Name: Finneon
FlavorText: The way its two tail fins flutter while it swims has earned it the nickname “BEAUTIFLY of the Sea.”

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: Lumineon swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokémon—its natural predators.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: Uses its gleaming fins to hunt its prey. The view of Lumineon schooling near the surface of the sea at night is breathtaking— it’s as though there were shining stars right there.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing patterns on its four fins.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: They traverse the deep waters as if crawling over the seafloor. The fantastic lights of its fins shine like stars in the night sky.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: Deep down at the bottom of the ocean, prey is scarce. Lumineon get into fierce disputes with Lanturn over food.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: This deep-sea Pokémon lives at the bottom of the sea. Its fins haul it over the seabed in search of its favorite food—Starmie.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

Name: Lumineon
FlavorText: It crawls along the seafloor using its long front fins like legs. It competes for food with Lanturn.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: Though ball-like in shape, this Pokémon is a proficient swimmer. I have discovered that if a Mantyke spends much time with schools of Remoraid, it will eventually achieve evolution.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: Scientists discovered that the distinctive patterns on its back differ by region.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: A friendly Pokémon that senses the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: It swims along with a school of Remoraid, and they’ll all fight together to repel attackers.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhat sluggish. The colder waters of the seas in this region may be the cause.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: Mantyke are friendly toward people and will approach boats closely. The patterns on their backs differ depending on their habitat.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: It’s highly friendly and easily tamed. Tours that take people swimming with Mantyke are a super-popular beach activity.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: The pattern on its back varies by region. It often swims in a school of Remoraid.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: People organize tours to see this Pokémon frolic and skim the tops of waves with Remoraid.

Name: Mantyke
FlavorText: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

Name: Snover
FlavorText: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.

Name: Snover
FlavorText: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain’s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

Name: Snover
FlavorText: One is likely to encounter this Pokémon while out in the snow. There are stories of Snover appearing in human settlements but doing no harm—rather, they bond with the children.

Name: Snover
FlavorText: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

Name: Snover
FlavorText: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

Name: Snover
FlavorText: The berries that grow around its belly are like ice pops. Galarian Darumaka absolutely love these berries.

Name: Snover
FlavorText: It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs into the snow to absorb water and keep its own temperature down.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: A powerful Pokémon that can split huge boulders with ease. Dislikes associating with others and chooses to live quietly deep within the mountains, playing with the snow.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as the Ice Monster.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: This Pokémon is known to bring blizzards. A shake of its massive body is enough to cause whiteout conditions.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

Name: Abomasnow
FlavorText: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as “The Ice Monster.”

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: They travel in groups of four or five, leaving signs for one another on trees and rocks. They bring down their prey with coordinated attacks.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: This species corners prey as a pack, under the guidance of a leader. Weavile displays increased cunning, leading me to speculate that its evolution caused further brain development.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: It sends signals to others of its kind by carving odd patterns on trees and ice.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: With its claws, it leaves behind signs for its friends to find. The number of distinct signs is said to be over 500.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: Thanks to its increased intelligence, scrapping over food is a thing of the past. A scratch from its claws will give you a case of frostbite!

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: One Weavile will trip a Sandshrew and flip it over, and then another Weavile will deal the finishing blow with its sharp claws.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: They dwell in cold places. This Pokémon’s main food source in Alola is Vulpix and Sandshrew, which they carefully divide among their group.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in trees with its claws as a signal to others.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: They communicate by clawing signs in boulders and work together to surround enemies.

Name: Weavile
FlavorText: It sends signals to others by carving odd patterns in frost-covered trees and ice.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed Magneton’s molecular structure, turning it into Magnezone.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: I theorize that a special magnetic field influenced this Pokémon, changing its molecular structure and causing it to evolve. It emits strange radio waves toward space from its antenna.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Its three units generate magnetism.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: It’s thought that a special magnetic field changed the molecular structure of this Pokémon’s body, and that’s what caused the Pokémon’s evolution.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it’s being controlled by some mysterious being.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: There are still people who believe that this Pokémon came from outer space. It emanates a powerful magnetic field.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: It uses radar to monitor its territory. Intruders are quickly disposed of with a hyper beam.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: As it zooms through the sky, this Pokémon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin, while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: Three units generate magnetism. There have been many mistaken reports of UFO sightings when Magnezone flies through the night sky.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: Sometimes the magnetism emitted by Magnezone is too strong, making them attract each other so they cannot move.

Name: Magnezone
FlavorText: A group tried to use scientific means to make Magnezone evolve, but their efforts ended in failure.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: Its tongue can extend and contract freely, and it is capable of reaching lengths over 10 times Lickilicky’s height. Beware of the saliva, as it contains corrosive elements.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: Lickilicky can do just about anything with its tongue, which is as dexterous as the human hand. In contrast, Lickilicky’s use of its fingers is clumsy.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: It uses its tongue much more skillfully than its hands or its feet. It can deftly pick up a single small bean with its tongue.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: A contest is under way to determine which one can stick its tongue out the farthest. The current record is...more than 82 feet.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: The long tongue is always soggy with slobber. The saliva contains a solvent that causes numbness.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: It has space in its throat to store saliva. It can also roll up its tongue and store it in the same spot.

Name: Lickilicky
FlavorText: Its saliva can decompose anything. It wraps its long tongue around things to coat them with its sticky saliva.

Name: Rhyperior
FlavorText: This Pokémon evolved through use of a curious item. Its rocklike hide is composed of a mysterious substance and can withstand a blow from a masterwork sword with nary a scratch.

Name: Rhyperior
FlavorText: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. On rare occasions, the Pokémon even shoots out Geodude.

Name: Rhyperior
