FlavorText: It relies on its carapace to deflect incoming attacks and throw its enemy off balance. As soon as that happens, it drives its drill into the foe.

Name: Rhyperior
FlavorText: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

Name: Rhyperior
FlavorText: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

Name: Rhyperior
FlavorText: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude. Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.

Name: Rhyperior
FlavorText: It can launch a rock held in its hand like a missile by tightening then expanding muscles instantly.

Name: Rhyperior
FlavorText: From holes in its palms, it fires out GEODUDE. Its carapace  can withstand volcanic eruptions.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance. It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping them around prey to ensnare them.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: Vine growth is accelerated for Tangrowth living in warm climates. If the vines grow long, Tangrowth shortens them by tearing parts of them off.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can’t even see its eyes.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it’s fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: Its arms are made of plants that bind themselves to things. They grow back right away if cut.

Name: Tangrowth
FlavorText: When it remains still, it appears to be a large shrub. Unsuspecting prey that wander near get ensnared by its vines.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: Its evolution was induced by an unusual item, and its electrical output rises along with its heart rate. From its tails, it can unleash an electric current measuring 20,000 volts.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of electricity.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: In terms of electrical-energy output, Electivire is one of the best among all Electric Pokémon. It discharges high-voltage currents from its tails.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: It grips its tail, which spews electricity, and then beats down opponents with the power of its electrified fist.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: When it gets excited, it thumps its chest. With every thud, thunder roars and electric sparks shower all around.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: It pushes the tips of its tails against its foes and then lets loose a high-voltage current. Its foes are burned to a crisp in an instant.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: The instant it presses the tips of its tails onto an opponent, it sends over 20,000 volts of electricity into the foe.

Name: Electivire
FlavorText: Heedless of enemy attacks, it closes in, shoves its tails onto the foe, then looses high voltage.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: Use of a strange item caused this Pokémon to evolve. Fireballs launched from the ends of its tubelike arms are hot enough to melt an iron pot in an instant.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: Living in the crater of a volcano has caused this Pokémon’s body to resemble its environment—it has an organ similar to a magma chamber.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: Magmortar takes down its enemies by shooting fireballs, which burn them to a blackened crisp. It avoids this method when hunting prey.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: There are still quite a few factories that rely on the flames provided by Magmortar to process metals.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: From its arm, it launches fireballs hotter than 3,500 degrees Fahrenheit. Its arm starts to melt when it fires a whole barrage.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: They dwell in volcanic craters. According to what is known, a single pair of male and female Magmortar lives in one volcano.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: When shooting 3,600 degree F fireballs from its arms, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: When launching 3,600 degrees F fireballs, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.

Name: Magmortar
FlavorText: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

Name: Togekiss
FlavorText: Scant few have ever sighted this Pokémon. After studying what literature remains, I am certain Togekiss will reveal itself when peace reigns in the land.

Name: Togekiss
FlavorText: It will never appear where there is strife. Sightings of this Pokémon have recently become rare.

Name: Togekiss
FlavorText: Known as a bringer of blessings, it’s been depicted on good-luck charms since ancient times.

Name: Togekiss
FlavorText: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they’ve hardly been seen at all.

Name: Togekiss
FlavorText: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another’s rights and avoid needless strife.

Name: Togekiss
FlavorText: As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.

Name: Togekiss
FlavorText: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

Name: Yanmega
FlavorText: Extremely violent. When hunting, it wastes none of its energy, aiming only for prey’s most vulnerable spots. Any who manage to tame this Pokémon must be of incredible bravery.

Name: Yanmega
FlavorText: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

Name: Yanmega
FlavorText: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

Name: Yanmega
FlavorText: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes’ heads instantly while flying by at high speed.

Name: Yanmega
FlavorText: Its jaw power is incredible. It is adept at biting apart foes while flying by at high speed.

Name: Yanmega
FlavorText: The beat of its wings is so powerful that it accidentally dislodges full-grown trees when it takes off in flight.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: The younger they are, the more they smell like fresh grass. With age, their fragrance takes on the odor of fallen leaves.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine, you’ll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: Cells similar to those of plants have been found in its fur. Its hard tail can fell a large tree with one stroke, and the tail’s sharpness exceeds even that of a sword crafted by a master.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s tail is blade sharp, with a fantastic cutting edge that can slice right though large trees.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: Galarians favor the distinctive aroma that drifts from this Pokémon’s leaves. There’s a popular perfume made using that scent.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: It gets its nutrition from photosynthesis. It lives a quiet life deep in forests where clean rivers flow.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: Although it doesn’t like disputes, it will sharpen the leaf on its tail into a blade and fight if it has to protect its friends.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: Its cellular composition is closer to that of a plant than an animal. It uses photosynthesis to produce its energy supply without eating food.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: With cells similar to those of plants, it performs photosynthesis inside its body and creates pure air.

Name: Leafeon
FlavorText: It basically does not fight. With cells similar to those of plants, it can perform photosynthesis.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere, creating flurries of diamond dust.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: Glaceon is able to lower its body temperature very quickly. It freezes the atmosphere, creating diamond dust that glitters like gems while it flutters and dances around.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: As a defense mechanism, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand out like needles.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: The coldness emanating from Glaceon causes powdery snow to form, making it quite a popular Pokémon at ski resorts.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: Any who become captivated by the beauty of the snowfall that Glaceon creates will be frozen before they know it.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: It can instantaneously freeze any moisture that’s around it, creating ice pellets to shoot at its prey.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: It protects itself by freezing its fur into sharp needles. It can drop its body temperature below –75 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: It freezes its fur into icicles, spiky and sharp, and tackles its prey.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: By controlling its body heat, it can freeze the atmosphere around it to make a diamond-dust flurry.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: It causes small ice crystals to form by lowering the temperature of the surrounding atmosphere.

Name: Glaceon
FlavorText: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

Name: Gliscor
FlavorText: It glides soundlessly on pitch-black wings and sinks sharp fangs into the throat of its prey. It takes on a look of satisfaction once it has entirely drained its prey of blood.

Name: Gliscor
FlavorText: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, Gliscor swoops!

Name: Gliscor
FlavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

Name: Gliscor
FlavorText: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

Name: Gliscor
FlavorText: It dances silently through the sky. When it approaches prey, it can land a critical hit in an instant.

Name: Gliscor
FlavorText: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly, it can circle the globe without flapping once.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: This species reached its zenith during the period known as the ice age. I suspect that Hisui’s frigid climate is in harmony with Mamoswine’s constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The ice age is over and the climate has warmed, so this Pokémon’s population has thinned.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: It looks strong, and that’s exactly what it is. As the weather grows colder, its ice tusks grow longer, thicker, and more impressive.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10,000 years. This Pokémon has been around a long, long, long time.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: When the temperature rose at the end of the ice age, most Mamoswine disappeared.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: A frozen one was dug up from soil dating back 10,000 years. It woke up to much amazement.

Name: Mamoswine
FlavorText: It flourished worldwide during the ice age but its population declined when the masses of ice began to dwindle.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: A curious item induced this evolution. The Pokémon’s offensive capabilities have greatly increased, but the strangeness of its behavior has magnified in equal measure. This worries me.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Additional software was installed to make it an even better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Some say an additional program made this Pokémon evolve, but even academics can’t agree on whether Porygon-Z is really an evolution.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z’s behavior.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Its behavior is noticeably unstable, which is apparently due to the incompetence of the engineer who updated its programming.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Its program was modified to facilitate extra-dimensional activities, but that led to noticeably strange behavior.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: In order to create a more advanced Pokémon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

Name: Porygon-Z
FlavorText: Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.

Name: Gallade
FlavorText: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.

Name: Gallade
FlavorText: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

Name: Gallade
FlavorText: The blades extending from its elbows are sharper than the finest swords. Its swordsmanship, albeit self-taught, is astonishingly impressive.

Name: Gallade
FlavorText: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using the extending swords on its elbows.

Name: Gallade
FlavorText: Sharply attuned to others’ wishes for help, this Pokémon seeks out those in need and aids them in battle.

Name: Gallade
FlavorText: True to its honorable-warrior image, it uses the blades on its elbows only in defense of something or someone.

Name: Gallade
FlavorText: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: It is able to emit powerful magnetism, allowing it control over the iron sand that forms its luscious mustache. Using this iron sand, Probopass forms hard stones with which it smites its prey.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: Its entire body exudes strong magnetism. Probopass controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: Although it can control its units known as Mini-Noses, they sometimes get lost and don’t come back.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: The main body controls three mobile units called Mini-Noses, which it maneuvers to catch prey.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: It radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances become unusable.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: It freely controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

Name: Probopass
FlavorText: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them, it can attack the foe from three directions.

Name: Dusknoir
FlavorText: Comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife. Known to mistakenly take the souls of those who yet have life left in them, albeit rarely.

Name: Dusknoir
FlavorText: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

Name: Dusknoir
FlavorText: With the mouth on its belly, Dusknoir swallows its target whole. The soul is the only thing eaten— Dusknoir disgorges the body before departing.

Name: Dusknoir
FlavorText: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.

Name: Dusknoir
FlavorText: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.

Name: Dusknoir
FlavorText: This feared Pokémon is said to travel to worlds unknown. Some even believe that it takes lost spirits along with it.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It freezes prey by blowing its −58 degree Fahrenheit breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: When it finds humans or Pokémon it likes, it freezes them and takes them to its chilly den, where they become decorations.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: A Pokémon inhabited by the soul of a woman who died bearing a grudge in the snowy mountains. Legends of Froslass placing deathly curses on misbehaving men send shivers down my spine.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It freezes foes with an icy breath that is nearly −60 degrees Fahrenheit. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It spits out cold air of nearly −60 degrees Fahrenheit to freeze its quarry. It brings frozen prey back to its lair and neatly lines them up.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: After a woman met her end on a snowy mountain, her regrets lingered on. From them, this Pokémon was born. Its favorite food is frozen souls.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It’s said that on nights of terrible blizzards, it comes down to human settlements. If you hear it knocking at your door, do not open it!

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It freezes hikers who have come to climb snowy mountains and carries them back to its home. It only goes after men it thinks are handsome.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: The soul of a woman lost on a snowy mountain possessed an icicle, becoming this Pokémon. The food it most relishes is the souls of men.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees Fahrenheit. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degrees F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as FROSLASS

Name: Froslass
FlavorText: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has possessed a lawn mower. It will mow down grass and flowers, then swagger around with pride at its accomplishments.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: The lawn mower is one of the household appliances that led to the development of the Rotom Dex.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: A form in which Rotom lurks within a misshapen wheelbarrow. The wheelbarrow’s mechanisms are bizarre. It’s a bothersome Pokémon, causing trouble by mowing down grass and trees.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: In this form, Rotom focuses its antics on plants. Any flowers you were growing are going to get mowed down.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This is Rotom after it’s seized control of a lawn mower that has a special motor. As it mows down grass, it scatters the clippings everywhere.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: There are several appliances that Rotom can inspirit, but the first one to be developed was the electric fan.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has entered an electric fan. It smirks with satisfaction over a prank well pulled after it blows away everything around it.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: A form in which Rotom lurks within a mysterious contraption. The contraption’s purpose is unknown. A bothersome Pokémon, causing trouble by stirring up powerful winds.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has taken over a fan that has a special motor. Its gusts of wind blow its opponents away!

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: In this form, Rotom applies its new power over wind to its love of pranks. It will happily blow away any important documents it can find.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: The special motor within the refrigerator is the key to bringing about Rotom’s change in form.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has entered a refrigerator. It leaps around gleefully after it uses cold air to freeze the area around it.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: A form in which Rotom lurks within a bizarre cupboard. The cupboard’s composition is unknown. A bothersome Pokémon, causing trouble by frosting everything over.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: When it’s like this, Rotom likes to play pranks that are freezing cold. You may find it’s turned the bath you just filled to solid ice!

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: Rotom assumes this form when it takes over a refrigerator powered by a special motor. It battles by spewing cold air.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: The model of washing machine that Rotom can inspirit has been discontinued, so these appliances are now traded at high prices.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has entered a washing machine. It nods with satisfaction after it floods the surrounding area.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: A form in which Rotom lurks within an odd bureau. The bureau’s purpose is unknown. A bothersome Pokémon, causing trouble by splashing cold water everywhere.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has possessed a washing machine that uses a special motor. It blasts out water to get enemies to back down.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This form of Rotom enjoys coming up with water-based pranks. Be careful with it if you don’t want your room flooded.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has possessed a convection microwave oven. It will sear the surrounding area with its burning heat, then smile in delight.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: If the convection microwave oven is not working properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will become lethargic.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: A form in which Rotom lurks within a strange cauldron. The cauldron’s origin is unknown. A bothersome Pokémon, causing trouble with the flames it spits.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This form of Rotom enjoys making mischief by turning up the heat. It will gleefully burn your favorite outfit.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This Rotom has possessed a convection microwave oven that uses a special motor. It also has a flair for manipulating flames.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: This bizarre Pokémon appears to be a will-o’-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: With a body made of plasma, it can inhabit all sorts of machines. It loves to surprise others.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

Name: Rotom
FlavorText: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

Name: Uxie
FlavorText: A Pokémon feared but also respected for stealing away the memories of evildoers. I have found records that suggest Uxie holds dominion over knowledge.

Name: Uxie
FlavorText: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

Name: Uxie
FlavorText: Known as the Being of Knowledge, it is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

Name: Uxie
FlavorText: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

Name: Uxie
FlavorText: When Uxie flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.

Name: Uxie
FlavorText: According to some sources, this Pokémon provided people with the intelligence necessary to solve various problems.

Name: Mesprit
FlavorText: Known as the Being of Emotion. In legend, this Pokémon was feared, as any who showed disrespect would have their emotions thrown into disarray.

Name: Mesprit
FlavorText: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake’s surface.

Name: Mesprit
FlavorText: It is known as the Being of Emotion. It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

Name: Mesprit
FlavorText: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

Name: Mesprit
FlavorText: When Mesprit flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.

Name: Mesprit
FlavorText: This Pokémon is said to have endowed the human heart with emotions, such as sorrow and joy.

Name: Azelf
FlavorText: The dreaded Being of Willpower. Legends tell of this Pokémon manipulating the will of its adversaries and turning them into puppets of its own.

Name: Azelf
FlavorText: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

Name: Azelf
FlavorText: It is known as the Being of Willpower. It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

Name: Azelf
FlavorText: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

Name: Azelf
FlavorText: When Azelf flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.

Name: Azelf
FlavorText: This Pokémon is said to have endowed humans with the determination needed to face any of life’s difficulties.

Name: Azelf
FlavorText: It is thought that UXIE, MESPRIT and AZELF all came from the same egg.

Name: Dialga
FlavorText: Radiant light caused Dialga to take on a form bearing a striking resemblance to the creator Pokémon. Dialga now wields such colossal strength that one must conclude this is its true form.

Name: Dialga
FlavorText: This Pokémon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.

Name: Dialga
FlavorText: This Pokémon is spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

Name: Dialga
FlavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

Name: Dialga
FlavorText: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

Name: Dialga
FlavorText: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when Dialga’s heart beats.

Name: Dialga
FlavorText: This Pokémon completely controls the flow of time. It uses its power to travel at will through the past and future.

Name: Palkia
FlavorText: It soars across the sky in a form that greatly resembles the creator of all things. Perhaps this imitation of appearance is Palkia’s strategy for gaining Arceus’s powers.

Name: Palkia
FlavorText: This Pokémon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.

Name: Palkia
FlavorText: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. Palkia appears in mythology.

Name: Palkia
FlavorText: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

Name: Palkia
FlavorText: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

Name: Palkia
FlavorText: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with Palkia’s every breath.

Name: Palkia
FlavorText: Its total control over the boundaries of space enable it to transport itself to faraway places or even other dimensions.

Name: Heatran
FlavorText: Stories tell of this Pokémon being birthed from the boiling magma within Mount Coronet. Its molten-steel body holds many mysteries.

Name: Heatran
FlavorText: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

Name: Heatran
FlavorText: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

Name: Heatran
FlavorText: Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.

Name: Regigigas
FlavorText: According to legend, Regigigas pulled landmasses together and bound them with rope to create the continent of Hisui. Though I have my doubts, the story could well contain a shred of truth.

Name: Regigigas
FlavorText: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

Name: Regigigas
FlavorText: It’s said that Regigigas created other Pokémon from many different materials before it moved the continents to where they are today.

Name: Regigigas
FlavorText: All over the world, there are legends that tell of Regigigas creating other Pokémon in its own image.

Name: Regigigas
FlavorText: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

Name: Regigigas
FlavorText: It is believed to have shaped REGIROCK, REGICE, and REGISTEEL out of clay, ice, and magma.

Name: Giratina
FlavorText: Giratina loses its legs upon changing into this form. I believe this Pokémon must hail from a world where the heavens and the earth are as one, though I have no way of proving it.

Name: Giratina
FlavorText: There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.

Name: Giratina
FlavorText: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

Name: Giratina
FlavorText: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

Name: Giratina
FlavorText: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

Name: Cresselia
FlavorText: Cresselia is reminiscent of the crescent moon. It leaves a brilliant line of light in its wake as it flies across the night sky. I daresay it resembles the heavenly maiden who created the Milky Way.

Name: Cresselia
FlavorText: When it flies, it releases shiny particles from its veil-like wings. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

Name: Cresselia
FlavorText: Those who sleep holding Cresselia’s feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

Name: Cresselia
FlavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

Name: Cresselia
FlavorText: On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.

Name: Phione
FlavorText: Can be seen floating offshore during seasons when the seas are warm. Its azure body blends in with the ocean waters—logic suggests this is a defense mechanism against natural predators.

Name: Phione
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

Name: Phione
FlavorText: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

Name: Phione
FlavorText: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

Name: Manaphy
FlavorText: Rumored to migrate across the oceans and visit Hisui’s coastal waters only rarely. Although Manaphy resembles Phione, it is also quite different. The relation between the two is unclear.

Name: Manaphy
FlavorText: Water makes up 80 percent of its body. This Pokémon is easily affected by its environment.

Name: Manaphy
FlavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

Name: Manaphy
FlavorText: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

Name: Manaphy
FlavorText: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

Name: Manaphy
FlavorText: Water makes up 80% of its body. This Pokémon is easily affected by its environment.

Name: Darkrai
FlavorText: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village’s inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.

Name: Darkrai
FlavorText: Folklore has it that on moonless nights, this Pokémon will make people see horrific nightmares.

Name: Darkrai
FlavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of a new moon.

Name: Darkrai
FlavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

Name: Darkrai
FlavorText: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

Name: Darkrai
FlavorText: To protect itself, it afflicts those around it with nightmares. However, it means no harm.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: Upon taking in the scent of a particular rare flower, Shaymin is enveloped in light, and its tiny body transforms. I took a whiff of the flower myself, but alas, my body remained unchanged.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: It lives in common flower patches but is rarely noticed. It is often mistaken for a flowering plant when curled up.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings  of gratitude are the message it delivers.

Name: Shaymin
FlavorText: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

Name: Arceus
FlavorText: It is the heavenly fount from which pours the light that shines across Hisui. Its luminance guides and protects all Pokémon. Hisuian mythology states that Arceus is the creator of all things.

Name: Arceus
FlavorText: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was the first Pokémon born before the universe even existed.

Name: Arceus
FlavorText: It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.

Name: Arceus
FlavorText: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

Name: Arceus
FlavorText: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

Name: Arceus
FlavorText: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing then shaped the world.

Name: Arceus
FlavorText: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing, then shaped the world.

Name: Victini
FlavorText: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.

Name: Victini
FlavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

Name: Victini
FlavorText: It creates an unlimited supply of energy inside its body, which it shares with those who touch it.

Name: Snivy
FlavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

Name: Snivy
FlavorText: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

Name: Snivy
FlavorText: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

Name: Servine
FlavorText: When it gets dirty, its leaves can’t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

Name: Servine
FlavorText: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

Name: Servine
FlavorText: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

Name: Serperior
FlavorText: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

Name: Serperior
FlavorText: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior’s noble eyes.

Name: Serperior
FlavorText: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.

Name: Tepig
FlavorText: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

Name: Tepig
FlavorText: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

Name: Tepig
FlavorText: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.

Name: Pignite
FlavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

Name: Pignite
FlavorText: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.

Name: Pignite
FlavorText: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.

Name: Emboar
FlavorText: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

Name: Emboar
FlavorText: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

Name: Emboar
FlavorText: A flaring beard of fire is proof that it is fired up. It is adept at using many different moves.

Name: Oshawott
FlavorText: This Pokémon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I’ve conferred upon this shell the name “scalchop.”

Name: Oshawott
FlavorText: The scalchop on its stomach isn’t just used for battle—it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

Name: Oshawott
FlavorText: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

Name: Oshawott
FlavorText: The scalchop on its stomach isn’t just used for battle--it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

Name: Oshawott
FlavorText: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.

Name: Dewott
FlavorText: Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.

Name: Dewott
FlavorText: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

Name: Dewott
FlavorText: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

Name: Dewott
FlavorText: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.

Name: Samurott
FlavorText: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokémon’s evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.

Name: Samurott
FlavorText: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

Name: Samurott
FlavorText: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.

Name: Samurott
FlavorText: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.

Name: Patrat
FlavorText: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.

Name: Patrat
FlavorText: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

Name: Patrat
FlavorText: Extremely cautious, they take shifts to maintain a constant watch of their nest. They feel insecure without a lookout.

Name: Watchog
FlavorText: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

Name: Watchog
FlavorText: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

Name: Watchog
FlavorText: They make the patterns on their bodies shine in order to threaten predators. Keen eyesight lets them see in the dark.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won’t forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: This Pokémon is popular with beginners because it’s intelligent, obedient to its Trainer’s commands, and easy to raise.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: This Pokémon has excellent judgment. If it decides it can’t defeat an opponent, it immediately turns tail and vamooses.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: The long fur surrounding its face functions as radar, enabling it to probe the condition of its battle opponents.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: Because it doesn’t yelp, it’s extremely popular with Trainers who live in apartment buildings.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it’s also smart enough to check its foe’s strength and avoid battle.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.

Name: Lillipup
FlavorText: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: The black fur that covers this Pokémon’s body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon. So much so that there’s a theory that Herdier was the first Pokémon to partner with people.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: It has been living with people for so long that portrayals of it can be found on the walls of caves from long, long ago.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: The longer its black fur grows, the harder and more impervious it gets. Claws and fangs can’t easily penetrate it.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: This Pokémon obeys its master’s orders faithfully. However, it refuses to listen to anything said by a person it doesn’t respect.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: Its dense black fur grows continuously. The high cost of keeping its hard fur properly groomed makes this a troublesome Pokémon to train.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: This very loyal Pokémon helps Trainers, and it also takes care of other Pokémon.

Name: Herdier
FlavorText: It loyally follows its Trainer’s orders. For ages, they have helped Trainers raise Pokémon.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It’s said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: These Pokémon seem to enjoy living with humans. Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up to people in about three days.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: Its fur is long and thick. A long time ago in cold regions, every household kept a Stoutland.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: It pays no mind to the cold, thanks to its long warm coat. Stoutland in Alola look a little uncomfortable.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: With this wise Pokémon, there could be no concern that it would ever attack people. Some parents even trust it to babysit.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant, it’s a trustworthy partner on rescue teams.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

Name: Stoutland
FlavorText: This extremely wise Pokémon excels at rescuing people stranded at sea or in the mountains.

Name: Purrloin
FlavorText: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

Name: Purrloin
FlavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.

Name: Purrloin
FlavorText: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

Name: Purrloin
FlavorText: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.

Name: Purrloin
FlavorText: Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.

Name: Liepard
FlavorText: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.

Name: Liepard
FlavorText: Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

Name: Liepard
FlavorText: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

Name: Liepard
FlavorText: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.

Name: Liepard
FlavorText: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

Name: Pansage
FlavorText: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.

Name: Pansage
FlavorText: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

Name: Pansage
FlavorText: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

Name: Simisage
FlavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

Name: Simisage
FlavorText: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.

Name: Simisage
FlavorText: It strikes its enemies with a thorn-covered tail. The leaf on its head is bitter.

Name: Pansear
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Pansear
FlavorText: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

Name: Pansear
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600° F.

Name: Pansear
FlavorText: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

Name: Simisear
FlavorText: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

Name: Simisear
FlavorText: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

Name: Simisear
FlavorText: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

Name: Panpour
FlavorText: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

Name: Panpour
FlavorText: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

Name: Panpour
FlavorText: It does not thrive in dry environments. It keeps itself damp by shooting water stored in its head tuft from its tail.

Name: Simipour
FlavorText: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

Name: Simipour
FlavorText: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.

Name: Simipour
FlavorText: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

Name: Munna
FlavorText: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.

Name: Munna
FlavorText: Late at night, it appears beside people’s pillows. As it feeds on dreams, the patterns on its body give off a faint glow.

Name: Munna
FlavorText: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.

Name: Munna
FlavorText: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.

Name: Munna
FlavorText: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

Name: Musharna
FlavorText: It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.

Name: Musharna
FlavorText: When dark mists emanate from its body, don’t get too near. If you do, your nightmares will become reality.

Name: Musharna
FlavorText: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

Name: Musharna
FlavorText: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

Name: Musharna
FlavorText: With the mist from its forehead, it can create shapes of things from dreams it has eaten.

Name: Pidove
FlavorText: It’s forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.

Name: Pidove
FlavorText: Where people go, these Pokémon follow. If you’re scattering food for them, be careful— several hundred of them can gather at once.

Name: Pidove
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

Name: Pidove
FlavorText: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.

Name: Pidove
FlavorText: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

Name: Tranquill
FlavorText: These bright Pokémon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.

Name: Tranquill
FlavorText: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.

Name: Tranquill
FlavorText: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

Name: Tranquill
FlavorText: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.

Name: Tranquill
FlavorText: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

Name: Unfezant
FlavorText: This Pokémon is intelligent and intensely proud. People will sit up and take notice if you become the Trainer of one.

Name: Unfezant
FlavorText: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.

Name: Unfezant
FlavorText: Females of this species are very capable fliers, particularly notable for their stamina. They also take longer to adjust to people.

Name: Unfezant
FlavorText: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

Name: Unfezant
FlavorText: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

Name: Unfezant
FlavorText: Males swing the plumage on their heads to threaten others, but females are better at flying.

Name: Blitzle
FlavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

Name: Blitzle
FlavorText: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

Name: Blitzle
FlavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

Name: Zebstrika
FlavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

Name: Zebstrika
FlavorText: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

Name: Zebstrika
FlavorText: This ill-tempered Pokémon is dangerous because when it’s angry, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: It’s as hard as steel, but apparently a long soak in water will cause it to soften a bit.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: It was found in a fissure in a layer of exposed rock. The material that makes up its body is dirt from several hundred years ago.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: The hexagonal hole is its ear. Deep in that ear is an energy core, so if you stick your hand in there, Roggenrola will be very angry!

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: The hexagonal cavity is its ear. It walks in the direction of sounds it hears, but if the sounds cease, it panics and topples over.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: Born deep within the ground, it compares itself with similar species, such as Geodude and Carbink, to settle which has the hardest body.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

Name: Roggenrola
FlavorText: The hexagonal-shaped hole is its ear. It has a tendency to walk in the direction the sound is coming from.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: If you see its orange crystals start to glow, be wary. It’s about to fire off bursts of energy.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: Its orange crystals are lumps of powerful energy. They’re valuable, so Boldore is sometimes targeted for them.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: The energy overflowing from its body has turned into orange crystals that are hard enough to smash diamonds.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: It explores caves in search of underground water. It’s not comfortable around water, so this Pokémon takes great care in lapping it up.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: Its orange crystal is a mass of energy. Just one crystal fragment would provide enough fuel for a hundred dump trucks.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: Because its energy was too great to be contained, the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.

Name: Boldore
FlavorText: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: This hardy Pokémon can often be found on construction sites and in mines, working alongside people and Copperajah.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: It absorbs rays of sunlight and shoots out energy. It’s usually lurking deep beneath the surface.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: When it fires off energy with all its might, the power creates countless fissures on its body.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: Known for its hefty horsepower, this Pokémon is a popular partner for construction workers.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: The blasts of energy it makes from sunbeams have terrifying power. However, it’s not able to fire its blasts at night or on rainy days.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in its energy core and fired as a ball of light.

Name: Gigalith
FlavorText: The solar energy absorbed by its body’s orange crystals is magnified internally and fired from its mouth.

Name: Woobat
FlavorText: It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.

Name: Woobat
FlavorText: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it’s evidence that Woobat live there.

Name: Woobat
FlavorText: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

Name: Woobat
FlavorText: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

Name: Woobat
FlavorText: Suction from its nostrils enables it to stick to cave walls during sleep. It leaves a heart-shaped mark behind.

Name: Swoobat
FlavorText: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.

Name: Swoobat
FlavorText: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won’t be able to fly for a little while.

Name: Swoobat
FlavorText: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

Name: Swoobat
FlavorText: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.

Name: Swoobat
FlavorText: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

Name: Drilbur
FlavorText: It’s a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.

Name: Drilbur
FlavorText: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

Name: Drilbur
FlavorText: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.

Name: Drilbur
FlavorText: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

Name: Drilbur
FlavorText: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

Name: Excadrill
FlavorText: Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.

Name: Excadrill
FlavorText: It’s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill’s rampant digging.

Name: Excadrill
FlavorText: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

Name: Excadrill
FlavorText: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

Name: Excadrill
FlavorText: Forming a drill with its steel claws and head, it can bore through a steel plate, no matter how thick it is.

Name: Audino
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.

Name: Audino
FlavorText: Audino’s sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino’s ears.

Name: Audino
FlavorText: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

Name: Audino
FlavorText: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.

Name: Audino
FlavorText: Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radarlike ability to understand its surroundings through slight sounds.

Name: Timburr
FlavorText: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.

Name: Timburr
FlavorText: It loves helping out with construction projects. It loves it so much that if rain causes work to halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

Name: Timburr
FlavorText: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

Name: Timburr
FlavorText: These Pokémon appear at building sites and help out with construction. They always carry squared logs.

Name: Timburr
FlavorText: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

Name: Gurdurr
FlavorText: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there’s skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.

Name: Gurdurr
FlavorText: It shows off its muscles to Machoke and other Gurdurr. If it fails to measure up to the other Pokémon, it lies low for a little while.

Name: Gurdurr
FlavorText: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

Name: Gurdurr
FlavorText: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steel beams to take down buildings.

Name: Gurdurr
FlavorText: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.

Name: Conkeldurr
FlavorText: When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.

Name: Conkeldurr
FlavorText: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete, even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

Name: Conkeldurr
FlavorText: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

Name: Conkeldurr
FlavorText: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

Name: Conkeldurr
FlavorText: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

Name: Tympole
FlavorText: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.

Name: Tympole
FlavorText: Graceful ripples running across the water’s surface are a sure sign that Tympole are singing in high-pitched voices below.

Name: Tympole
FlavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

Name: Tympole
FlavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.

Name: Tympole
FlavorText: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

Name: Palpitoad
FlavorText: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.

Name: Palpitoad
FlavorText: It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches, then entangles them with its sticky tongue.

Name: Palpitoad
FlavorText: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.

Name: Palpitoad
FlavorText: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

Name: Palpitoad
FlavorText: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.

Name: Seismitoad
FlavorText: This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.

Name: Seismitoad
FlavorText: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.

Name: Seismitoad
FlavorText: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

Name: Seismitoad
FlavorText: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.

Name: Seismitoad
FlavorText: By putting power into its bumps, it creates vibrations and increases the power of its punches.

Name: Throh
FlavorText: They train in groups of five. Any member that can’t keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.

Name: Throh
FlavorText: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh’s belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer’s sweat.

Name: Throh
FlavorText: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

Name: Throh
FlavorText: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

Name: Throh
FlavorText: When they encounter foes bigger than themselves, they try to throw them. They always travel in packs of five.

Name: Sawk
FlavorText: The karate chops of a Sawk that’s trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.

Name: Sawk
FlavorText: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it’s best to quietly pass by.

Name: Sawk
FlavorText: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

Name: Sawk
FlavorText: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.

Name: Sawk
FlavorText: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

Name: Sewaddle
FlavorText: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

Name: Sewaddle
FlavorText: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

Name: Sewaddle
FlavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

Name: Swadloon
FlavorText: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

Name: Swadloon
FlavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

Name: Swadloon
FlavorText: Preferring dark, damp places, it spends the entire day eating fallen leaves that lie around it.

Name: Leavanny
FlavorText: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

Name: Leavanny
FlavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.

Name: Leavanny
FlavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

Name: Venipede
FlavorText: Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokémon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.

Name: Venipede
FlavorText: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

Name: Venipede
FlavorText: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

Name: Venipede
FlavorText: It discovers what is going on around it by using the feelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.

Name: Venipede
FlavorText: Using the feelers on its head and tail, it picks up vibrations in the air to determine its prey’s location and state.

Name: Whirlipede
FlavorText: Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it’ll need for evolution.

Name: Whirlipede
FlavorText: This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

Name: Whirlipede
FlavorText: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

Name: Whirlipede
FlavorText: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

Name: Whirlipede
FlavorText: Storing energy for evolution, it sits. But, when predators approach, it moves to stab them with poison spikes.

Name: Scolipede
FlavorText: Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.

Name: Scolipede
FlavorText: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.

Name: Scolipede
FlavorText: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

Name: Scolipede
FlavorText: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.

Name: Scolipede
FlavorText: Highly aggressive, it uses the claws near its neck to dig into its opponents and poison them.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: When attacked, it expels cotton from its body to create a diversion. The cotton it loses grows back in quickly.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: To protect itself, it shoots cotton from its body. When it gets wet in the rain, its cotton grows moist and heavy, and it can’t move as well.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: Pillows and beds stuffed with cotton exhaled by Cottonee are soft and puffy, light and airy— altogether top quality.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: When it finds others of its kind, they all stick together. When enough of them have collected, the mass resembles a cumulonimbus cloud.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

Name: Cottonee
FlavorText: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it’ll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: Whimsicott doesn’t live in a fixed location. It floats around on whirling winds, appearing all over the place to perform its mischief.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: This nuisance sneaks into people’s homes, where it hides important things and scatters cotton all over the place.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: This Pokémon appears, riding upon the wind. But if the wind gusts up, it’ll blow the cotton on this Pokémon’s head clean off.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: It rides on the wind and slips into people’s homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.

Name: Whimsicott
FlavorText: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: If the leaves on its head are pruned with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: The deeper the color of a Petilil’s leaves, the healthier the Pokémon is. Petilil sometimes makes its home in a well-tended field or flowerbed.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: Petilil appears around sources of clean water. Boiling leaves from this Pokémon’s head results in a liquid that’s sometimes used as a bug repellent.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: They prefer clean water and soil. When the environment they live in turns bad, the whole bunch will up and move to a new area.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: Some say if you dry the leaves on its head, boil them down, and drink the infusion, your vigor will return, so Petilil is popular with the elderly.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: By pruning the leaves on its head with regularity, this Pokémon can be grown into a fine plump shape.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: Although the leaves on its head are bitter enough to cause dizziness, they provide relief from weariness—even more so when boiled.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

Name: Petilil
FlavorText: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: No matter how much time and money is spent raising it, its flowers are the most beautiful when they bloom in the wild.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: Essential oils made from Lilligant flowers have a sublime scent, but they’re also staggeringly expensive.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: It’s believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant’s head to bloom.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: It’s well liked by other Pokémon because of its beauty. The flower on its head needs constant care, or it will soon wither and rot.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: The fragrance of its flower differs slightly depending on the soil where it grew up. Sniffing the aroma calms your heart and mind.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: As soon as it finds a male to be its partner, the beautiful flower on its head darkens, droops, and withers away.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

Name: Lilligant
FlavorText: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not take good care of it.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: The power of its jaws is immense—enough to leave teeth marks in iron sheets. Its personality is also extremely vicious.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: These Pokémon form schools with others of the same color. The greatest foe of a school of blue Basculin is a school of red Basculin.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Known for their violence, these Pokémon have the most fights with schools of red-striped Basculin.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Blue-striped Basculin used to be a common food source. They apparently have an inoffensive, light flavor.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Some people call it “the thug of the lake.” Whether the differences in color are meaningful is not yet known.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Even Basculin, which devours everything it can with its huge jaws, is nothing more than food to organisms stronger than itself.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: It’s so vicious that it’s called the Thug of the River. Yet Basculin is still targeted by predators, such as Dondozo and Bombirdier.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Its temperament is vicious and aggressive. This Pokémon is also full of vitality and can multiply rapidly before anyone notices.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: In the past, it often appeared on the dinner table. The meat of red-striped Basculin is on the fatty side, and it’s more popular with the youth.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch— many people release them into lakes illicitly.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: When a school of Basculin appears in a lake, everything else disappears, except for Corphish and Crawdaunt. That’s how violent Basculin are.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Savage, violent Pokémon, red and blue Basculin are always fighting each other over territory.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Red and blue Basculin usually do not get along, but sometimes members of one school mingle with the other’s school.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.

Name: Basculin
FlavorText: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: Sandile is small, but its legs and lower body are powerful. Pushing sand aside as it goes, Sandile moves through the desert as if it’s swimming.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: The desert gets cold at night, so when the sun sets, this Pokémon burrows deep into the sand and sleeps until sunrise.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: Sandile’s still not good at hunting, so it mostly eats things that have collapsed in the desert. It’s called “the cleaner of the desert.”

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: Alola, where it’s warm all year round, is a comfortable environment for this Pokémon. Sometimes you’ll even see it outside of deserts.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: It conceals itself in the sand and chomps down on the legs of any prey that unwarily walk over it. Its favorite food is Trapinch.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

Name: Sandile
FlavorText: It moves along below the sand’s surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.

Name: Krokorok
