FlavorText: Thanks to the special membrane covering its eyes, it can see its surroundings clearly, even in the middle of the night.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: Although this Pokémon has specialized eyes that allow it to see in the dark, Krokorok won’t move much at night—the desert gets cold after sunset.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: Krokorok has specialized eyes that enable it to see in the dark. This ability lets Krokorok hunt in the dead of night without getting lost.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: Krokorok really hates it when its body gets cold. On nights when the temperature drops, it digs deep into the desert sands.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.

Name: Krokorok
FlavorText: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: After clamping down with its powerful jaws, it twists its body around to rip its prey in half.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: While terribly aggressive, Krookodile also has the patience to stay hidden under sand for days, lying in wait for prey.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sands. Krookodile’s mighty jaws can bite through heavy plates of iron with almost no effort at all.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: It conceals itself in sandstorms that Flygon whip up and waits patiently for prey to appear.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: When it spots prey, even at a distance of over 30 miles, it swims through the desert as if it were water, then jumps out and chomps them.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.

Name: Krookodile
FlavorText: It can expand the focus of its eyes, enabling it to see objects in the far distance as if it were using binoculars.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: It lived in snowy areas for so long that its fire sac cooled off and atrophied. It now has an organ that generates cold instead.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it’s pushed or pulled.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: Darumaka’s droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100° F.

Name: Darumaka
FlavorText: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: Darmanitan takes this form when enraged. It won’t stop spewing flames until its rage has settled, even if its body starts to melt.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: Anger has reignited its atrophied flame sac. This Pokémon spews fire everywhere as it rampages indiscriminately.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: Though it has a gentle disposition, it’s also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: On days when blizzards blow through, it comes down to where people live. It stashes food in the snowball on its head, taking it home for later.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: When wounded, it stops moving. It goes as still as stone to meditate, sharpening its mind and spirit.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: Through meditation, it calms its raging spirit and hones its psychic powers.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: When weakened in battle, it transforms into a stone statue. Then it sharpens its mind and fights on mentally.

Name: Darmanitan
FlavorText: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

Name: Maractus
FlavorText: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They’re jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

Name: Maractus
FlavorText: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

Name: Maractus
FlavorText: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

Name: Maractus
FlavorText: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

Name: Maractus
FlavorText: When it moves rhythmically, it makes a sound similar to maracas, making the surprised Pokémon flee.

Name: Dwebble
FlavorText: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

Name: Dwebble
FlavorText: When it finds a stone appealing, it creates a hole inside it and uses it as its home. This Pokémon is the natural enemy of Roggenrola and Rolycoly.

Name: Dwebble
FlavorText: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

Name: Dwebble
FlavorText: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

Name: Dwebble
FlavorText: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

Name: Crustle
FlavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They’re mighty enough to crack Rhyperior’s carapace.

Name: Crustle
FlavorText: This highly territorial Pokémon prefers dry climates. It won’t come out of its boulder on rainy days.

Name: Crustle
FlavorText: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

Name: Crustle
FlavorText: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.

Name: Crustle
FlavorText: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.

Name: Scraggy
FlavorText: It protects itself with its durable skin. It’s thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.

Name: Scraggy
FlavorText: If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokémon.

Name: Scraggy
FlavorText: It stretches its saggy skin up to its neck to protect itself. The saggier their skin, the more respect they garner.

Name: Scraggy
FlavorText: They move in small groups, walking around lazily. Anyone who makes eye contact gets smacked with a headbutt.

Name: Scraggy
FlavorText: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

Name: Scraggy
FlavorText: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

Name: Scraggy
FlavorText: It immediately headbutts anyone that makes eye contact with it. Its skull is massively thick.

Name: Scrafty
FlavorText: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.

Name: Scrafty
FlavorText: As halfhearted as this Pokémon’s kicks may seem, they pack enough power to shatter Conkeldurr’s concrete pillars.

Name: Scrafty
FlavorText: It taunts its opponents by spitting. It has a certain territory that it never leaves its whole life long.

Name: Scrafty
FlavorText: This Pokémon may be rude, but it takes very good care of its family, its friends, and its turf.

Name: Scrafty
FlavorText: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

Name: Scrafty
FlavorText: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.

Name: Scrafty
FlavorText: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

Name: Sigilyph
FlavorText: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.

Name: Sigilyph
FlavorText: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians’ emissaries.

Name: Sigilyph
FlavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

Name: Sigilyph
FlavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.

Name: Sigilyph
FlavorText: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

Name: Yamask
FlavorText: It’s said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.

Name: Yamask
FlavorText: A clay slab with cursed engravings took possession of a Yamask. The slab is said to be absorbing the Yamask’s dark power.

Name: Yamask
FlavorText: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.

Name: Yamask
FlavorText: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that’s said to have been the face it had when it was still human.

Name: Yamask
FlavorText: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

Name: Yamask
FlavorText: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. Each retains memories of its former life.

Name: Yamask
FlavorText: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves in past ages. Each retains memories of its former life.

Name: Cofagrigus
FlavorText: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They’re symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.

Name: Cofagrigus
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a body of sparkling gold. People say it no longer remembers that it was once human.

Name: Cofagrigus
FlavorText: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

Name: Cofagrigus
FlavorText: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

Name: Cofagrigus
FlavorText: They pretend to be elaborate coffins to teach lessons to grave robbers. Their bodies are covered in pure gold.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: Tirtouga is considered to be the ancestor of many turtle Pokémon. It was restored to life from a fossil.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: Its hunting grounds encompassed a broad area, from the land to more than half a mile deep in the ocean.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: It was restored from an ancient fossil. Tirtouga lived in the sea but came up onto the land to search for prey.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: Reputed to be the ancestor of most turtle Pokémon, it lived in warm seas approximately a hundred million years ago.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: Based on studies of its skeletal structure, it can apparently dive to ocean depths of over half a mile.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swam in oceans. It is thought they also went on land to attack prey.

Name: Tirtouga
FlavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. It swam skillfully and dove to depths beyond half a mile.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: This Pokémon emerges from the water in search of prey despite the fact that it moves more slowly on land.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: Carracosta completely devours its prey—bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta’s own shell grows thick and sturdy.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: Carracosta eats every last bit of the prey it catches, even the shells and bones, to further strengthen its sturdy shell.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: Its jaws are terrifyingly powerful. It could eat Omastar and Omanyte whole and not be bothered in the slightest by their shells.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: Active both on land and in the sea, this Pokémon drags its land-based prey into the water to finish it off.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: It constructed its sturdy shell by crunching and swallowing the hard shells or bones of its prey.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

Name: Carracosta
FlavorText: Incredible jaw strength enables them to chew up steel beams and rocks along with their prey.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: Archen is said to be the ancestor of bird Pokémon. It lived in treetops, eating berries and bug Pokémon.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested, Archen is unable to fly. But it’s very good at jumping.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: Restored from a fossil, this ancient bird Pokémon has wings but can’t yet fly.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: Once thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon, some of the latest research suggests that may not be the case.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: To all appearances flightless, it was able to glide down from tall treetops to snag its prey.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: It is the ancestor of all bird Pokémon. Archen itself could not actually fly but moved by hopping from treetop to treetop.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: Revived from a fossil, this Pokémon is thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon.

Name: Archen
FlavorText: It was revived from an ancient fossil. Not able to fly, it lived in treetops and hopped from one branch to another.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: Though capable of flight, Archeops was apparently better at hunting on the ground.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, the muscles it uses to flap its wings are still weak, so it needs a long runway in order to take off.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: This ancient Pokémon’s plumage is delicate, so if anyone other than an experienced professional tries to restore it, they will fail.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: They hunted in flocks. When one Archeops had the prey cornered, another would swoop on it.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: Although apparently able to fly, they tended to run along the ground, averaging speeds of roughly 25 mph.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

Name: Archeops
FlavorText: It runs better than it flies. It catches prey by running at speeds comparable to those of an automobile.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born from a bag stuffed with trash. Galarian Weezing relish the fumes belched by Trubbish.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: If a young Pokémon or child breathes in the toxic gas that Trubbish belches out, it could be a life-threatening situation.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: Poisonous gas leaks out of it when it breathes. Muk that catch a whiff of that stench will come drooling.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: It gorges on trash until its stomach is full. Then it belches toxic gas. An unlucky whiff of gas will put a person in the hospital.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: Unsanitary places are what they like best. They can be spotted in Alola, often with Grimer in hot pursuit.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: The combination of garbage bags and industrial waste caused the chemical reaction that created this Pokémon.

Name: Trubbish
FlavorText: Wanting more garbage, they follow people who litter. They always belch poison gas.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: It sprays toxic gas from its mouth and fingers. If the gas engulfs you, the toxins will seep in all the way down to your bones.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: Due to Gigantamax energy, this Pokémon’s toxic gas has become much thicker, congealing into masses shaped like discarded toys.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: The toxic liquid it launches from its right arm is so virulent that it can kill a weakened creature instantly.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: Some say the reason Garbodor in Alola are a little stronger than their counterparts elsewhere is the presence of Muk, their natural enemy.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: It locks opponents in place with its left hand, immobilizing them by entirely dousing their bodies with poisonous liquid.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: For a time, their numbers increased explosively in Alola. Since the arrival of Grimer, their population has decreased dramatically.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: Beware the poisonous liquid it shoots from its right arm. If even a little of it gets on you, you’ll experience the effects of the unidentified toxin.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

Name: Garbodor
FlavorText: They absorb garbage and make it part of their bodies. They shoot a poisonous liquid from their right-hand fingertips.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: Zorua sometimes transforms into a person and goes into cities to search for food. When Zorua does this, it usually takes on the form of a child.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: Zorua is a timid Pokémon. This disposition seems to be what led to the development of Zorua’s ability to take on the forms of other creatures.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: If a normally talkative child suddenly stops talking, it may have been replaced by Zorua.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a cowardly disposition, so when it’s not around friends, it basically always stays transformed as something else.

Name: Zorua
FlavorText: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark’s own body.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: Seeking to ease the burden of their solitude, lonely Trainers tell Zoroark to show illusions to them.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: This Pokémon cares deeply about others of its kind, and it will conjure terrifying illusions to keep its den and pack safe.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: If it thinks humans are going to discover its den, Zoroark shows them visions that make them wander around in the woods.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: It doesn’t just transform itself—it also has the power to make hundreds of people see its illusions.

Name: Zoroark
FlavorText: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

Name: Minccino
FlavorText: They pet each other with their tails as a form of greeting. Of the two, the one whose tail is fluffier is a bit more boastful.

Name: Minccino
FlavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

Name: Minccino
FlavorText: When its tail has gotten dirty from self-cleaning or from cleaning its nest, Minccino spends a whole day washing its tail in clean spring water.

Name: Minccino
FlavorText: A clean freak that will not allow even the slightest mess, it uses its tail like a mop to thoroughly clean any and all filth.

Name: Minccino
FlavorText: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

Name: Minccino
FlavorText: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.

Name: Minccino
FlavorText: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

Name: Cinccino
FlavorText: A special oil that seeps through their fur helps them avoid attacks. The oil fetches a high price at market.

Name: Cinccino
FlavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

Name: Cinccino
FlavorText: The oil that seeps from its body is really smooth. For people troubled by bad skin, this oil is an effective treatment.

Name: Cinccino
FlavorText: The white parts of its coat are covered in an oil secreted from its body, so this Pokémon can slide right away from its enemies’ attacks.

Name: Cinccino
FlavorText: Cinccino’s body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

Name: Cinccino
FlavorText: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their fur repels dust and prevents static electricity from building up.

Name: Cinccino
FlavorText: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

Name: Gothita
FlavorText: Beware of touching the ribbon-shaped feelers that control its psychic power. Gothita will begin bawling if you do.

Name: Gothita
FlavorText: This Pokémon is normally very innocent. When it is staring at something invisible, it is unblinking and utterly silent.

Name: Gothita
FlavorText: Even when nobody seems to be around, Gothita can still be heard making a muted cry. Many believe it’s speaking to something only it can see.

Name: Gothita
FlavorText: Though they’re still only babies, there’s psychic power stored in their ribbonlike feelers, and sometimes they use that power to fight.

Name: Gothita
FlavorText: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

Name: Gothita
FlavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

Name: Gothita
FlavorText: It stares intently at everything. It can become so obsessed with watching that it doesn’t notice attacks.

Name: Gothorita
FlavorText: Using its psychic power, it arranges pebbles to form the shapes of constellations. Some people believe this Pokémon came from outer space.

Name: Gothorita
FlavorText: This Pokémon will hypnotize children to put them to sleep before carrying them away. Be wary of nights when the starlight is bright.

Name: Gothorita
FlavorText: On nights when the stars shine, this Pokémon’s psychic power is at its strongest. It’s unknown just what link Gothorita has to the greater universe.

Name: Gothorita
FlavorText: It’s said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokémon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.

Name: Gothorita
FlavorText: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

Name: Gothorita
FlavorText: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

Name: Gothorita
FlavorText: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

Name: Gothitelle
FlavorText: It gazes at the stars to predict the future. It acts somewhat detached because it has seen the end of all existence.

Name: Gothitelle
FlavorText: Gothitelle unleashes psychic energy and shows opponents dreams of the universe’s end. These dreams are apparently ethereal and beautiful.

Name: Gothitelle
FlavorText: A criminal who was shown his fate by a Gothitelle went missing that same day and was never seen again.

Name: Gothitelle
FlavorText: It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It’s also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.

Name: Gothitelle
FlavorText: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers’ life spans.

Name: Gothitelle
FlavorText: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

Name: Gothitelle
FlavorText: It can see the future from the movement of the stars. When it learns its Trainer’s life span, it cries in sadness.

Name: Solosis
FlavorText: Many say that the special liquid covering this Pokémon’s body would allow it to survive in the vacuum of space.

Name: Solosis
FlavorText: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

Name: Solosis
FlavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

Name: Solosis
FlavorText: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.

Name: Solosis
FlavorText: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they can survive in any environment.

Name: Duosion
FlavorText: Its brain has split into two, and the two halves rarely think alike. Its actions are utterly unpredictable.

Name: Duosion
FlavorText: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile—but only if its two brains can agree with each other.

Name: Duosion
FlavorText: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

Name: Duosion
FlavorText: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

Name: Duosion
FlavorText: When their brains, now divided in two, are thinking the same thoughts, these Pokémon exhibit their maximum power.

Name: Reuniclus
FlavorText: It’s said that drinking the liquid surrounding Reuniclus grants wisdom. Problem is, the liquid is highly toxic to anything besides Reuniclus itself.

Name: Reuniclus
FlavorText: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokémon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.

Name: Reuniclus
FlavorText: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

Name: Reuniclus
FlavorText: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders psychically.

Name: Reuniclus
FlavorText: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

Name: Ducklett
FlavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

Name: Ducklett
FlavorText: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

Name: Ducklett
FlavorText: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

Name: Swanna
FlavorText: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

Name: Swanna
FlavorText: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

Name: Swanna
FlavorText: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: When the morning sun hit an icicle, it wished not to melt, and thus Vanillite was born. At night, it buries itself in snow to sleep.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: It exhales cold air that is at –58 degrees Fahrenheit. When it’s in a warm place, it shrinks little by little.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: It feels pleasantly cool when embraced. This Pokémon is treasured by households in warm regions.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: Born of an icicle, this Pokémon uses its frosty breath to make ice crystals, causing snow to fall.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: The temperature of their breath is -58 degrees Fahrenheit. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: Theoretically, this Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. Their breath is -58° F.

Name: Vanillite
FlavorText: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it’s a kind Pokémon.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: This hearty Pokémon survived the Ice Age. It’s incredibly popular in very hot regions.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: It sprays its enemies with grains of ice to freeze them. Most Vanillish in Alola are smaller than average.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: This Pokémon has existed since the Ice Age. It controls particles of ice, freezes its opponents, and then shatters them with a headbutt.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: Hot days cause its body to melt. It can be restored by refreezing it, but the process leaves its body slightly warped.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: They cool down the surrounding air and create ice particles, which they use to freeze their foes.

Name: Vanillish
FlavorText: It conceals itself from enemy eyes by creating many small ice particles and hiding among them.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: Vanilluxe is born when two Vanillish, half-melted by the day’s light, stick to each other and freeze together in the cold return of night.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: It blasts blizzards from its two mouths. It can create snow anywhere, so it gets a lot of love from skiers and snowboarders.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: Even if it loses one of its heads, it can live relatively problem-free. It makes snow clouds inside its body.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: Each of its two heads has a brain, and when they are in agreement, it attacks its enemies by exhaling a violent blizzard.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.

Name: Vanilluxe
FlavorText: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: This Pokémon will playfully headbutt those it gets along well with. It has antlers hidden under its flower, so the headbutts are a little painful.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: Deerling’s scent changes with the seasons, but when the Pokémon is in its Winter Form, it has hardly any scent at all.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. When a distinct grassy smell starts to waft from one, you know that summer has begun.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: To prevent Deerling from entering their fields, many farmers will have several Lycanroc stand guard, as they are the natural enemy of Deerling.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: Despite Deerling’s adorable appearance, farmers consider it a nuisance since it loves plant shoots and will eat them all up.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. In early spring, these Pokémon give off a delicate, sweet, and calming scent.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. In this form, Deerling have a softly sweet scent that lingers in the nose.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: These Pokémon are not shy—they will behave as they please, even in front of people. If you feed one of them, it will quickly take a liking to you.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon’s fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: Their coloring changes according to the seasons and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.

Name: Deerling
FlavorText: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: Though there are many enthusiasts for Sawsbuck as a species, this seasonal form in particular is not very popular.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: It’s said that Sawsbuck are calm and easy to tame during the season when they take on this form, so it’s the perfect time to make one your partner.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s leaves can be made into a black tea, the taste of which varies depending on the region of origin. Paldea’s is especially aromatic.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: There are many Sawsbuck enthusiasts. The thicker and larger the branches and leaves on its antlers, the more majestic the Sawsbuck is thought to be.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: There are many Sawsbuck enthusiasts. The paler the pink flowers that bloom on its antlers, the more beautiful the Sawsbuck is considered to be.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: It seems that a Sawsbuck with many flowers on its antlers will grow at a slightly slower pace because the flowers absorb the Pokémon’s nutrients.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: Sawsbuck in their Autumn Form are known for having very short tempers. The males fight each other incessantly.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: There are many Sawsbuck enthusiasts. The darker the red of the foliage that hangs from its antlers, the more stylish the Sawsbuck is thought to be.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

Name: Sawsbuck
FlavorText: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can’t fly properly.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: As it flies, it scatters electricity around, so bird Pokémon keep their distance. That’s why Emolga can keep all its food to itself.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: They store up electricity to fly through the air. When thunder cracks at night, sometimes there are almost enough of them to blot out the sky.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: It grills berries and bug Pokémon with electric shocks and makes a meal of them. It usually nests in the holes gouged in trees by Pikipek.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: It glides using its cape-like membrane. Electrical energy scatters from it, shocking its friends and foes alike.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.

Name: Emolga
FlavorText: It glides on its outstretched membrane while shocking foes with the electricity stored in the pouches on its cheeks.

Name: Karrablast
FlavorText: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet’s shell. Karrablast doesn’t eat the shell— it eats only the contents.

Name: Karrablast
FlavorText: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

Name: Karrablast
FlavorText: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

Name: Karrablast
FlavorText: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

Name: Karrablast
FlavorText: When they feel threatened, they spit an acidic liquid to drive attackers away. This Pokémon targets Shelmet.

Name: Escavalier
FlavorText: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch’d.

Name: Escavalier
FlavorText: They use shells they’ve stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They’re very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.

Name: Escavalier
FlavorText: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

Name: Escavalier
FlavorText: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

Name: Escavalier
FlavorText: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: This Pokémon prefers damp places. It spurts out poison spores to repel approaching enemies.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: There is a theory that the developer of the modern-day Poké Ball really liked Foongus, but this has not been confirmed.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: The spores released from this Pokémon’s hands are highly poisonous, but when thoroughly dried, the spores can be used as stomach medicine.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: No one knows what the Poké Ball–like pattern on Foongus means or why Foongus has it.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball then releases poison spores.

Name: Foongus
FlavorText: For some reason, this Pokémon resembles a Poké Ball. They release poison spores to repel those who try to catch them.

Name: Amoonguss
FlavorText: Amoonguss mimics Poké Balls. It is not yet clear whether this mimicry is effective against other Pokémon.

Name: Amoonguss
FlavorText: Be wary of the poisonous spores it releases. Mushrooms resembling Amoonguss’s caps will grow out of anywhere the spores touch.

Name: Amoonguss
FlavorText: Amoonguss generally doesn’t move much. It tends to stand still near Poké Balls that have been dropped on the ground.

Name: Amoonguss
FlavorText: This Pokémon puffs poisonous spores at its foes. If the spores aren’t washed off quickly, they’ll grow into mushrooms wherever they land.

Name: Amoonguss
FlavorText: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

Name: Amoonguss
FlavorText: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

Name: Amoonguss
FlavorText: It moves the caps on both arms and does a dance to lure prey. It prefers damp places.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokémon.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps, five miles below the ocean’s surface.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: Its thin, veillike arms have tens of thousands of poisonous stingers. Females have slightly longer stingers.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: Using the invisible poison spikes on its veillike arms and legs, it paralyzes its enemies and causes them to drown.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: It wraps its veillike arms and legs around prey swimming by and drags them down to the depths of the ocean.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag them down to their lairs, five miles below the surface.

Name: Frillish
FlavorText: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: Most of this Pokémon’s body composition is identical to sea water. It makes sunken ships its lair.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: The crown on its head gets bigger and bigger as it absorbs more and more of the life-force of other creatures.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: These Pokémon have body compositions that are mostly identical to seawater. They make their lairs from sunken ships.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: Fishermen are terrified of Jellicent. It’s rumored to drag them into the sea and steal their lives away.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: Jellicent is always hanging around fancy cruise ships and tankers, hoping to drag away its prey.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: Its body is mostly seawater. It’s said there’s a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.

Name: Jellicent
FlavorText: They propel themselves by expelling absorbed seawater from their bodies. Their favorite food is life energy.

Name: Alomomola
FlavorText: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.

Name: Alomomola
FlavorText: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

Name: Alomomola
FlavorText: The reason it helps Pokémon in a weakened condition is that any Pokémon coming after them may also attack Alomomola.

Name: Alomomola
FlavorText: Fishermen take them along on long voyages, because if you have an Alomomola with you, there’ll be no need for a doctor or medicine.

Name: Alomomola
FlavorText: It uses its special mucus to close the wounds of injured Pokémon. The reason for this behavior remains unknown.

Name: Alomomola
FlavorText: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.

Name: Alomomola
FlavorText: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

Name: Joltik
FlavorText: Joltik latch on to other Pokémon and suck out static electricity. They’re often found sticking to Yamper’s hindquarters.

Name: Joltik
FlavorText: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It’s soaking up static electricity because it can’t produce a charge on its own.

Name: Joltik
FlavorText: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

Name: Joltik
FlavorText: Since it can’t generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

Name: Joltik
FlavorText: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

Name: Galvantula
FlavorText: It lays traps of electrified threads near the nests of bird Pokémon, aiming to snare chicks that are not yet good at flying.

Name: Galvantula
FlavorText: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

Name: Galvantula
FlavorText: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

Name: Galvantula
FlavorText: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.

Name: Galvantula
FlavorText: It creates barriers from electrified silk that stun foes. This works as a weapon as well as a defense.

Name: Ferroseed
FlavorText: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed’s spikes grow big and strong.

Name: Ferroseed
FlavorText: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn’t very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.

Name: Ferroseed
FlavorText: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

Name: Ferroseed
FlavorText: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

Name: Ferroseed
FlavorText: They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.

Name: Ferrothorn
FlavorText: Its spikes are harder than steel. This Pokémon crawls across rock walls by stabbing the spikes on its feelers into the stone.

Name: Ferrothorn
FlavorText: This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

Name: Ferrothorn
FlavorText: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

Name: Ferrothorn
FlavorText: By swinging around its three spiky feelers and shooting spikes, it can obliterate an opponent.

Name: Ferrothorn
FlavorText: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

Name: Klink
FlavorText: It’s suspected that Klink were the inspiration behind ancient people’s invention of the first gears.

Name: Klink
FlavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

Name: Klink
FlavorText: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

Name: Klink
FlavorText: Interlocking two bodies and spinning around generates the energy they need to live.

Name: Klink
FlavorText: Two bodies comprise a fixed pair. They spin around each other to generate energy.

Name: Klang
FlavorText: Many companies in the Galar region choose Klang as their logo. This Pokémon is considered the symbol of industrial technology.

Name: Klang
FlavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon’s rotation speed increases sharply.

Name: Klang
FlavorText: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn’t return, it will die.

Name: Klang
FlavorText: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

Name: Klang
FlavorText: Spinning minigears are rotated at high speed and repeatedly fired away. It is dangerous if the gears don’t return.

Name: Klinklang
FlavorText: The three gears that compose this Pokémon spin at high speed. Its new spiked gear isn’t a living creature.

Name: Klinklang
FlavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

Name: Klinklang
FlavorText: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

Name: Klinklang
FlavorText: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

Name: Klinklang
FlavorText: The minigear spins at high speed. Then the energy from the red core charges the minigear to make it ready to fire.

Name: Tynamo
FlavorText: These Pokémon move in schools. They have an electricity-generating organ, so they discharge electricity if in danger.

Name: Tynamo
FlavorText: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

Name: Tynamo
FlavorText: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

Name: Eelektrik
FlavorText: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

Name: Eelektrik
FlavorText: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

Name: Eelektrik
FlavorText: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.

Name: Eelektross
FlavorText: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.

Name: Eelektross
FlavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

Name: Eelektross
FlavorText: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.

Name: Elgyem
FlavorText: This Pokémon was discovered about 50 years ago. Its highly developed brain enables it to exert its psychic powers.

Name: Elgyem
FlavorText: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

Name: Elgyem
FlavorText: This Pokémon is shrouded in mystery. It’s said to have appeared from a UFO that fell from the sky about 50 years ago.

Name: Elgyem
FlavorText: It controls tremendous psychic power. Most reports of alien sightings are actually just people mistaking Elgyem for an alien.

Name: Elgyem
FlavorText: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.

Name: Elgyem
FlavorText: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

Name: Elgyem
FlavorText: This Pokémon had never been seen until it appeared from far in the desert 50 years ago.

Name: Beheeyem
FlavorText: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.

Name: Beheeyem
FlavorText: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

Name: Beheeyem
FlavorText: It has strong psychic powers. Using its fingers that flash three different colors, it controls its opponents and rewrites their memories.

Name: Beheeyem
FlavorText: With its psychic powers, it rewrites its opponents’ memories. You, too, may have already had your memories rewritten.

Name: Beheeyem
FlavorText: It uses psychic power to control an opponent’s brain and tamper with its memories.

Name: Beheeyem
FlavorText: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three fingers, but those patterns haven’t been decoded.

Name: Beheeyem
FlavorText: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

Name: Litwick
FlavorText: The younger the life this Pokémon absorbs, the brighter and eerier the flame on its head burns.

Name: Litwick
FlavorText: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.

Name: Litwick
FlavorText: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

Name: Litwick
FlavorText: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.

Name: Litwick
FlavorText: Its flame is usually out, but it starts shining when it absorbs life force from people or Pokémon.

Name: Lampent
FlavorText: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.

Name: Lampent
FlavorText: This Pokémon appears just before someone passes away, so it’s feared as an emissary of death.

Name: Lampent
FlavorText: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

Name: Lampent
FlavorText: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.

Name: Lampent
FlavorText: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

Name: Chandelure
FlavorText: In homes illuminated by Chandelure instead of lights, funerals were a constant occurrence— or so it’s said.

Name: Chandelure
FlavorText: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

Name: Chandelure
FlavorText: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

Name: Chandelure
FlavorText: Being consumed in Chandelure’s flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.

Name: Chandelure
FlavorText: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

Name: Axew
FlavorText: If you see peculiar teeth marks on boulders or trees, it means an Axew is likely living nearby.

Name: Axew
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in nests that are made in the ground. People in ancient times used its tusks as cooking knives.

Name: Axew
FlavorText: They play with each other by knocking their large tusks together. Their tusks break sometimes, but they grow back so quickly that it isn’t a concern.

Name: Axew
FlavorText: These Pokémon nest in the ground and use their tusks to crush hard berries. Crushing berries is also how they test each other’s strength.

Name: Axew
FlavorText: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

Name: Axew
FlavorText: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

Name: Axew
FlavorText: Its large tusks have a tendency to break, but each time they grow back, they grow in harder and sturdier.

Name: Fraxure
FlavorText: Fraxure uses its thick tusks to neatly cut prey into two portions—one to eat now and one to save for later.

Name: Fraxure
FlavorText: Because its tusks don’t grow back once they break, this Pokémon apparently won’t use them unless truly necessary.

Name: Fraxure
FlavorText: Its skin is as hard as a suit of armor. Fraxure’s favorite strategy is to tackle its opponents, stabbing them with its tusks at the same time.

Name: Fraxure
FlavorText: After battle, this Pokémon carefully sharpens its tusks on river rocks. It needs to take care of its tusks—if one breaks, it will never grow back.

Name: Fraxure
FlavorText: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

Name: Fraxure
FlavorText: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.

Name: Fraxure
FlavorText: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

Name: Haxorus
FlavorText: It overwhelms enemies with its prized tusks, which are sharp enough to cut through a metal transmission tower in one strike.

Name: Haxorus
FlavorText: This Pokémon nests in caves and abandoned mines. It is docile, but it will become incredibly angry if its tusks are touched, so beware.

Name: Haxorus
FlavorText: While usually kindhearted, it can be terrifying if angered. Tusks that can slice through steel beams are how Haxorus deals with its adversaries.

Name: Haxorus
FlavorText: Its resilient tusks are its pride and joy. It licks up dirt to take in the minerals it needs to keep its tusks in top condition.

Name: Haxorus
FlavorText: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

Name: Haxorus
FlavorText: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

Name: Haxorus
FlavorText: Its tusks are incredibly destructive. They can easily slice through a thick, sturdy steel column every time.

Name: Cubchoo
FlavorText: When Cubchoo starts sneezing, watch out! If it spatters you with its frosty snot, you’ll get frostbite.

Name: Cubchoo
FlavorText: Many of this species can be found along the shorelines of cold regions. If a Cubchoo lacks dangling snot, there’s a chance it is sick.

Name: Cubchoo
FlavorText: It sniffles before performing a move, using its frosty snot to provide an icy element to any move that needs it.

Name: Cubchoo
FlavorText: When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn’t like.

Name: Cubchoo
FlavorText: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

Name: Cubchoo
FlavorText: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus provides the raw material for its moves.

Name: Cubchoo
FlavorText: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

Name: Beartic
FlavorText: Feared as the Snow-White Demon in northern lands, Beartic uses its frosty claws and fangs to attack prey.

Name: Beartic
FlavorText: It is a ferocious, carnivorous Pokémon. Once it captures its prey, it will breathe cold air onto the prey to freeze and preserve it.

Name: Beartic
FlavorText: It swims energetically through frigid seas. When it gets tired, it freezes the seawater with its breath so it can rest on the ice.

Name: Beartic
FlavorText: It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.

Name: Beartic
FlavorText: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

Name: Beartic
FlavorText: They love the cold seas of the north. They create pathways across the ocean waters by freezing their own breath.

Name: Beartic
FlavorText: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: Cryogonal uses its chains of ice to constrict its opponents and then flash-freezes them where they stand.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: Cryogonal appear during cold seasons. It is said that people and Pokémon who die on snowy mountains are reborn into these Pokémon.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: When the weather gets hot, these Pokémon turn into water vapor. Cryogonal are almost never seen during summer.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: With its icy chains, Cryogonal freezes those it encounters. It then takes its victims away to somewhere unknown.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148° F.

Name: Cryogonal
FlavorText: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

Name: Shelmet
FlavorText: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.

Name: Shelmet
FlavorText: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.

Name: Shelmet
FlavorText: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

Name: Shelmet
FlavorText: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.

Name: Shelmet
FlavorText: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

Name: Accelgor
FlavorText: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.

Name: Accelgor
FlavorText: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

Name: Accelgor
FlavorText: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

Name: Accelgor
FlavorText: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes very light and can fight with ninja-like movements.

Name: Accelgor
FlavorText: When its body dries out, it weakens. So it wraps a membrane around itself for protection while it spits poison.

Name: Stunfisk
FlavorText: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.

Name: Stunfisk
FlavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.

Name: Stunfisk
FlavorText: For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

Name: Stunfisk
FlavorText: Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokémon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity.

Name: Stunfisk
FlavorText: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

Name: Stunfisk
FlavorText: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

Name: Stunfisk
FlavorText: When its opponent can’t be paralyzed, it contorts itself with unexpected speed and flops away.

Name: Mienfoo
FlavorText: Though small, Mienfoo’s temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.

Name: Mienfoo
FlavorText: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

Name: Mienfoo
FlavorText: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.

Name: Mienfoo
FlavorText: They can often be seen in packs in the morning, slowly moving their bodies through a series of poses.

Name: Mienfoo
FlavorText: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

Name: Mienfoo
FlavorText: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.

Name: Mienfoo
FlavorText: They have mastered elegant combos. As they concentrate, their battle moves become swifter and more precise.

Name: Mienshao
FlavorText: Delivered at blinding speeds, kicks from this Pokémon can shatter massive boulders into tiny pieces.

Name: Mienshao
FlavorText: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

Name: Mienshao
FlavorText: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you’re in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!

Name: Mienshao
FlavorText: It overwhelms its opponents with continuous attacks and then slowly stores up power before delivering the finishing blow.

Name: Mienshao
FlavorText: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

Name: Mienshao
FlavorText: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

Name: Mienshao
FlavorText: They use the long fur on their arms as a whip to strike their opponents.

Name: Druddigon
FlavorText: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.

Name: Druddigon
FlavorText: Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips sunbathing—it won’t be able to move if its body gets too cold.

Name: Druddigon
FlavorText: It infiltrates tunnels that Pokémon like Diglett and Dugtrio have dug and quietly waits for prey to pass through.

Name: Druddigon
FlavorText: The red skin on its face is harder than rock. In narrow caves, it squares off against its enemies and charges face-first right into them.

Name: Druddigon
FlavorText: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

Name: Druddigon
FlavorText: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.

Name: Druddigon
FlavorText: It runs through the narrow tunnels formed by Excadrill and Onix. It uses its sharp claws to catch prey.

Name: Golett
FlavorText: This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.

Name: Golett
FlavorText: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

Name: Golett
FlavorText: Although ancient people apparently built it by working with clay, the source of its energy is unclear.

Name: Golett
FlavorText: Its movements are powered by a mysterious energy. It has continued to move since ancient times, so its power may soon run out.

Name: Golett
FlavorText: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It’s been active for thousands of years.

Name: Golett
FlavorText: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

Name: Golett
FlavorText: These Pokémon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

Name: Golurk
FlavorText: There’s a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn’t been proven.

Name: Golurk
FlavorText: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

Name: Golurk
FlavorText: When the seal on its chest is removed, it rages indiscriminately, turning the whole town around it into a mountain of rubble.

Name: Golurk
FlavorText: Some say that ancient people invented Golurk to serve as a laborer. It follows its master’s orders faithfully.

Name: Golurk
FlavorText: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

Name: Golurk
FlavorText: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.

Name: Golurk
FlavorText: Golurk were created to protect people and Pokémon. They run on a mysterious energy.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: Any chips in its blades would prove fatal for it. After each battle, it diligently maintains its blades using its favorite sharpening stone.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch, it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: A pack of these Pokémon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: It follows Bisharp’s orders to a tee when it attacks enemies. After slashing an opponent, Pawniard clangs both of its blades together.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: After shredding its prey, it sharpens its blades on a stone by the river. Each Pawniard has its own favorite sharpening stone.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

Name: Pawniard
FlavorText: They fight at Bisharp’s command. They cling to their prey and inflict damage by sinking their blades into it.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: Bisharp mercilessly cuts its opponents to pieces with the sharp blades covering its body. It will do anything to win.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: This Pokémon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: It’s accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: It leads a group of Pawniard. Bisharp doesn’t even change its expression when it deals the finishing blow to an opponent.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: No matter how strong the Bisharp, it’s said that if the blade on its head is chipped, it will retire from its position as the boss.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: This pitiless Pokémon commands a group of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.

Name: Bisharp
FlavorText: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

Name: Bouffalant
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

Name: Bouffalant
FlavorText: These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

Name: Bouffalant
FlavorText: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

Name: Bouffalant
FlavorText: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.

Name: Bouffalant
FlavorText: They are known to charge so wildly that if a train were to enter their territory, they would send it flying.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: With its sharp claws, this Pokémon pierces its prey, and then it pecks at them. Although it also consumes berries, it’s a carnivore at heart.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: They pick fights indiscriminately. They grow stronger and more powerful each time they faint or are injured.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: Its chick-like looks belie its hotheadedness. It challenges its parents at every opportunity, desperate to prove its strength.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: A combative Pokémon, it’s ready to pick a fight with anyone. It has talons that can crush hard berries.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: If it spies a strong Pokémon, Rufflet can’t resist challenging it to a battle. But if Rufflet loses, it starts bawling.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: Known as a natural-born warrior, soon after its hatching, it will challenge its parent to a fight in order to gain their acceptance.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: With its powerful legs and sturdy claws, it can crack even the hard shells of Shellder and pluck out their insides.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

Name: Rufflet
FlavorText: It stands up to massive opponents, not out of courage, but out of recklessness. But that is how it gets stronger.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokémon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water’s surface.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky get from their peers.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: Because this Pokémon is hotheaded and belligerent, it’s Corviknight that’s taken the role of transportation in Galar.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokémon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: Known as “the hero of the skies,” this Pokémon is so proud and so brave that it will never retreat, even when it’s injured.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: The more scars it has on its front, the more heroic it’s considered to be. Those with many scars on their back are mocked by the flock.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: It’s thought that people disturbed their habitats in the past, so Braviary banded together to fight back.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: With its brave disposition, it fears nothing—not even death. Ancient Alolan people respected it, referring to it as “the hero of the sky.”

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

Name: Braviary
FlavorText: The more scars they have, the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky  get from their peers.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: It wears a bone to protect its rear. It often squabbles with others of its kind over particularly comfy bones.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: Its healthy appetite leads to visible growth spurts. It often has to replace the bones it wears as its size increases.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: Mandibuzz gives it the bones it wears. Vullaby’s wings are short, so it can’t fly yet, but it jumps around, dreaming of wide open skies.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: It can’t fly yet and must wait until its wings have developed more. Since it’s still at a playful age, it hops around friskily.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: It protects its plump posterior with the bones of prey it has consumed. As it grows, it  replaces the bones.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.

Name: Vullaby
FlavorText: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: Although it’s a bit of a ruffian, this Pokémon will take lost Vullaby under its wing and care for them till they’re ready to leave the nest.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: It’s always searching for food for Vullaby. When it finds a weak Pokémon, Mandibuzz swoops it right off to its nest.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: It skillfully arranges the bones of its prey to construct its nest. Most of the bones are Cubone.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokémon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is Cubone.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: They adorn themselves beautifully with bones. This is supposedly an effort to attract males, but no male Mandibuzz have ever been found.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spot prey, they attack and carry it back to their nest with ease.

Name: Mandibuzz
FlavorText: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

Name: Heatmor
FlavorText: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

Name: Heatmor
FlavorText: There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

Name: Heatmor
FlavorText: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

Name: Heatmor
FlavorText: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues, they burn through Durant’s steel bodies and consume their insides.

Name: Heatmor
FlavorText: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

Name: Durant
FlavorText: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

Name: Durant
FlavorText: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.

Name: Durant
FlavorText: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

Name: Durant
FlavorText: Individuals each play different roles in driving Heatmor, their natural predator, away from their colony.

Name: Durant
