FlavorText: Durant dig nests in mountains. They build their complicated, interconnected tunnels into mazes.

Name: Deino
FlavorText: It nests deep inside a cave. Food there is scarce, so Deino will sink its teeth into anything that moves and attempt to eat it.

Name: Deino
FlavorText: It can’t see, so its first approach to examining things is to bite them. You will be covered in wounds until a Deino warms up to you.

Name: Deino
FlavorText: Because it can’t see, this Pokémon is constantly biting at everything it touches, trying to keep track of its surroundings.

Name: Deino
FlavorText: When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.

Name: Deino
FlavorText: Lacking sight, it’s unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

Name: Deino
FlavorText: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

Name: Deino
FlavorText: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

Name: Zweilous
FlavorText: The two heads have different likes and dislikes. Because the heads fight with each other, Zweilous gets stronger without needing to rely on others.

Name: Zweilous
FlavorText: The two heads do not get along at all. If you don’t give each head the same amount of attention, they’ll begin fighting out of jealousy.

Name: Zweilous
FlavorText: Their two heads will fight each other over a single piece of food. Zweilous are covered in scars even without battling others.

Name: Zweilous
FlavorText: While hunting for prey, Zweilous wanders its territory, its two heads often bickering over which way to go.

Name: Zweilous
FlavorText: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

Name: Zweilous
FlavorText: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.

Name: Zweilous
FlavorText: Since their two heads do not get along and compete with each other for food, they always eat too much.

Name: Hydreigon
FlavorText: It’s said that Hydreigon grew ferocious because people in times long past loathed it, considering it to be evil incarnate and attacking it relentlessly.

Name: Hydreigon
FlavorText: Only the central head has a brain. It is very intelligent, but it thinks only of destruction.

Name: Hydreigon
FlavorText: The three heads take turns sinking their teeth into the opponent. Their attacks won’t slow until their target goes down.

Name: Hydreigon
FlavorText: There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.

Name: Hydreigon
FlavorText: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

Name: Hydreigon
FlavorText: The heads on their arms do not have brains. They use all three heads to consume and destroy everything.

Name: Hydreigon
FlavorText: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: In ancient times, Larvesta was worshiped as the emissary of the sun. However, it was also viewed as a burden since it often caused forest fires.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: This Pokémon was called the Larva That Stole the Sun. The fire Larvesta spouts from its horns can cut right through a sheet of iron.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: Larvesta’s body is warm all over. It spouts fire from the tips of its horns to intimidate predators and scare prey.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: The people of ancient times believed that Larvesta fell from the sun.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: It protects itself with flame. Long years ago, people believed Larvesta had a nest on the sun.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: When battling opponents, it sprays fire from its five horns. The max temperature of the flames can reach nearly 5,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.

Name: Larvesta
FlavorText: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: This Pokémon scatters burning scales. Most of the danger of these scales is not in their heat—it’s in the way they rob the surrounding air of oxygen.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: Its burning body causes it to be unpopular in hot parts of the world, but in cold ones, Volcarona is revered as an embodiment of the sun.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: This Pokémon emerges from a cocoon formed of raging flames. Ancient murals depict Volcarona as a deity of fire.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it’s trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: According to legends, it was hatched from a flaming cocoon to save people and Pokémon that were suffering from the cold.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: As it flies, it scatters its flaming scales. It was feared by ancient people, who referred to it as “the rage of the sun.”

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of their battles, since they use their six wings to scatter their ember scales.

Name: Volcarona
FlavorText: Thought to be an embodiment of the sun, it appeared during a bitterly cold winter and saved Pokémon from freezing.

Name: Cobalion
FlavorText: From the moment it’s born, this Pokémon radiates the air of a leader. Its presence will calm even vicious foes.

Name: Cobalion
FlavorText: This Pokémon appears in a legend alongside Terrakion and Virizion, fighting against humans in defense of the Unova region’s Pokémon.

Name: Cobalion
FlavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

Name: Cobalion
FlavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

Name: Cobalion
FlavorText: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

Name: Terrakion
FlavorText: In Unovan legend, Terrakion battled against humans in an effort to protect other Pokémon.

Name: Terrakion
FlavorText: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokémon.

Name: Terrakion
FlavorText: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

Name: Terrakion
FlavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

Name: Terrakion
FlavorText: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

Name: Virizion
FlavorText: It darts around opponents with a flurry of quick movements, slicing them up with its horns.

Name: Virizion
FlavorText: A legend tells of this Pokémon working together with Cobalion and Terrakion to protect the Pokémon of the Unova region.

Name: Virizion
FlavorText: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

Name: Virizion
FlavorText: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

Name: Virizion
FlavorText: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

Name: Tornadus
FlavorText: An example of what is known as a “form change,” though I suspect this strange avian guise to be Tornadus’s true form. Tornadus has been sighted crossing the ocean while in this form.

Name: Tornadus
FlavorText: This storm-stirring Pokémon is said to cause the seasons to turn by whipping up the air. I suspect its humanlike form to be a false one.

Name: Tornadus
FlavorText: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

Name: Tornadus
FlavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

Name: Tornadus
FlavorText: In every direction it flies, creating winds so powerful, they blow everything away.

Name: Thundurus
FlavorText: Quick as a flash, it materializes out of nowhere. It pulverizes foes into nothingness with showers of devastatingly powerful lightning bolts launched from the string of orbs on its tail.

Name: Thundurus
FlavorText: They say this wielder of electricity has waged war with its nemesis, Tornadus, since time immemorial. The lightning bolts it hurls pierce the very earth and enrich the soil.

Name: Thundurus
FlavorText: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

Name: Thundurus
FlavorText: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

Name: Thundurus
FlavorText: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

Name: Reshiram
FlavorText: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

Name: Reshiram
FlavorText: Flames spew from its tail as it flies through the sky like a jet airplane. It’s said that this Pokémon will scorch the world.

Name: Reshiram
FlavorText: When Reshiram’s tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world’s weather.

Name: Reshiram
FlavorText: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

Name: Reshiram
FlavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

Name: Zekrom
FlavorText: Mythology tells us that if people lose the righteousness in their hearts, their kingdoms will be razed by Zekrom’s lightning.

Name: Zekrom
FlavorText: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.

Name: Zekrom
FlavorText: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

Name: Zekrom
FlavorText: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.

Name: Zekrom
FlavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.

Name: Landorus
FlavorText: Landorus soars through the sky in this form, bestowing plentiful harvests upon the land and earning the people’s reverence. It can traverse the whole of Hisui in a mere couple of hours.

Name: Landorus
FlavorText: When the incarnations of wind and of lightning clash, Landorus arrives to quell the conflict. After the tempests and thunderbolts abate, the land is sure to be blessed with bountiful harvests.

Name: Landorus
FlavorText: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

Name: Landorus
FlavorText: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

Name: Landorus
FlavorText: The energy that comes pouring from its tail increases the nutrition in the soil, making crops grow to great size.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: The sameness of Zekrom’s and Kyurem’s genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Zekrom. Kyurem can now use the power of both electricity and ice.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: It’s said that this Pokémon battles in order to protect the ideal world that will exist in the future for people and Pokémon.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: It has foreseen that a world of truth will arrive for people and Pokémon. It strives to protect that future.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: The sameness of Reshiram’s and Kyurem’s genes allowed Kyurem to absorb Reshiram. Kyurem can now use the power of both fire and ice.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: It appears that this Pokémon uses its powers over ice to freeze its own body in order to stabilize its cellular structure.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

Name: Kyurem
FlavorText: It can produce ultracold air. Its body is frozen.

Name: Keldeo
FlavorText: The power that lay hidden in its body now covers its horn, turning it into a sword that can slice through anything.

Name: Keldeo
FlavorText: Keldeo has strengthened its resolve for battle, filling its body with power and changing its form.

Name: Keldeo
FlavorText: They say that Keldeo must survive harsh battles and fully develop the horn on its forehead before this Pokémon’s true power will awaken.

Name: Keldeo
FlavorText: Cobalion, Terrakion, and Virizion taught this Pokémon how to fight. It dashes across the world, seeking more opportunities to further its training.

Name: Keldeo
FlavorText: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

Name: Keldeo
FlavorText: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

Name: Keldeo
FlavorText: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

Name: Meloetta
FlavorText: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

Name: Meloetta
FlavorText: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

Name: Meloetta
FlavorText: Many famous songs have been inspired by the melodies that Meloetta plays.

Name: Genesect
FlavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

Name: Genesect
FlavorText: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

Name: Genesect
FlavorText: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.

Name: Chespin
FlavorText: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn’t faze it.

Name: Chespin
FlavorText: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

Name: Quilladin
FlavorText: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won’t start fights.

Name: Quilladin
FlavorText: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

Name: Chesnaught
FlavorText: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

Name: Chesnaught
FlavorText: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

Name: Fennekin
FlavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

Name: Fennekin
FlavorText: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Braixen
FlavorText: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

Name: Braixen
FlavorText: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

Name: Delphox
FlavorText: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

Name: Delphox
FlavorText: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

Name: Froakie
FlavorText: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

Name: Froakie
FlavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

Name: Frogadier
FlavorText: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute’s time.

Name: Frogadier
FlavorText: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

Name: Greninja
FlavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

Name: Greninja
FlavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

Name: Bunnelby
FlavorText: It’s very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight’s flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.

Name: Bunnelby
FlavorText: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.

Name: Bunnelby
FlavorText: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

Name: Bunnelby
FlavorText: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

Name: Diggersby
FlavorText: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.

Name: Diggersby
FlavorText: With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It’s a huge help during tunnel construction.

Name: Diggersby
FlavorText: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it’s finished digging, it lounges lazily.

Name: Diggersby
FlavorText: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: Fletchling can be found in both rural and urban areas. They once had a huge territorial dispute with Squawkabilly. Fights broke out all over town.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: This Pokémon is normally calm, but once it enters battle, its hormonal balance changes and it becomes aggressive.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: When this Pokémon gets excited, its body temperature increases sharply. If you touch a Fletchling with bare hands, you might get burned.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: Its melodious cries are actually warnings. Fletchling will mercilessly peck at anything that enters its territory.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: Its body is always warm. Trainers who live in cold areas apparently sleep with it in their bed.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: While it’s an amiable Pokémon, if you touch it unexpectedly, it will heat up its body in an instant, and you’ll be burned.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: When it’s excited, its temperature can double, spiking hormone production in its body.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: This amiable Pokémon is easy to train. But when battle is joined, it shows its ferocious side.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it’s merciless to intruders that enter its territory.

Name: Fletchling
FlavorText: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Its territory has a radius of just over a mile. If any bird Pokémon should enter, it will show them no mercy.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass where bug Pokémon might be hiding and then catches them as they come leaping out.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Fletchinder are exceedingly territorial and aggressive. These Pokémon fight among themselves over feeding grounds.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Fletchinder launches embers into the den of its prey. When the prey comes leaping out, Fletchinder’s sharp talons finish it off.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Its speed right after takeoff already puts it in the top speed class of all bird Pokémon.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: It scatters embers in the tall grass. Then bug Pokémon, frightened by the flames, come flying out, and Fletchinder gobbles them up.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: It will not tolerate other Fletchinder entering its territory, which has a radius of several miles.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: When it gets excited, it vents sparks from the gaps between its feathers. These unburnable feathers are used as a fireproof material.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: It has top-notch flying capabilities. It flies around easily, even while carrying prey that weighs more than 220 lbs.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Talonflame dives toward prey at speeds of up to 310 mph and assaults them with powerful kicks, giving the prey no chance to escape.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Talonflame mainly preys upon other bird Pokémon. To intimidate opponents, it sends embers spewing from gaps between its feathers.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Bird Pokémon make up most of its diet. It approaches at high speeds and smacks them down to the ground with its powerful kick.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Its tough wings don’t allow fire to pass through them. A long time ago, firefighters’ outfits were made from Talonflame wings.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: It zooms directly at its prey at flight speeds of close to 310 mph, while fiery embers scatter from gaps in its feathers.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Its favorite foods are Wingull and Pikipek. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

Name: Scatterbug
FlavorText: This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder to repel enemies. It will eat different plants depending on where it lives.

Name: Scatterbug
FlavorText: Any poison this Pokémon takes in is converted into a black powder and secreted. That’s why Scatterbug can eat poisonous leaves and roots.

Name: Scatterbug
FlavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

Name: Scatterbug
FlavorText: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

Name: Spewpa
FlavorText: Spewpa doesn’t live in a fixed location. It roams where it pleases across the fields and mountains, building up the energy it needs to evolve.

Name: Spewpa
FlavorText: If Rufflet attacks this Pokémon by pecking at it, it will retaliate with its sharp fur and poisonous black powder.

Name: Spewpa
FlavorText: The beaks of bird Pokémon can’t begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

Name: Spewpa
FlavorText: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land with little rain. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands with little rain.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a verdant land. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from verdant lands.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a mysterious land. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from a mysterious land.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land with distinct seasons. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands with distinct seasons.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land of vast space. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands of vast space.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a place with many islands. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from places with many islands.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in frigid lands. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from frigid lands.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land of severe cold. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands of severe cold.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land bathed in light. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands bathed in light.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land with a tropical climate. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands with a tropical climate.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a parched land. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from parched lands.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land where large rivers flow. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands where large rivers flow.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a snowy land. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from snowy lands.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a special land. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from a special land.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land of perpetual summer. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands of perpetual summer.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land with intense rainfall. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands with intense rainfall.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a sun-drenched land. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from sun-drenched lands.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land with ocean breezes. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands with ocean breezes.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land where flowers bloom. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands where flowers bloom.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land of tropical rain forests. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands of tropical rain forests.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon’s wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

Name: Vivillon
FlavorText: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: The more a Litleo trains its body and spirit by battling mighty enemies, the hotter its mane will grow.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: When Litleo are young, female Pyroar will teach them how to hunt. Once the Litleo mature, they will leave the pride and set out on their own.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: When they’re young, they live with a pride. Once they’re able to hunt prey on their own, they’re kicked out and have to make their own way.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The mane of a male Pyroar heats up to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit during battle. Merely approaching it will cause severe burns.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The females of a pride work together to bring down prey. It’s thanks to them that their pride doesn’t starve.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn’t use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The males are usually lazy, but when attacked by a strong foe, a male will protect its friends with no regard for its own safety.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride’s cubs.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: It unleashes a variety of moves by drawing forth the power hidden within flowers. This Pokémon is particularly fond of yellow flowers.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: This Flabébé rides a yellow flower. The Pokémon is defenseless and vulnerable before it has found and received power from a flower.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: When evening falls, it searches out a place blooming with flowers of the same white color as itself, and then it goes to sleep.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: This Flabébé rides a white flower. The wind blows this Pokémon around as it drifts in search of flower gardens.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: This Flabébé rides a red flower. Immediately after birth, this Pokémon begins flying around in search of a flower it likes.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: This Pokémon can draw forth the power hidden within blooming wild flowers. It is particularly fond of red flowers.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: It receives strength from flowers and gives them some of its energy in return. This Pokémon likes orange flowers best of all.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: This Flabébé rides an orange flower. On its head, it wears a crown of pollen that has healing properties.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: This Pokémon likes blue flowers best of all. It floats upward using the power emanating from its flower and bobs along lightly through the air.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: Once it finds a flower it likes, this Pokémon will spend the rest of its life taking care of its flower. This Flabébé rides a blue flower.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: Flabébé wears a crown made from pollen it’s collected from its flower. The crown has hidden healing properties.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: It’s not safe without the power of a flower, but it will keep traveling around until it finds one with the color and shape it wants.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind’s embrace with an untroubled heart.

Name: Flabébé
FlavorText: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: Floette can draw forth the latent capabilities of Grass-type Pokémon. It syncs with yellow flowers.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: This Pokémon can draw forth the power hidden within yellow flowers. This power then becomes the moves Floette uses to protect itself.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: If it finds someone messing up a flower bed, it will attack them without mercy. This Floette takes particularly good care of white flowers.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: Floette that are fond of white flowers can also easily sync with flowers of other colors.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses red wavelengths of light to pour its own energy into flowers and draw forth their latent potential.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: This Pokémon draws forth what power is left in withered flowers to make them healthy again. It holds a red flower.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: This Pokémon cannot use moves on its own. When it syncs with flowers, it becomes able to use Grass-type moves.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: This Pokémon can draw forth the most power when in sync with orange flowers, compared to flowers of other colors.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: It exchanges power with flowers via wavelengths of visible light. This form of Floette can sync with the wavelength that produces the color blue.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: Whenever this Pokémon finds flowering plants that are withering, it will bring them back to its territory and care for them until they are healthy.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: Terrifying energy is concealed within its ominous flower, but Floette still swings it about innocently.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: The flower it’s holding can no longer be found blooming anywhere. It’s also thought to contain terrifying power.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: It gives its own power to flowers, pouring its heart into caring for them. Floette never forgives anyone who messes up a flower bed.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: It raises flowers and uses them as weapons. The more gorgeous the blossom, the more power it contains.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.

Name: Floette
FlavorText: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: This Pokémon battles by drawing forth the power of yellow flowers. It ruthlessly punishes anyone who tramples on flowering plants.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: It is said that there was once a Florges that protected the garden of a castle for over 300 years.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: A Florges adorned with white flowers can sync with the wavelengths of various colors to draw forth their power.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: A flower garden made by a white-flowered Florges will be beautifully decorated with flowering plants of many different colors.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: They say that flower gardens created by Florges are constantly showered with a power that can heal both body and spirit.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: This Pokémon creates an impressive flower garden in its territory. It draws forth the power of the red flowers around its neck.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: In times long past, castle governors would lovingly raise Florges to care for their castles’ exquisite gardens.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: Its orange flowers fire off powerful beams, attacking as if they were a battery of artillery.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: Blue pigments were tremendously expensive in the past, so paintings of blue Florges are highly valuable.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: Though usually compassionate, Florges will hunt down anyone who vandalizes its flower garden, showing no mercy even if they beg for their lives.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: Its life can span several hundred years. It’s said to devote its entire life to protecting gardens.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: It controls the flowers it grows. The petal blizzards that Florges triggers are overwhelming in their beauty and power.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.

Name: Florges
FlavorText: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: As long as it has sunlight and water, Skiddo can make energy with the leaves on its body, allowing it to live on rocky mountains barren of food.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: Until recently, people living in the mountains would ride on the backs of these Pokémon to traverse the mountain paths.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn’t need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in herds in mountainous places. The victor in their contests of clashing horns will become the leader of the herd.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: It can sense the feelings of others by touching them with its horns. This species has assisted people with their work since 5,000 years ago.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: Wanting to make sure it’s taken seriously, Pancham’s always giving others a glare. But if it’s not focusing, it ends up smiling.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master’s actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: It’s desperate to intimidate its opponents. Be nice and pretend to be scared if you catch it glaring at you intensely.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: It follows Pangoro around like a henchman. When Pancham makes a big mistake, its leaf gets taken away.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: There’s no point to the leaf in its mouth, aside from an effort to look cool. It’s mischievous, so it’s not well suited to inexperienced Trainers.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: It grows up imitating the behavior of Pangoro, which it looks up to as a leader.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can’t help grinning if anyone pats its head.

Name: Pancham
FlavorText: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: This Pokémon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: Pangoro is the type to talk with its fists. It doesn’t say much as it pummels opponents with enough force to send a dump truck flying.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: This rowdy Pokémon boasts great physical strength. Many Trainers are also smitten by its lively character.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent’s movements. It’s eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: It boasts superb physical strength. Those who wish to become Pangoro’s Trainer have no choice but to converse with their fists.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.

Name: Pangoro
FlavorText: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

Name: Furfrou
FlavorText: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.

Name: Furfrou
FlavorText: There was an era when aristocrats would compete to see who could trim their Furfrou’s fur into the most exquisite style.

Name: Furfrou
FlavorText: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.

Name: Furfrou
FlavorText: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

Name: Espurr
FlavorText: There’s enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can’t be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.

Name: Espurr
FlavorText: Though Espurr’s expression never changes, behind that blank stare is an intense struggle to contain its devastating psychic power.

Name: Espurr
FlavorText: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

Name: Espurr
FlavorText: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

Name: Meowstic
FlavorText: If it doesn’t hold back when it unleashes its psychic power, it can tear apart a tanker. Its unfriendliness is part of its charm.

Name: Meowstic
FlavorText: Females are a bit more selfish and aggressive than males. If they don’t get what they want, they will torment you with their psychic abilities.

Name: Meowstic
FlavorText: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It’s when they’re protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.

Name: Meowstic
FlavorText: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden, however.

Name: Meowstic
FlavorText: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.

Name: Meowstic
FlavorText: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

Name: Honedge
FlavorText: The blue eye on the sword’s handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people’s lives away.

Name: Honedge
FlavorText: Honedge’s soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge’s body.

Name: Honedge
FlavorText: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person’s arm and drains that person’s life energy completely.

Name: Honedge
FlavorText: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

Name: Doublade
FlavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

Name: Doublade
FlavorText: Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.

Name: Doublade
FlavorText: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

Name: Doublade
FlavorText: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

Name: Aegislash
FlavorText: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokémon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.

Name: Aegislash
FlavorText: This stance is dedicated to offense. It can cleave any opponent with the strength and weight of its steel blade.

Name: Aegislash
FlavorText: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokémon to build a kingdom to its liking.

Name: Aegislash
FlavorText: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.

Name: Aegislash
FlavorText: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

Name: Aegislash
FlavorText: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.

Name: Spritzee
FlavorText: The scent its body gives off enraptures those who smell it. Noble ladies had no shortage of love for Spritzee.

Name: Spritzee
FlavorText: A scent pouch within this Pokémon’s body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.

Name: Spritzee
FlavorText: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

Name: Spritzee
FlavorText: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

Name: Aromatisse
FlavorText: The scents Aromatisse can produce range from sweet smells that bolster allies to foul smells that sap an opponent’s will to fight.

Name: Aromatisse
FlavorText: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokémon’s companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.

Name: Aromatisse
FlavorText: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

Name: Aromatisse
FlavorText: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

Name: Swirlix
FlavorText: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix’s fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.

Name: Swirlix
FlavorText: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

Name: Swirlix
FlavorText: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.

Name: Swirlix
FlavorText: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

Name: Slurpuff
FlavorText: Slurpuff’s fur contains a lot of air, making it soft to the touch and lighter than it looks.

Name: Slurpuff
FlavorText: By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

Name: Slurpuff
FlavorText: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human’s, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It’s like it can see with its nose!

Name: Slurpuff
FlavorText: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

Name: Inkay
FlavorText: By exposing foes to the blinking of its luminescent spots, Inkay demoralizes them, and then it seizes the chance to flee.

Name: Inkay
FlavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

Name: Inkay
FlavorText: When exchanging information with others of its kind, it flashes the light-emitting spots on its body in a complex rhythm.

Name: Inkay
FlavorText: It draws prey near with its blinking lights and then wraps them up in its long tentacles and holds them in place.

Name: Inkay
FlavorText: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent’s will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.

Name: Inkay
FlavorText: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

Name: Malamar
FlavorText: It’s said that Malamar’s hypnotic powers played a role in certain history-changing events.

Name: Malamar
FlavorText: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar’s control.

Name: Malamar
FlavorText: It flashes the pattern on its torso to control its prey and draw them in. The edges of its fins are supremely sharp.

Name: Malamar
FlavorText: When it comes to strong hypnosis, there’s an endless number of people who utilize Malamar for their nefarious deeds.

Name: Malamar
FlavorText: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

Name: Malamar
FlavorText: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: If the two don’t work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won’t survive.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: Barbaracle’s legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head’s orders.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a poor swimmer. If it’s caught in a fierce storm, it will sometimes get washed far away and become unable to return to its home.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: Skrelp evades its enemies by hiding amid drifting seaweed. It eats rotten seaweed to create its poison.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: Skrelp looks like a piece of rotten seaweed, so it can blend in with seaweed drifting on the ocean and avoid being detected by enemies.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokémon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It’s not good at swimming, so it clings to the seaweed. In the Alola region, it’s often found near Dhelmise.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It vanishes into seaweed and remains perfectly still to avoid attacks from large Pokémon. Rotten seaweed is its main food source.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: Since Finizen is the better swimmer, Dragalge will approach it under the cover of seaweed, then immobilize it with a poisonous attack.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: Using a liquid poison, Dragalge indiscriminately attacks anything that wanders into its territory. This poison can corrode the undersides of boats.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: Dragalge generates dragon energy by sticking the plume on its head out above the ocean’s surface and bathing it in sunlight.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: Dragalge uses a poisonous liquid capable of corroding metal to send tankers that enter its territory to the bottom of the sea.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: It blends in with seaweed to ambush its prey and then takes them down with a poisonous liquid strong enough to melt metal.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: This vicious Pokémon sprays a poisonous liquid on opponents that come near. For whatever reason, it gets along really well with Dhelmise.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.

Name: Dragalge
FlavorText: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Clauncher’s claws will regrow if they fall off. The meat inside the claws is edible, but it has a distinct flavor that doesn’t appeal to all tastes.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: This Pokémon launches water by detonating gas inside its right claw. It snipes flying Pokémon.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: By detonating gas that accumulates in its right claw, this Pokémon launches water like a bullet. This is how Clauncher defeats its enemies.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Clauncher’s claws can fall off during battle, but they’ll regenerate. The meat inside the claws is popular as a delicacy in Galar.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: It moves around by jetting water from its right pincer. It has a poor sense of balance, so it’s terrible at swimming straight.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Its claws occasionally fall off, and it keeps a low profile until they grow back. The meat of its claws is so delicious!

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: The cannonballs of seawater that Clawitzer launches from its claw are powerful enough to punch through tanker hulls.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Clawitzer can move through the water at a speed of 60 knots by using gas inside its body to expel water from the back of its claw.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Clawitzer’s right arm is a cannon that launches projectiles made of seawater. Shots from a Clawitzer’s cannon arm can sink a tanker.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: After using the feelers on its oversized claw to detect the location of prey, Clawitzer launches a cannonball of water at its target.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Its right arm is packed with meat. When its pincer falls off, it’s exported to be used as a cooking ingredient.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: It compresses the water it has sucked up and then projects it with enough power to punch a hole right through a thick sheet of iron.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

Name: Helioptile
FlavorText: The sun powers this Pokémon’s electricity generation. Interruption of that process stresses Helioptile to the point of weakness.

Name: Helioptile
FlavorText: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon’s electric moves.

Name: Helioptile
FlavorText: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

Name: Helioptile
FlavorText: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

Name: Heliolisk
FlavorText: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.

Name: Heliolisk
FlavorText: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

Name: Heliolisk
FlavorText: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

Name: Heliolisk
FlavorText: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

Name: Tyrunt
FlavorText: This Pokémon is selfish and likes to be pampered. It can also inflict grievous wounds on its Trainer just by playing around.

Name: Tyrunt
FlavorText: This is an ancient Pokémon, revived in modern times. It has a violent disposition, and it’ll tear apart anything it gets between its hefty jaws.

Name: Tyrunt
FlavorText: Tyrunt is spoiled and selfish. It may just be trying to frolic, but sometimes the ones it’s trying to frolic with are gravely injured.

Name: Tyrunt
FlavorText: Its large jaw has incredible destructive power. Some theories suggest that its restored form is different from its form of long ago.

Name: Tyrunt
FlavorText: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.

Name: Tyrunt
FlavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

Name: Tyrantrum
FlavorText: A single bite of Tyrantrum’s massive jaws will demolish a car. This Pokémon was the king of the ancient world.

Name: Tyrantrum
FlavorText: This Pokémon is from about 100,000,000 years ago. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.

Name: Tyrantrum
FlavorText: The king of the ancient world, it can easily crunch a car with the devastating strength of its enormous jaws.

Name: Tyrantrum
FlavorText: Complete restoration is impossible, allowing room for theories that its entire body was once covered in a feather-like coat.

Name: Tyrantrum
FlavorText: Nothing could stop this Pokémon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.

Name: Tyrantrum
FlavorText: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

Name: Amaura
FlavorText: Amaura is an ancient Pokémon that has gone extinct. Specimens of this species can sometimes be found frozen in ice.

Name: Amaura
FlavorText: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past, it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

Name: Amaura
FlavorText: Amaura was restored successfully, but it’s not expected to live long because of the heat of the current environment.

Name: Amaura
FlavorText: It lived in cold areas in ancient times. It’s said that when Amaura whinnies, auroras appear in the night sky.

Name: Amaura
FlavorText: This calm Pokémon lived in a cold land where there were no violent predators like Tyrantrum.

Name: Amaura
FlavorText: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

Name: Aurorus
FlavorText: When gripped by rage, Aurorus will emanate freezing air, covering everything around it in ice.

Name: Aurorus
FlavorText: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It’s said that when this Pokémon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.

Name: Aurorus
FlavorText: This usually quiet and kindly Pokémon has a surface temperature of around –240 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Aurorus
FlavorText: An Aurorus was found frozen solid within a glacier, just as it appeared long ago, which became quite a big event in the news.

Name: Aurorus
FlavorText: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent’s attack.

Name: Aurorus
FlavorText: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: Sylveon cuts an elegant figure as it dances lightly around, feelers fluttering, but its piercing moves aim straight for its opponents’ weak spots.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses its ribbonlike feelers to send a soothing aura into its opponents, erasing their hostility.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: It emits a soothing aura from its ribbon-shaped organs. It wraps these appendages around quarrelers to instantly restore calm to the situation.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: There’s a Galarian fairy tale that describes a beautiful Sylveon vanquishing a dreadful dragon Pokémon.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: By releasing enmity-erasing waves from its ribbonlike feelers, Sylveon stops any conflict.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: Sylveon wraps its ribbonlike feelers around its Trainer’s arm because this touch enables it to read its Trainer’s feelings.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: Once a fight breaks out, it will unflinchingly charge at dragon Pokémon that are many times larger than itself.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: When this Pokémon sights its prey, it swirls its ribbonlike feelers as a distraction. A moment later, it pounces.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: Its ribbonlike feelers give off an aura that weakens hostility in its prey, causing them to let down their guard. Then it attacks.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: It wraps its ribbonlike feelers around the arm of its beloved Trainer and walks with him or her.

Name: Sylveon
FlavorText: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: Hawlucha live quietly without flocking together. They fight constantly with their natural enemies: noisy groups of Primeape.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: It always strikes a pose before going for its finishing move. Sometimes opponents take advantage of that time to counterattack.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: In combat, Hawlucha leaps nimbly about, taking advantage of its opponents’ blind spots. It’s also skilled at using superb submission holds.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: It overwhelms opponents with quick moves, but sometimes it showboats for too long when it’s using a special move and gets itself into a pinch.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

Name: Hawlucha
FlavorText: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: Dedenne emit electrical waves from the whiskers on their cheeks to communicate with each other. When low on electricity, they curl up and sleep.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: It’s small and its electricity-generating organ is not fully developed, so it uses its tail to absorb electricity from people’s homes and charge itself.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: Since Dedenne can’t generate much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: A Dedenne’s whiskers pick up electrical waves other Dedenne send out. These Pokémon share locations of food or electricity with one another.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: It sneaks into people’s homes and steals electricity from their outlets. When your electric bill seems off, it’s the handiwork of this rascal.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

Name: Dedenne
FlavorText: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: It’s said that somewhere in the world, there’s a mineral vein housing a large pack of slumbering Carbink. It’s also said that this pack has a queen.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: To keep the jewels on their bodies free of tarnish, packs of Carbink use their soft manes to polish one another’s jewels.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: Some say that deep beneath the surface of the world, a pack of Carbink live with their queen in a kingdom of jewels.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: Although this Pokémon is not especially rare, its glittering, jewel-draped body draws attention from people.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: Born from the high temperatures and pressures deep underground, it defends itself by firing beams from the jewel part of its body.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It’s occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

Name: Carbink
FlavorText: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: Goomy’s horns are excellent sensory organs that cover all five of Goomy’s senses. Goomy picks up on danger from the movement of the air.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: Most of a Goomy’s body is water. A membrane covers the whole Pokémon to prevent it from shriveling up in dry weather.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: Goomy hides away in the shade of trees, where it’s nice and humid. If the slime coating its body dries out, the Pokémon instantly becomes lethargic.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: Their horns are powerful sensors. As soon as Goomy pick up any sign of enemies, they go into hiding. This is how they’ve survived.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: Because most of its body is water, it will dry up if the weather becomes too arid. It’s considered the weakest dragon Pokémon.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: Its body is mostly water. If it dries out, it will die, so it’s always sitting with perfect stillness in the shade.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: It uses its horns to check out its surroundings. They’re very sensitive, so if you grab them, it will feel a strong shock and be unable to move.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: Its source of protection is its slimy, germ-laden mucous membrane. Anyone who touches it needs some thorough hand-washing.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: The weakest of all Dragon-type Pokémon, it’s unable to breathe if its skin dries out, so it sticks to shady places.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: It’s covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.

Name: Goomy
FlavorText: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui’s water.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: When Sliggoo senses danger, the mucus coating its entire body becomes more concentrated—it’ll dissolve anything.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: The swirly protrusion on its back is filled with all its vital organs, such as its brain and heart.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: The lump on its back contains its tiny brain. It thinks only of food and escaping its enemies.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: Although this Pokémon isn’t very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: Its entire body is covered with gooey mucus that can dissolve anything. Be sure to put gloves on if you’re going to touch it.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: It crawls along sluggishly. The swirly protrusion on its back is filled with its brain and other organs.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s mucous can dissolve anything. Toothless, it sprays mucous on its prey. Once they’re nicely dissolved, it slurps them up.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: It has trouble drawing a line between friends and food. It will calmly try to melt and eat even those it gets along well with.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.

Name: Sliggoo
FlavorText: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy—it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: This Pokémon is uncontrollable when enraged. It rampages on and on, lashing its tail with enough power to send a dump truck flying.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: It loves the rain. This mellow Pokémon can be seen walking around on the plains and in the mountains on rainy days.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: Its form of offense is forcefully stretching out its horns. The strikes land 100 times harder than any blow from a heavyweight boxer.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don’t mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: Underneath its slimy skin is a thick layer of fat, and the combination of the two makes enemies’ attacks slide right off.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: It’s very friendly toward people. If you grow close to it, Goodra will hug you with its sticky, slime-covered body. Don’t get mad.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: It gets picked on because it’s meek. But then, whoever teased it gets to feel the full force of its horns and a good swatting from its thick tail.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: An amazingly friendly Pokémon, but if left to itself, loneliness overcomes it, and it oozes gooey tears.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that’s the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.

Name: Goodra
FlavorText: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: Once it absorbs a key’s metal ions, it discards the key without a second thought. However, it will hang on to keys it favors for decades.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: Klefki sucks in metal ions with the horn topping its head. It seems this Pokémon loves keys so much that its head needed to look like one, too.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: This Pokémon is constantly collecting keys. Entrust a Klefki with important keys, and the Pokémon will protect them no matter what.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: Long ago it lived in mines, but once the minerals that make up its diet became scarcer, Klefki began appearing in human settlements.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: Although it’s unclear why it collects keys, giving it a key makes Klefki very happy. However, it apparently only likes master keys.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: It inserts its horn into chinks in metal, absorbing metal ions. For some reason, it collects keys.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: This even-tempered Pokémon has a habit of collecting keys. It will sneak into people’s homes to steal their keys.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

Name: Klefki
FlavorText: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit’s rebirth as this Pokémon.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: An unknown spirit came to lodge in a tree stump, creating this Pokémon. A cure-all can be made from an infusion of its green leaves.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: By imitating the voice of a child, it causes people to get hopelessly lost deep in the forest. It’s trying to make friends with them.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: According to legend, medicine to cure any illness can be made by plucking the green leaves on its head, brewing them, and boiling down the liquid.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: These Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died in the forest. Their cries sound like eerie screams.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: This Pokémon controls trees via roots stretching from its feet, and it will attack anyone that dares to ravage the forest.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: It’s feared as a ghost of the forest. Lumberjacks bring along Fire types, which Trevenant hates, when they enter the forest.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: Through its roots, it exerts control over other trees. A deadly curse falls upon anyone cutting down trees in forests where Trevenant dwell.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: This Pokémon is said to devour anyone daring to ravage the forest. To the creatures dwelling in the forest, it offers great kindness.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It’s kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Massive Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where a great number of lost souls lingered.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Supersized Pumpkaboo are very partial to the spirits of people who were of similarly superior proportions.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Large Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where many lost souls lingered.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: When taking spirits to the afterlife, large Pumpkaboo prefer the spirits of adults to those of children.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Small Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where few lost souls lingered.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: When taking spirits to the afterlife, small Pumpkaboo prefer the spirits of children to those of adults.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: A supersized Pumpkaboo evolves into a supersized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Supersized Gourgeist aren’t picky. They will forcefully drag anyone off to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: A large-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a large-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Large Gourgeist put on the guise of adults, taking the hands of children to lead them to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: A small-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a small-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Small Gourgeist pretend to be children to fool adults. Anyone who falls for the act gets carried away to the hereafter.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

Name: Bergmite
FlavorText: Bergmite protects itself by coating its body in ice formed by frigid air of −148 degrees Fahrenheit. It fights with Frigibax whenever they meet.

Name: Bergmite
FlavorText: They live in mountainous regions of frigid cold. On rare occasions, they ride on the back of an Avalugg to cross seas and move to new habitats.

Name: Bergmite
FlavorText: Lives on mountains blanketed in perennial snow. It freezes water vapor in the air to make the ice helmet that it dons for defense.

Name: Bergmite
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in areas of frigid cold. It secures itself to the back of an Avalugg by freezing its feet in place.

Name: Bergmite
FlavorText: They chill the air around them to −150 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing the water in the air into ice that they use as armor.

Name: Bergmite
FlavorText: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

Name: Bergmite
FlavorText: It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

Name: Avalugg
FlavorText: The armor of ice covering its lower jaw puts steel to shame and can shatter rocks with ease. This Pokémon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow.

Name: Avalugg
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses its massive icy body to flatten anything that gets in its way. When it’s floating out on the ocean, it looks exactly like drift ice.
