Name: Avalugg
FlavorText: As Avalugg walks along with Bergmite on its back, it comes across pods of Cetitan. It lets them pass to avoid conflict.

Name: Avalugg
FlavorText: As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokémon’s body returns to a pristine state overnight.

Name: Avalugg
FlavorText: At high latitudes, this Pokémon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

Name: Avalugg
FlavorText: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.

Name: Avalugg
FlavorText: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: Noibat can change the frequency of its sound waves at will, and it generates ultrasonic waves of up to 200,000 hertz.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: No wavelength of sound is beyond Noibat’s ability to produce. The ultrasonic waves it generates can overcome much larger Pokémon.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: After nightfall, they emerge from the caves they nest in during the day. Using their ultrasonic waves, they go on the hunt for ripened fruit.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: It flies around in search of fruit to eat. It uses ultrasonic waves to detect which fruits are ripe.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: Fruits are its favorite foods. This gourmet carefully picks out just the ripe ones using its sonar.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.

Name: Noibat
FlavorText: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: In the dark, even Hydreigon are terrified of this Pokémon. But in the light, Noivern is the one that avoids battle.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: Ultrasonic waves emitted by a Noivern can pulverize a large boulder. This Pokémon has a cruel disposition.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: Flying through the darkness, it weakens enemies with ultrasonic waves that could crush stone. Its fangs finish the fight.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: Aggressive and cruel, this Pokémon will ruthlessly torment enemies that are helpless in the dark.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: This hot-blooded Pokémon attacks anything it sees with ultrasonic waves that can crush boulders.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: Although it has a violent disposition, if you give it a nice ripe fruit that it loves, Noivern will suddenly become tame.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

Name: Noivern
FlavorText: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

Name: Xerneas
FlavorText: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

Name: Xerneas
FlavorText: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

Name: Yveltal
FlavorText: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

Name: Yveltal
FlavorText: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: Born when all of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered together, it uses force to neutralize those who harm the ecosystem.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: This is Zygarde’s perfected form. From the orifice on its chest, it radiates high-powered energy that eliminates everything.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: This is Zygarde’s 100% form. It has enough power to overwhelm even Xerneas or Yveltal.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: This is Zygarde’s form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: Born when around 10% of Zygarde’s cells have been gathered from all over, this form is skilled in close-range combat.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: This is Zygarde when about 10% of its pieces have been assembled. It leaps at its opponent’s chest and sinks its sharp fangs into them.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: This is Zygarde’s form when about 10% of its cells have been gathered. It runs across the land at speeds greater than 60 mph.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: Its sharp fangs make short work of finishing off its enemies, but it’s unable to maintain this body indefinitely. After a period of time, it falls apart.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: This is Zygarde’s form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: It’s thought to be monitoring the ecosystem. There are rumors that even greater power lies hidden within it.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: It’s hypothesized that it’s monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.

Name: Zygarde
FlavorText: When the Kalos region’s ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

Name: Diancie
FlavorText: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

Name: Diancie
FlavorText: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

Name: Hoopa
FlavorText: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

Name: Hoopa
FlavorText: In its true form, it possess a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.

Name: Hoopa
FlavorText: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

Name: Hoopa
FlavorText: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

Name: Volcanion
FlavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

Name: Volcanion
FlavorText: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: During the day, it builds up energy via photosynthesis. At night, it flies silently through the sky, on the prowl for prey.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and has been known to use its Trainer’s pocket or bag as a nest.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: Silently it glides, drawing near its targets. Before they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: Regularly basks in sunlight to gather power—presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: It never slacks when it comes to the task of cleaning its feathers. Thorough preening keeps it looking spiffy and its blade quills nice and sharp.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: Supremely sensitive to the presence of others, it can detect opponents standing behind it, flinging its sharp feathers to take them out.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don’t groom it diligently, it will stop listening to you.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: It throws sharp feathers called blade quills at enemies or prey. It seldom misses.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye’s feathers insulates the Pokémon against Hisui’s extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent’s weak point before they notice what’s happening.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye’s shots never miss.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: Decidueye can nock and fire an arrow at an enemy in a tenth of a second, so its battles are decided in the blink of an eye.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can’t afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: Although basically cool and cautious, when it’s caught by surprise, it’s seized by panic.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: Trying to pet Litten before it trusts you will result in a nasty scratch from its sharp claws. Be careful.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: It spends even the smallest amount of downtime grooming its fur with its tongue. Loose fur gathers in its stomach and serves as fuel for fiery moves.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: Its coat regrows twice a year. When the time comes, Litten sets its own body on fire and burns away the old fur.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: It doesn’t allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: When facing a powerful enemy, Torracat’s fighting spirit gets pumped up, and its fire bell blazes hotter.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: In the midst of battle, the fire pouch on Torracat’s neck rings like a bell and produces stronger flames than usual.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: When its mane is standing on end, you can tell it’s feeling good. When it isn’t feeling well, its fur will lie down flat.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer’s whole body covered in scratches.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: It boasts powerful front legs. With a single punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: Incineroar’s rough and aggressive behavior is its most notable trait, but the way it helps out small Pokémon shows that it has a kind side as well.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: It excels at violent, no-holds-barred battles. The temperature of the flames that issue from its navel exceeds 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flames around its waist become especially intense.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: Although it’s rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: After hurling ferocious punches and flinging furious kicks, it finishes opponents off by spewing fire from around its navel.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it’s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer’s orders with complete nonchalance.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: If Popplio want to create big, powerful balloons, they must be persistent. It takes daily practice for these Pokémon to develop their skills.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: It creates special bouncy balloons to send at its opponents. When the balloons pop, the sheer force of their bursting is what deals damage.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: Popplio gets on top of its bouncy water balloons to jump higher. It’s quite the acrobatic fighter!

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: This Pokémon can control water bubbles. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big bubbles.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It’s famous for being a hard worker.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: On nights when the sea is calm, Brionne dance with one another to the singing of the Primarina that’s leading them.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: As if dancing, it artfully dodges the attacks of its enemies. All the while, it’s busy forming a bunch of balloons to overwhelm its foes.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: It attacks by smacking its enemies with the exploding water balloons that it creates.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn’t know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: For Primarina, every battle’s a stage. Its singing and the dancing of its balloons will mesmerize the audience.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: With its mouth, it makes sonic waves that sound like beautiful singing. It uses the sonic waves to control its water balloons.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: Also known as a songstress, it has a fantastical look on moonlit nights when it leads its colony in song.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle. This Pokémon’s Trainer must prioritize the daily maintenance of its throat at all costs.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

Name: Pikipek
FlavorText: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!

Name: Pikipek
FlavorText: It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

Name: Pikipek
FlavorText: This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.

Name: Pikipek
FlavorText: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

Name: Trumbeak
FlavorText: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.

Name: Trumbeak
FlavorText: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.

Name: Trumbeak
FlavorText: By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of calls and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.

Name: Trumbeak
FlavorText: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

Name: Toucannon
FlavorText: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.

Name: Toucannon
FlavorText: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

Name: Toucannon
FlavorText: Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.

Name: Toucannon
FlavorText: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

Name: Yungoos
FlavorText: It spends its waking hours searching endlessly for food. When Yungoos is hungry, its ferocity gains a certain edge.

Name: Yungoos
FlavorText: Its stomach fills most of its torso. It wanders the same path every day, searching for fresh food.

Name: Yungoos
FlavorText: Although it will eat anything, it prefers fresh living things, so it marches down streets in search of prey.

Name: Yungoos
FlavorText: Its stomach takes up most of its long torso. It’s a big eater, so the amount Trainers have to spend on its food is no laughing matter.

Name: Yungoos
FlavorText: It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.

Name: Yungoos
FlavorText: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

Name: Gumshoos
FlavorText: Gumshoos specializes in relentlessly tracking down prey. The simple-minded Skwovet doesn’t seem to provide Gumshoos enough challenge.

Name: Gumshoos
FlavorText: Once it finds signs of prey, it will patiently stake out the location, waiting until the sun goes down.

Name: Gumshoos
FlavorText: Patient by nature, this Pokémon loses control of itself and pounces when it spots its favorite meal—Rattata!

Name: Gumshoos
FlavorText: Although it wasn’t originally found in Alola, this Pokémon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.

Name: Gumshoos
FlavorText: It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it’s diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokémon boasts incredible patience.

Name: Gumshoos
FlavorText: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing by nightfall.

Name: Grubbin
FlavorText: It uses its big jaws to dig nests into the forest floor, and it loves to feed on sweet tree sap.

Name: Grubbin
FlavorText: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

Name: Grubbin
FlavorText: It spits a sticky thread to stop opponents in their tracks, and then it grabs them in its sharp, sturdy mandibles to take them down.

Name: Grubbin
FlavorText: If you find its nest, you shouldn’t stick your hand inside. You’ll get bitten by an irritated Grubbin.

Name: Grubbin
FlavorText: They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokémon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokémon.

Name: Grubbin
FlavorText: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

Name: Charjabug
FlavorText: Its digestive processes convert the leaves it eats into electricity. An electric sac in its belly stores the electricity for later use.

Name: Charjabug
FlavorText: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

Name: Charjabug
FlavorText: Its stout shell provides excellent defense from attacks. It uses electricity on persistent opponents.

Name: Charjabug
FlavorText: It buries itself in fallen leaves and barely moves, munching away on humus. If you accidentally step on one, you’ll get a shock!

Name: Charjabug
FlavorText: From the food it digests, it generates electricity, and it stores this energy in its electric sac.

Name: Charjabug
FlavorText: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.

Name: Vikavolt
FlavorText: If it carries a Charjabug to use as a spare battery, a flying Vikavolt can rapidly fire high-powered beams of electricity.

Name: Vikavolt
FlavorText: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

Name: Vikavolt
FlavorText: Vikavolt flusters opponents with acrobatic flying maneuvers. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electric beam attack.

Name: Vikavolt
FlavorText: It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its strong jaws and fires off powerful jolts of electricity.

Name: Vikavolt
FlavorText: It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokémon with shocking beams of electrical energy.

Name: Vikavolt
FlavorText: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

Name: Crabrawler
FlavorText: If it loses its pincers, they’ll quickly regrow. The pincers are popular ingredients in paella since their shells produce a tasty soup stock.

Name: Crabrawler
FlavorText: This Pokémon punches trees and eats the berries that drop down, training itself and getting food at the same time.

Name: Crabrawler
FlavorText: Crabrawler has been known to mistake Exeggutor for a coconut tree and climb it. The enraged Exeggutor shakes it off and stomps it.

Name: Crabrawler
FlavorText: Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.

Name: Crabrawler
FlavorText: It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.

Name: Crabrawler
FlavorText: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

Name: Crabominable
FlavorText: Though its punches are powerful, this Pokémon’s movements are sluggish. It blows icy bubbles from its mouth to immobilize its opponents.

Name: Crabominable
FlavorText: The detached pincers of these Pokémon are delicious. Some Trainers bring Lechonk into the mountains just to search for them.

Name: Crabominable
FlavorText: Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling. There are records of its turning back avalanches with a flurry of punches.

Name: Crabominable
FlavorText: It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!

Name: Crabominable
FlavorText: It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.

Name: Crabominable
FlavorText: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: The elegant, attractive dance of these Oricorio is popular with adults, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This form of Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. It uses ethereal dance steps to call forth the spirits of the dead.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Some dancers use its graceful, elegant dancing as inspiration.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It charms its opponents with its refined dancing. When they let their guard down, it places a curse on them that will bring on their demise.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It summons the dead with its dreamy dancing. From their malice, it draws power with which to curse its enemies.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Its elegant, attractive dance will send the minds and hearts of its enemies to another world.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. It gets so caught up in its dancing that it sometimes doesn’t hear its Trainer’s orders.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It relaxes its opponents with its elegant dancing. When they let their guard down, it showers them with psychic energy.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. Its enemies’ hearts melt at the sight of its gently swaying hips.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio relaxes by swaying gently. This increases its psychic energy, which it then fires at its enemies.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: The energetic, cheerful dance of these Oricorio is popular with children, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This form of Oricorio has sipped yellow nectar. It uses nimble steps to approach opponents, then knocks them out with electric punches.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has drunk bright yellow nectar. When it sees someone looking glum, it will try to cheer them up with a dance.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It lifts its opponents’ spirits with its cheerful dance moves. When they let their guard down, it electrocutes them with a jolt.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It creates an electric charge by rubbing its feathers together. It dances over to its enemies and delivers shocking electrical punches.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has sipped bright yellow nectar. Its bright, cheerful dance melts the hearts of its enemies.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This form of Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. It elevates its mind with the gentle steps of its dance, then unleashes its psychic energy.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: The airy dance of these Oricorio is popular as a means of maintaining good health, but the Oricorio themselves are hard to find in Paldea.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Pokémon is incredibly popular, possibly because its passionate dancing is a great match with the temperament of Paldean people.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

Name: Cutiefly
FlavorText: An opponent’s aura can tell Cutiefly what that opponent’s next move will be. Then Cutiefly can glide around the attack and strike back.

Name: Cutiefly
FlavorText: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur’s pollen.

Name: Cutiefly
FlavorText: Cutiefly can pick up the auras of living things. It skillfully reads those auras to predict its foes’ movements and make fools of them.

Name: Cutiefly
FlavorText: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. In fields of flowers, it gets into skirmishes with Butterfree over food.

Name: Cutiefly
FlavorText: Myriads of Cutiefly flutter above the heads of people who have auras resembling those of flowers.

Name: Cutiefly
FlavorText: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it’s able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

Name: Ribombee
FlavorText: Ribombee absolutely hate getting wet or rained on. In the cloudy Galar region, they are very seldom seen.

Name: Ribombee
FlavorText: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs’ effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.

Name: Ribombee
FlavorText: It can predict the weather from moisture levels and wind direction. Ribombee only reveals itself when there are a few clear days in a row.

Name: Ribombee
FlavorText: Rain makes pollen damp, so Ribombee hates rain. When it sees ominous clouds, it finds a hollow in a tree, where it waits stock-still.

Name: Ribombee
FlavorText: Some of Ribombee’s pollen puffs are highly nutritious. They are sometimes sold as supplements.

Name: Ribombee
FlavorText: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: This Pokémon travels in a pack with others until it grows up. When its mood turns sour, it starts striking the ground with the rocks on its neck.

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: This Pokémon intimidates opponents by striking the ground with the rocks on its neck. The moment an opponent flinches, Rockruff attacks.

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: This Pokémon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that’s proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: As they develop, their disposition grows more violent and aggressive. Many Trainers find them too much to handle and abandon them.

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: This Pokémon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer’s side.

Name: Rockruff
FlavorText: It’s considered to be a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: These Pokémon have both calm and ferocious qualities. It’s said that this form of Lycanroc is the most troublesome to raise.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: Normally this Pokémon doesn’t even bark, but once it enters battle, it will relentlessly drive the opponent into a corner.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: These Pokémon have both calm and ferocious qualities. Their temperamental nature makes them a difficult species to raise.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: This form of Lycanroc is normally calm and quiet. Once a battle begins, however, this Pokémon displays a ferocious fighting spirit.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: This strange form is the result of its evolving at dusk. It’s very rare in Alola.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: Bathed in the setting sun of evening, Lycanroc has undergone a special kind of evolution. An intense fighting spirit underlies its calmness.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: This Lycanroc has an extremely vicious temperament. It will happily sustain injuries for the sake of taking down its opponent.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses its rocky mane to slash any who approach. It will even disobey its Trainer if it dislikes the orders it was given.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: It’s invigorated by powerful opponents—the stronger the better. A full-force headbutt from one of these Lycanroc can shatter giant boulders.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: This form of Lycanroc is reckless. It charges headlong at its opponents, attacking without any care about what injuries it might receive.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: It has no problem ignoring orders it doesn’t like. It doesn’t seem to mind getting hurt at all—as long as it can finish off its opponent.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: It goads its enemies into attacking, withstands the hits, and in return, delivers a headbutt, crushing their bones with its rocky mane.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: The more intimidating the opponent it faces, the more this Pokémon’s blood boils. It will attack with no regard for its own safety.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: It has a calm and collected demeanor. It swiftly closes in on its prey, then slices them with the rocks in its mane.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: With swift movements, this Pokémon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc’s fangs are always aimed toward opponents’ weak spots.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: The sharp rocks in its mane can cut like knives. Lycanroc wears its prey down by degrees before finishing them off.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.

Name: Lycanroc
FlavorText: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When facing tough opponents, they get into formation. But if they get wounded in battle, they’ll scatter and become solitary again.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: On their own, they’re very weak. But when Wishiwashi pool their power together in a school, they become a demon of the sea.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Called “demon of the sea” by some, when Wishiwashi are injured in battle and their numbers dwindle, they become a regular school.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Wishiwashi assemble in this formation to face off against strong foes. It boasts a strength that earned it the name “demon of the sea.”

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: At their appearance, even Gyarados will flee. When they team up to use Water Gun, its power exceeds that of Hydro Pump.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Weak Wishiwashi school together to concentrate their power. Their united force makes them the demon of the sea, feared near and far.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When it’s in a jam, its shining eyes attract others of its kind. The light from its eyes is visible almost 25 miles away.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: They’re weak, so they move in schools. However, they can also often be seen all alone, having strayed from the school.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: It’s awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When it’s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: It has excellent regenerative capabilities. Legs that a Mareanie has lost have a very bitter, astringent flavor—they’re not suitable as food.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: This Pokémon wanders the seaside looking for food. It often gets electric shocks from broken Pincurchin spines that it tries to eat.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: Unlike their Alolan counterparts, the Mareanie of the Galar region have not yet figured out that the branches of Corsola are delicious.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it’s impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: Aside from its head, its body parts regenerate quickly if they’re cut off. After a good night’s sleep, Mareanie is back to normal.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: They eat Corsola branches, so Mareanie are hated by craftsmen who work with Corsola branches that have naturally fallen off.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: It’s found crawling on beaches and seafloors. The coral that grows on Corsola’s head is as good as a five-star banquet to this Pokémon.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Toxapex gets into fierce battles with Bruxish over areas where warm ocean currents flow, but the odds are always against it.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives within a dome made by its own legs. Toxapex monitors its surroundings by sensing the flow of the tide through its spikes.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Within the poison sac in its body is a poison so toxic that Pokémon as large as Wailord will still be suffering three days after it first takes effect.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokémon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: With its 12 legs, it creates a dome to shelter within. The flow of the tides doesn’t affect Toxapex in there, so it’s very comfortable.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: To attack, this Pokémon sends toxic spikes flying at its enemies. Ones that come close get mown down by the claws on its feet.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Those attacked by Toxapex’s poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: Though a slow walker, Mudbray is plenty strong. Its pace doesn’t change even when it’s loaded with 50 times its own body weight.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won’t dry out even if it’s exposed to the sun for a long time.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: It eats dirt to create mud and smears this mud all over its feet, giving them the grip needed to walk on rough terrain without slipping.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokémon. It’s skilled at making use of mud.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: Possessing mighty power, Mudbray can be loaded with 50 times its own body weight and will be totally fine.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: It loves playing in the mud. If it isn’t showered with mud on a daily basis, it gets stressed out and stops listening to its Trainer.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition. Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mire all form part of its daily routine.

Name: Mudbray
FlavorText: The mud stuck to Mudbray’s hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: Its legs are fortified with mud and harder than stone, and they can reduce a large truck to scrap with one kick.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: This Pokémon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: Mudsdale has so much stamina that it could carry over 10 tons across the Galar region without rest or sleep.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale’s legs sets harder than stone. It’s so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: It can trudge mountain roads without rest for three days and three nights, all the while dragging a 10-ton load.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: It remains calm and unmoving no matter the situation. It mixes dirt with the saliva in its mouth to make a special kind of mud.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: Its heavy, mud-covered kicks are its best means of attack, and it can reduce large trucks to scrap without breaking a sweat.

Name: Mudsdale
FlavorText: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: Dewpider normally lives underwater. When it comes onto land in search of food, it takes water with it in the form of a bubble on its head.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: It can only breathe oxygen that has dissolved in water, so it wears a water bubble on its head when it walks around on land.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other’s way.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: When it comes across enemies or potential prey, this Pokémon smashes its water-bubble-covered head into them.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It has a habit of storing things it values in its water bubble. If its Trainer doesn’t watch out, Araquanid will try to put them in its bubble!

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokémon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: Many Trainers give their Fomantis their own flowerpots so they can sunbathe in peace and quiet.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted. It fires off beams using energy it gathers by bathing in the sun.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: During the day, Fomantis basks in sunlight and sleeps peacefully. It wakes and moves around at night.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: When bathed in sunlight, this Pokémon emits a pleasantly sweet scent, which causes bug Pokémon to gather around it.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: They give off a sweet and refreshing scent. Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where Fomantis are hiding.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: A lot of time and effort is required to maintain the vivid colors of its petals. This Pokémon puts its Trainer’s attentiveness to the test.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: The petals on this Pokémon’s arms are thin and super sharp, and they can fire laser beams if Lurantis gathers light first.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: This Pokémon resembles a beautiful flower. A properly raised Lurantis will have gorgeous, brilliant colors.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it’s dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokémon.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokémon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: It fires beams from its sickle-shaped petals. These beams are powerful enough to cleave through thick metal plates.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’s vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: It likes damp dark places. When night falls, the spores filling the caps of its mushrooms glow.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: It scatters its shining spores around itself. Even though they’re dangerous, nighttime tours of forests where Morelull live are popular.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: If you see a light deep in a forest at night, don’t go near. Shiinotic will make you fall fast asleep.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: When it starts fighting for territory with Parasect, the entire area gets completely coated in spores!

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: It puts its prey to sleep and siphons off their vitality through the tip of its arms. If one of its kind is weakened, it helps by sending it vitality.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: This sneaky Pokémon will slink behind its prey and immobilize it with poisonous gas before the prey even realizes Salandit is there.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit’s poisonous gas.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: It weakens opponents and sends them reeling with its poisonous gas. Salandit doesn’t deal well with Spinda, since it’s always reeling.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can’t evolve.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: Volcanoes or dry, craggy places are its home. It emanates a sweet-smelling poisonous gas that attracts bug Pokémon, then attacks them.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: When two Salazzle meet, they will use their pheromone gas to fight over the males in each other’s group.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: It punishes Salandit that couldn’t bring it food with a fierce slap of its flame-spewing palm.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of luscious perfumes.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

Name: Stufful
FlavorText: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.

Name: Stufful
FlavorText: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

Name: Stufful
FlavorText: Stufful hates to be hugged or touched in any way. It will squirm, thrash, and resist with amazing power.

Name: Stufful
FlavorText: It boasts power enough to split large trees in half. The organ on its rear releases an odor that it uses to communicate with others of its kind.

Name: Stufful
FlavorText: A touch from anyone except a known friend sends it into a surging frenzy. It’s an incredibly dangerous Pokémon.

Name: Stufful
FlavorText: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

Name: Bewear
FlavorText: The moves it uses to take down its prey would make a martial artist jealous. It tucks subdued prey under its arms to carry them to its nest.

Name: Bewear
FlavorText: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

Name: Bewear
FlavorText: It boasts tremendous physical strength. Many people call it the most dangerous Pokémon in the Alola region.

Name: Bewear
FlavorText: It waves its hands wildly in intimidation and warning. Life is over for anyone who doesn’t run away as fast as possible.

Name: Bewear
FlavorText: This Pokémon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.

Name: Bewear
FlavorText: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: A Greedent drawn in by the sweet scent of these Pokémon will tuck the Bounsweet in among the berries in its tail and carry them all away.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: When under attack, it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent that is extremely appetizing to bird Pokémon.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: It tries to resist being swallowed by a bird Pokémon by spinning the sepals on its head. It’s usually a fruitless attempt.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokémon are always after it, but it’s not intelligent enough to care.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Although it’s too sugary for human consumption, Bounsweet’s sweat can be watered down into a juice with just the right amount of sweetness.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: Steenee bounces energetically through forests. If the rind that peels off its body is pulverized, it can be used to treat stomach pains.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokémon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: As it twirls like a dancer, a sweet smell spreads out around it. Anyone who inhales the scent will feel a surge of happiness.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: It bounces around, swinging the sepals on its head with abandon. They’re quite painful when they smack you!

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: It’s protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokémon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn’t care.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: This Pokémon is always bouncing around energetically. Other Pokémon are attracted by its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: This Pokémon launches fierce yet elegant kicks with its long, slender legs. It views Quaquaval as its rival.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if someone touches the crown on its calyx.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokémon’s legs leaves a wound in the opponent’s body and soul that will never heal.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: This feared Pokémon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A Pokémon with an aggressive personality and a mastery of kicking, it cackles every time it kicks an opponent.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it can knock out even kickboxing champions with a single blow.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A Pokémon known for the beauty of its well-shaped legs, it sometimes appears as a mascot in advertisements for beauty salons.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

Name: Comfey
FlavorText: These Pokémon smell very nice. All Comfey wear different flowers, so each of these Pokémon has its own individual scent.

Name: Comfey
FlavorText: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won’t wither once they’re attached to a Comfey.

Name: Comfey
FlavorText: It picks flowers and sticks them to its body with fluids it produces. The aroma that wafts from its petals has a healing effect.

Name: Comfey
FlavorText: It stretches sticky vines out from its head and picks flowers to adorn itself with. When it doesn’t have any flowers, it feels uneasy.

Name: Comfey
FlavorText: Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine have a relaxing effect, so this Pokémon is a hit with many people.

Name: Comfey
FlavorText: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives quietly in the depths of the forest. The purple, cape-like fur gets longer and longer as Oranguru ages.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: People used to mistake Oranguru for a human when they saw it issue command after command to the other Pokémon of the forest.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: With waves of its fan—made from leaves and its own fur—Oranguru skillfully gives instructions to other Pokémon.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: Oranguru don’t get along with each other, so they’re always engaging in battles of wits to decide which one is superior.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: It normally spends its time meditating in the treetops. It throws Poké Balls and gives other Pokémon orders as it pleases.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.

Name: Oranguru
FlavorText: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so it’s best suited to veteran Trainers.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: The boss chooses 10 members of the group to go out hunting. The hunting party will evenly split the food they find with the rest of the group.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: This Pokémon battles by throwing hard berries. It won’t obey a Trainer who throws Poké Balls without skill.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: Berries are its weapons as well as the staple of its diet. The one that can throw a berry the farthest is the boss of the troop.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: They use their saliva to stick leaves to their shoulders. You can tell what troop they belong to from the position of the leaves.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.

Name: Passimian
FlavorText: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy’s presence.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: An astonishingly cowardly Pokémon, Wimpod will whir its legs at high speeds to run away if anything comes near it.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: It will pick up anything it finds on the ground. Sometimes it finds coins, so Murkrow and Meowth will go after it.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds. A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down on anything edible, no matter how rotten.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner’s meal.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: Its claws, which it can extend and retract at will, are its greatest weapons. Golisopod is sometimes accompanied by Wimpod.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: The shell covering its body is as hard as diamond. This Pokémon will do anything it takes to win.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends most of its time peacefully meditating in caves deep beneath the sea.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: It flings sand into the eyes of its prey and tries to close in on them while they’re blinded, but since Sandygast is so slow, the prey tends to escape.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: If it loses its shovel, it will stick something else—like a branch—in its head to make do until it finds another shovel.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: Sandygast mainly inhabits beaches. It takes control of anyone who puts their hand into its mouth, forcing them to make its body bigger.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: Grudges of the dead have possessed a mound of sand and become a Pokémon. Sandygast is fond of the shovel on its head.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: If you build sand mounds when you’re playing, destroy them before you go home, or they may get possessed and become Sandygast.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: It likes the shovel on its head, so Sandygast will get serious and fight any children who come to take it back.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.

Name: Sandygast
FlavorText: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this Pokémon embodies the grudges of the departed.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: From the hollows in its arms, it fires the bones of its victims, which are all dried up after being drained of their vitality.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped, it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives on beaches, but it hates water. Palossand can’t maintain its castle-like shape if it gets drenched by a heavy rain.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. It pulls its prey down into the sand by controlling the sand itself, and then it sucks out their souls.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: Once it has whipped up a sandstorm to halt its opponents in their tracks, this terrifying Pokémon snatches away their vitality.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: Each of its grains of sand has its own will. Palossand eats small Pokémon and siphons away their vital essence while they’re still alive.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.

Name: Palossand
FlavorText: Possessed people controlled by this Pokémon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: Its entire body is covered in its own slime. If you accidentally step on one, you’ll slip, and it will get mad and smack you!

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: These Pokémon line the beaches. The sticky mucous that covers their bodies can be used to soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.

Name: Type: Null
FlavorText: It was modeled after a mighty Pokémon of myth. The mask placed upon it limits its power in order to keep it under control.

Name: Type: Null
FlavorText: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.

Name: Type: Null
FlavorText: There’s danger of its going on a rampage, so its true power is sealed away beneath its control mask.

Name: Type: Null
FlavorText: A Pokémon weapon developed for a specific mission, it went berserk during an experiment, so it was cryogenically frozen.

Name: Type: Null
FlavorText: Due to the danger that this synthetic Pokémon may go on a rampage, it wears a control mask to restrain its power.

Name: Type: Null
FlavorText: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has some hidden special power.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: It has the ability to change its type based on the memory it’s holding. This is its <Type>-type form.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: Thanks to its awakened powers, it can change to the <Type> type to match the memory it has equipped.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: Its capacity to change types unleashed, it shines silver due to the energy springing forth from within.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: Having been awakened successfully, it can change its type and battle—just like a certain Pokémon depicted in legends.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: Upon awakening, its RKS System is activated. By employing specific memories, this Pokémon can adapt its type to confound its enemies.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: It destroyed its own control mask. It has become capable of changing its type by equipping special memories.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: The final factor needed to release this Pokémon’s true power was a strong bond with a Trainer it trusts.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: Through the bond it formed with its Trainer, its will was strengthened, and it was able to destroy its control mask.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: This is its form once it has awakened and evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is greatly increased.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: Although its name was Type: Null at first, the boy who evolved it into this form gave it the name by which it is now known.

Name: Silvally
FlavorText: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This Pokémon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: This is its form when its shell has fallen off. The color of its core depends on the materials that made up the food it ate.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: Places where Minior fall from the night sky are few and far between, with Alola being one of the precious few.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: If its core stays exposed, it will soon die off. It’s possible that it may survive if it’s put into a Poké Ball quickly enough.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: It eats dust in the atmosphere. The composition of the dust determines the color of its core.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: Although its outer shell is uncommonly durable, the shock of falling to the ground smashes the shell to smithereens.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokémon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokémon was born from mutated nanoparticles.

Name: Minior
FlavorText: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.

Name: Komala
FlavorText: A potent anesthetic can be made by diluting Komala’s drool. This anesthetic was used for surgeries in the past.

Name: Komala
FlavorText: Komala spends its entire life sleeping. It feeds on leaves that contain a potent poison only Komala can break down.

Name: Komala
FlavorText: It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative properties of the leaves that form its diet.

Name: Komala
FlavorText: It stays asleep from the moment it’s born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.

Name: Komala
FlavorText: The log it holds was given to it by its parents at birth. It has also been known to cling to the arm of a friendly Trainer.

Name: Komala
FlavorText: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: Its exploding shell poses a real danger but is sensitive to moisture. On rainy days, Turtonator takes silent refuge in caves.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: It lives in volcanoes and eats sulfur and other minerals. Materials from the food it eats form the basis of its explosive shell.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

Name: Togedemaru
FlavorText: When it’s in trouble, it curls up into a ball, makes its fur spikes stand on end, and then discharges electricity indiscriminately.

Name: Togedemaru
FlavorText: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

Name: Togedemaru
FlavorText: Its capacity to produce electricity is somewhat limited, so it gets charged up by letting lightning strike it!

Name: Togedemaru
FlavorText: When it’s surprised or agitated, the 14 fur spikes on its back will stand up involuntarily.

Name: Togedemaru
FlavorText: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.

Name: Togedemaru
FlavorText: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: Mimikyu was only recently identified as a Pokémon. Previously, people thought it was just a ghost wearing a cloth.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: A gust of wind revealed what hides under this Pokémon’s rag to a passing Trainer, who went home and died painfully that very night.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: Although it’s a quiet, lonely Pokémon, if you try to look at what’s under its rag, it will become agitated and resist violently.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: A lonely Pokémon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokémon.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: It has taken damage and can no longer hold the head of its cloth disguise upright. For as long as it lives, Mimikyu will never forget its attacker.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: Even as it struggles beneath the cloth to repair the broken neck of its disguise, Mimikyu keeps up its impersonation of Pikachu.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: Its disguise made from an old rag allowed it to avoid an attack, but the impact broke the neck of the disguise. Now everyone knows it’s a Mimikyu.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: There will be no forgiveness for any who reveal that it was pretending to be Pikachu. It will bring the culprit down, even at the cost of its own life.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: Sad that its true identity may be exposed, Mimikyu will mercilessly seek revenge on any opponent that breaks its neck.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: It stands in front of a mirror, trying to fix its broken neck as if its life depended on it. It has a hard time getting it right, so it’s crying inside.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: If its neck is broken or its rag torn during an attack, it works through the night to patch it.

Name: Mimikyu
FlavorText: After going to all the effort of disguising itself, its neck was broken. Whatever is inside is probably unharmed, but it’s still feeling sad.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: When sunlight reflects on the ripples created by a Bruxish grinding its teeth, the water all around sparkles brilliantly.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by this process from the protuberance on its head.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie’s spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder’s shell is no match for it.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

Name: Drampa
FlavorText: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it’s angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.

Name: Drampa
FlavorText: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

Name: Drampa
FlavorText: It appears in towns and plays with the children. Drampa will protect kids when they’re in danger, so their moms don’t have to worry.

Name: Drampa
FlavorText: If a child it has made friends with is bullied, Drampa will find the bully’s house and burn it to the ground.

Name: Drampa
FlavorText: This Pokémon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.

Name: Drampa
FlavorText: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: After lowering its anchor, it waits for its prey. It catches large Wailord and drains their life-force.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: Its chain-like green seaweed can stretch outward for hundreds of yards. For some reason, it gets along well with Skrelp.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey like Wailord.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

Name: Jangmo-o
FlavorText: Jangmo-o strikes its scales to communicate with others of its kind. Its scales are actually fur that’s become as hard as metal.

Name: Jangmo-o
FlavorText: They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together. The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

Name: Jangmo-o
FlavorText: It will never show an enemy its back in battle. Ancient warriors liked Jangmo-o for its valiant disposition and made it one of their own.

Name: Jangmo-o
FlavorText: It smacks the scales on its head against rocks or against the ground to frighten its opponents. It can also contact its friends with these noises.

Name: Jangmo-o
FlavorText: They live in mountains where no trace of humans can be detected. Jangmo-o grow little by little as they battle one another.

Name: Jangmo-o
FlavorText: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

Name: Hakamo-o
FlavorText: Before attacking its enemies, it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.

Name: Hakamo-o
FlavorText: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body are signs of its strength. It shows them off to defeated opponents.

Name: Hakamo-o
FlavorText: The scales it sheds can be molded and processed to make pots and pans. They conduct heat well, so they’re a popular item.

Name: Hakamo-o
FlavorText: It makes noise by clanging its scales together. When the rhythm has reached its peak, Hakamo-o attacks.

Name: Hakamo-o
FlavorText: It sheds and regrows its scales on a continuous basis. The scales become harder and sharper each time they’re regrown.

Name: Hakamo-o
FlavorText: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

Name: Kommo-o
FlavorText: Certain ruins have paintings of ancient warriors wearing armor made of Kommo-o scales.

Name: Kommo-o
FlavorText: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

Name: Kommo-o
FlavorText: It battles valiantly with its fists, which are armored in steel scales. Kommo-o specializes in uppercuts.

Name: Kommo-o
FlavorText: When it howls after finishing off its prey, the metallic sounds of its celebrating comrades can be heard from all around.

Name: Kommo-o
FlavorText: Its rigid scales function as offense and defense. In the past, its scales were processed and used to make weapons and other commodities.

Name: Kommo-o
FlavorText: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

Name: Tapu Koko
FlavorText: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.

Name: Tapu Koko
FlavorText: Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

Name: Tapu Koko
FlavorText: It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.

Name: Tapu Koko
FlavorText: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.

Name: Tapu Lele
FlavorText: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.

Name: Tapu Lele
FlavorText: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

Name: Tapu Lele
FlavorText: As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.

Name: Tapu Lele
FlavorText: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula’ula controls plants.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: The guardian deity of Ula’ula is a lazy Pokémon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: Although it’s called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water. People say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

Name: Cosmog
FlavorText: Cosmog is very curious but not very cautious, often placing itself in danger. If things start to look dicey, it teleports away.

Name: Cosmog
