FlavorText: This Pokémon came from another universe. Its gaseous body is so light that even a gentle breeze can blow it away.

Name: Cosmog
FlavorText: Whether or not it’s a Pokémon from this world is a mystery. When it’s in a jam, it warps away to a safe place to hide.

Name: Cosmog
FlavorText: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

Name: Cosmog
FlavorText: In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It’s said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.

Name: Cosmog
FlavorText: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.

Name: Cosmoem
FlavorText: It sucks in dust from the air at an astounding rate, frantically building up energy within its core as preparation for evolution.

Name: Cosmoem
FlavorText: The absorption of starlight fuels this Pokémon’s growth. The shell that encases it is harder than any known material.

Name: Cosmoem
FlavorText: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.

Name: Cosmoem
FlavorText: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.

Name: Cosmoem
FlavorText: There’s something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.

Name: Cosmoem
FlavorText: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.

Name: Solgaleo
FlavorText: Solgaleo was once known as the Beast That Devours the Sun. Energy in the form of light radiates boundlessly from it.

Name: Solgaleo
FlavorText: When light radiates from its body, this Pokémon could almost appear to be the sun. It will dispel any darkness and light up the world.

Name: Solgaleo
FlavorText: In writings from the distant past, it’s called by the name “the beast that devours the sun.”

Name: Solgaleo
FlavorText: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.

Name: Solgaleo
FlavorText: This Pokémon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.

Name: Solgaleo
FlavorText: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

Name: Lunala
FlavorText: It steals the light from its surroundings and then becomes the full moon, showering its own light across the night sky.

Name: Lunala
FlavorText: Known as the Beast That Calls the Moon, this Pokémon lives by taking in any and all light and converting it into its own energy.

Name: Lunala
FlavorText: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms here to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.

Name: Lunala
FlavorText: Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name “the beast that calls the moon.”

Name: Lunala
FlavorText: Said to live in another world, this Pokémon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.

Name: Lunala
FlavorText: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.

Name: Nihilego
FlavorText: It appeared in this world from an Ultra Wormhole. Nihilego appears to be a parasite that lives by feeding on people and Pokémon.

Name: Nihilego
FlavorText: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

Name: Nihilego
FlavorText: One of the Ultra Beasts. It’s unclear whether or not this Pokémon is sentient, but sometimes it can be observed behaving like a young girl.

Name: Nihilego
FlavorText: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.

Name: Buzzwole
FlavorText: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.

Name: Buzzwole
FlavorText: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Buzzwole
FlavorText: A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast. Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a single punch.

Name: Buzzwole
FlavorText: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

Name: Pheromosa
FlavorText: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Pheromosa
FlavorText: A life-form that lives in another world, its body is thin and supple, but it also possesses great power.

Name: Pheromosa
FlavorText: One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.

Name: Pheromosa
FlavorText: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.

Name: Xurkitree
FlavorText: They’ve been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.

Name: Xurkitree
FlavorText: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Xurkitree
FlavorText: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.

Name: Xurkitree
FlavorText: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.

Name: Celesteela
FlavorText: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Celesteela
FlavorText: One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.

Name: Celesteela
FlavorText: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.

Name: Celesteela
FlavorText: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.

Name: Kartana
FlavorText: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Kartana
FlavorText: This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

Name: Kartana
FlavorText: One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.

Name: Kartana
FlavorText: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

Name: Guzzlord
FlavorText: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry—it is certainly always devouring something.

Name: Guzzlord
FlavorText: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Guzzlord
FlavorText: A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.

Name: Guzzlord
FlavorText: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It’s one of the Ultra Beasts.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: The light pouring out from all over its body affects living things and nature, impacting them in various ways.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: This is its form when it has absorbed overwhelming light energy. It fires laser beams from all over its body.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: When Necrozma latches on to Lunala, it becomes vicious, seeing enemies everywhere it looks. It will burn the world with lasers.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: Necrozma has subjugated Lunala entirely, forcing the unfortunate Pokémon to emit its light energy for Necrozma to consume.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: This is its form while it’s devouring the light of Lunala. It grasps foes in its giant claws and rips them apart with brute force.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: Lunala no longer has a will of its own. Now under the control of Necrozma, it continuously expels all of its energy.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: Necrozma has attached itself to Solgaleo. It siphons away its host’s limitless energy, exploiting that energy to fuel a rampage.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: When it dominates Solgaleo, it takes on this form. It’s a vicious Pokémon, mangling prey with its many claws—including those on its back.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: This is Necrozma’s form while it’s absorbing the power of Solgaleo, making it extremely ferocious and impossible to control.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: This is its form while it is devouring the light of Solgaleo. It pounces on foes and then slashes them with the claws on its four limbs and back.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: It needs light to survive, and it goes on a rampage seeking it out. Its laser beams will cut anything to pieces.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn’t devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It’s apparently from another world.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.

Name: Necrozma
FlavorText: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form, apparently asleep underground, is thought to have come from another world in ancient times.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: It functions thanks to its artificial soul. The vivid decoration is proof that it was presented as a gift to royalty.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: This is its form from almost 500 years ago. Its body is nothing more than a container—its artificial heart is the actual life-form.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: This gorgeous Magearna looks as it did at the time of its invention. Its luxurious decoration pleased the king’s daughter.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: This beautiful form reflects Magearna’s appearance when first presented to a king’s daughter 500 years ago.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.

Name: Magearna
FlavorText: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

Name: Marshadow
FlavorText: This Pokémon can conceal itself in any shadow, so it went undiscovered for a long time.

Name: Marshadow
FlavorText: By slipping into the shadow of a martial arts master and copying their movements, this Pokémon learned the ultimate techniques.

Name: Marshadow
FlavorText: It sinks into the shadows of people and Pokémon, where it can understand their feelings and copy their capabilities.

Name: Marshadow
FlavorText: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.

Name: Marshadow
FlavorText: It lurks in the shadows of others, copying their movements and powers. This Pokémon is craven and cowering.

Name: Marshadow
FlavorText: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.

Name: Poipole
FlavorText: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.

Name: Poipole
FlavorText: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

Name: Naganadel
FlavorText: One kind of Ultra Beast, it fires a glowing, venomous liquid from its needles. This liquid is also immensely adhesive.

Name: Naganadel
FlavorText: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

Name: Stakataka
FlavorText: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute’s true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.

Name: Stakataka
FlavorText: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

Name: Blacephalon
FlavorText: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents’ surprise to rob them of their vitality.

Name: Blacephalon
FlavorText: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

Name: Zeraora
FlavorText: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.

Name: Zeraora
FlavorText: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.

Name: Zeraora
FlavorText: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.

Name: Zeraora
FlavorText: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

Name: Meltan
FlavorText: They live as a group, but when the time comes, one strong Meltan will absorb all the others and evolve.

Name: Meltan
FlavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

Name: Meltan
FlavorText: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

Name: Melmetal
FlavorText: It can send electric beams streaking out from the hole in its belly. The beams’ tremendous energy can vaporize an opponent in one shot.

Name: Melmetal
FlavorText: In a distant land, there are legends about a cyclopean giant. In fact, the giant was a Melmetal that was flooded with Gigantamax energy.

Name: Melmetal
FlavorText: Centrifugal force is behind the punches of Melmetal’s heavy hex-nut arms. Melmetal is said to deliver the strongest punches of all Pokémon.

Name: Melmetal
FlavorText: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

Name: Melmetal
FlavorText: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

Name: Grookey
FlavorText: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.

Name: Grookey
FlavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

Name: Thwackey
FlavorText: When it’s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won’t even notice that it’s already knocked out its opponent.

Name: Thwackey
FlavorText: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: Rillaboom has become one with its forest of drums and continues to lay down beats that shake all of Galar.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy has caused Rillaboom’s stump to grow into a drum set that resembles a forest.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

Name: Scorbunny
FlavorText: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it’s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

Name: Scorbunny
FlavorText: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon’s body. Once that happens, it’s ready to fight at full power.

Name: Raboot
FlavorText: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

Name: Raboot
FlavorText: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy can sometimes cause the diameter of this Pokémon’s fireball to exceed 300 feet.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: Infused with Cinderace’s fighting spirit, the gigantic Pyro Ball never misses its targets and completely roasts opponents.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

Name: Sobble
FlavorText: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

Name: Sobble
FlavorText: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won’t be able to resist weeping.

Name: Drizzile
FlavorText: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

Name: Drizzile
FlavorText: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: It has excellent sniping skills. Shooting a berry rolling along over nine miles away is a piece of cake for this Pokémon.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: Gigantamax Inteleon’s Water Gun move fires at Mach 7. As the Pokémon takes aim, it uses the crest on its head to gauge wind and temperature.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

Name: Skwovet
FlavorText: No matter how much it stuffs its belly with food, it is always anxious about getting hungry again. So, it stashes berries in its cheeks and tail.

Name: Skwovet
FlavorText: It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no berries to be found, Skwovet will stuff pebbles into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.

Name: Skwovet
FlavorText: It eats berries nonstop—a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It’ll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.

Name: Skwovet
FlavorText: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

Name: Greedent
FlavorText: This Pokémon makes off with heaps of fallen berries by wrapping them in its tail, which is roughly twice the length of its body.

Name: Greedent
FlavorText: If it spots a berry tree, it will immediately go to gather berries without a sideways glance—even if it’s in the middle of a battle.

Name: Greedent
FlavorText: Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.

Name: Greedent
FlavorText: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn’t notice the loss.

Name: Rookidee
FlavorText: The females are fussier than the males. If another creature dirties a female Rookidee’s wings, it’ll peck the offender relentlessly in a burning rage.

Name: Rookidee
FlavorText: This Pokémon is brave and reckless. The white markings around a Rookidee’s eyes intimidate fainthearted Pokémon.

Name: Rookidee
FlavorText: Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

Name: Rookidee
FlavorText: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

Name: Corvisquire
FlavorText: This intelligent Pokémon will quickly learn how to use any tool it can hold in its beak or its talons.

Name: Corvisquire
FlavorText: It’s said that the reason behind Corvisquire’s high level of intelligence is the large size of its brain relative to those of other bird Pokémon.

Name: Corvisquire
FlavorText: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent’s strength.

Name: Corvisquire
FlavorText: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

Name: Corviknight
FlavorText: The eight feathers on its back are called blade birds, and they can launch off its body to attack foes independently.

Name: Corviknight
FlavorText: Imbued with Gigantamax energy, its wings can whip up winds more forceful than any a hurricane could muster. The gusts blow everything away.

Name: Corviknight
FlavorText: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.

Name: Corviknight
FlavorText: Corviknight can’t serve as a taxi service in Paldea because the Pokémon’s natural predators will attack it while it flies, endangering the customer.

Name: Corviknight
FlavorText: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region’s airborne taxi service.

Name: Corviknight
FlavorText: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

Name: Blipbug
FlavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

Name: Blipbug
FlavorText: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.

Name: Dottler
FlavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

Name: Dottler
FlavorText: It barely moves, but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

Name: Orbeetle
FlavorText: If it were to utilize every last bit of its power, it could control the minds of every living being in its vicinity.

Name: Orbeetle
FlavorText: Its brain has grown to a gargantuan size, as has the rest of its body. This Pokémon’s intellect and psychic abilities are overpowering.

Name: Orbeetle
FlavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.

Name: Orbeetle
FlavorText: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

Name: Nickit
FlavorText: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.

Name: Nickit
FlavorText: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

Name: Thievul
FlavorText: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.

Name: Thievul
FlavorText: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

Name: Gossifleur
FlavorText: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

Name: Gossifleur
FlavorText: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

Name: Eldegoss
FlavorText: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.

Name: Eldegoss
FlavorText: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

Name: Wooloo
FlavorText: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

Name: Wooloo
FlavorText: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

Name: Dubwool
FlavorText: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

Name: Dubwool
FlavorText: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: Its large front tooth is still growing in. When the tooth itches, this Pokémon will bite another Chewtle’s horn, and the two Pokémon will tussle.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: In the Galar region, there’s a tale about this Pokémon chewing up a mountain and using the rubble to stop a flood.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: It responded to Gigantamax energy by becoming bipedal. First it comes crashing down on foes, and then it finishes them off with its massive jaws.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: Its massive, jagged teeth can crush a boulder in a single bite. This Pokémon has an extremely vicious disposition.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

Name: Yamper
FlavorText: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

Name: Yamper
FlavorText: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

Name: Boltund
FlavorText: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

Name: Boltund
FlavorText: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

Name: Rolycoly
FlavorText: Chunks of the surface of this Pokémon’s body that have grown old and flaked off have long been used for fuel as an alternative to coal.

Name: Rolycoly
FlavorText: On sunny days, Rolycoly will come out onto grassy plains and roll around. Then it will eat the grass that gets tangled in its wheel-like leg.

Name: Rolycoly
FlavorText: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

Name: Rolycoly
FlavorText: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: Due to the coal tar created inside it, the heap of coal on Carkol’s back never falls apart, even when the Pokémon rolls around at high speeds.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: When Galar was hit by a harsh cold wave, this Pokémon served as a giant heating stove and saved many lives.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: Its body is a colossal stove. With Gigantamax energy stoking the fire, this Pokémon’s flame burns hotter than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: It’s gentle usually but fearsome when angered. With a body that burns at over 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit, it crushes foes and turns them to ash.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: To intimidate its opponents, Coalossal will vigorously shake its body, scattering coal from its smoldering back.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: While it’s engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: It grows by eating the flesh of an apple. Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen the apple’s skin and prevent it from rotting.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: As soon as it’s born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it’s just an apple and nothing more.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: If it stretches its neck, the strong aroma of its nectar pours out. The scent is so sickeningly sweet that one whiff makes other Pokémon faint.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: Under the influence of Gigantamax energy, it produces much more sweet nectar, and its shape has changed to resemble a giant apple.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It uses its own body fluid to repair its apple. Strong Flapple that have won many battles have apples that are clay colored all over.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It flutters around while seeking an opening in the opponent’s guard, then attacks by spitting acidic liquid strong enough to melt metal.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: Due to Gigantamax energy, this Pokémon’s nectar has thickened. The increased viscosity lets the nectar absorb more damage than before.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: It blasts its opponents with massive amounts of sweet, sticky nectar, drowning them under the deluge.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: When some Lechonk come along to lick the sweet nectar on Appletun’s back, Appletun will spew sticky nectar at them to drive them away.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: It feeds mainly on sweet apples. It will also eat small bug Pokémon that are attracted by its sweet nectar.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

Name: Silicobra
FlavorText: Silicobra’s large nostrils are specialized for spraying sand, so this Pokémon is not very good at telling apart different smells.

Name: Silicobra
FlavorText: Silicobra’s neck pouch, which can inflate and deflate like a balloon, gets more elastic each time Silicobra sheds its skin.

Name: Silicobra
FlavorText: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

Name: Silicobra
FlavorText: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

Name: Sandaconda
FlavorText: Sand swirls around its body with such speed and power that it could pulverize a skyscraper.

Name: Sandaconda
FlavorText: Its sand pouch has grown to tremendous proportions. More than 1,000,000 tons of sand now swirl around its body.

Name: Sandaconda
FlavorText: The sand it spews contains sharp, pointy gravel, which is actually just sand that Sandaconda’s saliva has hardened into irregular shapes.

Name: Sandaconda
FlavorText: It will expand its body as much as it can and then contract itself, blasting out sand with enough force to wash away a dump truck.

Name: Sandaconda
FlavorText: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

Name: Sandaconda
FlavorText: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: The slightest shock is sometimes enough to get this Pokémon to spit out the Arrokuda lodged in its throat.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: Cramorant’s gluttony led it to try to swallow an Arrokuda whole, which in turn led to Cramorant getting an Arrokuda stuck in its throat.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: The half-swallowed Pikachu is so startled that it isn’t struggling yet, but it’s still looking for a chance to strike back.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: This Cramorant has accidentally gotten a Pikachu lodged in its gullet. Cramorant is choking a little, but it isn’t really bothered.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: It takes down prey by charging into them with its hard, pointed jaw. But Arrokuda’s eyesight is poor, so this tactic has a low success rate.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: Arrokuda can swim quickly only in a straight line. The ones that become sluggish from overeating are the first to be targeted by flocks of Wattrel.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: After it’s eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That’s when Cramorant swallows it up.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It’s very proud of that jaw.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: It swims at speeds of over 100 knots and battles fiercely with pods of Finizen over prey.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: It spins its tail fins to leap from the water, then viciously bites down on Wingull flying close to the water’s surface.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a jaw that’s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda’s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

Name: Toxel
FlavorText: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokémon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.

Name: Toxel
FlavorText: It has no problem drinking dirty water. An organ inside Toxel’s body filters such water into a poisonous liquid that is harmless to Toxel.

Name: Toxel
FlavorText: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

Name: Toxel
FlavorText: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: Out of control after its own poison penetrated its brain, it tears across the land in a rampage, contaminating the earth with toxic sweat.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: Its excessive electric energy is its weapon. This Pokémon can build up more electricity than any thundercloud.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: As it gulps down stagnant water and generates electricity in its body, a sound like a rhythm played by a bass guitar reverberates all around.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: Many youths admire the way this Pokémon listlessly picks fights and keeps its cool no matter what opponent it faces.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: It has an electrical organ on its chest. While generating electricity, it fills its surroundings with what sounds like the strumming of a bass guitar.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: Capable of generating 15,000 volts of electricity, this Pokémon looks down on all that would challenge it.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: The jolts of electricity it launches by violently strumming the protrusions on its chest easily exceed 15,000 volts.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: As it scatters toxic sweat and emits electricity, a melody that sounds like it came from a guitar reverberates through the surrounding area.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

Name: Toxtricity
FlavorText: When this Pokémon sounds as if it’s strumming a guitar, it’s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

Name: Sizzlipede
FlavorText: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

Name: Sizzlipede
FlavorText: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: The heat that comes off a Gigantamax Centiskorch may destabilize air currents. Sometimes it can even cause storms.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy has evoked a rise in its body temperature, now reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Its heat waves incinerate its enemies.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

Name: Clobbopus
FlavorText: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.

Name: Clobbopus
FlavorText: It’s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

Name: Grapploct
FlavorText: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

Name: Grapploct
FlavorText: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: Sinistea gets into your body when you drink it, and then it steals your vitality from within. It also tastes awful.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: The soul of someone who died alone possessed some leftover tea. This Pokémon appears in hotels and houses.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: This Sinistea lives in an antique teacup. As valuable as this Pokémon is, its awful taste remains unchanged.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: Some fanatics will go to great pains to prepare the perfect tea and teacup, eagerly waiting for a Sinistea to come and possess their selections.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: It absorbs the life-force of those who drink it. It waits patiently, but opportunities are fleeting— it tastes so bad that it gets spat out immediately.

Name: Sinistea
FlavorText: The swirl pattern in this Pokémon’s body is its weakness. If it gets stirred, the swirl loses its shape, and Sinistea gets dizzy.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: These Pokémon multiply by creeping into teapots and pouring themselves into leftover tea.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: The tea that composes Polteageist’s body has a distinct and enjoyable flavor. Drinking too much, however, can be fatal.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokémon to come along and pour itself into it, turning the tea into a new Polteageist.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: Though risky to drink, this Pokémon’s tea tastes delicious. Gourmets who have no fear of danger drink Polteageist tea day after day.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: Apparently a Polteageist’s disposition is affected by the type of tea the Pokémon came from. What teapot it inhabits makes no difference.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: When angered, it launches tea from its body at the offender’s mouth. The tea causes strong chills if swallowed.

Name: Polteageist
FlavorText: Trainers Polteageist trusts will be allowed to experience its distinctive flavor and aroma firsthand by sampling just a tiny bit of its tea.

Name: Hatenna
FlavorText: It senses the feelings of other living creatures. Be careful not to expose it to strong emotions for too long, or it will end up exhausted.

Name: Hatenna
FlavorText: Because the emotions of others constantly flow into its head, this Pokémon prefers environments where no other creatures live.

Name: Hatenna
FlavorText: If this Pokémon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.

Name: Hatenna
FlavorText: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures’ emotions. If you don’t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

Name: Hattrem
FlavorText: The moment this Pokémon finds someone who’s emitting strong emotions, it will pummel them senseless with its braids to silence them.

Name: Hattrem
FlavorText: To this Pokémon, strong emotions apparently feel like incredibly loud noises—even if the emotions are happy ones.

Name: Hattrem
FlavorText: Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.

Name: Hattrem
FlavorText: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

Name: Hatterene
FlavorText: Beams like lightning shoot down from its tentacles. It’s known to some as the Raging Goddess.

Name: Hatterene
FlavorText: This Pokémon can read the emotions of creatures over 30 miles away. The minute it senses hostility, it goes on the attack.

Name: Hatterene
FlavorText: Beware of forests that show no signs of living creatures within. You may have wandered into Hatterene’s territory.

Name: Hatterene
FlavorText: Hatterene knocks out those that intrude in its home forest by blasting them with a beam, then slashing with claws enhanced by psychic power.

Name: Hatterene
FlavorText: If you’re too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.

Name: Hatterene
FlavorText: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

Name: Impidimp
FlavorText: They live in groups, pestering and playing pranks on each other to polish their troublemaking skills.

Name: Impidimp
FlavorText: The reason this Pokémon causes trouble for those it feels close to is because Impidimp itself gets irritable if it can’t absorb negative emotions.

Name: Impidimp
FlavorText: It sneaks into people’s homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.

Name: Impidimp
FlavorText: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

Name: Morgrem
FlavorText: This Pokémon absorbs negative emotions and turns them into energy. It’s popular with people who tend to think gloomy thoughts.

Name: Morgrem
FlavorText: Morgrem prefers dirty tactics, like ambushing, because it doesn’t have confidence in its brawn.

Name: Morgrem
FlavorText: With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.

Name: Morgrem
FlavorText: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it’s trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

Name: Grimmsnarl
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy has caused more hair to sprout all over its body. With the added strength, it can jump over the world’s tallest building.

Name: Grimmsnarl
FlavorText: By transforming its leg hair, this Pokémon delivers power-packed drill kicks that can bore huge holes in Galar’s terrain.

Name: Grimmsnarl
FlavorText: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn’t given up on its petty misdeeds and pranks.

Name: Grimmsnarl
FlavorText: This Pokémon has complete control over its hair. Grimmsnarl normally keeps its hair wrapped around its body to support its muscles.

Name: Grimmsnarl
FlavorText: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.

Name: Grimmsnarl
FlavorText: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

Name: Obstagoon
FlavorText: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

Name: Obstagoon
FlavorText: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

Name: Perrserker
FlavorText: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.

Name: Perrserker
FlavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

Name: Cursola
FlavorText: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.

Name: Cursola
FlavorText: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon’s core spirit.

Name: Sirfetch'd
FlavorText: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.

Name: Sirfetch'd
FlavorText: Only Farfetch’d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon’s leek withers, it will retire from combat.

Name: Mr. Rime
FlavorText: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

Name: Mr. Rime
FlavorText: It’s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

Name: Runerigus
FlavorText: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you’ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.

Name: Runerigus
FlavorText: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

Name: Milcery
FlavorText: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.

Name: Milcery
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a sweet and tart flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on a sweet and tart flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a mixed flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on a mixed flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a complex flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on a complex flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a refreshing flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on a refreshing flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a salty flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on a salty flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream an aromatic flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on an aromatic flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a sour flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on a sour flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it’s decorated with cream.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: It launches swarms of missiles, each made of cream and loaded with 100,000 kilocalories. Get hit by one of these, and your head will swim.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: Cream pours endlessly from this Pokémon’s body. The cream stiffens when compressed by an impact. A harder impact results in harder cream.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The cells that compose its cream fluctuated suddenly during evolution, giving the cream a bitter flavor.

Name: Alcremie
FlavorText: The moment it evolved, it took on a bitter flavor. This is because of the way its cells spontaneously shifted during evolution.

Name: Falinks
FlavorText: The leader, known as the brass, uses its extendible horn to issue orders to the others when it’s time to change formation.

Name: Falinks
FlavorText: The brass, which is the one that stands at the front and issues orders, is the strongest and smartest of the six.

Name: Falinks
FlavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

Name: Falinks
FlavorText: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass’s orders are absolute.

Name: Pincurchin
FlavorText: This Pokémon is so timid that even brushing against seaweed will make it discharge electricity in surprise. Its lips do not conduct electricity.

Name: Pincurchin
FlavorText: This Pokémon generates electricity when it digests food. It uses its five hard teeth to scrape seaweed off surfaces and eat it.

Name: Pincurchin
FlavorText: It stores electricity in each spine. Even if one gets broken off, it still continues to emit electricity for at least three hours.

Name: Pincurchin
FlavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

Name: Snom
FlavorText: Within its internal organs, Snom amplifies the frigid air it gets from eating snow and then uses this amplified air to create icicle-like spikes.

Name: Snom
FlavorText: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow, so it will eat its way up a mountain, aiming for the peak.

Name: Snom
FlavorText: It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.

Name: Snom
FlavorText: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

Name: Frosmoth
FlavorText: It causes blizzards as it flies around with its huge, chill-emanating wings. Clean meltwater is its favorite thing to drink.

Name: Frosmoth
FlavorText: Frosmoth senses air currents with its antennae. It sends its scales drifting on frigid air, making them fall like snow.

Name: Frosmoth
FlavorText: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.

Name: Frosmoth
FlavorText: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Stonjourner
FlavorText: This Pokémon spends its life gazing at the setting sun. It strides leisurely across grassy plains on legs of rock that weigh over 400 pounds each.

Name: Stonjourner
FlavorText: The elemental composition of the rocks that form its body were found to match the bedrock of a land far away from this Pokémon’s habitat.

Name: Stonjourner
FlavorText: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.

Name: Stonjourner
FlavorText: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun’s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: Contrary to its looks, Eiscue is a poor swimmer. It creates ice balls at the tip of its single hair to lure prey in and fish them up.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: The ice that was covering this Eiscue’s face has shattered. Eiscue emits cold air from the tip of its hair to protect its head, which is sensitive to heat.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: The hair on its head connects to the surface of its brain. When this Pokémon has something on its mind, its hair chills the air around it.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: The ice covering this Pokémon’s face has shattered, revealing a slightly worried expression that many people are enamored with.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: If you lick the ice covering its face, you’ll find it has a faintly salty taste. This species rode here on ocean currents from a cold, faraway land.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: On hot days, these Pokémon press their ice cube heads together and pass the time cooling each other down.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

Name: Eiscue
FlavorText: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: In search of happy feelings—such as joy and gratitude—Indeedee bustles around, taking diligent care of people and other Pokémon.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: It dislikes conflict. If a fight occurs in its territory, it uses psychic power to throw things at the combatants in an effort to drive them away.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: They diligently serve people and Pokémon so they can gather feelings of gratitude. The females are particularly good at babysitting.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: These intelligent Pokémon touch horns with each other to share information between them.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: This Pokémon never leaves its Trainer’s side. It predicts their actions with its psychic power and takes care of their day-to-day needs.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: This Pokémon picks up on the positive emotions of other creatures via its horns and uses those emotions to fuel itself.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

Name: Indeedee
FlavorText: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.

Name: Morpeko
FlavorText: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.

Name: Morpeko
FlavorText: Intense hunger drives it to extremes of violence, and the electricity in its cheek sacs has converted into a Dark-type energy.

Name: Morpeko
FlavorText: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

Name: Morpeko
FlavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It’s also generating electricity.

Name: Cufant
FlavorText: Cufant can lift loads weighing five tons. In the mornings, it heads into caves with its herd, in search of the ore on which these Pokémon feed.

Name: Cufant
FlavorText: Using the pointy tip of its trunk, it carves off chunks of hard rocks to eat. It is very docile and helps people with physical labor.

Name: Cufant
FlavorText: If a job requires serious strength, this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.

Name: Cufant
FlavorText: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It’s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

Name: Copperajah
FlavorText: After this Pokémon has Gigantamaxed, its massive nose can utterly demolish large structures with a single smashing blow.

Name: Copperajah
FlavorText: So much power is packed within its trunk that if it were to unleash that power, the resulting blast could level mountains and change the landscape.

Name: Copperajah
FlavorText: Copperajah are prideful, cantankerous Pokémon. Specimens with vibrant green skin command the respect of others of their kind.

Name: Copperajah
FlavorText: This Pokémon was brought to Paldea long ago by people from a faraway land. It’s so strong that it can easily pull an airplane.

Name: Copperajah
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

Name: Copperajah
FlavorText: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

Name: Dracozolt
FlavorText: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.

Name: Dracozolt
FlavorText: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

Name: Arctozolt
FlavorText: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.

Name: Arctozolt
FlavorText: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

Name: Dracovish
FlavorText: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.

Name: Dracovish
FlavorText: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

Name: Arctovish
FlavorText: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

Name: Arctovish
FlavorText: Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

Name: Duraludon
FlavorText: The hardness of its cells is exceptional, even among Steel types. It also has a body structure that’s resistant to earthquakes.

Name: Duraludon
FlavorText: It’s grown to resemble a skyscraper. Parts of its towering body glow due to a profusion of energy.

Name: Duraludon
FlavorText: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

Name: Duraludon
FlavorText: Its body resembles polished metal, and it’s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

Name: Dreepy
FlavorText: It has a habit of biting at Clauncher even though it doesn’t feed on them. This is said to be vestigial behavior from when Dreepy was alive.

Name: Dreepy
FlavorText: In the evening, groups of Dreepy will fly at high speeds over the ocean and poke at Pokémon in the water for fun.

Name: Dreepy
FlavorText: If this weak Pokémon is by itself, a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it train, it can evolve and become much stronger.

Name: Dreepy
FlavorText: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

Name: Drakloak
FlavorText: This Pokémon stores up energy in its lungs, then shoots it out. It takes care of Dreepy and battles alongside them until they’re all grown up.

Name: Drakloak
FlavorText: This Pokémon flies around at over 120 miles per hour. If a Drakloak is defeated in a battle, its Dreepy will wander off without a second thought.

Name: Drakloak
FlavorText: Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for, it gets so uneasy it’ll try to substitute any Pokémon it finds for the missing Dreepy.

Name: Drakloak
FlavorText: It’s capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

Name: Dragapult
FlavorText: The fastest Dragapult of the group is always surrounded by Dreepy that want to fly at sonic speed.

Name: Dragapult
FlavorText: Dragapult can make its whole body transparent by clearing its mind and focusing. Even the Dreepy in Dragapult’s horns become invisible.

Name: Dragapult
FlavorText: Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult’s horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.

Name: Dragapult
FlavorText: When it isn’t battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

Name: Zacian
FlavorText: Able to cut down anything with a single strike, it became known as the Fairy King’s Sword, and it inspired awe in friend and foe alike.

Name: Zacian
FlavorText: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.

Name: Zacian
FlavorText: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

Name: Zacian
FlavorText: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

Name: Zamazenta
FlavorText: Now that it’s equipped with its shield, it can shrug off impressive blows, including the attacks of Dynamax Pokémon.

Name: Zamazenta
FlavorText: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master’s Shield. It was feared and respected by all.

Name: Zamazenta
FlavorText: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.

Name: Zamazenta
FlavorText: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

Name: Eternatus
FlavorText: Infinite amounts of energy pour from this Pokémon’s enlarged core, warping the surrounding space-time.

Name: Eternatus
FlavorText: As a result of Rose’s meddling, Eternatus absorbed all the energy in the Galar region. It’s now in a state of power overload.

Name: Eternatus
FlavorText: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

Name: Eternatus
FlavorText: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

Name: Kubfu
FlavorText: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.

Name: Kubfu
FlavorText: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in defeating foes by raining many blows down on them. Its strikes are nonstop, flowing like a river.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: It’s believed that this Pokémon modeled its fighting style on the flow of a river—sometimes rapid, sometimes calm.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: All it takes is a glare from this Pokémon to take the lives of those with evil in their hearts—or so they say.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: As it waits for the right moment to unleash its Gigantamax power, this Pokémon maintains a perfect one-legged stance. It won’t even twitch.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: The energy released by this Pokémon’s fists forms shock waves that can blow away Dynamax Pokémon in just one hit.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: People call it the embodiment of rage. It’s said that this Pokémon’s terrifying expression and shout will rid the world of malevolence.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: This Zarude’s special strength stems from its love and care for an orphaned human child that the Pokémon has raised since the child’s infancy.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: This Zarude left its pack to raise a human child. The cloth Zarude would wrap the child with has a comforting scent that calmed the child’s crying.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: Once the vines on Zarude’s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It’s incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

Name: Regieleki
FlavorText: Its entire body is made up of a single organ that generates electrical energy. Regieleki is capable of creating all Galar’s electricity.

Name: Regieleki
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the Pokémon’s latent power.

Name: Regidrago
FlavorText: Its body is composed of crystallized dragon energy. Regidrago is said to have the powers of every dragon Pokémon.

Name: Regidrago
FlavorText: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.

Name: Glastrier
FlavorText: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength, and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.

Name: Glastrier
FlavorText: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It’s also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

Name: Spectrier
FlavorText: As it dashes through the night, Spectrier absorbs the life-force of sleeping creatures. It craves silence and solitude.

Name: Spectrier
FlavorText: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn’t use its sense of sight. Spectrier’s kicks are said to separate soul from body.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: Legend says that by using its power to see all events from past to future, this Pokémon saved the creatures of a forest from a meteorite strike.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: It’s said that Calyrex and a Pokémon that had bonded with it ran all across the Galar region to bring green to the wastelands.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: It’s said that this Pokémon once moved a large forest—and all the Pokémon living there—to a new location overnight.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: According to lore, this Pokémon showed no mercy to those who got in its way, yet it would heal its opponents’ wounds after battle.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

Name: Wyrdeer
FlavorText: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

Name: Kleavor
FlavorText: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one’s only recourse is to flee.

Name: Ursaluna
FlavorText: I believe it was Hisui’s swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

Name: Basculegion
FlavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui’s rivers is Basculegion’s equal.

Name: Sneasler
FlavorText: Because of Sneasler’s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.

Name: Overqwil
FlavorText: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname “sea fiend.” It slurps up poison to nourish itself.

Name: Enamorus
FlavorText: A different guise from its feminine humanoid form. From the clouds, it descends upon those who treat any form of life with disrespect and metes out wrathful, ruthless punishment.

Name: Enamorus
FlavorText: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon’s love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

Name: Sprigatito
FlavorText: The sweet scent its body gives off mesmerizes those around it. The scent grows stronger when this Pokémon is in the sun.

Name: Sprigatito
FlavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

Name: Floragato
FlavorText: The hardness of Floragato’s fur depends on the Pokémon’s mood. When Floragato is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and needle sharp.

Name: Floragato
FlavorText: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

Name: Meowscarada
FlavorText: With skillful misdirection, it rigs foes with pollen-packed flower bombs. Meowscarada sets off the bombs before its foes realize what’s going on.

Name: Meowscarada
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

Name: Fuecoco
FlavorText: Its flame sac is small, so energy is always leaking out. This energy is released from the dent atop Fuecoco’s head and flickers to and fro.

Name: Fuecoco
FlavorText: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

Name: Crocalor
FlavorText: The valve in Crocalor’s flame sac is closely connected to its vocal cords. This Pokémon utters a guttural cry as it spews flames every which way.

Name: Crocalor
FlavorText: The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon’s head.

Name: Skeledirge
FlavorText: Skeledirge’s gentle singing soothes the souls of all that hear it. It burns its enemies to a crisp with flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Skeledirge
FlavorText: The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge’s head gained a soul.

Name: Quaxly
FlavorText: Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.

Name: Quaxly
FlavorText: This Pokémon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.

Name: Quaxwell
FlavorText: The hardworking Quaxwell observes people and Pokémon from various regions and incorporates their movements into its own dance routines.

Name: Quaxwell
FlavorText: These Pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.

Name: Quaquaval
FlavorText: Dancing in ways that evoke far-away places, this Pokémon mesmerizes all that see it. Flourishes of its decorative water feathers slice into its foes.

Name: Quaquaval
FlavorText: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.

Name: Lechonk
FlavorText: This Pokémon spurns all but the finest of foods. Its body gives off an herblike scent that bug Pokémon detest.

Name: Lechonk
FlavorText: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging.

Name: Oinkologne
FlavorText: This is a meticulous Pokémon that likes to keep things tidy. It shrouds itself in a floral aroma that soothes the Pokémon around it.

Name: Oinkologne
FlavorText: This Pokémon sends a flowerlike scent wafting about. Well-developed muscles in its legs allow it to leap more than 16 feet with no trouble at all.

Name: Oinkologne
FlavorText: It entrances female Pokémon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.

Name: Oinkologne
FlavorText: Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.

Name: Tarountula
FlavorText: The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the thread’s strength is the topic of ongoing research.

Name: Tarountula
FlavorText: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon’s natural enemy.

Name: Spidops
FlavorText: Spidops covers its territory in tough, sticky threads to set up traps for intruders.

Name: Spidops
FlavorText: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

Name: Nymble
FlavorText: It’s highly skilled at a fighting style in which it uses its jumping capabilities to dodge incoming attacks while also dealing damage to opponents.

Name: Nymble
FlavorText: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

Name: Lokix
FlavorText: It uses its normally folded third set of legs when in Showdown Mode. This places a huge burden on its body, so it can’t stay in this mode for long.

Name: Lokix
FlavorText: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.

Name: Pawmi
FlavorText: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.

Name: Pawmi
FlavorText: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

Name: Pawmo
FlavorText: Pawmo uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.

Name: Pawmo
FlavorText: When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

Name: Pawmot
FlavorText: Pawmot’s fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.

Name: Pawmot
FlavorText: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

Name: Tandemaus
FlavorText: The pair sticks together no matter what. They split any food they find exactly in half and then eat it together.

Name: Tandemaus
FlavorText: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.

Name: Maushold
FlavorText: The little one just appeared one day. They all live together like a family, but the relationship between the three is still unclear.

Name: Maushold
FlavorText: They build huge nests with many rooms that are used for different purposes, such as eating and sleeping.

Name: Maushold
FlavorText: The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.

Name: Maushold
FlavorText: The two little ones just appeared one day. The group might be a family of related Pokémon, but nobody knows for sure.

Name: Fidough
FlavorText: The yeast in Fidough’s breath is useful for cooking, so this Pokémon has been protected by people since long ago.

Name: Fidough
FlavorText: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough’s breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon’s vicinity.

Name: Dachsbun
FlavorText: The surface of this Pokémon’s skin hardens when exposed to intense heat, and its body has an appetizing aroma.

Name: Dachsbun
FlavorText: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon’s body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.

Name: Smoliv
FlavorText: This Pokémon converts nutrients into oil, which it stores in the fruit on its head. It can easily go a whole week without eating or drinking.

Name: Smoliv
FlavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

Name: Dolliv
FlavorText: It basks in the sun to its heart’s content until the fruits on its head ripen. After that, Dolliv departs from human settlements and goes on a journey.

Name: Dolliv
FlavorText: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

Name: Arboliva
FlavorText: This Pokémon drives back enemies by launching its rich, aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder.

Name: Arboliva
FlavorText: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.

Name: Squawkabilly
FlavorText: Though these Squawkabilly are the fewest in number, they have no trouble living in towns since they blend in with the white buildings.

Name: Squawkabilly
FlavorText: This Pokémon dislikes being alone. It has a strong sense of community and survives by cooperating with allies.

Name: Squawkabilly
FlavorText: The yellow Squawkabilly are especially fierce. They’ve even been known to drive other bird Pokémon out of town.

Name: Squawkabilly
FlavorText: These Squawkabilly are hotheaded, and their fighting style is vicious. They’ll leap within reach of their foes to engage in close combat.

Name: Squawkabilly
FlavorText: Blue-feathered Squawkabilly view their green-feathered counterparts as rivals, since the latter make up the largest, most powerful groups.

Name: Squawkabilly
FlavorText: The largest of their flocks can contain more than 50 individuals. They fly around towns and forests, searching for food and making a racket.

Name: Squawkabilly
FlavorText: Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When they’re out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.

Name: Squawkabilly
