FlavorText: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

Name: Nacli
FlavorText: The ground scrapes its body as it travels, causing it to leave salt behind. Salt is constantly being created and replenished inside Nacli’s body.

Name: Nacli
FlavorText: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

Name: Naclstack
FlavorText: It compresses rock salt inside its body and shoots out hardened salt pellets with enough force to perforate an iron sheet.

Name: Naclstack
FlavorText: This Pokémon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey’s body.

Name: Garganacl
FlavorText: Many Pokémon gather around Garganacl, hoping to lick at its mineral-rich salt.

Name: Garganacl
FlavorText: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.

Name: Charcadet
FlavorText: Its firepower increases when it fights, reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. It likes berries that are rich in fat.

Name: Charcadet
FlavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

Name: Armarouge
FlavorText: This Pokémon clads itself in armor that has been fortified by psychic and fire energy, and it shoots blazing fireballs.

Name: Armarouge
FlavorText: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

Name: Ceruledge
FlavorText: An old set of armor steeped in grudges caused this Pokémon’s evolution. Ceruledge cuts its enemies to pieces without mercy.

Name: Ceruledge
FlavorText: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

Name: Tadbulb
FlavorText: It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, Tadbulb will float higher off the ground.

Name: Tadbulb
FlavorText: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

Name: Bellibolt
FlavorText: What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by Bellibolt’s belly-button dynamo.

Name: Bellibolt
FlavorText: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

Name: Wattrel
FlavorText: These Pokémon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and they’re a popular delicacy.

Name: Wattrel
FlavorText: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

Name: Kilowattrel
FlavorText: It uses its throat sac to store electricity generated by its wings. There’s hardly any oil in its feathers, so it is a poor swimmer.

Name: Kilowattrel
FlavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

Name: Maschiff
FlavorText: Its well-developed jaw and fangs are strong enough to crunch through boulders, and its thick fat makes for an excellent defense.

Name: Maschiff
FlavorText: It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously, but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see Maschiff’s face.

Name: Mabosstiff
FlavorText: Mabosstiff loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.

Name: Mabosstiff
FlavorText: This Pokémon can store energy in its large dewlap. Mabosstiff unleashes this energy all at once to blow away enemies.

Name: Shroodle
FlavorText: To keep enemies away from its territory, it paints markings around its nest using a poisonous liquid that has an acrid odor.

Name: Shroodle
FlavorText: Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.

Name: Grafaiai
FlavorText: Each Grafaiai paints its own individual pattern, and it will paint that same pattern over and over again throughout its life.

Name: Grafaiai
FlavorText: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

Name: Bramblin
FlavorText: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

Name: Bramblin
FlavorText: A soul unable to move on to the afterlife was blown around by the wind until it got tangled up with dried grass and became a Pokémon.

Name: Brambleghast
FlavorText: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.

Name: Brambleghast
FlavorText: It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs, it expels the prey and discards it.

Name: Toedscool
FlavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

Name: Toedscool
FlavorText: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

Name: Toedscruel
FlavorText: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.

Name: Toedscruel
FlavorText: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

Name: Klawf
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives on sheer cliffs. It sidesteps opponents’ attacks, then lunges for their weak spots with its claws.

Name: Klawf
FlavorText: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can’t remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

Name: Capsakid
FlavorText: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.

Name: Capsakid
FlavorText: The more sunlight this Pokémon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.

Name: Scovillain
FlavorText: The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.

Name: Scovillain
FlavorText: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.

Name: Rellor
FlavorText: It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.

Name: Rellor
FlavorText: This Pokémon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.

Name: Rabsca
FlavorText: An infant sleeps inside the ball. Rabsca rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.

Name: Rabsca
FlavorText: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.

Name: Flittle
FlavorText: It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.

Name: Flittle
FlavorText: Flittle’s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon’s belly.

Name: Espathra
FlavorText: It emits psychic power from the gaps between its multicolored frills and sprints at speeds greater than 120 mph.

Name: Espathra
FlavorText: It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance, it has a vicious temperament.

Name: Tinkatink
FlavorText: This Pokémon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until it’s satisfied with the result.

Name: Tinkatink
FlavorText: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

Name: Tinkatuff
FlavorText: These Pokémon make their homes in piles of scrap metal. They test the strength of each other’s hammers by smashing them together.

Name: Tinkatuff
FlavorText: This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.

Name: Tinkaton
FlavorText: The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it gets swung around easily by Tinkaton as it steals whatever it pleases and carries its plunder back home.

Name: Tinkaton
FlavorText: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.

Name: Wiglett
FlavorText: Though it looks like Diglett, Wiglett is an entirely different species. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of environmental adaptation.

Name: Wiglett
FlavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

Name: Wugtrio
FlavorText: A variety of fish Pokémon, Wugtrio was once considered to be a regional form of Dugtrio.

Name: Wugtrio
FlavorText: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.

Name: Bombirdier
FlavorText: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.

Name: Bombirdier
FlavorText: It gathers things up in an apron made from shed feathers added to the Pokémon’s chest feathers, then drops those things from high places for fun.

Name: Finizen
FlavorText: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.

Name: Finizen
FlavorText: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: This hero of the ocean swims at a speed of 50 knots and saves drowning people and Pokémon.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: This Pokémon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.

Name: Varoom
FlavorText: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.

Name: Varoom
FlavorText: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

Name: Revavroom
FlavorText: Revavroom viciously threatens others with the sound of its exhaust. It sticks its tongue out from its cylindrical mouth and sprays toxic fluids.

Name: Revavroom
FlavorText: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders—now numbering eight—to generate energy.

Name: Cyclizar
FlavorText: It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The rider’s body heat warms Cyclizar’s back and lifts the Pokémon’s spirit.

Name: Cyclizar
FlavorText: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

Name: Orthworm
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in arid deserts. It maintains its metal body by consuming iron from the soil.

Name: Orthworm
FlavorText: When attacked, this Pokémon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.

Name: Glimmet
FlavorText: Glimmet’s toxic mineral crystals look just like flower petals. This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder like pollen to protect itself.

Name: Glimmet
FlavorText: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

Name: Glimmora
FlavorText: Glimmora’s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.

Name: Glimmora
FlavorText: When this Pokémon detects danger, it will open up its crystalline petals and fire beams from its conical body.

Name: Greavard
FlavorText: This friendly Pokémon doesn’t like being alone. Pay it even the slightest bit of attention, and it will follow you forever.

Name: Greavard
FlavorText: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

Name: Houndstone
FlavorText: A lovingly mourned Pokémon was reborn as Houndstone. It doesn’t like anyone touching the protuberance atop its head.

Name: Houndstone
FlavorText: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokémon, this one is most loyal to its master.

Name: Flamigo
FlavorText: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as “synchronizing,” an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.

Name: Flamigo
FlavorText: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

Name: Cetoddle
FlavorText: It lives in frigid regions in pods of five or so individuals. It loves the minerals found in snow and ice.

Name: Cetoddle
FlavorText: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.

Name: Cetitan
FlavorText: Ice energy builds up in the horn on its upper jaw, causing the horn to reach cryogenic temperatures that freeze its surroundings.

Name: Cetitan
FlavorText: This Pokémon wanders around snowy, icy areas. It protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.

Name: Veluza
FlavorText: Veluza has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.

Name: Veluza
FlavorText: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

Name: Dondozo
FlavorText: It treats Tatsugiri like its boss and follows it loyally. Though powerful, Dondozo is apparently not very smart.

Name: Dondozo
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: It’s one of the most intelligent dragon Pokémon. It camouflages itself by inflating its throat sac.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: Bird Pokémon are its main prey. This Pokémon knows it’s weak, so it hunts with a partner.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: This Pokémon tricks its opponents by playing dead. It is small and weak, but it uses its smarts to survive.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: This species’ differing colors and patterns are apparently the result of Tatsugiri changing itself to suit the preferences of the prey it lures in.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

Name: Annihilape
FlavorText: It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.

Name: Annihilape
FlavorText: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

Name: Clodsire
FlavorText: It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.

Name: Clodsire
FlavorText: When attacked, this Pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It’s a risky move that puts everything on the line.

Name: Farigiraf
FlavorText: The hardened head from the tail protects the head of the main body as Farigiraf whips its long neck around to headbutt enemies.

Name: Farigiraf
FlavorText: Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this Pokémon is 10 times stronger than Girafarig’s.

Name: Dudunsparce
FlavorText: A recent study uncovered that the number of segments a Dudunsparce’s body has is determined by the Pokémon’s genes.

Name: Dudunsparce
FlavorText: The gentle Dudunsparce will put Pokémon that wander into its nest onto its back and carry them to the entrance.

Name: Dudunsparce
FlavorText: It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.

Name: Dudunsparce
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.

Name: Kingambit
FlavorText: Though it commands a massive army in battle, it’s not skilled at devising complex strategies. It just uses brute strength to keep pushing.

Name: Kingambit
FlavorText: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

Name: Great Tusk
FlavorText: This creature resembles a mysterious Pokémon that, according to a paranormal magazine, has lived since ancient times.

Name: Great Tusk
FlavorText: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.

Name: Scream Tail
FlavorText: It resembles a mysterious Pokémon described in a paranormal magazine as a Jigglypuff from one billion years ago.

Name: Scream Tail
FlavorText: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokémon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.

Name: Brute Bonnet
FlavorText: It bears a slight resemblance to a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a cross between a dinosaur and a mushroom.

Name: Brute Bonnet
FlavorText: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.

Name: Flutter Mane
FlavorText: It has similar features to a ghostly pterosaur that was covered in a paranormal magazine, but the two have little else in common.

Name: Flutter Mane
FlavorText: This Pokémon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.

Name: Slither Wing
FlavorText: This Pokémon somewhat resembles an ancient form of Volcarona that was introduced in a dubious magazine.

Name: Slither Wing
FlavorText: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

Name: Sandy Shocks
FlavorText: It slightly resembles a Magneton that lived for 10,000 years and was featured in an article in a paranormal magazine.

Name: Sandy Shocks
FlavorText: No records exist of this Pokémon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.

Name: Iron Treads
FlavorText: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.

Name: Iron Treads
FlavorText: This Pokémon closely resembles a scientific weapon that a paranormal magazine claimed was sent to this planet by aliens.

Name: Iron Bundle
FlavorText: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

Name: Iron Bundle
FlavorText: Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.

Name: Iron Hands
FlavorText: This Pokémon shares many similarities with Iron Hands, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.

Name: Iron Hands
FlavorText: It is very similar to a cyborg covered exclusively by a paranormal magazine. The cyborg was said to be the modified form of a certain athlete.

Name: Iron Jugulis
FlavorText: It’s possible that Iron Jugulis, an object described in an old book, may actually be this Pokémon.

Name: Iron Jugulis
FlavorText: It resembles a certain Pokémon introduced in a paranormal magazine, described as the offspring of a Hydreigon that fell in love with a robot.

Name: Iron Moth
FlavorText: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

Name: Iron Moth
FlavorText: This Pokémon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.

Name: Iron Thorns
FlavorText: Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as Iron Thorns.

Name: Iron Thorns
FlavorText: It has some similarities to a Pokémon introduced in a dubious magazine as a Tyranitar from one billion years into the future.

Name: Frigibax
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in forests and craggy areas. Using the power of its dorsal fin, it cools the inside of its nest like a refrigerator.

Name: Frigibax
FlavorText: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.

Name: Arctibax
FlavorText: It attacks with the blade of its frozen dorsal fin by doing a front flip in the air. Arctibax’s strong back and legs allow it to pull off this technique.

Name: Arctibax
FlavorText: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

Name: Baxcalibur
FlavorText: It launches itself into battle by flipping upside down and spewing frigid air from its mouth. It finishes opponents off with its dorsal blade.

Name: Baxcalibur
FlavorText: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

Name: Gimmighoul
FlavorText: It wanders around, carrying an old coin on its back. It survives by draining the life-force from humans who try to pick up its coin.

Name: Gimmighoul
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born from passion that seeped into a coin. It wanders, apparently seeking to return to the treasure chest it once inhabited.

Name: Gimmighoul
FlavorText: It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes it’s actually a Pokémon.

Name: Gimmighoul
FlavorText: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

Name: Gholdengo
FlavorText: It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. Gholdengo overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.

Name: Gholdengo
FlavorText: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.

Name: Wo-Chien
FlavorText: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.

Name: Wo-Chien
FlavorText: The grudge of a person punished for writing the king’s evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokémon.

Name: Chien-Pao
FlavorText: The hatred of those who perished by the sword long ago has clad itself in snow and become a Pokémon.

Name: Chien-Pao
FlavorText: This Pokémon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.

Name: Ting-Lu
FlavorText: It slowly brings its exceedingly heavy head down upon the ground, splitting the earth open with huge fissures that run over 160 feet deep.

Name: Ting-Lu
FlavorText: The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokémon.

Name: Chi-Yu
FlavorText: The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokémon.

Name: Chi-Yu
FlavorText: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.

Name: Roaring Moon
FlavorText: According to an article in a dubious magazine, this Pokémon has some connection to a phenomenon that occurs in a certain region.

Name: Roaring Moon
FlavorText: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.

Name: Iron Valiant
FlavorText: It’s possible that this is the object listed as Iron Valiant in a certain expedition journal.

Name: Iron Valiant
FlavorText: It has some similarities to a mad scientist’s invention covered in a paranormal magazine.

Name: Koraidon
FlavorText: It has similar characteristics to a creature described in an old book as the Winged King.

Name: Koraidon
FlavorText: The ecology and other data about this Pokémon are unknown. It was named Koraidon by the professor who discovered it.

Name: Koraidon
FlavorText: This Pokémon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.

Name: Koraidon
FlavorText: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

Name: Miraidon
FlavorText: It was given the name Miraidon by the professor who discovered it. Its ecology and other details are unknown.

Name: Miraidon
FlavorText: Its characteristics match those of a mysterious object recorded in an old expedition journal as the Iron Serpent.

Name: Miraidon
FlavorText: This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.

Name: Miraidon
FlavorText: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.
